Bulbasaur.Name: Bulbasaur
Bulbasaur.Description: For some time after its birth, it grows by taking nourishment from the seed on its back.
Bulbasaur.Evolution: Bulbasaur evolves to Ivysaur starting from level 16, which evolves to Venusaur starting from level 32.

Ivysaur.Name: Ivysaur
Ivysaur.Description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower’s coming bloom.
Ivysaur.Evolution: Ivysaur evolves from Bulbasaur starting from level 16 and evolves to Venusaur starting from level 32.

Venusaur.Name: Venusaur
Venusaur.Description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.
Venusaur.Evolution: Venusaur evolves from Ivysaur starting from level 32, which evolves from Bulbasaur starting from level 16.

Charmander.Name: Charmander
Charmander.Description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If the Pokémon is healthy, its tail burns intensely.
Charmander.Evolution: Charmander evolves to Charmeleon starting from level 16, which evolves to Charizard starting from level 36.

Charmeleon.Name: Charmeleon
Charmeleon.Description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
Charmeleon.Evolution: Charmeleon evolves from Charmander starting from level 16 and evolves to Charizard starting from level 36.

Charizard.Name: Charizard
Charizard.Description: It is said that Charizard’s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
Charizard.Evolution: Charizard evolves from Charmeleon starting from level 36, which evolves from Charmander starting from level 16.

Squirtle.Name: Squirtle
Squirtle.Description: It hides in its shell to protect itself, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
Squirtle.Evolution: Squirtle evolves to Wartortle starting from level 16, which evolves to Blastoise starting from level 36.

Wartortle.Name: Wartortle
Wartortle.Description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
Wartortle.Evolution: Wartortle evolves from Squirtle starting from level 16 and evolves to Blastoise starting from level 36.

Blastoise.Name: Blastoise
Blastoise.Description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
Blastoise.Evolution: Blastoise evolves from Wartortle starting from level 36, which evolves from Squirtle starting from level 16.

Caterpie.Name: Caterpie
Caterpie.Description: It releases a stench from its red antennae to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.
Caterpie.Evolution: Caterpie evolves to Metapod starting from level 7, which evolves to Butterfree starting from level 10.

Metapod.Name: Metapod
Metapod.Description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. The Pokémon quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.
Metapod.Evolution: Metapod evolves from Caterpie starting from level 7 and evolves to Butterfree starting from level 10.

Butterfree.Name: Butterfree
Butterfree.Description: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
Butterfree.Evolution: Butterfree evolves from Metapod starting from level 10, which evolves from Caterpie starting from level 7.

Weedle.Name: Weedle
Weedle.Description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.
Weedle.Evolution: Weedle evolves to Kakuna starting from level 7, which evolves to Beedrill starting from level 10.

Kakuna.Name: Kakuna
Kakuna.Description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
Kakuna.Evolution: Kakuna evolves from Weedle starting from level 7 and evolves to Beedrill starting from level 10.

Beedrill.Name: Beedrill
Beedrill.Description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.
Beedrill.Evolution: Beedrill evolves from Kakuna starting from level 10, which evolves from Weedle starting from level 7.

Pidgey.Name: Pidgey
Pidgey.Description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
Pidgey.Evolution: Pidgey evolves to Pidgeotto starting from level 18, which evolves to Pidgeot starting from level 36.

Pidgeotto.Name: Pidgeotto
Pidgeotto.Description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.
Pidgeotto.Evolution: Pidgeotto evolves from Pidgey starting from level 18 and evolves to Pidgeot starting from level 36.

Pidgeot.Name: Pidgeot
Pidgeot.Description: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
Pidgeot.Evolution: Pidgeot evolves from Pidgeotto starting from level 36, which evolves from Pidgey starting from level 18.

Rattata.Name: Rattata
Rattata.Description: It’s cautious in the extreme, and its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
Rattata.Evolution: Rattata evolves to Raticate starting from level 20.

Raticate.Name: Raticate
Raticate.Description: It whittles down its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder block walls.
Raticate.Evolution: Raticate evolves from Rattata starting from level 20.

Spearow.Name: Spearow
Spearow.Description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.
Spearow.Evolution: Spearow evolves to Fearow starting from level 20.

Fearow.Name: Fearow
Fearow.Description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.
Fearow.Evolution: Fearow evolves from Spearow starting from level 20.

Ekans.Name: Ekans
Ekans.Description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.
Ekans.Evolution: Ekans evolves to Arbok starting from level 22.

Arbok.Name: Arbok
Arbok.Description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.
Arbok.Evolution: Arbok evolves from Ekans starting from level 22.

Pikachu.Name: Pikachu
Pikachu.Description: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
Pikachu.Evolution: Pikachu evolves from Pichu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Raichu using a Thunder Stone.

Raichu.Name: Raichu
Raichu.Description: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.
Raichu.Evolution: Raichu evolves from Pikachu using a Thunder Stone, which evolves from Pichu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Sandshrew.Name: Sandshrew
Sandshrew.Description: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
Sandshrew.Evolution: Sandshrew evolves to Sandslash starting from level 22.

Sandslash.Name: Sandslash
Sandslash.Description: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.
Sandslash.Evolution: Sandslash evolves from Sandshrew starting from level 22.

Nidoran\u2642.Name: Nidoran♂
Nidoran\u2642.Description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.
Nidoran\u2642.Evolution: Nidoran♂ evolves to Nidorino starting from level 16, which evolves to Nidoking using a Moon Stone.

Nidoran\u2640.Name: Nidoran♀
Nidoran\u2640.Description: While this Pokémon does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the venom it secretes from its barbs can be fatal.
Nidoran\u2640.Evolution: Nidoran♀ evolves to Nidorina starting from level 16, which evolves to Nidoqueen using a Moon Stone.

Nidorina.Name: Nidorina
Nidorina.Description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow more slowly than Nidorino’s.
Nidorina.Evolution: Nidorina evolves from Nidoran♀ starting from level 16 and evolves to Nidoqueen using a Moon Stone.

Nidoqueen.Name: Nidoqueen
Nidoqueen.Description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.
Nidoqueen.Evolution: Nidoqueen evolves from Nidorina using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Nidoran♀ starting from level 16.

Nidorino.Name: Nidorino
Nidorino.Description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes venom upon impact.
Nidorino.Evolution: Nidorino evolves from Nidoran♂ starting from level 16 and evolves to Nidoking using a Moon Stone.

Nidoking.Name: Nidoking
Nidoking.Description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.
Nidoking.Evolution: Nidoking evolves from Nidorino using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Nidoran♂ starting from level 16.

Clefairy.Name: Clefairy
Clefairy.Description: It can be found in quiet mountain areas on a full moon’s night. Its dancing and its tiny, faintly glowing wings confer upon it a lovely fairylike quality.
Clefairy.Evolution: Clefairy evolves from Cleffa when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Clefable using a Moon Stone.

Clefable.Name: Clefable
Clefable.Description: Legend says that on clear, quiet nights, it listens for the voices of its kin living on the moon. I, too, often think of my homeland, so far away.
Clefable.Evolution: Clefable evolves from Clefairy using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Cleffa when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Vulpix.Name: Vulpix
Vulpix.Description: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.
Vulpix.Evolution: Vulpix evolves to Ninetales using a Fire Stone.

Ninetales.Name: Ninetales
Ninetales.Description: The coat of gleaming golden fur is quite magnificent. This species is said to store sacred power in its nine long tails and to live for a millennium.
Ninetales.Evolution: Ninetales evolves from Vulpix using a Fire Stone.

Jigglypuff.Name: Jigglypuff
Jigglypuff.Description: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.
Jigglypuff.Evolution: Jigglypuff evolves from Igglybuff when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Wigglytuff using a Moon Stone.

Wigglytuff.Name: Wigglytuff
Wigglytuff.Description: The rich, fluffy fur that covers its body feels so good that anyone who feels it can’t stop touching it.
Wigglytuff.Evolution: Wigglytuff evolves from Jigglypuff using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Igglybuff when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Zubat.Name: Zubat
Zubat.Description: Makes its home in gloomy caves. Atrophied eyes have left this Pokémon blind, so it scans its surroundings via sound waves that it emits from its mouth as it flies.
Zubat.Evolution: Zubat evolves to Golbat starting from level 22, which evolves to Crobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Golbat.Name: Golbat
Golbat.Description: It sinks its sharp fangs into other creatures and slurps up their blood. A closer look at the fangs reveals that they are hollow and akin to straws.
Golbat.Evolution: Golbat evolves from Zubat starting from level 22 and evolves to Crobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Oddish.Name: Oddish
Oddish.Description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.
Oddish.Evolution: Oddish evolves to Gloom starting from level 21, which evolves to Vileplume using a Leaf Stone and evolves to Bellossom using a Sun Stone.

Gloom.Name: Gloom
Gloom.Description: The nectar it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious that it can make noses curl from more than a mile away.
Gloom.Evolution: Gloom evolves from Oddish starting from level 21 and evolves to Vileplume using a Leaf Stone and evolves to Bellossom using a Sun Stone.

Vileplume.Name: Vileplume
Vileplume.Description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
Vileplume.Evolution: Vileplume evolves from Gloom using a Leaf Stone, which evolves from Oddish starting from level 21.

Paras.Name: Paras
Paras.Description: Sometimes seen at the foot of trees in humid forests. The mushrooms on its back—called tochukaso—are not present on infant specimens and instead emerge as Paras matures.
Paras.Evolution: Paras evolves to Parasect starting from level 24.

Parasect.Name: Parasect
Parasect.Description: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect’s actions.
Parasect.Evolution: Parasect evolves from Paras starting from level 24.

Venonat.Name: Venonat
Venonat.Description: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.
Venonat.Evolution: Venonat evolves to Venomoth starting from level 31.

Venomoth.Name: Venomoth
Venomoth.Description: When it attacks, it flaps its large wings violently to scatter its poisonous powder all around.
Venomoth.Evolution: Venomoth evolves from Venonat starting from level 31.

Diglett.Name: Diglett
Diglett.Description: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.
Diglett.Evolution: Diglett evolves to Dugtrio starting from level 26.

Dugtrio.Name: Dugtrio
Dugtrio.Description: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.
Dugtrio.Evolution: Dugtrio evolves from Diglett starting from level 26.

Meowth.Name: Meowth
Meowth.Description: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.
Meowth.Evolution: Meowth evolves to Persian starting from level 28.

Persian.Name: Persian
Persian.Description: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.
Persian.Evolution: Persian evolves from Meowth starting from level 28.

Psyduck.Name: Psyduck
Psyduck.Description: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.
Psyduck.Evolution: Psyduck evolves to Golduck starting from level 33.

Golduck.Name: Golduck
Golduck.Description: It swims gracefully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.
Golduck.Evolution: Golduck evolves from Psyduck starting from level 33.

Mankey.Name: Mankey
Mankey.Description: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.
Mankey.Evolution: Mankey evolves to Primeape starting from level 28.

Primeape.Name: Primeape
Primeape.Description: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.
Primeape.Evolution: Primeape evolves from Mankey starting from level 28.

Growlithe.Name: Growlithe
Growlithe.Description: It’s very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
Growlithe.Evolution: Growlithe evolves to Arcanine using a Fire Stone.

Poliwag.Name: Poliwag
Poliwag.Description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.
Poliwag.Evolution: Poliwag evolves to Poliwhirl starting from level 25, which evolves to Poliwrath using a Water Stone and evolves to Politoed when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Poliwhirl.Name: Poliwhirl
Poliwhirl.Description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.
Poliwhirl.Evolution: Poliwhirl evolves from Poliwag starting from level 25 and evolves to Poliwrath using a Water Stone and evolves to Politoed when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Arcanine.Name: Arcanine
Arcanine.Description: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.
Arcanine.Evolution: Arcanine evolves from Growlithe using a Fire Stone.

Poliwrath.Name: Poliwrath
Poliwrath.Description: With its extremely tough muscles, it could keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.
Poliwrath.Evolution: Poliwrath evolves from Poliwhirl using a Water Stone, which evolves from Poliwag starting from level 25.

Abra.Name: Abra
Abra.Description: Spends 18 hours of the day sleeping. Even while asleep, Abra can control its psychic powers—should danger approach, the Pokémon will simply teleport away.
Abra.Evolution: Abra evolves to Kadabra starting from level 16, which evolves to Alakazam when traded.

Kadabra.Name: Kadabra
Kadabra.Description: There are rumors that a child with mystical powers became a Kadabra; however, this remains unverified. I suspect that the spoon Kadabra holds enhances its brain waves.
Kadabra.Evolution: Kadabra evolves from Abra starting from level 16 and evolves to Alakazam when traded.

Alakazam.Name: Alakazam
Alakazam.Description: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.
Alakazam.Evolution: Alakazam evolves from Kadabra when traded, which evolves from Abra starting from level 16.

Machop.Name: Machop
Machop.Description: Though as small as a child, it has strength enough to easily throw a well-built adult. Striving to become ever stronger, Machop trains by carrying a Graveler on its shoulders.
Machop.Evolution: Machop evolves to Machoke starting from level 28, which evolves to Machamp when traded.

Machoke.Name: Machoke
Machoke.Description: A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists with tasks such as construction and clearing land.
Machoke.Evolution: Machoke evolves from Machop starting from level 28 and evolves to Machamp when traded.

Machamp.Name: Machamp
Machamp.Description: In close combat, its four arms afford it offensive and defensive supremacy. In but a blink, this valiant Pokémon can overwhelm its foes with more than 1,000 blows from its fists.
Machamp.Evolution: Machamp evolves from Machoke when traded, which evolves from Machop starting from level 28.

Bellsprout.Name: Bellsprout
Bellsprout.Description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.
Bellsprout.Evolution: Bellsprout evolves to Weepinbell starting from level 21, which evolves to Victreebel using a Leaf Stone.

Weepinbell.Name: Weepinbell
Weepinbell.Description: This Pokémon has the appearance of a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.
Weepinbell.Evolution: Weepinbell evolves from Bellsprout starting from level 21 and evolves to Victreebel using a Leaf Stone.

Victreebel.Name: Victreebel
Victreebel.Description: In its mouth, it pools a fragrant nectar-like fluid. The fluid is really an acid that dissolves anything.
Victreebel.Evolution: Victreebel evolves from Weepinbell using a Leaf Stone, which evolves from Bellsprout starting from level 21.

Tentacool.Name: Tentacool
Tentacool.Description: They fire beams from the glassy, magenta orbs that resemble eyes atop their heads, and they drift in shallow seas. During low tide, they can sometimes be found on beaches, desiccated.
Tentacool.Evolution: Tentacool evolves to Tentacruel starting from level 30.

Tentacruel.Name: Tentacruel
Tentacruel.Description: It has 80 tentacles, each with a venomous tip. These tentacles are also extendible, lengthening when Tentacruel attempts to catch prey. Use caution.
Tentacruel.Evolution: Tentacruel evolves from Tentacool starting from level 30.

Geodude.Name: Geodude
Geodude.Description: Makes its home in mountainous regions, using its arms to climb along harsh mountain roads. Can be troublesome—carelessly kicking one will cause it to fly into a rage and chase after you.
Geodude.Evolution: Geodude evolves to Graveler starting from level 25, which evolves to Golem when traded.

Graveler.Name: Graveler
Graveler.Description: Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads.
Graveler.Evolution: Graveler evolves from Geodude starting from level 25 and evolves to Golem when traded.

Golem.Name: Golem
Golem.Description: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.
Golem.Evolution: Golem evolves from Graveler when traded, which evolves from Geodude starting from level 25.

Ponyta.Name: Ponyta
Ponyta.Description: These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.
Ponyta.Evolution: Ponyta evolves to Rapidash starting from level 40.

Rapidash.Name: Rapidash
Rapidash.Description: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.
Rapidash.Evolution: Rapidash evolves from Ponyta starting from level 40.

Slowpoke.Name: Slowpoke
Slowpoke.Description: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.
Slowpoke.Evolution: Slowpoke evolves to Slowbro starting from level 37 and evolves to Slowking when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Slowbro.Name: Slowbro
Slowbro.Description: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.
Slowbro.Evolution: Slowbro evolves from Slowpoke starting from level 37.

Magnemite.Name: Magnemite
Magnemite.Description: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges electromagnetic waves and so on from the units at its sides.
Magnemite.Evolution: Magnemite evolves to Magneton starting from level 30, which evolves to Magnezone using a Thunder Stone.

Magneton.Name: Magneton
Magneton.Description: They’re formed by several Magnemite linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
Magneton.Evolution: Magneton evolves from Magnemite starting from level 30 and evolves to Magnezone using a Thunder Stone.

Farfetch'd.Name: Farfetch'd
Farfetch'd.Description: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

Doduo.Name: Doduo
Doduo.Description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
Doduo.Evolution: Doduo evolves to Dodrio starting from level 31.

Dodrio.Name: Dodrio
Dodrio.Description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. This Pokémon runs at nearly 40 mph.
Dodrio.Evolution: Dodrio evolves from Doduo starting from level 31.

Seel.Name: Seel
Seel.Description: This Pokémon lives on icebergs. It uses the sharp point on its head to break up ice as it swims in the sea.
Seel.Evolution: Seel evolves to Dewgong starting from level 34.

Dewgong.Name: Dewgong
Dewgong.Description: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.
Dewgong.Evolution: Dewgong evolves from Seel starting from level 34.

Grimer.Name: Grimer
Grimer.Description: When two of these Pokémon’s bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.
Grimer.Evolution: Grimer evolves to Muk starting from level 38.

Muk.Name: Muk
Muk.Description: It’s so stinky! Muk’s body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.
Muk.Evolution: Muk evolves from Grimer starting from level 38.

Shellder.Name: Shellder
Shellder.Description: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.
Shellder.Evolution: Shellder evolves to Cloyster using a Water Stone.

Cloyster.Name: Cloyster
Cloyster.Description: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.
Cloyster.Evolution: Cloyster evolves from Shellder using a Water Stone.

Gastly.Name: Gastly
Gastly.Description: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.
Gastly.Evolution: Gastly evolves to Haunter starting from level 25, which evolves to Gengar when traded.

Haunter.Name: Haunter
Haunter.Description: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, Haunter lurks, silently stalking its next victim.
Haunter.Evolution: Haunter evolves from Gastly starting from level 25 and evolves to Gengar when traded.

Gengar.Name: Gengar
Gengar.Description: Hiding in people’s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.
Gengar.Evolution: Gengar evolves from Haunter when traded, which evolves from Gastly starting from level 25.

Onix.Name: Onix
Onix.Description: This chain of immense stones resembles a giant serpent. Tremors shake the earth above as it burrows deep beneath the ground, feeding on boulders as it goes.
Onix.Evolution: Onix evolves to Steelix when traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Drowzee.Name: Drowzee
Drowzee.Description: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.
Drowzee.Evolution: Drowzee evolves to Hypno starting from level 26.

Hypno.Name: Hypno
Hypno.Description: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.
Hypno.Evolution: Hypno evolves from Drowzee starting from level 26.

Krabby.Name: Krabby
Krabby.Description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are lost in battle.
Krabby.Evolution: Krabby evolves to Kingler starting from level 28.

Kingler.Name: Kingler
Kingler.Description: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.
Kingler.Evolution: Kingler evolves from Krabby starting from level 28.

Voltorb.Name: Voltorb
Voltorb.Description: It’s usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.
Voltorb.Evolution: Voltorb evolves to Electrode starting from level 30.

Electrode.Name: Electrode
Electrode.Description: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of the Bomb Ball.
Electrode.Evolution: Electrode evolves from Voltorb starting from level 30.

Exeggcute.Name: Exeggcute
Exeggcute.Description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.
Exeggcute.Evolution: Exeggcute evolves to Exeggutor using a Leaf Stone.

Exeggutor.Name: Exeggutor
Exeggutor.Description: It is called the Walking Jungle. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
Exeggutor.Evolution: Exeggutor evolves from Exeggcute using a Leaf Stone.

Cubone.Name: Cubone
Cubone.Description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.
Cubone.Evolution: Cubone evolves to Marowak starting from level 28 in the nighttime.

Marowak.Name: Marowak
Marowak.Description: The bones it uses have been in its possession since it was born. It has a ferocious nature.
Marowak.Evolution: Marowak evolves from Cubone starting from level 28 in the nighttime.

Hitmonlee.Name: Hitmonlee
Hitmonlee.Description: Its legs can stretch to double their length. First-time foes are startled by Hitmonlee’s extensible reach.
Hitmonlee.Evolution: Hitmonlee evolves from Tyrogue starting from level 20 when its Attack is higher than its Defense.

Hitmonchan.Name: Hitmonchan
Hitmonchan.Description: When Hitmonchan twists its arm while throwing a punch, the blow will pulverize even concrete. The Pokémon rests after three minutes of fighting.
Hitmonchan.Evolution: Hitmonchan evolves from Tyrogue starting from level 20 when its Defense is higher than its Attack.

Lickitung.Name: Lickitung
Lickitung.Description: Wields its long tongue deftly, as though it were an arm. The Pokémon’s viscous saliva, once it has been collected and boiled down, yields a strong and highly useful adhesive.
Lickitung.Evolution: Lickitung evolves to Lickilicky when leveled up while knowing Rollout.

Koffing.Name: Koffing
Koffing.Description: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell; they are also explosive.
Koffing.Evolution: Koffing evolves to Weezing starting from level 35.

Weezing.Name: Weezing
Weezing.Description: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.
Weezing.Evolution: Weezing evolves from Koffing starting from level 35.

Rhyhorn.Name: Rhyhorn
Rhyhorn.Description: Ludicrously strong—when it butts heads with a mountain, it is the mountain that shatters. But its short legs struggle with turns, and it is incapable of stopping unless it collides with something.
Rhyhorn.Evolution: Rhyhorn evolves to Rhydon starting from level 42, which evolves to Rhyperior when traded while holding a Protector.

Rhydon.Name: Rhydon
Rhydon.Description: Rapidly rotates its horn to bore through bedrock. It swaggers around volcanic regions, protected from the lava’s heat by its tough, armorlike hide.
Rhydon.Evolution: Rhydon evolves from Rhyhorn starting from level 42 and evolves to Rhyperior when traded while holding a Protector.

Chansey.Name: Chansey
Chansey.Description: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.
Chansey.Evolution: Chansey evolves from Happiny when leveled up while holding a Oval Stone in the daytime and evolves to Blissey when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Tangela.Name: Tangela
Tangela.Description: It is cloaked entirely in blue vines, preventing any glimpse of its true identity. The vines impart a refreshing sensation when chewed—they’re useful as a spice.
Tangela.Evolution: Tangela evolves to Tangrowth when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Kangaskhan.Name: Kangaskhan
Kangaskhan.Description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets its baby out to play only when it feels safe to do so.

Horsea.Name: Horsea
Horsea.Description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits black ink and flees.
Horsea.Evolution: Horsea evolves to Seadra starting from level 32, which evolves to Kingdra when traded while holding a Dragon Scale.

Seadra.Name: Seadra
Seadra.Description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.
Seadra.Evolution: Seadra evolves from Horsea starting from level 32 and evolves to Kingdra when traded while holding a Dragon Scale.

Goldeen.Name: Goldeen
Goldeen.Description: It swims at a steady five knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.
Goldeen.Evolution: Goldeen evolves to Seaking starting from level 33.

Seaking.Name: Seaking
Seaking.Description: To protect its family, it will fight with its drill-sharp horn. It lives in hollowed rocks in streams.
Seaking.Evolution: Seaking evolves from Goldeen starting from level 33.

Staryu.Name: Staryu
Staryu.Description: If Staryu’s body is damaged, it will regenerate as long as the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.
Staryu.Evolution: Staryu evolves to Starmie using a Water Stone.

Starmie.Name: Starmie
Starmie.Description: At the center of its body is a red core that sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.
Starmie.Evolution: Starmie evolves from Staryu using a Water Stone.

Mr. Mime.Name: Mr. Mime
Mr. Mime.Description: The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.
Mr. Mime.Evolution: Mr. Mime evolves from Mime Jr. when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Scyther.Name: Scyther
Scyther.Description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.
Scyther.Evolution: Scyther evolves to Scizor when traded while holding a Metal Coat and evolves to Kleavor when leveled up.

Jynx.Name: Jynx
Jynx.Description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.
Jynx.Evolution: Jynx evolves from Smoochum starting from level 30.

Electabuzz.Name: Electabuzz
Electabuzz.Description: Feeds on electrical energy. During sudden showers beneath looming thunderclouds, one can observe Electabuzz scaling tall trees, where the Pokémon will then wait for lightning to strike.
Electabuzz.Evolution: Electabuzz evolves from Elekid starting from level 30 and evolves to Electivire when traded while holding a Electirizer.

Magmar.Name: Magmar
Magmar.Description: Legend has it that this Pokémon was born from the crater of a volcano. When wounded, it bathes in lava to heal its body, much as one would soak in a hot spring.
Magmar.Evolution: Magmar evolves from Magby starting from level 30 and evolves to Magmortar when traded while holding a Magmarizer.

Pinsir.Name: Pinsir
Pinsir.Description: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn apart. What it can’t tear, it tosses far away.

Tauros.Name: Tauros
Tauros.Description: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd’s protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.

Magikarp.Name: Magikarp
Magikarp.Description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Magikarp.Evolution: Magikarp evolves to Gyarados starting from level 20.

Gyarados.Name: Gyarados
Gyarados.Description: It appears whenever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.
Gyarados.Evolution: Gyarados evolves from Magikarp starting from level 20.

Lapras.Name: Lapras
Lapras.Description: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.

Ditto.Name: Ditto
Ditto.Description: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

Eevee.Name: Eevee
Eevee.Description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.
Eevee.Evolution: Eevee evolves to Vaporeon using a Water Stone, evolves to Jolteon using a Thunder Stone, evolves to Flareon using a Fire Stone, evolves to Espeon when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime, evolves to Umbreon when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime, evolves to Leafeon using a Leaf Stone, evolves to Glaceon using a Ice Stone and evolves to Sylveon when leveled up while knowing a Fairy-type move.

Vaporeon.Name: Vaporeon
Vaporeon.Description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can’t be seen when it melts away into water.
Vaporeon.Evolution: Vaporeon evolves from Eevee using a Water Stone.

Jolteon.Name: Jolteon
Jolteon.Description: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.
Jolteon.Evolution: Jolteon evolves from Eevee using a Thunder Stone.

Flareon.Name: Flareon
Flareon.Description: It fluffs out its fur collar to cool down its body temperature, which can reach 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.
Flareon.Evolution: Flareon evolves from Eevee using a Fire Stone.

Porygon.Name: Porygon
Porygon.Description: It has no discernible heartbeat and does not seem to draw breath, and yet it appears to function without issue. I cannot even begin to explain this utterly bizarre anomaly.
Porygon.Evolution: Porygon evolves to Porygon2 when traded while holding a Upgrade, which evolves to Porygon-Z when traded while holding a Dubious Disc.

Omanyte.Name: Omanyte
Omanyte.Description: It’s a Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.
Omanyte.Evolution: Omanyte evolves to Omastar starting from level 40.

Omastar.Name: Omastar
Omastar.Description: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.
Omastar.Evolution: Omastar evolves from Omanyte starting from level 40.

Kabuto.Name: Kabuto
Kabuto.Description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a sturdy shell.
Kabuto.Evolution: Kabuto evolves to Kabutops starting from level 40.

Kabutops.Name: Kabutops
Kabutops.Description: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.
Kabutops.Evolution: Kabutops evolves from Kabuto starting from level 40.

Snorlax.Name: Snorlax
Snorlax.Description: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.
Snorlax.Evolution: Snorlax evolves from Munchlax when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Articuno.Name: Articuno
Articuno.Description: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

Zapdos.Name: Zapdos
Zapdos.Description: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

Moltres.Name: Moltres
Moltres.Description: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.

Dratini.Name: Dratini
Dratini.Description: It is born large to start with. It repeatedly sheds its skin as it steadily grows longer.
Dratini.Evolution: Dratini evolves to Dragonair starting from level 30, which evolves to Dragonite starting from level 55.

Dragonair.Name: Dragonair
Dragonair.Description: It is called the divine Pokémon. When its entire body brightens slightly, the weather changes.
Dragonair.Evolution: Dragonair evolves from Dratini starting from level 30 and evolves to Dragonite starting from level 55.

Dragonite.Name: Dragonite
Dragonite.Description: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.
Dragonite.Evolution: Dragonite evolves from Dragonair starting from level 55, which evolves from Dratini starting from level 30.

Mewtwo.Name: Mewtwo
Mewtwo.Description: Mewtwo was created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

Mew.Name: Mew
Mew.Description: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

Chikorita.Name: Chikorita
Chikorita.Description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the air’s temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.
Chikorita.Evolution: Chikorita evolves to Bayleef starting from level 16, which evolves to Meganium starting from level 32.

Bayleef.Name: Bayleef
Bayleef.Description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
Bayleef.Evolution: Bayleef evolves from Chikorita starting from level 16 and evolves to Meganium starting from level 32.

Meganium.Name: Meganium
Meganium.Description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.
Meganium.Evolution: Meganium evolves from Bayleef starting from level 32, which evolves from Chikorita starting from level 16.

Cyndaquil.Name: Cyndaquil
Cyndaquil.Description: Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.
Cyndaquil.Evolution: Cyndaquil evolves to Quilava starting from level 14, which evolves to Typhlosion starting from level 36.

Quilava.Name: Quilava
Quilava.Description: This creature’s fur is most mysterious—it is wholly impervious to the burning touch of flame. Should Quilava turn its back to you, take heed! Such a posture indicates a forthcoming attack.
Quilava.Evolution: Quilava evolves from Cyndaquil starting from level 14 and evolves to Typhlosion starting from level 36.

Typhlosion.Name: Typhlosion
Typhlosion.Description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.
Typhlosion.Evolution: Typhlosion evolves from Quilava starting from level 36, which evolves from Cyndaquil starting from level 14.

Totodile.Name: Totodile
Totodile.Description: It has a habit of biting everything with its well-developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.
Totodile.Evolution: Totodile evolves to Croconaw starting from level 18, which evolves to Feraligatr starting from level 30.

Croconaw.Name: Croconaw
Croconaw.Description: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.
Croconaw.Evolution: Croconaw evolves from Totodile starting from level 18 and evolves to Feraligatr starting from level 30.

Feraligatr.Name: Feraligatr
Feraligatr.Description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
Feraligatr.Evolution: Feraligatr evolves from Croconaw starting from level 30, which evolves from Totodile starting from level 18.

Sentret.Name: Sentret
Sentret.Description: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.
Sentret.Evolution: Sentret evolves to Furret starting from level 15.

Furret.Name: Furret
Furret.Description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
Furret.Evolution: Furret evolves from Sentret starting from level 15.

Hoothoot.Name: Hoothoot
Hoothoot.Description: It switches its standing foot so quickly that the switch can’t be seen. It cries at the same time every day.
Hoothoot.Evolution: Hoothoot evolves to Noctowl starting from level 20.

Noctowl.Name: Noctowl
Noctowl.Description: If it flips its head upside down, it’s a sign that it is engaged in very complex thinking.
Noctowl.Evolution: Noctowl evolves from Hoothoot starting from level 20.

Ledyba.Name: Ledyba
Ledyba.Description: It’s so timid that it can’t move unless it’s with a swarm. It conveys its feelings through scent.
Ledyba.Evolution: Ledyba evolves to Ledian starting from level 18.

Ledian.Name: Ledian
Ledian.Description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.
Ledian.Evolution: Ledian evolves from Ledyba starting from level 18.

Spinarak.Name: Spinarak
Spinarak.Description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong thread. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.
Spinarak.Evolution: Spinarak evolves to Ariados starting from level 22.

Ariados.Name: Ariados
Ariados.Description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
Ariados.Evolution: Ariados evolves from Spinarak starting from level 22.

Crobat.Name: Crobat
Crobat.Description: Its hind limbs have become another set of wings. Crobat expertly maneuvers its four wings to dart in exquisite fashion through even the most confined caves without losing any speed.
Crobat.Evolution: Crobat evolves from Golbat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves from Zubat starting from level 22.

Chinchou.Name: Chinchou
Chinchou.Description: It discharges positive and negative electricity from the tips of its antennae to shock its foes.
Chinchou.Evolution: Chinchou evolves to Lanturn starting from level 27.

Lanturn.Name: Lanturn
Lanturn.Description: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed the Deep-Sea Star.
Lanturn.Evolution: Lanturn evolves from Chinchou starting from level 27.

Pichu.Name: Pichu
Pichu.Description: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.
Pichu.Evolution: Pichu evolves to Pikachu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Raichu using a Thunder Stone.

Cleffa.Name: Cleffa
Cleffa.Description: In silhouette, they resemble twinkling starlight. When shooting stars rain from the night sky, Cleffa gather in numbers and dance as though they are indeed incarnations of the stars.
Cleffa.Evolution: Cleffa evolves to Clefairy when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Clefable using a Moon Stone.

Igglybuff.Name: Igglybuff
Igglybuff.Description: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.
Igglybuff.Evolution: Igglybuff evolves to Jigglypuff when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Wigglytuff using a Moon Stone.

Togepi.Name: Togepi
Togepi.Description: This ovate creature is frequently mistaken for a moving egg when encountered out in the fields or in the mountains. Its guileless smile soothes the soul.
Togepi.Evolution: Togepi evolves to Togetic when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Togekiss using a Shiny Stone.

Togetic.Name: Togetic
Togetic.Description: No records exist of Togetic being seen in the wilds. Rumors abound that it evolves under the loving care of a trusted human companion, upon whom the Pokémon then bestows great joy.
Togetic.Evolution: Togetic evolves from Togepi when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Togekiss using a Shiny Stone.

Natu.Name: Natu
Natu.Description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
Natu.Evolution: Natu evolves to Xatu starting from level 25.

Xatu.Name: Xatu
Xatu.Description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.
Xatu.Evolution: Xatu evolves from Natu starting from level 25.

Mareep.Name: Mareep
Mareep.Description: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.
Mareep.Evolution: Mareep evolves to Flaaffy starting from level 15, which evolves to Ampharos starting from level 30.

Flaaffy.Name: Flaaffy
Flaaffy.Description: Because of its rubbery, electricity-resistant skin, it can store lots of electricity in its fur.
Flaaffy.Evolution: Flaaffy evolves from Mareep starting from level 15 and evolves to Ampharos starting from level 30.

Ampharos.Name: Ampharos
Ampharos.Description: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean’s surface.
Ampharos.Evolution: Ampharos evolves from Flaaffy starting from level 30, which evolves from Mareep starting from level 15.

Bellossom.Name: Bellossom
Bellossom.Description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
Bellossom.Evolution: Bellossom evolves from Gloom using a Sun Stone, which evolves from Oddish starting from level 21.

Marill.Name: Marill
Marill.Description: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.
Marill.Evolution: Marill evolves from Azurill when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Azumarill starting from level 18.

Azumarill.Name: Azumarill
Azumarill.Description: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.
Azumarill.Evolution: Azumarill evolves from Marill starting from level 18, which evolves from Azurill when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Sudowoodo.Name: Sudowoodo
Sudowoodo.Description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.
Sudowoodo.Evolution: Sudowoodo evolves from Bonsly when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Politoed.Name: Politoed
Politoed.Description: A group of Poliwag and Poliwhirl will form with a Politoed as the leader. Politoed’s cries make the Pokémon of the group obey.
Politoed.Evolution: Politoed evolves from Poliwhirl when traded while holding a King's Rock, which evolves from Poliwag starting from level 25.

Hoppip.Name: Hoppip
Hoppip.Description: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.
Hoppip.Evolution: Hoppip evolves to Skiploom starting from level 18, which evolves to Jumpluff starting from level 27.

Skiploom.Name: Skiploom
Skiploom.Description: When the weather grows cold, Skiploom’s flower closes and the Pokémon cannot photosynthesize, so it flies away to warmer regions.
Skiploom.Evolution: Skiploom evolves from Hoppip starting from level 18 and evolves to Jumpluff starting from level 27.

Jumpluff.Name: Jumpluff
Jumpluff.Description: Beware its cotton spores. If you accidentally breathe them in, you’ll be racked with coughs and itchiness.
Jumpluff.Evolution: Jumpluff evolves from Skiploom starting from level 27, which evolves from Hoppip starting from level 18.

Aipom.Name: Aipom
Aipom.Description: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.
Aipom.Evolution: Aipom evolves to Ambipom when leveled up while knowing Double Hit.

Sunkern.Name: Sunkern
Sunkern.Description: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.
Sunkern.Evolution: Sunkern evolves to Sunflora using a Sun Stone.

Sunflora.Name: Sunflora
Sunflora.Description: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.
Sunflora.Evolution: Sunflora evolves from Sunkern using a Sun Stone.

Yanma.Name: Yanma
Yanma.Description: Its frail wings are so thin that one can see clear through them. However, during flight these wings exhibit the power to churn air with force enough to launch a house skyward.
Yanma.Evolution: Yanma evolves to Yanmega when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Wooper.Name: Wooper
Wooper.Description: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
Wooper.Evolution: Wooper evolves to Quagsire starting from level 20.

Quagsire.Name: Quagsire
Quagsire.Description: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.
Quagsire.Evolution: Quagsire evolves from Wooper starting from level 20.

Espeon.Name: Espeon
Espeon.Description: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy’s actions.
Espeon.Evolution: Espeon evolves from Eevee when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Umbreon.Name: Umbreon
Umbreon.Description: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.
Umbreon.Evolution: Umbreon evolves from Eevee when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Murkrow.Name: Murkrow
Murkrow.Description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.
Murkrow.Evolution: Murkrow evolves to Honchkrow using a Dusk Stone.

Slowking.Name: Slowking
Slowking.Description: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
Slowking.Evolution: Slowking evolves from Slowpoke when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Misdreavus.Name: Misdreavus
Misdreavus.Description: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.
Misdreavus.Evolution: Misdreavus evolves to Mismagius using a Dusk Stone.

Unown.Name: Unown
Unown.Description: It is hard to believe these strangely shaped Pokémon are truly living creatures. I’ve pointed out that the species’ many forms resemble writing from other lands; no one will take me seriously.

Wobbuffet.Name: Wobbuffet
Wobbuffet.Description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. This behavior is said to be proof that its tail hides a secret.
Wobbuffet.Evolution: Wobbuffet evolves from Wynaut starting from level 15.

Girafarig.Name: Girafarig
Girafarig.Description: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

Pineco.Name: Pineco
Pineco.Description: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.
Pineco.Evolution: Pineco evolves to Forretress starting from level 31.

Forretress.Name: Forretress
Forretress.Description: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.
Forretress.Evolution: Forretress evolves from Pineco starting from level 31.

Dunsparce.Name: Dunsparce
Dunsparce.Description: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

Gligar.Name: Gligar
Gligar.Description: Its tail is tipped by a thick, horrible stinger. To bring down prey, it will first obscure their vision by covering their faces with its body, and then it will use the stinger to inject them with venom.
Gligar.Evolution: Gligar evolves to Gliscor when leveled up while holding a Razor Fang in the nighttime.

Steelix.Name: Steelix
Steelix.Description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard—not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.
Steelix.Evolution: Steelix evolves from Onix when traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Snubbull.Name: Snubbull
Snubbull.Description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by many people to be cute.
Snubbull.Evolution: Snubbull evolves to Granbull starting from level 23.

Granbull.Name: Granbull
Granbull.Description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.
Granbull.Evolution: Granbull evolves from Snubbull starting from level 23.

Qwilfish.Name: Qwilfish
Qwilfish.Description: Experienced fishers say they try to catch Qwilfish in the brief moment that these Pokémon become defenseless just after launching poisonous spikes.

Scizor.Name: Scizor
Scizor.Description: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.
Scizor.Evolution: Scizor evolves from Scyther when traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Shuckle.Name: Shuckle
Shuckle.Description: It stores berries in its shell. The berries mix with its body fluids to become delicious juices.

Heracross.Name: Heracross
Heracross.Description: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

Sneasel.Name: Sneasel
Sneasel.Description: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.
Sneasel.Evolution: Sneasel evolves to Weavile when leveled up while holding a Razor Claw in the nighttime.

Teddiursa.Name: Teddiursa
Teddiursa.Description: Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon have a smile back on its face.
Teddiursa.Evolution: Teddiursa evolves to Ursaring starting from level 30.

Ursaring.Name: Ursaring
Ursaring.Description: It is quite skilled at climbing trees. If it comes across a Primeape while searching for berries in the treetops, trouble will surely ensue.
Ursaring.Evolution: Ursaring evolves from Teddiursa starting from level 30.

Slugma.Name: Slugma
Slugma.Description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
Slugma.Evolution: Slugma evolves to Magcargo starting from level 38.

Magcargo.Name: Magcargo
Magcargo.Description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Flames burst from gaps in its shell made of hardened magma.
Magcargo.Evolution: Magcargo evolves from Slugma starting from level 38.

Swinub.Name: Swinub
Swinub.Description: Swinub excels at sniffing out mushrooms buried beneath grass or snow. Since ancient times, the people of Hisui have often relied upon this skill.
Swinub.Evolution: Swinub evolves to Piloswine starting from level 33, which evolves to Mamoswine when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Piloswine.Name: Piloswine
Piloswine.Description: The long fur of this Pokémon covers its eyes, ears, and even limbs, allowing Piloswine to resist harshly frigid conditions. The Pokémon’s white tusks can be used to defeat its enemies.
Piloswine.Evolution: Piloswine evolves from Swinub starting from level 33 and evolves to Mamoswine when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Corsola.Name: Corsola
Corsola.Description: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

Remoraid.Name: Remoraid
Remoraid.Description: Spits water from its mouth with incredible accuracy. It captures Burmy by shooting them down off the branches from which they dangle.
Remoraid.Evolution: Remoraid evolves to Octillery starting from level 25.

Octillery.Name: Octillery
Octillery.Description: While Octillery still shoots water from its mouth, the drastic anatomical difference between it and Remoraid meant that for a long time, no one believed the former evolved from the latter.
Octillery.Evolution: Octillery evolves from Remoraid starting from level 25.

Delibird.Name: Delibird
Delibird.Description: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

Mantine.Name: Mantine
Mantine.Description: This calm and gentle Pokémon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokémon due to this behavior.
Mantine.Evolution: Mantine evolves from Mantyke when leveled up.

Skarmory.Name: Skarmory
Skarmory.Description: Skarmory is clad entirely in ironhard armor. It flies at speeds over 180 mph.

Houndour.Name: Houndour
Houndour.Description: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.
Houndour.Evolution: Houndour evolves to Houndoom starting from level 24.

Houndoom.Name: Houndoom
Houndoom.Description: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.
Houndoom.Evolution: Houndoom evolves from Houndour starting from level 24.

Kingdra.Name: Kingdra
Kingdra.Description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.
Kingdra.Evolution: Kingdra evolves from Seadra when traded while holding a Dragon Scale, which evolves from Horsea starting from level 32.

Phanpy.Name: Phanpy
Phanpy.Description: It is far stronger than it appears. If a Phanpy is swinging its trunk around and your arm gets hit by it, your arm bone will shatter.
Phanpy.Evolution: Phanpy evolves to Donphan starting from level 25.

Donphan.Name: Donphan
Donphan.Description: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.
Donphan.Evolution: Donphan evolves from Phanpy starting from level 25.

Porygon2.Name: Porygon2
Porygon2.Description: A bizarre item caused this Pokémon to evolve. While it now exhibits many new gestures and expressions, its biology remains inscrutable.
Porygon2.Evolution: Porygon2 evolves from Porygon when traded while holding a Upgrade and evolves to Porygon-Z when traded while holding a Dubious Disc.

Stantler.Name: Stantler
Stantler.Description: It’s said that this Pokémon used to be stronger long ago when it had many enemies, and that it was even able to evolve under its own power.

Smeargle.Name: Smeargle
Smeargle.Description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

Tyrogue.Name: Tyrogue
Tyrogue.Description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.
Tyrogue.Evolution: Tyrogue evolves to Hitmonlee starting from level 20 when its Attack is higher than its Defense, evolves to Hitmonchan starting from level 20 when its Defense is higher than its Attack and evolves to Hitmontop starting from level 20 when its Attack is equal to its Defense.

Hitmontop.Name: Hitmontop
Hitmontop.Description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by a factor of 10.
Hitmontop.Evolution: Hitmontop evolves from Tyrogue starting from level 20 when its Attack is equal to its Defense.

Smoochum.Name: Smoochum
Smoochum.Description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.
Smoochum.Evolution: Smoochum evolves to Jynx starting from level 30.

Elekid.Name: Elekid
Elekid.Description: They generate electricity by spinning their arms. During a thunderstorm, if one hears the lively voices of children out in the wilderness, what one is actually hearing are the voices of Elekid.
Elekid.Evolution: Elekid evolves to Electabuzz starting from level 30, which evolves to Electivire when traded while holding a Electirizer.

Magby.Name: Magby
Magby.Description: This Pokémon lives in volcanic areas. With each breath, sparks spurt from its mouth and nose. When Magby is in good health, its flames gain a yellow tint.
Magby.Evolution: Magby evolves to Magmar starting from level 30, which evolves to Magmortar when traded while holding a Magmarizer.

Miltank.Name: Miltank
Miltank.Description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

Blissey.Name: Blissey
Blissey.Description: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
Blissey.Evolution: Blissey evolves from Chansey when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves from Happiny when leveled up while holding a Oval Stone in the daytime.

Raikou.Name: Raikou
Raikou.Description: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

Entei.Name: Entei
Entei.Description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

Suicune.Name: Suicune
Suicune.Description: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

Larvitar.Name: Larvitar
Larvitar.Description: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.
Larvitar.Evolution: Larvitar evolves to Pupitar starting from level 30, which evolves to Tyranitar starting from level 55.

Pupitar.Name: Pupitar
Pupitar.Description: Its shell is as hard as bedrock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.
Pupitar.Evolution: Pupitar evolves from Larvitar starting from level 30 and evolves to Tyranitar starting from level 55.

Tyranitar.Name: Tyranitar
Tyranitar.Description: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.
Tyranitar.Evolution: Tyranitar evolves from Pupitar starting from level 55, which evolves from Larvitar starting from level 30.

Lugia.Name: Lugia
Lugia.Description: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

Ho-Oh.Name: Ho-Oh
Ho-Oh.Description: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

Celebi.Name: Celebi
Celebi.Description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

Treecko.Name: Treecko
Treecko.Description: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny hooks, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.
Treecko.Evolution: Treecko evolves to Grovyle starting from level 16, which evolves to Sceptile starting from level 36.

Grovyle.Name: Grovyle
Grovyle.Description: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.
Grovyle.Evolution: Grovyle evolves from Treecko starting from level 16 and evolves to Sceptile starting from level 36.

Sceptile.Name: Sceptile
Sceptile.Description: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.
Sceptile.Evolution: Sceptile evolves from Grovyle starting from level 36, which evolves from Treecko starting from level 16.

Torchic.Name: Torchic
Torchic.Description: A fire burns inside it, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
Torchic.Evolution: Torchic evolves to Combusken starting from level 16, which evolves to Blaziken starting from level 36.

Combusken.Name: Combusken
Combusken.Description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.
Combusken.Evolution: Combusken evolves from Torchic starting from level 16 and evolves to Blaziken starting from level 36.

Blaziken.Name: Blaziken
Blaziken.Description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.
Blaziken.Evolution: Blaziken evolves from Combusken starting from level 36, which evolves from Torchic starting from level 16.

Mudkip.Name: Mudkip
Mudkip.Description: Using the fin on its head, Mudkip senses the flow of water to keep track of what’s going on around it. Mudkip has the strength to heft boulders.
Mudkip.Evolution: Mudkip evolves to Marshtomp starting from level 16, which evolves to Swampert starting from level 36.

Marshtomp.Name: Marshtomp
Marshtomp.Description: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.
Marshtomp.Evolution: Marshtomp evolves from Mudkip starting from level 16 and evolves to Swampert starting from level 36.

Swampert.Name: Swampert
Swampert.Description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.
Swampert.Evolution: Swampert evolves from Marshtomp starting from level 36, which evolves from Mudkip starting from level 16.

Poochyena.Name: Poochyena
Poochyena.Description: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
Poochyena.Evolution: Poochyena evolves to Mightyena starting from level 18.

Mightyena.Name: Mightyena
Mightyena.Description: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.
Mightyena.Evolution: Mightyena evolves from Poochyena starting from level 18.

Zigzagoon.Name: Zigzagoon
Zigzagoon.Description: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
Zigzagoon.Evolution: Zigzagoon evolves to Linoone starting from level 20.

Linoone.Name: Linoone
Linoone.Description: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
Linoone.Evolution: Linoone evolves from Zigzagoon starting from level 20.

Wurmple.Name: Wurmple
Wurmple.Description: Likes sap and is abundant in the wild. Why it evolves into various different forms is unknown. One cannot tell from a Wurmple’s appearance which form it will take when it evolves.
Wurmple.Evolution: Wurmple evolves to Silcoon starting from level 7, which evolves to Beautifly starting from level 10 and evolves to Cascoon starting from level 7, which evolves to Dustox starting from level 10.

Silcoon.Name: Silcoon
Silcoon.Description: Wraps itself in thin strings of silk while it stores energy for evolution. It can’t extend its limbs and its movement is slow, but its eyes keep a sharp lookout—Silcoon is always on guard.
Silcoon.Evolution: Silcoon evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7 and evolves to Beautifly starting from level 10.

Beautifly.Name: Beautifly
Beautifly.Description: A colorful and incredibly beautiful but also greedy Pokémon. In an effort to keep its favorite food all to itself, it will chase away Combee as they try to gather nectar.
Beautifly.Evolution: Beautifly evolves from Silcoon starting from level 10, which evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7.

Cascoon.Name: Cascoon
Cascoon.Description: The silk coating its body is thin but sufficiently strong. Cascoon’s silk has a luster and texture superior to that of Silcoon’s, and clothes made using Cascoon silk are regarded as top-notch.
Cascoon.Evolution: Cascoon evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7 and evolves to Dustox starting from level 10.

Dustox.Name: Dustox
Dustox.Description: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.
Dustox.Evolution: Dustox evolves from Cascoon starting from level 10, which evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7.

Lotad.Name: Lotad
Lotad.Description: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry for Pokémon that can’t swim.
Lotad.Evolution: Lotad evolves to Lombre starting from level 14, which evolves to Ludicolo using a Water Stone.

Lombre.Name: Lombre
Lombre.Description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
Lombre.Evolution: Lombre evolves from Lotad starting from level 14 and evolves to Ludicolo using a Water Stone.

Ludicolo.Name: Ludicolo
Ludicolo.Description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.
Ludicolo.Evolution: Ludicolo evolves from Lombre using a Water Stone, which evolves from Lotad starting from level 14.

Seedot.Name: Seedot
Seedot.Description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon that try to peck at it.
Seedot.Evolution: Seedot evolves to Nuzleaf starting from level 14, which evolves to Shiftry using a Leaf Stone.

Nuzleaf.Name: Nuzleaf
Nuzleaf.Description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in the forest.
Nuzleaf.Evolution: Nuzleaf evolves from Seedot starting from level 14 and evolves to Shiftry using a Leaf Stone.

Shiftry.Name: Shiftry
Shiftry.Description: By flapping its leafy fans, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.
Shiftry.Evolution: Shiftry evolves from Nuzleaf using a Leaf Stone, which evolves from Seedot starting from level 14.

Taillow.Name: Taillow
Taillow.Description: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.
Taillow.Evolution: Taillow evolves to Swellow starting from level 22.

Swellow.Name: Swellow
Swellow.Description: It circles the sky in search of prey and dives sharply to catch its target.
Swellow.Evolution: Swellow evolves from Taillow starting from level 22.

Wingull.Name: Wingull
Wingull.Description: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.
Wingull.Evolution: Wingull evolves to Pelipper starting from level 25.

Pelipper.Name: Pelipper
Pelipper.Description: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.
Pelipper.Evolution: Pelipper evolves from Wingull starting from level 25.

Ralts.Name: Ralts
Ralts.Description: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.
Ralts.Evolution: Ralts evolves to Kirlia starting from level 20, which evolves to Gardevoir starting from level 30 and evolves to Gallade using a Dawn Stone.

Kirlia.Name: Kirlia
Kirlia.Description: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.
Kirlia.Evolution: Kirlia evolves from Ralts starting from level 20 and evolves to Gardevoir starting from level 30 and evolves to Gallade using a Dawn Stone.

Gardevoir.Name: Gardevoir
Gardevoir.Description: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.
Gardevoir.Evolution: Gardevoir evolves from Kirlia starting from level 30, which evolves from Ralts starting from level 20.

Surskit.Name: Surskit
Surskit.Description: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.
Surskit.Evolution: Surskit evolves to Masquerain starting from level 22.

Masquerain.Name: Masquerain
Masquerain.Description: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.
Masquerain.Evolution: Masquerain evolves from Surskit starting from level 22.

Shroomish.Name: Shroomish
Shroomish.Description: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.
Shroomish.Evolution: Shroomish evolves to Breloom starting from level 23.

Breloom.Name: Breloom
Breloom.Description: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.
Breloom.Evolution: Breloom evolves from Shroomish starting from level 23.

Slakoth.Name: Slakoth
Slakoth.Description: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.
Slakoth.Evolution: Slakoth evolves to Vigoroth starting from level 18, which evolves to Slaking starting from level 36.

Vigoroth.Name: Vigoroth
Vigoroth.Description: It is always hungry because it won’t stop rampaging. Even while it is eating, it can’t keep still.
Vigoroth.Evolution: Vigoroth evolves from Slakoth starting from level 18 and evolves to Slaking starting from level 36.

Slaking.Name: Slaking
Slaking.Description: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.
Slaking.Evolution: Slaking evolves from Vigoroth starting from level 36, which evolves from Slakoth starting from level 18.

Nincada.Name: Nincada
Nincada.Description: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.
Nincada.Evolution: Nincada evolves to Ninjask starting from level 20 and evolves to Shedinja somehow.

Ninjask.Name: Ninjask
Ninjask.Description: Because they move so quickly, they sometimes become unseeable. They congregate around tree sap.
Ninjask.Evolution: Ninjask evolves from Nincada starting from level 20.

Shedinja.Name: Shedinja
Shedinja.Description: It is a discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

Whismur.Name: Whismur
Whismur.Description: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.
Whismur.Evolution: Whismur evolves to Loudred starting from level 20, which evolves to Exploud starting from level 40.

Loudred.Name: Loudred
Loudred.Description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Loudred.Evolution: Loudred evolves from Whismur starting from level 20 and evolves to Exploud starting from level 40.

Exploud.Name: Exploud
Exploud.Description: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.
Exploud.Evolution: Exploud evolves from Loudred starting from level 40, which evolves from Whismur starting from level 20.

Makuhita.Name: Makuhita
Makuhita.Description: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.
Makuhita.Evolution: Makuhita evolves to Hariyama starting from level 24.

Hariyama.Name: Hariyama
Hariyama.Description: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.
Hariyama.Evolution: Hariyama evolves from Makuhita starting from level 24.

Azurill.Name: Azurill
Azurill.Description: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.
Azurill.Evolution: Azurill evolves to Marill when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Azumarill starting from level 18.

Nosepass.Name: Nosepass
Nosepass.Description: Once the people of Hisui discovered that its red nose always points north, they grew to rely on it greatly when traveling afar. The nose seems to work in a similar way to ancient compasses.
Nosepass.Evolution: Nosepass evolves to Probopass using a Thunder Stone.

Skitty.Name: Skitty
Skitty.Description: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in circles, chasing its own tail.
Skitty.Evolution: Skitty evolves to Delcatty using a Moon Stone.

Delcatty.Name: Delcatty
Delcatty.Description: It is highly popular among Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
Delcatty.Evolution: Delcatty evolves from Skitty using a Moon Stone.

Sableye.Name: Sableye
Sableye.Description: Materials from gems it has eaten float to the surface of its body and can form an infinite number of patterns among individuals.

Mawile.Name: Mawile
Mawile.Description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

Aron.Name: Aron
Aron.Description: It usually lives deep in mountains. But when it’s hungry, it shows up at the foot of the mountains and eats railroad tracks and cars.
Aron.Evolution: Aron evolves to Lairon starting from level 32, which evolves to Aggron starting from level 42.

Lairon.Name: Lairon
Lairon.Description: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.
Lairon.Evolution: Lairon evolves from Aron starting from level 32 and evolves to Aggron starting from level 42.

Aggron.Name: Aggron
Aggron.Description: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
Aggron.Evolution: Aggron evolves from Lairon starting from level 42, which evolves from Aron starting from level 32.

Meditite.Name: Meditite
Meditite.Description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.
Meditite.Evolution: Meditite evolves to Medicham starting from level 37.

Medicham.Name: Medicham
Medicham.Description: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.
Medicham.Evolution: Medicham evolves from Meditite starting from level 37.

Electrike.Name: Electrike
Electrike.Description: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
Electrike.Evolution: Electrike evolves to Manectric starting from level 26.

Manectric.Name: Manectric
Manectric.Description: It discharges electricity from its mane. The Pokémon creates a thundercloud overhead from which to drop lightning bolts.
Manectric.Evolution: Manectric evolves from Electrike starting from level 26.

Plusle.Name: Plusle
Plusle.Description: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

Minun.Name: Minun
Minun.Description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

Volbeat.Name: Volbeat
Volbeat.Description: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise’s sweet aroma.

Illumise.Name: Illumise
Illumise.Description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

Roselia.Name: Roselia
Roselia.Description: Though beautiful, it has highly poisonous thorns. There is an old tradition in my homeland wherein one would send these thorns to an opponent to challenge them to a duel.
Roselia.Evolution: Roselia evolves from Budew when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime and evolves to Roserade using a Shiny Stone.

Gulpin.Name: Gulpin
Gulpin.Description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
Gulpin.Evolution: Gulpin evolves to Swalot starting from level 26.

Swalot.Name: Swalot
Swalot.Description: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.
Swalot.Evolution: Swalot evolves from Gulpin starting from level 26.

Carvanha.Name: Carvanha
Carvanha.Description: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.
Carvanha.Evolution: Carvanha evolves to Sharpedo starting from level 30.

Sharpedo.Name: Sharpedo
Sharpedo.Description: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as the Bully of the Sea.
Sharpedo.Evolution: Sharpedo evolves from Carvanha starting from level 30.

Wailmer.Name: Wailmer
Wailmer.Description: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nostrils.
Wailmer.Evolution: Wailmer evolves to Wailord starting from level 40.

Wailord.Name: Wailord
Wailord.Description: It’s the biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.
Wailord.Evolution: Wailord evolves from Wailmer starting from level 40.

Numel.Name: Numel
Numel.Description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.
Numel.Evolution: Numel evolves to Camerupt starting from level 33.

Camerupt.Name: Camerupt
Camerupt.Description: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
Camerupt.Evolution: Camerupt evolves from Numel starting from level 33.

Torkoal.Name: Torkoal
Torkoal.Description: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

Spoink.Name: Spoink
