Spoink.Description: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.
Spoink.Evolution: Spoink evolves to Grumpig starting from level 32.

Grumpig.Name: Grumpig
Grumpig.Description: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.
Grumpig.Evolution: Grumpig evolves from Spoink starting from level 32.

Spinda.Name: Spinda
Spinda.Description: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Their tottering steps hinder the aim of foes.

Trapinch.Name: Trapinch
Trapinch.Description: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
Trapinch.Evolution: Trapinch evolves to Vibrava starting from level 35, which evolves to Flygon starting from level 45.

Vibrava.Name: Vibrava
Vibrava.Description: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.
Vibrava.Evolution: Vibrava evolves from Trapinch starting from level 35 and evolves to Flygon starting from level 45.

Flygon.Name: Flygon
Flygon.Description: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as the Desert Spirit.
Flygon.Evolution: Flygon evolves from Vibrava starting from level 45, which evolves from Trapinch starting from level 35.

Cacnea.Name: Cacnea
Cacnea.Description: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.
Cacnea.Evolution: Cacnea evolves to Cacturne starting from level 32.

Cacturne.Name: Cacturne
Cacturne.Description: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.
Cacturne.Evolution: Cacturne evolves from Cacnea starting from level 32.

Swablu.Name: Swablu
Swablu.Description: It can’t relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.
Swablu.Evolution: Swablu evolves to Altaria starting from level 35.

Altaria.Name: Altaria
Altaria.Description: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Altaria.Evolution: Altaria evolves from Swablu starting from level 35.

Zangoose.Name: Zangoose
Zangoose.Description: If it comes across a Seviper, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.

Seviper.Name: Seviper
Seviper.Description: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It’s Zangoose’s archrival.

Lunatone.Name: Lunatone
Lunatone.Description: It becomes active on nights with a full moon, so it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

Solrock.Name: Solrock
Solrock.Description: This new Pokémon species is rumored to be an avatar of the sun. The Pokémon gives off light while spinning.

Barboach.Name: Barboach
Barboach.Description: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.
Barboach.Evolution: Barboach evolves to Whiscash starting from level 30.

Whiscash.Name: Whiscash
Whiscash.Description: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.
Whiscash.Evolution: Whiscash evolves from Barboach starting from level 30.

Corphish.Name: Corphish
Corphish.Description: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
Corphish.Evolution: Corphish evolves to Crawdaunt starting from level 30.

Crawdaunt.Name: Crawdaunt
Crawdaunt.Description: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.
Crawdaunt.Evolution: Crawdaunt evolves from Corphish starting from level 30.

Baltoy.Name: Baltoy
Baltoy.Description: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.
Baltoy.Evolution: Baltoy evolves to Claydol starting from level 36.

Claydol.Name: Claydol
Claydol.Description: An ancient clay figurine was exposed to a mysterious ray of light, and it came to life as a Pokémon.
Claydol.Evolution: Claydol evolves from Baltoy starting from level 36.

Lileep.Name: Lileep
Lileep.Description: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
Lileep.Evolution: Lileep evolves to Cradily starting from level 40.

Cradily.Name: Cradily
Cradily.Description: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.
Cradily.Evolution: Cradily evolves from Lileep starting from level 40.

Anorith.Name: Anorith
Anorith.Description: This Pokémon ancestor was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with its claws.
Anorith.Evolution: Anorith evolves to Armaldo starting from level 40.

Armaldo.Name: Armaldo
Armaldo.Description: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.
Armaldo.Evolution: Armaldo evolves from Anorith starting from level 40.

Feebas.Name: Feebas
Feebas.Description: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.
Feebas.Evolution: Feebas evolves to Milotic when leveled up.

Milotic.Name: Milotic
Milotic.Description: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.
Milotic.Evolution: Milotic evolves from Feebas when leveled up.

Castform.Name: Castform
Castform.Description: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

Snowy Castform.Name: Snowy Castform
Snowy Castform.Description: This is Castform’s form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!

Sunny Castform.Name: Sunny Castform
Sunny Castform.Description: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!

Rainy Castform.Name: Rainy Castform
Rainy Castform.Description: This is Castform’s form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn’t change to this form.

Kecleon.Name: Kecleon
Kecleon.Description: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.

Shuppet.Name: Shuppet
Shuppet.Description: It feeds on the dark emotions of sadness and hatred, which make it grow steadily stronger.
Shuppet.Evolution: Shuppet evolves to Banette starting from level 37.

Banette.Name: Banette
Banette.Description: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
Banette.Evolution: Banette evolves from Shuppet starting from level 37.

Duskull.Name: Duskull
Duskull.Description: I’ve heard that the children of Hisui all begin to behave once they’ve been told the story of how this Pokémon roams about before the witching hour to spirit away misbehaving children.
Duskull.Evolution: Duskull evolves to Dusclops starting from level 37, which evolves to Dusknoir when traded while holding a Reaper Cloth.

Dusclops.Name: Dusclops
Dusclops.Description: There are rumors that peeking inside its bandage-wrapped body will cause one to get pulled in through the gaps between the bandages, never to return. I’ve been too scared to verify.
Dusclops.Evolution: Dusclops evolves from Duskull starting from level 37 and evolves to Dusknoir when traded while holding a Reaper Cloth.

Tropius.Name: Tropius
Tropius.Description: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

Chimecho.Name: Chimecho
Chimecho.Description: Can emit waves of air powerful enough to knock out prey taller than itself. I hypothesize that it amplifies the faint sound of wind within its body.
Chimecho.Evolution: Chimecho evolves from Chingling when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Absol.Name: Absol
Absol.Description: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.

Wynaut.Name: Wynaut
Wynaut.Description: They grow strong by pushing up against one another en masse. They love eating sweet fruit.
Wynaut.Evolution: Wynaut evolves to Wobbuffet starting from level 15.

Snorunt.Name: Snorunt
Snorunt.Description: It is said that a home visited by a Snorunt will prosper. It can withstand cold of −150 degrees Fahrenheit.
Snorunt.Evolution: Snorunt evolves to Glalie starting from level 42 and evolves to Froslass using a Dawn Stone.

Glalie.Name: Glalie
Glalie.Description: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.
Glalie.Evolution: Glalie evolves from Snorunt starting from level 42.

Spheal.Name: Spheal
Spheal.Description: During the season when drift ice approaches the shore, Spheal prefers living on the ice—where fewer predators lurk—rather than the land. Its fur retains heat superbly and resists harsh cold.
Spheal.Evolution: Spheal evolves to Sealeo starting from level 32, which evolves to Walrein starting from level 44.

Sealeo.Name: Sealeo
Sealeo.Description: Its white whiskers are very sensitive. Sealeo will balance Spheal on the tip of its nose, checking its scent and its feel to be sure the Spheal is healthy.
Sealeo.Evolution: Sealeo evolves from Spheal starting from level 32 and evolves to Walrein starting from level 44.

Walrein.Name: Walrein
Walrein.Description: Its thick tusks are strong enough to shatter drift ice. They have been known to break, but they will grow back by the next year. The Hisui region is well known for these broken tusks.
Walrein.Evolution: Walrein evolves from Sealeo starting from level 44, which evolves from Spheal starting from level 32.

Clamperl.Name: Clamperl
Clamperl.Description: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.
Clamperl.Evolution: Clamperl evolves to Huntail when traded while holding a Deep Sea Tooth and evolves to Gorebyss when traded while holding a Deep Sea Scale.

Huntail.Name: Huntail
Huntail.Description: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.
Huntail.Evolution: Huntail evolves from Clamperl when traded while holding a Deep Sea Tooth.

Gorebyss.Name: Gorebyss
Gorebyss.Description: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.
Gorebyss.Evolution: Gorebyss evolves from Clamperl when traded while holding a Deep Sea Scale.

Relicanth.Name: Relicanth
Relicanth.Description: This rare Pokémon was discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Luvdisc.Name: Luvdisc
Luvdisc.Description: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

Bagon.Name: Bagon
Bagon.Description: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.
Bagon.Evolution: Bagon evolves to Shelgon starting from level 30, which evolves to Salamence starting from level 50.

Shelgon.Name: Shelgon
Shelgon.Description: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.
Shelgon.Evolution: Shelgon evolves from Bagon starting from level 30 and evolves to Salamence starting from level 50.

Salamence.Name: Salamence
Salamence.Description: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.
Salamence.Evolution: Salamence evolves from Shelgon starting from level 50, which evolves from Bagon starting from level 30.

Beldum.Name: Beldum
Beldum.Description: They converse with one another by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
Beldum.Evolution: Beldum evolves to Metang starting from level 20, which evolves to Metagross starting from level 45.

Metang.Name: Metang
Metang.Description: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won’t be scratched if it collides with a jet.
Metang.Evolution: Metang evolves from Beldum starting from level 20 and evolves to Metagross starting from level 45.

Metagross.Name: Metagross
Metagross.Description: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
Metagross.Evolution: Metagross evolves from Metang starting from level 45, which evolves from Beldum starting from level 20.

Regirock.Name: Regirock
Regirock.Description: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, Regirock attaches rocks to repair itself.

Regice.Name: Regice
Regice.Description: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of −328 degrees Fahrenheit.

Registeel.Name: Registeel
Registeel.Description: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

Latias.Name: Latias
Latias.Description: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

Latios.Name: Latios
Latios.Description: It is a highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its forelegs in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

Kyogre.Name: Kyogre
Kyogre.Description: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

Groudon.Name: Groudon
Groudon.Description: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.

Rayquaza.Name: Rayquaza
Rayquaza.Description: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

Jirachi.Name: Jirachi
Jirachi.Description: It is said to wake up for just seven days every 1,000 years and use its power to grant any wish.

Deoxys.Name: Deoxys
Deoxys.Description: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteorite underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

Turtwig.Name: Turtwig
Turtwig.Description: This Pokémon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.
Turtwig.Evolution: Turtwig evolves to Grotle starting from level 18, which evolves to Torterra starting from level 32.

Grotle.Name: Grotle
Grotle.Description: Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.
Grotle.Evolution: Grotle evolves from Turtwig starting from level 18 and evolves to Torterra starting from level 32.

Torterra.Name: Torterra
Torterra.Description: This remarkable, large-bodied Pokémon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.
Torterra.Evolution: Torterra evolves from Grotle starting from level 32, which evolves from Turtwig starting from level 18.

Chimchar.Name: Chimchar
Chimchar.Description: Full of vigor and always in high spirits. It was once known by the name “Lantern-Tail” and feared as some kind of apparition.
Chimchar.Evolution: Chimchar evolves to Monferno starting from level 14, which evolves to Infernape starting from level 36.

Monferno.Name: Monferno
Monferno.Description: The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.
Monferno.Evolution: Monferno evolves from Chimchar starting from level 14 and evolves to Infernape starting from level 36.

Infernape.Name: Infernape
Infernape.Description: A tall, hardy Pokémon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance—truly a sight to behold.
Infernape.Evolution: Infernape evolves from Monferno starting from level 36, which evolves from Chimchar starting from level 14.

Piplup.Name: Piplup
Piplup.Description: Prefers cold climes and appears along coasts. It’s an adorable little thing—as cute as any child—but it’s also prideful, unwilling to accept handouts from people.
Piplup.Evolution: Piplup evolves to Prinplup starting from level 16, which evolves to Empoleon starting from level 36.

Prinplup.Name: Prinplup
Prinplup.Description: It swims gracefully through the frigid sea and sings with a voice like the roaring tide. It has powerful, sturdy wings and dignity to match.
Prinplup.Evolution: Prinplup evolves from Piplup starting from level 16 and evolves to Empoleon starting from level 36.

Empoleon.Name: Empoleon
Empoleon.Description: Since ancient times, it has been revered by the people of Hisui, who call it the Master of the Waves. Its wings are a match for even master-crafted blades.
Empoleon.Evolution: Empoleon evolves from Prinplup starting from level 36, which evolves from Piplup starting from level 16.

Starly.Name: Starly
Starly.Description: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.
Starly.Evolution: Starly evolves to Staravia starting from level 14, which evolves to Staraptor starting from level 34.

Staravia.Name: Staravia
Staravia.Description: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
Staravia.Evolution: Staravia evolves from Starly starting from level 14 and evolves to Staraptor starting from level 34.

Staraptor.Name: Staraptor
Staraptor.Description: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.
Staraptor.Evolution: Staraptor evolves from Staravia starting from level 34, which evolves from Starly starting from level 14.

Bidoof.Name: Bidoof
Bidoof.Description: Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.
Bidoof.Evolution: Bidoof evolves to Bibarel starting from level 15.

Bibarel.Name: Bibarel
Bibarel.Description: Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokémon create dams on rivers to live in.
Bibarel.Evolution: Bibarel evolves from Bidoof starting from level 15.

Kricketot.Name: Kricketot
Kricketot.Description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
Kricketot.Evolution: Kricketot evolves to Kricketune starting from level 10.

Kricketune.Name: Kricketune
Kricketune.Description: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.
Kricketune.Evolution: Kricketune evolves from Kricketot starting from level 10.

Shinx.Name: Shinx
Shinx.Description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.
Shinx.Evolution: Shinx evolves to Luxio starting from level 15, which evolves to Luxray starting from level 30.

Luxio.Name: Luxio
Luxio.Description: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.
Luxio.Evolution: Luxio evolves from Shinx starting from level 15 and evolves to Luxray starting from level 30.

Luxray.Name: Luxray
Luxray.Description: Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.
Luxray.Evolution: Luxray evolves from Luxio starting from level 30, which evolves from Shinx starting from level 15.

Budew.Name: Budew
Budew.Description: When the sun’s light strengthens, the bud atop this Pokémon’s head opens. This is a sign to the people that the harsh winter is over, and the season of budding has begun.
Budew.Evolution: Budew evolves to Roselia when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime, which evolves to Roserade using a Shiny Stone.

Roserade.Name: Roserade
Roserade.Description: Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.
Roserade.Evolution: Roserade evolves from Roselia using a Shiny Stone, which evolves from Budew when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Cranidos.Name: Cranidos
Cranidos.Description: An incredibly rare sight. They duel each other by ramming their heads together, and the resulting sound echoes throughout the area like the pealing of a bell.
Cranidos.Evolution: Cranidos evolves to Rampardos starting from level 30.

Rampardos.Name: Rampardos
Rampardos.Description: Very little is known about its biology. Can knock down massive trees by smashing its beautiful, pearl-like crown against them.
Rampardos.Evolution: Rampardos evolves from Cranidos starting from level 30.

Shieldon.Name: Shieldon
Shieldon.Description: Much remains unknown about this Pokémon, as few have ever seen it. However, we know that it is calm and dislikes conflict, and it enjoys polishing its face against trees and rocks.
Shieldon.Evolution: Shieldon evolves to Bastiodon starting from level 30.

Bastiodon.Name: Bastiodon
Bastiodon.Description: Its face is sturdy—as strong as diamond—and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat.
Bastiodon.Evolution: Bastiodon evolves from Shieldon starting from level 30.

Burmy.Name: Burmy
Burmy.Description: If its cloak is even slightly damaged, Burmy will immediately repair it with whatever is close at hand. The Pokémon within the cloak is scrawny and vulnerable to the cold.
Burmy.Evolution: Burmy evolves to Wormadam starting from level 20 and evolves to Mothim starting from level 20.

Wormadam.Name: Wormadam
Wormadam.Description: The cloak—fashioned from plant matter—has merged with the Pokémon and is now part of the body, like fur or skin. I suspect this fusion is an effect of the energy involved in evolution.
Wormadam.Evolution: Wormadam evolves from Burmy starting from level 20.

Mothim.Name: Mothim
Mothim.Description: Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers, Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.
Mothim.Evolution: Mothim evolves from Burmy starting from level 20.

Combee.Name: Combee
Combee.Description: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.
Combee.Evolution: Combee evolves to Vespiquen starting from level 21.

Vespiquen.Name: Vespiquen
Vespiquen.Description: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control Combee.
Vespiquen.Evolution: Vespiquen evolves from Combee starting from level 21.

Pachirisu.Name: Pachirisu
Pachirisu.Description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

Buizel.Name: Buizel
Buizel.Description: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.
Buizel.Evolution: Buizel evolves to Floatzel starting from level 26.

Floatzel.Name: Floatzel
Floatzel.Description: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and help fishers carry what they caught.
Floatzel.Evolution: Floatzel evolves from Buizel starting from level 26.

Cherubi.Name: Cherubi
Cherubi.Description: Once the fruit growing alongside the main body is large and plump, Cherubi will use the nutrients within to evolve. The fruit then detaches, becoming nourishment for other creatures.
Cherubi.Evolution: Cherubi evolves to Cherrim starting from level 25.

Cherrim.Name: Cherrim
Cherrim.Description: Motionless, save for the occasional quiver. A rich array of Pokémon can be found gathered around it, drawn by the scent exuded from Cherrim’s folded petals.
Cherrim.Evolution: Cherrim evolves from Cherubi starting from level 25.

Shellos.Name: Shellos
Shellos.Description: Found in abundance on seashores bordering warm waters. Shellos are unexpectedly friendly and will crawl toward any person they see. Take care not to get coated in mucus!
Shellos.Evolution: Shellos evolves to Gastrodon starting from level 30.

Gastrodon.Name: Gastrodon
Gastrodon.Description: Eats beach sand for nourishment. Should one Gastrodon encounter another of a different color, a fierce battle will inevitably ensue.
Gastrodon.Evolution: Gastrodon evolves from Shellos starting from level 30.

Ambipom.Name: Ambipom
Ambipom.Description: To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.
Ambipom.Evolution: Ambipom evolves from Aipom when leveled up while knowing Double Hit.

Drifloon.Name: Drifloon
Drifloon.Description: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”
Drifloon.Evolution: Drifloon evolves to Drifblim starting from level 28.

Drifblim.Name: Drifblim
Drifblim.Description: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.
Drifblim.Evolution: Drifblim evolves from Drifloon starting from level 28.

Buneary.Name: Buneary
Buneary.Description: My hypothesis as to why Buneary rolls up its ears is that its hearing is far too keen. I surmise that the Pokémon protects its hearing by limiting the sound that may enter its ears.
Buneary.Evolution: Buneary evolves to Lopunny when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Lopunny.Name: Lopunny
Lopunny.Description: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokémon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.
Lopunny.Evolution: Lopunny evolves from Buneary when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Mismagius.Name: Mismagius
Mismagius.Description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.
Mismagius.Evolution: Mismagius evolves from Misdreavus using a Dusk Stone.

Honchkrow.Name: Honchkrow
Honchkrow.Description: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than 100 of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.
Honchkrow.Evolution: Honchkrow evolves from Murkrow using a Dusk Stone.

Glameow.Name: Glameow
Glameow.Description: Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokémon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.
Glameow.Evolution: Glameow evolves to Purugly starting from level 38.

Purugly.Name: Purugly
Purugly.Description: Though impudent and difficult to tame, Purugly enjoys great popularity due to its fur, the beauty of which surpasses even velveteen.
Purugly.Evolution: Purugly evolves from Glameow starting from level 38.

Chingling.Name: Chingling
Chingling.Description: This Pokémon gave me an excruciating headache when it seemingly cried out without making a sound. Perhaps there are some sounds that the human ear is simply incapable of hearing.
Chingling.Evolution: Chingling evolves to Chimecho when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Stunky.Name: Stunky
Stunky.Description: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.
Stunky.Evolution: Stunky evolves to Skuntank starting from level 34.

Skuntank.Name: Skuntank
Skuntank.Description: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.
Skuntank.Evolution: Skuntank evolves from Stunky starting from level 34.

Bronzor.Name: Bronzor
Bronzor.Description: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.
Bronzor.Evolution: Bronzor evolves to Bronzong starting from level 33.

Bronzong.Name: Bronzong
Bronzong.Description: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.
Bronzong.Evolution: Bronzong evolves from Bronzor starting from level 33.

Bonsly.Name: Bonsly
Bonsly.Description: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.
Bonsly.Evolution: Bonsly evolves to Sudowoodo when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Mime Jr..Name: Mime Jr.
Mime Jr..Description: Known to turn up in bustling marketplaces now and again. It mimics people much as a child would, then watches how they react, eyes sparkling.
Mime Jr..Evolution: Mime Jr. evolves to Mr. Mime when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Happiny.Name: Happiny
Happiny.Description: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It’s bothered by how curly its hair looks.
Happiny.Evolution: Happiny evolves to Chansey when leveled up while holding a Oval Stone in the daytime, which evolves to Blissey when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Chatot.Name: Chatot
Chatot.Description: A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.

Spiritomb.Name: Spiritomb
Spiritomb.Description: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.

Gible.Name: Gible
Gible.Description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
Gible.Evolution: Gible evolves to Gabite starting from level 24, which evolves to Garchomp starting from level 48.

Gabite.Name: Gabite
Gabite.Description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
Gabite.Evolution: Gabite evolves from Gible starting from level 24 and evolves to Garchomp starting from level 48.

Garchomp.Name: Garchomp
Garchomp.Description: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.
Garchomp.Evolution: Garchomp evolves from Gabite starting from level 48, which evolves from Gible starting from level 24.

Munchlax.Name: Munchlax
Munchlax.Description: Its robust stomach allows it to nonchalantly devour even rotted matter. It pays frequent visits to villages, seeking out food scraps intended for compost.
Munchlax.Evolution: Munchlax evolves to Snorlax when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Riolu.Name: Riolu
Riolu.Description: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions, such as joy and rage, in the form of waves.
Riolu.Evolution: Riolu evolves to Lucario when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Lucario.Name: Lucario
Lucario.Description: A well-trained one can use its aura to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.
Lucario.Evolution: Lucario evolves from Riolu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Hippopotas.Name: Hippopotas
Hippopotas.Description: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.
Hippopotas.Evolution: Hippopotas evolves to Hippowdon starting from level 34.

Hippowdon.Name: Hippowdon
Hippowdon.Description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.
Hippowdon.Evolution: Hippowdon evolves from Hippopotas starting from level 34.

Skorupi.Name: Skorupi
Skorupi.Description: Its claws are not only razor-sharp but poisonous, making Skorupi a highly dangerous Pokémon. It seems to be weakened by cold temperatures, however.
Skorupi.Evolution: Skorupi evolves to Drapion starting from level 40.

Drapion.Name: Drapion
Drapion.Description: Has a brutish, ferocious temperament. With immense strength and a sturdy shell off which swords will bounce, it rampages about and wreaks havoc.
Drapion.Evolution: Drapion evolves from Skorupi starting from level 40.

Croagunk.Name: Croagunk
Croagunk.Description: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
Croagunk.Evolution: Croagunk evolves to Toxicroak starting from level 37.

Toxicroak.Name: Toxicroak
Toxicroak.Description: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
Toxicroak.Evolution: Toxicroak evolves from Croagunk starting from level 37.

Carnivine.Name: Carnivine
Carnivine.Description: Though this is a plant Pokémon, it has a gluttonous and unruly temperament. Carnivine attacks its prey with its cavernous maw wide open.

Finneon.Name: Finneon
Finneon.Description: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.
Finneon.Evolution: Finneon evolves to Lumineon starting from level 31.

Lumineon.Name: Lumineon
Lumineon.Description: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.
Lumineon.Evolution: Lumineon evolves from Finneon starting from level 31.

Mantyke.Name: Mantyke
Mantyke.Description: Though ball-like in shape, this Pokémon is a proficient swimmer. I have discovered that if a Mantyke spends much time with schools of Remoraid, it will eventually achieve evolution.
Mantyke.Evolution: Mantyke evolves to Mantine when leveled up.

Snover.Name: Snover
Snover.Description: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.
Snover.Evolution: Snover evolves to Abomasnow starting from level 40.

Abomasnow.Name: Abomasnow
Abomasnow.Description: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
Abomasnow.Evolution: Abomasnow evolves from Snover starting from level 40.

Weavile.Name: Weavile
Weavile.Description: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
Weavile.Evolution: Weavile evolves from Sneasel when leveled up while holding a Razor Claw in the nighttime.

Magnezone.Name: Magnezone
Magnezone.Description: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed Magneton’s molecular structure, turning it into Magnezone.
Magnezone.Evolution: Magnezone evolves from Magneton using a Thunder Stone, which evolves from Magnemite starting from level 30.

Lickilicky.Name: Lickilicky
Lickilicky.Description: Its tongue can extend and contract freely, and it is capable of reaching lengths over 10 times Lickilicky’s height. Beware of the saliva, as it contains corrosive elements.
Lickilicky.Evolution: Lickilicky evolves from Lickitung when leveled up while knowing Rollout.

Rhyperior.Name: Rhyperior
Rhyperior.Description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a curious item. Its rocklike hide is composed of a mysterious substance and can withstand a blow from a masterwork sword with nary a scratch.
Rhyperior.Evolution: Rhyperior evolves from Rhydon when traded while holding a Protector, which evolves from Rhyhorn starting from level 42.

Tangrowth.Name: Tangrowth
Tangrowth.Description: Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.
Tangrowth.Evolution: Tangrowth evolves from Tangela when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Electivire.Name: Electivire
Electivire.Description: Its evolution was induced by an unusual item, and its electrical output rises along with its heart rate. From its tails, it can unleash an electric current measuring 20,000 volts.
Electivire.Evolution: Electivire evolves from Electabuzz when traded while holding a Electirizer, which evolves from Elekid starting from level 30.

Magmortar.Name: Magmortar
Magmortar.Description: Use of a strange item caused this Pokémon to evolve. Fireballs launched from the ends of its tubelike arms are hot enough to melt an iron pot in an instant.
Magmortar.Evolution: Magmortar evolves from Magmar when traded while holding a Magmarizer, which evolves from Magby starting from level 30.

Togekiss.Name: Togekiss
Togekiss.Description: Scant few have ever sighted this Pokémon. After studying what literature remains, I am certain Togekiss will reveal itself when peace reigns in the land.
Togekiss.Evolution: Togekiss evolves from Togetic using a Shiny Stone, which evolves from Togepi when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Yanmega.Name: Yanmega
Yanmega.Description: Extremely violent. When hunting, it wastes none of its energy, aiming only for prey’s most vulnerable spots. Any who manage to tame this Pokémon must be of incredible bravery.
Yanmega.Evolution: Yanmega evolves from Yanma when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Leafeon.Name: Leafeon
Leafeon.Description: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.
Leafeon.Evolution: Leafeon evolves from Eevee using a Leaf Stone.

Glaceon.Name: Glaceon
Glaceon.Description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.
Glaceon.Evolution: Glaceon evolves from Eevee using a Ice Stone.

Gliscor.Name: Gliscor
Gliscor.Description: It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.
Gliscor.Evolution: Gliscor evolves from Gligar when leveled up while holding a Razor Fang in the nighttime.

Mamoswine.Name: Mamoswine
Mamoswine.Description: This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui’s frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine’s constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.
Mamoswine.Evolution: Mamoswine evolves from Piloswine when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power, which evolves from Swinub starting from level 33.

Porygon-Z.Name: Porygon-Z
Porygon-Z.Description: A curious item induced this evolution. The Pokémon’s offensive capabilities have greatly increased, but the strangeness of its behavior has magnified in equal measure. This worries me.
Porygon-Z.Evolution: Porygon-Z evolves from Porygon2 when traded while holding a Dubious Disc, which evolves from Porygon when traded while holding a Upgrade.

Gallade.Name: Gallade
Gallade.Description: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
Gallade.Evolution: Gallade evolves from Kirlia using a Dawn Stone, which evolves from Ralts starting from level 20.

Probopass.Name: Probopass
Probopass.Description: It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.
Probopass.Evolution: Probopass evolves from Nosepass using a Thunder Stone.

Dusknoir.Name: Dusknoir
Dusknoir.Description: Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.
Dusknoir.Evolution: Dusknoir evolves from Dusclops when traded while holding a Reaper Cloth, which evolves from Duskull starting from level 37.

Froslass.Name: Froslass
Froslass.Description: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.
Froslass.Evolution: Froslass evolves from Snorunt using a Dawn Stone.

Rotom.Name: Rotom
Rotom.Description: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

Uxie.Name: Uxie
Uxie.Description: A Pokémon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.

Mesprit.Name: Mesprit
Mesprit.Description: Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokémon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.

Azelf.Name: Azelf
Azelf.Description: The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokémon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.

Dialga.Name: Dialga
Dialga.Description: This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.

Palkia.Name: Palkia
Palkia.Description: This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.

Heatran.Name: Heatran
Heatran.Description: Stories tell of this Pokémon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.

Regigigas.Name: Regigigas
Regigigas.Description: According to legend, Regigigas pulled landmasses together and bound them with rope to create the continent of Hisui. Though I have my doubts, the story could well contain a shred of truth.

Giratina.Name: Giratina
Giratina.Description: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.

Cresselia.Name: Cresselia
Cresselia.Description: Cresselia is reminiscent of the crescent moon. It leaves a brilliant line of light in its wake as it flies across the night sky. I daresay it resembles the heavenly maiden who created the Milky Way.

Phione.Name: Phione
Phione.Description: Can be seen floating offshore during seasons when the seas are warm. Its azure body blends in with the ocean waters—logic suggests this is a defense mechanism against natural predators.

Manaphy.Name: Manaphy
Manaphy.Description: Rumored to migrate across the oceans and visit Hisui’s coastal waters only rarely. Although Manaphy resembles Phione, it is also quite different. The relation between the two is unclear.

Darkrai.Name: Darkrai
Darkrai.Description: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village’s inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.

Shaymin.Name: Shaymin
Shaymin.Description: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.

Arceus.Name: Arceus
Arceus.Description: It is the heavenly fount from which pours the light that shines across Hisui. Its luminance guides and protects all Pokémon. Hisuian mythology states that Arceus is the creator of all things.

Victini.Name: Victini
Victini.Description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.

Snivy.Name: Snivy
Snivy.Description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
Snivy.Evolution: Snivy evolves to Servine starting from level 17, which evolves to Serperior starting from level 36.

Servine.Name: Servine
Servine.Description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
Servine.Evolution: Servine evolves from Snivy starting from level 17 and evolves to Serperior starting from level 36.

Serperior.Name: Serperior
Serperior.Description: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
Serperior.Evolution: Serperior evolves from Servine starting from level 36, which evolves from Snivy starting from level 17.

Tepig.Name: Tepig
Tepig.Description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.
Tepig.Evolution: Tepig evolves to Pignite starting from level 17, which evolves to Emboar starting from level 36.

Pignite.Name: Pignite
Pignite.Description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.
Pignite.Evolution: Pignite evolves from Tepig starting from level 17 and evolves to Emboar starting from level 36.

Emboar.Name: Emboar
Emboar.Description: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
Emboar.Evolution: Emboar evolves from Pignite starting from level 36, which evolves from Tepig starting from level 17.

Oshawott.Name: Oshawott
Oshawott.Description: This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I’ve conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”
Oshawott.Evolution: Oshawott evolves to Dewott starting from level 17, which evolves to Samurott starting from level 36.

Dewott.Name: Dewott
Dewott.Description: Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.
Dewott.Evolution: Dewott evolves from Oshawott starting from level 17 and evolves to Samurott starting from level 36.

Samurott.Name: Samurott
Samurott.Description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
Samurott.Evolution: Samurott evolves from Dewott starting from level 36, which evolves from Oshawott starting from level 17.

Patrat.Name: Patrat
Patrat.Description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.
Patrat.Evolution: Patrat evolves to Watchog starting from level 20.

Watchog.Name: Watchog
Watchog.Description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.
Watchog.Evolution: Watchog evolves from Patrat starting from level 20.

Lillipup.Name: Lillipup
Lillipup.Description: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.
Lillipup.Evolution: Lillipup evolves to Herdier starting from level 16, which evolves to Stoutland starting from level 32.

Herdier.Name: Herdier
Herdier.Description: The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.
Herdier.Evolution: Herdier evolves from Lillipup starting from level 16 and evolves to Stoutland starting from level 32.

Stoutland.Name: Stoutland
Stoutland.Description: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.
Stoutland.Evolution: Stoutland evolves from Herdier starting from level 32, which evolves from Lillipup starting from level 16.

Purrloin.Name: Purrloin
Purrloin.Description: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.
Purrloin.Evolution: Purrloin evolves to Liepard starting from level 20.

Liepard.Name: Liepard
Liepard.Description: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.
Liepard.Evolution: Liepard evolves from Purrloin starting from level 20.

Pansage.Name: Pansage
Pansage.Description: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.
Pansage.Evolution: Pansage evolves to Simisage using a Leaf Stone.

Simisage.Name: Simisage
Simisage.Description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Simisage.Evolution: Simisage evolves from Pansage using a Leaf Stone.

Pansear.Name: Pansear
Pansear.Description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Pansear.Evolution: Pansear evolves to Simisear using a Fire Stone.

Simisear.Name: Simisear
Simisear.Description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
Simisear.Evolution: Simisear evolves from Pansear using a Fire Stone.

Panpour.Name: Panpour
Panpour.Description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
Panpour.Evolution: Panpour evolves to Simipour using a Water Stone.

Simipour.Name: Simipour
Simipour.Description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.
Simipour.Evolution: Simipour evolves from Panpour using a Water Stone.

Munna.Name: Munna
Munna.Description: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.
Munna.Evolution: Munna evolves to Musharna using a Moon Stone.

Musharna.Name: Musharna
Musharna.Description: It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.
Musharna.Evolution: Musharna evolves from Munna using a Moon Stone.

Pidove.Name: Pidove
Pidove.Description: It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.
Pidove.Evolution: Pidove evolves to Tranquill starting from level 21, which evolves to Unfezant starting from level 32.

Tranquill.Name: Tranquill
Tranquill.Description: These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.
Tranquill.Evolution: Tranquill evolves from Pidove starting from level 21 and evolves to Unfezant starting from level 32.

Unfezant.Name: Unfezant
Unfezant.Description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
Unfezant.Evolution: Unfezant evolves from Tranquill starting from level 32, which evolves from Pidove starting from level 21.

Blitzle.Name: Blitzle
Blitzle.Description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
Blitzle.Evolution: Blitzle evolves to Zebstrika starting from level 27.

Zebstrika.Name: Zebstrika
Zebstrika.Description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Zebstrika.Evolution: Zebstrika evolves from Blitzle starting from level 27.

Roggenrola.Name: Roggenrola
Roggenrola.Description: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.
Roggenrola.Evolution: Roggenrola evolves to Boldore starting from level 25, which evolves to Gigalith when traded.

Boldore.Name: Boldore
Boldore.Description: It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.
Boldore.Evolution: Boldore evolves from Roggenrola starting from level 25 and evolves to Gigalith when traded.

Gigalith.Name: Gigalith
Gigalith.Description: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.
Gigalith.Evolution: Gigalith evolves from Boldore when traded, which evolves from Roggenrola starting from level 25.

Woobat.Name: Woobat
Woobat.Description: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.
Woobat.Evolution: Woobat evolves to Swoobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Swoobat.Name: Swoobat
Swoobat.Description: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.
Swoobat.Evolution: Swoobat evolves from Woobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Drilbur.Name: Drilbur
Drilbur.Description: It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.
Drilbur.Evolution: Drilbur evolves to Excadrill starting from level 31.

Excadrill.Name: Excadrill
Excadrill.Description: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.
Excadrill.Evolution: Excadrill evolves from Drilbur starting from level 31.

Audino.Name: Audino
Audino.Description: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

Timburr.Name: Timburr
Timburr.Description: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.
Timburr.Evolution: Timburr evolves to Gurdurr starting from level 25, which evolves to Conkeldurr when traded.

Gurdurr.Name: Gurdurr
Gurdurr.Description: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there’s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.
Gurdurr.Evolution: Gurdurr evolves from Timburr starting from level 25 and evolves to Conkeldurr when traded.

Conkeldurr.Name: Conkeldurr
Conkeldurr.Description: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.
Conkeldurr.Evolution: Conkeldurr evolves from Gurdurr when traded, which evolves from Timburr starting from level 25.

Tympole.Name: Tympole
Tympole.Description: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.
Tympole.Evolution: Tympole evolves to Palpitoad starting from level 25, which evolves to Seismitoad starting from level 36.

Palpitoad.Name: Palpitoad
Palpitoad.Description: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.
Palpitoad.Evolution: Palpitoad evolves from Tympole starting from level 25 and evolves to Seismitoad starting from level 36.

Seismitoad.Name: Seismitoad
Seismitoad.Description: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.
Seismitoad.Evolution: Seismitoad evolves from Palpitoad starting from level 36, which evolves from Tympole starting from level 25.

Throh.Name: Throh
Throh.Description: They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.

Sawk.Name: Sawk
Sawk.Description: The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.

Sewaddle.Name: Sewaddle
Sewaddle.Description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.
Sewaddle.Evolution: Sewaddle evolves to Swadloon starting from level 20, which evolves to Leavanny when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Swadloon.Name: Swadloon
Swadloon.Description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
Swadloon.Evolution: Swadloon evolves from Sewaddle starting from level 20 and evolves to Leavanny when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Leavanny.Name: Leavanny
Leavanny.Description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.
Leavanny.Evolution: Leavanny evolves from Swadloon when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves from Sewaddle starting from level 20.

Venipede.Name: Venipede
Venipede.Description: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.
Venipede.Evolution: Venipede evolves to Whirlipede starting from level 22, which evolves to Scolipede starting from level 30.

Whirlipede.Name: Whirlipede
Whirlipede.Description: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.
Whirlipede.Evolution: Whirlipede evolves from Venipede starting from level 22 and evolves to Scolipede starting from level 30.

Scolipede.Name: Scolipede
Scolipede.Description: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.
Scolipede.Evolution: Scolipede evolves from Whirlipede starting from level 30, which evolves from Venipede starting from level 22.

Cottonee.Name: Cottonee
Cottonee.Description: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.
Cottonee.Evolution: Cottonee evolves to Whimsicott using a Sun Stone.

Whimsicott.Name: Whimsicott
Whimsicott.Description: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.
Whimsicott.Evolution: Whimsicott evolves from Cottonee using a Sun Stone.

Petilil.Name: Petilil
Petilil.Description: If the leaves on its head are pruned with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.
Petilil.Evolution: Petilil evolves to Lilligant using a Sun Stone.

Lilligant.Name: Lilligant
Lilligant.Description: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.
Lilligant.Evolution: Lilligant evolves from Petilil using a Sun Stone.

Basculin.Name: Basculin
Basculin.Description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.

Sandile.Name: Sandile
Sandile.Description: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.
Sandile.Evolution: Sandile evolves to Krokorok starting from level 29, which evolves to Krookodile starting from level 40.

Krokorok.Name: Krokorok
Krokorok.Description: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.
Krokorok.Evolution: Krokorok evolves from Sandile starting from level 29 and evolves to Krookodile starting from level 40.

Krookodile.Name: Krookodile
Krookodile.Description: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
Krookodile.Evolution: Krookodile evolves from Krokorok starting from level 40, which evolves from Sandile starting from level 29.

Darumaka.Name: Darumaka
Darumaka.Description: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it’s pushed or pulled.
Darumaka.Evolution: Darumaka evolves to Darmanitan starting from level 35.

Darmanitan.Name: Darmanitan
Darmanitan.Description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
Darmanitan.Evolution: Darmanitan evolves from Darumaka starting from level 35.

Maractus.Name: Maractus
Maractus.Description: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

Dwebble.Name: Dwebble
Dwebble.Description: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.
Dwebble.Evolution: Dwebble evolves to Crustle starting from level 34.

Crustle.Name: Crustle
Crustle.Description: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.
Crustle.Evolution: Crustle evolves from Dwebble starting from level 34.

Scraggy.Name: Scraggy
Scraggy.Description: It protects itself with its durable skin. It’s thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.
Scraggy.Evolution: Scraggy evolves to Scrafty starting from level 39.

Scrafty.Name: Scrafty
Scrafty.Description: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.
Scrafty.Evolution: Scrafty evolves from Scraggy starting from level 39.

Sigilyph.Name: Sigilyph
Sigilyph.Description: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

Yamask.Name: Yamask
Yamask.Description: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.
Yamask.Evolution: Yamask evolves to Cofagrigus starting from level 34.

Cofagrigus.Name: Cofagrigus
Cofagrigus.Description: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They’re symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.
Cofagrigus.Evolution: Cofagrigus evolves from Yamask starting from level 34.

Tirtouga.Name: Tirtouga
Tirtouga.Description: Tirtouga is considered to be the ancestor of many turtle Pokémon. It was restored to life from a fossil.
Tirtouga.Evolution: Tirtouga evolves to Carracosta starting from level 37.

Carracosta.Name: Carracosta
Carracosta.Description: This Pokémon emerges from the water in search of prey despite the fact that it moves more slowly on land.
Carracosta.Evolution: Carracosta evolves from Tirtouga starting from level 37.

Archen.Name: Archen
Archen.Description: Archen is said to be the ancestor of bird Pokémon. It lived in treetops, eating berries and bug Pokémon.
Archen.Evolution: Archen evolves to Archeops starting from level 37.

Archeops.Name: Archeops
Archeops.Description: Though capable of flight, Archeops was apparently better at hunting on the ground.
Archeops.Evolution: Archeops evolves from Archen starting from level 37.

Trubbish.Name: Trubbish
Trubbish.Description: This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.
Trubbish.Evolution: Trubbish evolves to Garbodor starting from level 36.

Garbodor.Name: Garbodor
Garbodor.Description: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
Garbodor.Evolution: Garbodor evolves from Trubbish starting from level 36.

Zorua.Name: Zorua
Zorua.Description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
Zorua.Evolution: Zorua evolves to Zoroark starting from level 30.

Zoroark.Name: Zoroark
Zoroark.Description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
Zoroark.Evolution: Zoroark evolves from Zorua starting from level 30.

Minccino.Name: Minccino
Minccino.Description: They pet each other with their tails as a form of greeting. Of the two, the one whose tail is fluffier is a bit more boastful.
Minccino.Evolution: Minccino evolves to Cinccino using a Shiny Stone.

Cinccino.Name: Cinccino
Cinccino.Description: A special oil that seeps through their fur helps them avoid attacks. The oil fetches a high price at market.
Cinccino.Evolution: Cinccino evolves from Minccino using a Shiny Stone.

Gothita.Name: Gothita
Gothita.Description: Beware of touching the ribbon-shaped feelers that control its psychic power. Gothita will begin bawling if you do.
Gothita.Evolution: Gothita evolves to Gothorita starting from level 32, which evolves to Gothitelle starting from level 41.

Gothorita.Name: Gothorita
Gothorita.Description: Using its psychic power, it arranges pebbles to form the shapes of constellations. Some people believe this Pokémon came from outer space.
Gothorita.Evolution: Gothorita evolves from Gothita starting from level 32 and evolves to Gothitelle starting from level 41.

Gothitelle.Name: Gothitelle
Gothitelle.Description: It gazes at the stars to predict the future. It acts somewhat detached because it has seen the end of all existence.
Gothitelle.Evolution: Gothitelle evolves from Gothorita starting from level 41, which evolves from Gothita starting from level 32.

Solosis.Name: Solosis
Solosis.Description: Many say that the special liquid covering this Pokémon’s body would allow it to survive in the vacuum of space.
Solosis.Evolution: Solosis evolves to Duosion starting from level 32, which evolves to Reuniclus starting from level 41.

Duosion.Name: Duosion
Duosion.Description: Its brain has split into two, and the two halves rarely think alike. Its actions are utterly unpredictable.
Duosion.Evolution: Duosion evolves from Solosis starting from level 32 and evolves to Reuniclus starting from level 41.

Reuniclus.Name: Reuniclus
Reuniclus.Description: It’s said that drinking the liquid surrounding Reuniclus grants wisdom. Problem is, the liquid is highly toxic to anything besides Reuniclus itself.
Reuniclus.Evolution: Reuniclus evolves from Duosion starting from level 41, which evolves from Solosis starting from level 32.

Ducklett.Name: Ducklett
Ducklett.Description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.
Ducklett.Evolution: Ducklett evolves to Swanna starting from level 35.

Swanna.Name: Swanna
Swanna.Description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
Swanna.Evolution: Swanna evolves from Ducklett starting from level 35.

Vanillite.Name: Vanillite
Vanillite.Description: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.
Vanillite.Evolution: Vanillite evolves to Vanillish starting from level 35, which evolves to Vanilluxe starting from level 47.

Vanillish.Name: Vanillish
Vanillish.Description: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it’s a kind Pokémon.
Vanillish.Evolution: Vanillish evolves from Vanillite starting from level 35 and evolves to Vanilluxe starting from level 47.

Vanilluxe.Name: Vanilluxe
Vanilluxe.Description: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.
Vanilluxe.Evolution: Vanilluxe evolves from Vanillish starting from level 47, which evolves from Vanillite starting from level 35.

Deerling.Name: Deerling
Deerling.Description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon’s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.
Deerling.Evolution: Deerling evolves to Sawsbuck starting from level 34.

Sawsbuck.Name: Sawsbuck
Sawsbuck.Description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.
Sawsbuck.Evolution: Sawsbuck evolves from Deerling starting from level 34.

Emolga.Name: Emolga
Emolga.Description: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can’t fly properly.

Karrablast.Name: Karrablast
Karrablast.Description: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet’s shell. Karrablast doesn’t eat the shell— it eats only the contents.
Karrablast.Evolution: Karrablast evolves to Escavalier when traded.

Escavalier.Name: Escavalier
Escavalier.Description: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch’d.
Escavalier.Evolution: Escavalier evolves from Karrablast when traded.

Foongus.Name: Foongus
Foongus.Description: This Pokémon prefers damp places. It spurts out poison spores to repel approaching enemies.
Foongus.Evolution: Foongus evolves to Amoonguss starting from level 39.

Amoonguss.Name: Amoonguss
Amoonguss.Description: Amoonguss mimics Poké Balls. It is not yet clear whether this mimicry is effective against other Pokémon.
Amoonguss.Evolution: Amoonguss evolves from Foongus starting from level 39.

Frillish.Name: Frillish
Frillish.Description: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.
Frillish.Evolution: Frillish evolves to Jellicent starting from level 40.

Jellicent.Name: Jellicent
Jellicent.Description: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It’s rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.
Jellicent.Evolution: Jellicent evolves from Frillish starting from level 40.

Alomomola.Name: Alomomola
Alomomola.Description: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

Joltik.Name: Joltik
Joltik.Description: Joltik latch on to other Pokémon and suck out static electricity. They’re often found sticking to Yamper’s hindquarters.
Joltik.Evolution: Joltik evolves to Galvantula starting from level 36.

Galvantula.Name: Galvantula
Galvantula.Description: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokémon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.
Galvantula.Evolution: Galvantula evolves from Joltik starting from level 36.

Ferroseed.Name: Ferroseed
Ferroseed.Description: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed’s spikes grow big and strong.
Ferroseed.Evolution: Ferroseed evolves to Ferrothorn starting from level 40.

Ferrothorn.Name: Ferrothorn
Ferrothorn.Description: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.
Ferrothorn.Evolution: Ferrothorn evolves from Ferroseed starting from level 40.

Klink.Name: Klink
Klink.Description: It’s suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people’s invention of the first gears.
Klink.Evolution: Klink evolves to Klang starting from level 38, which evolves to Klinklang starting from level 49.

Klang.Name: Klang
Klang.Description: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokémon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.
Klang.Evolution: Klang evolves from Klink starting from level 38 and evolves to Klinklang starting from level 49.

Klinklang.Name: Klinklang
Klinklang.Description: The three gears that compose this Pokémon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn’t a living creature.
Klinklang.Evolution: Klinklang evolves from Klang starting from level 49, which evolves from Klink starting from level 38.

Tynamo.Name: Tynamo
Tynamo.Description: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.
Tynamo.Evolution: Tynamo evolves to Eelektrik starting from level 39, which evolves to Eelektross using a Thunder Stone.

Eelektrik.Name: Eelektrik
Eelektrik.Description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
Eelektrik.Evolution: Eelektrik evolves from Tynamo starting from level 39 and evolves to Eelektross using a Thunder Stone.

Eelektross.Name: Eelektross
Eelektross.Description: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.
Eelektross.Evolution: Eelektross evolves from Eelektrik using a Thunder Stone, which evolves from Tynamo starting from level 39.

Elgyem.Name: Elgyem
Elgyem.Description: This Pokémon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.
Elgyem.Evolution: Elgyem evolves to Beheeyem starting from level 42.

Beheeyem.Name: Beheeyem
Beheeyem.Description: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.
Beheeyem.Evolution: Beheeyem evolves from Elgyem starting from level 42.

Litwick.Name: Litwick
Litwick.Description: The younger the life this Pokémon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.
Litwick.Evolution: Litwick evolves to Lampent starting from level 41, which evolves to Chandelure using a Dusk Stone.

Lampent.Name: Lampent
Lampent.Description: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.
Lampent.Evolution: Lampent evolves from Litwick starting from level 41 and evolves to Chandelure using a Dusk Stone.

Chandelure.Name: Chandelure
Chandelure.Description: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence— or so it’s said.
Chandelure.Evolution: Chandelure evolves from Lampent using a Dusk Stone, which evolves from Litwick starting from level 41.

Axew.Name: Axew
Axew.Description: If you see peculiar teeth marks on boulders or trees, it means an Axew is likely living nearby.
Axew.Evolution: Axew evolves to Fraxure starting from level 38, which evolves to Haxorus starting from level 48.

Fraxure.Name: Fraxure
Fraxure.Description: Fraxure uses its thick tusks to neatly cut prey into two portions—one to eat now and one to save for later.
Fraxure.Evolution: Fraxure evolves from Axew starting from level 38 and evolves to Haxorus starting from level 48.

Haxorus.Name: Haxorus
Haxorus.Description: It overwhelms enemies with its prized tusks, which are sharp enough to cut through a metal transmission tower in one strike.
Haxorus.Evolution: Haxorus evolves from Fraxure starting from level 48, which evolves from Axew starting from level 38.

Cubchoo.Name: Cubchoo
Cubchoo.Description: When Cubchoo starts sneezing, watch out! If it spatters you with its frosty snot, you’ll get frostbite.
Cubchoo.Evolution: Cubchoo evolves to Beartic starting from level 37.

Beartic.Name: Beartic
Beartic.Description: Feared as the Snow-White Demon in northern lands, Beartic uses its frosty claws and fangs to attack prey.
Beartic.Evolution: Beartic evolves from Cubchoo starting from level 37.

Cryogonal.Name: Cryogonal
Cryogonal.Description: Cryogonal uses its chains of ice to constrict its opponents and then flash-freezes them where they stand.

Shelmet.Name: Shelmet
Shelmet.Description: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.
Shelmet.Evolution: Shelmet evolves to Accelgor when traded.

Accelgor.Name: Accelgor
Accelgor.Description: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.
Accelgor.Evolution: Accelgor evolves from Shelmet when traded.

Stunfisk.Name: Stunfisk
Stunfisk.Description: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

Mienfoo.Name: Mienfoo
Mienfoo.Description: Though small, Mienfoo’s temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.
Mienfoo.Evolution: Mienfoo evolves to Mienshao starting from level 50.

Mienshao.Name: Mienshao
Mienshao.Description: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokémon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.
Mienshao.Evolution: Mienshao evolves from Mienfoo starting from level 50.

Druddigon.Name: Druddigon
Druddigon.Description: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

Golett.Name: Golett
Golett.Description: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.
Golett.Evolution: Golett evolves to Golurk starting from level 43.

Golurk.Name: Golurk
Golurk.Description: There’s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn’t been proven.
Golurk.Evolution: Golurk evolves from Golett starting from level 43.

Pawniard.Name: Pawniard
Pawniard.Description: Any chips in its blades would prove fatal for it. After each battle, it diligently maintains its blades using its favorite sharpening stone.
Pawniard.Evolution: Pawniard evolves to Bisharp starting from level 52.

Bisharp.Name: Bisharp
Bisharp.Description: Bisharp mercilessly cuts its opponents to pieces with the sharp blades covering its body. It will do anything to win.
Bisharp.Evolution: Bisharp evolves from Pawniard starting from level 52.

Bouffalant.Name: Bouffalant
Bouffalant.Description: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

Rufflet.Name: Rufflet
Rufflet.Description: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.
Rufflet.Evolution: Rufflet evolves to Braviary starting from level 54.

Braviary.Name: Braviary
Braviary.Description: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
Braviary.Evolution: Braviary evolves from Rufflet starting from level 54.

Vullaby.Name: Vullaby
Vullaby.Description: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.
Vullaby.Evolution: Vullaby evolves to Mandibuzz starting from level 54.

Mandibuzz.Name: Mandibuzz
Mandibuzz.Description: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.
Mandibuzz.Evolution: Mandibuzz evolves from Vullaby starting from level 54.

Heatmor.Name: Heatmor
Heatmor.Description: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

Durant.Name: Durant
Durant.Description: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

Deino.Name: Deino
Deino.Description: It nests deep inside a cave. Food there is scarce, so Deino will sink its teeth into anything that moves and attempt to eat it.
Deino.Evolution: Deino evolves to Zweilous starting from level 50, which evolves to Hydreigon starting from level 64.

Zweilous.Name: Zweilous
Zweilous.Description: The two heads have different likes and dislikes. Because the heads fight with each other, Zweilous gets stronger without needing to rely on others.
Zweilous.Evolution: Zweilous evolves from Deino starting from level 50 and evolves to Hydreigon starting from level 64.

Hydreigon.Name: Hydreigon
Hydreigon.Description: It’s said that Hydreigon grew ferocious because people in times long past loathed it, considering it to be evil incarnate and attacking it relentlessly.
Hydreigon.Evolution: Hydreigon evolves from Zweilous starting from level 64, which evolves from Deino starting from level 50.

Larvesta.Name: Larvesta
Larvesta.Description: In ancient times, Larvesta was worshiped as the emissary of the sun. However, it was also viewed as a burden since it often caused forest fires.
Larvesta.Evolution: Larvesta evolves to Volcarona starting from level 59.

Volcarona.Name: Volcarona
Volcarona.Description: This Pokémon scatters burning scales. Most of the danger of these scales is not in their heat—it’s in the way they rob the surrounding air of oxygen.
Volcarona.Evolution: Volcarona evolves from Larvesta starting from level 59.

Cobalion.Name: Cobalion
Cobalion.Description: From the moment it’s born, this Pokémon radiates the air of a leader. Its presence will calm even vicious foes.

Terrakion.Name: Terrakion
Terrakion.Description: In Unovan legend, Terrakion battled against humans in an effort to protect other Pokémon.

Virizion.Name: Virizion
Virizion.Description: It darts around opponents with a flurry of quick movements, slicing them up with its horns.

Tornadus.Name: Tornadus
Tornadus.Description: This storm-stirring Pokémon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.

Thundurus.Name: Thundurus
Thundurus.Description: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.

Reshiram.Name: Reshiram
Reshiram.Description: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

Zekrom.Name: Zekrom
Zekrom.Description: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom’s lightning.

Landorus.Name: Landorus
Landorus.Description: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

Kyurem.Name: Kyurem
Kyurem.Description: It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.

Keldeo.Name: Keldeo
Keldeo.Description: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

Meloetta.Name: Meloetta
Meloetta.Description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Genesect.Name: Genesect
Genesect.Description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

Chespin.Name: Chespin
Chespin.Description: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn’t faze it.
Chespin.Evolution: Chespin evolves to Quilladin starting from level 16, which evolves to Chesnaught starting from level 36.

Quilladin.Name: Quilladin
