Quilladin.Description: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won’t start fights.
Quilladin.Evolution: Quilladin evolves from Chespin starting from level 16 and evolves to Chesnaught starting from level 36.

Chesnaught.Name: Chesnaught
Chesnaught.Description: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.
Chesnaught.Evolution: Chesnaught evolves from Quilladin starting from level 36, which evolves from Chespin starting from level 16.

Fennekin.Name: Fennekin
Fennekin.Description: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
Fennekin.Evolution: Fennekin evolves to Braixen starting from level 16, which evolves to Delphox starting from level 36.

Braixen.Name: Braixen
Braixen.Description: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
Braixen.Evolution: Braixen evolves from Fennekin starting from level 16 and evolves to Delphox starting from level 36.

Delphox.Name: Delphox
Delphox.Description: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
Delphox.Evolution: Delphox evolves from Braixen starting from level 36, which evolves from Fennekin starting from level 16.

Froakie.Name: Froakie
Froakie.Description: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
Froakie.Evolution: Froakie evolves to Frogadier starting from level 16, which evolves to Greninja starting from level 36.

Frogadier.Name: Frogadier
Frogadier.Description: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.
Frogadier.Evolution: Frogadier evolves from Froakie starting from level 16 and evolves to Greninja starting from level 36.

Greninja.Name: Greninja
Greninja.Description: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
Greninja.Evolution: Greninja evolves from Frogadier starting from level 36, which evolves from Froakie starting from level 16.

Bunnelby.Name: Bunnelby
Bunnelby.Description: It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.
Bunnelby.Evolution: Bunnelby evolves to Diggersby starting from level 20.

Diggersby.Name: Diggersby
Diggersby.Description: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.
Diggersby.Evolution: Diggersby evolves from Bunnelby starting from level 20.

Fletchling.Name: Fletchling
Fletchling.Description: Fletchling can be found in both rural and urban areas. They once had a huge territorial dispute with Squawkabilly. Fights broke out all over town.
Fletchling.Evolution: Fletchling evolves to Fletchinder starting from level 17, which evolves to Talonflame starting from level 35.

Fletchinder.Name: Fletchinder
Fletchinder.Description: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.
Fletchinder.Evolution: Fletchinder evolves from Fletchling starting from level 17 and evolves to Talonflame starting from level 35.

Talonflame.Name: Talonflame
Talonflame.Description: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.
Talonflame.Evolution: Talonflame evolves from Fletchinder starting from level 35, which evolves from Fletchling starting from level 17.

Scatterbug.Name: Scatterbug
Scatterbug.Description: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.
Scatterbug.Evolution: Scatterbug evolves to Spewpa starting from level 9, which evolves to Vivillon starting from level 12.

Spewpa.Name: Spewpa
Spewpa.Description: Spewpa doesn’t live in a fixed location. It roams where it pleases across the fields and mountains, building up the energy it needs to evolve.
Spewpa.Evolution: Spewpa evolves from Scatterbug starting from level 9 and evolves to Vivillon starting from level 12.

Vivillon.Name: Vivillon
Vivillon.Description: The patterns on this Pokémon’s wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.
Vivillon.Evolution: Vivillon evolves from Spewpa starting from level 12, which evolves from Scatterbug starting from level 9.

Litleo.Name: Litleo
Litleo.Description: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.
Litleo.Evolution: Litleo evolves to Pyroar starting from level 35.

Pyroar.Name: Pyroar
Pyroar.Description: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.
Pyroar.Evolution: Pyroar evolves from Litleo starting from level 35.

Flab\u00e9b\u00e9.Name: Flabébé
Flab\u00e9b\u00e9.Description: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’s collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.
Flab\u00e9b\u00e9.Evolution: Flabébé evolves to Floette starting from level 19, which evolves to Florges using a Shiny Stone.

Floette.Name: Floette
Floette.Description: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.
Floette.Evolution: Floette evolves from Flabébé starting from level 19 and evolves to Florges using a Shiny Stone.

Florges.Name: Florges
Florges.Description: Its life can span several hundred years. It’s said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.
Florges.Evolution: Florges evolves from Floette using a Shiny Stone, which evolves from Flabébé starting from level 19.

Skiddo.Name: Skiddo
Skiddo.Description: As long as it has sunlight and water, Skiddo can make energy with the leaves on its body, allowing it to live on rocky mountains barren of food.
Skiddo.Evolution: Skiddo evolves to Gogoat starting from level 32.

Gogoat.Name: Gogoat
Gogoat.Description: These Pokémon live in herds in mountainous places. The victor in their contests of clashing horns will become the leader of the herd.
Gogoat.Evolution: Gogoat evolves from Skiddo starting from level 32.

Pancham.Name: Pancham
Pancham.Description: Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.
Pancham.Evolution: Pancham evolves to Pangoro starting from level 32.

Pangoro.Name: Pangoro
Pangoro.Description: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.
Pangoro.Evolution: Pangoro evolves from Pancham starting from level 32.

Furfrou.Name: Furfrou
Furfrou.Description: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

Espurr.Name: Espurr
Espurr.Description: There’s enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can’t be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.
Espurr.Evolution: Espurr evolves to Meowstic starting from level 25.

Meowstic.Name: Meowstic
Meowstic.Description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
Meowstic.Evolution: Meowstic evolves from Espurr starting from level 25.

Honedge.Name: Honedge
Honedge.Description: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.
Honedge.Evolution: Honedge evolves to Doublade starting from level 35, which evolves to Aegislash using a Dusk Stone.

Doublade.Name: Doublade
Doublade.Description: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.
Doublade.Evolution: Doublade evolves from Honedge starting from level 35 and evolves to Aegislash using a Dusk Stone.

Aegislash.Name: Aegislash
Aegislash.Description: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
Aegislash.Evolution: Aegislash evolves from Doublade using a Dusk Stone, which evolves from Honedge starting from level 35.

Spritzee.Name: Spritzee
Spritzee.Description: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.
Spritzee.Evolution: Spritzee evolves to Aromatisse when traded while holding a Sachet.

Aromatisse.Name: Aromatisse
Aromatisse.Description: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent’s will to fight.
Aromatisse.Evolution: Aromatisse evolves from Spritzee when traded while holding a Sachet.

Swirlix.Name: Swirlix
Swirlix.Description: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix’s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.
Swirlix.Evolution: Swirlix evolves to Slurpuff when traded while holding a Whipped Dream.

Slurpuff.Name: Slurpuff
Slurpuff.Description: Slurpuff’s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.
Slurpuff.Evolution: Slurpuff evolves from Swirlix when traded while holding a Whipped Dream.

Inkay.Name: Inkay
Inkay.Description: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.
Inkay.Evolution: Inkay evolves to Malamar starting from level 30.

Malamar.Name: Malamar
Malamar.Description: It’s said that Malamar’s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.
Malamar.Evolution: Malamar evolves from Inkay starting from level 30.

Binacle.Name: Binacle
Binacle.Description: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.
Binacle.Evolution: Binacle evolves to Barbaracle starting from level 39.

Barbaracle.Name: Barbaracle
Barbaracle.Description: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.
Barbaracle.Evolution: Barbaracle evolves from Binacle starting from level 39.

Skrelp.Name: Skrelp
Skrelp.Description: This Pokémon is a poor swimmer. If it’s caught in a fierce storm, it will sometimes get washed far away and become unable to return to its home.
Skrelp.Evolution: Skrelp evolves to Dragalge starting from level 48.

Dragalge.Name: Dragalge
Dragalge.Description: Since Finizen is the better swimmer, Dragalge will approach it under the cover of seaweed, then immobilize it with a poisonous attack.
Dragalge.Evolution: Dragalge evolves from Skrelp starting from level 48.

Clauncher.Name: Clauncher
Clauncher.Description: Clauncher’s claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn’t appeal to all tastes.
Clauncher.Evolution: Clauncher evolves to Clawitzer starting from level 37.

Clawitzer.Name: Clawitzer
Clawitzer.Description: The cannonballs of seawater that Clawitzer launches from its claw are powerful enough to punch through tanker hulls.
Clawitzer.Evolution: Clawitzer evolves from Clauncher starting from level 37.

Helioptile.Name: Helioptile
Helioptile.Description: The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.
Helioptile.Evolution: Helioptile evolves to Heliolisk using a Sun Stone.

Heliolisk.Name: Heliolisk
Heliolisk.Description: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.
Heliolisk.Evolution: Heliolisk evolves from Helioptile using a Sun Stone.

Tyrunt.Name: Tyrunt
Tyrunt.Description: This Pokémon is selfish and likes to be pampered. It can also inflict grievous wounds on its Trainer just by playing around.
Tyrunt.Evolution: Tyrunt evolves to Tyrantrum starting from level 39 in the daytime.

Tyrantrum.Name: Tyrantrum
Tyrantrum.Description: A single bite of Tyrantrum’s massive jaws will demolish a car. This Pokémon was the king of the ancient world.
Tyrantrum.Evolution: Tyrantrum evolves from Tyrunt starting from level 39 in the daytime.

Amaura.Name: Amaura
Amaura.Description: Amaura is an ancient Pokémon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.
Amaura.Evolution: Amaura evolves to Aurorus starting from level 39 in the nighttime.

Aurorus.Name: Aurorus
Aurorus.Description: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.
Aurorus.Evolution: Aurorus evolves from Amaura starting from level 39 in the nighttime.

Sylveon.Name: Sylveon
Sylveon.Description: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.
Sylveon.Evolution: Sylveon evolves from Eevee when leveled up while knowing a Fairy-type move.

Hawlucha.Name: Hawlucha
Hawlucha.Description: Hawlucha live quietly without flocking together. They fight constantly with their natural enemies: noisy groups of Primeape.

Dedenne.Name: Dedenne
Dedenne.Description: Dedenne emit electrical waves from the whiskers on their cheeks to communicate with each other. When low on electricity, they curl up and sleep.

Carbink.Name: Carbink
Carbink.Description: It’s said that somewhere in the world, there’s a mineral vein housing a large pack of slumbering Carbink. It’s also said that this pack has a queen.

Goomy.Name: Goomy
Goomy.Description: Goomy’s horns are excellent sensory organs that cover all five of Goomy’s senses. Goomy picks up on danger from the movement of the air.
Goomy.Evolution: Goomy evolves to Sliggoo starting from level 40, which evolves to Goodra starting from level 50.

Sliggoo.Name: Sliggoo
Sliggoo.Description: When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated—it’ll dissolve anything.
Sliggoo.Evolution: Sliggoo evolves from Goomy starting from level 40 and evolves to Goodra starting from level 50.

Goodra.Name: Goodra
Goodra.Description: This Pokémon is uncontrollable when enraged. It rampages on and on, lashing its tail with enough power to send a dump truck flying.
Goodra.Evolution: Goodra evolves from Sliggoo starting from level 50, which evolves from Goomy starting from level 40.

Klefki.Name: Klefki
Klefki.Description: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.

Phantump.Name: Phantump
Phantump.Description: With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.
Phantump.Evolution: Phantump evolves to Trevenant when traded.

Trevenant.Name: Trevenant
Trevenant.Description: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.
Trevenant.Evolution: Trevenant evolves from Phantump when traded.

Pumpkaboo.Name: Pumpkaboo
Pumpkaboo.Description: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.
Pumpkaboo.Evolution: Pumpkaboo evolves to Gourgeist when traded.

Gourgeist.Name: Gourgeist
Gourgeist.Description: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.
Gourgeist.Evolution: Gourgeist evolves from Pumpkaboo when traded.

Bergmite.Name: Bergmite
Bergmite.Description: Bergmite protects itself by coating its body in ice formed by frigid air of −148 degrees Fahrenheit. It fights with Frigibax whenever they meet.
Bergmite.Evolution: Bergmite evolves to Avalugg starting from level 37.

Avalugg.Name: Avalugg
Avalugg.Description: This Pokémon uses its massive icy body to flatten anything that gets in its way. When it’s floating out on the ocean, it looks exactly like drift ice.
Avalugg.Evolution: Avalugg evolves from Bergmite starting from level 37.

Noibat.Name: Noibat
Noibat.Description: Noibat can change the frequency of its sound waves at will, and it generates ultrasonic waves of up to 200,000 hertz.
Noibat.Evolution: Noibat evolves to Noivern starting from level 48.

Noivern.Name: Noivern
Noivern.Description: In the dark, even Hydreigon are terrified of this Pokémon. But in the light, Noivern is the one that avoids battle.
Noivern.Evolution: Noivern evolves from Noibat starting from level 48.

Xerneas.Name: Xerneas
Xerneas.Description: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

Yveltal.Name: Yveltal
Yveltal.Description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

Zygarde.Name: Zygarde
Zygarde.Description: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

Diancie.Name: Diancie
Diancie.Description: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

Hoopa.Name: Hoopa
Hoopa.Description: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

Volcanion.Name: Volcanion
Volcanion.Description: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

Rowlet.Name: Rowlet
Rowlet.Description: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.
Rowlet.Evolution: Rowlet evolves to Dartrix starting from level 17, which evolves to Decidueye starting from level 34.

Dartrix.Name: Dartrix
Dartrix.Description: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power—presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.
Dartrix.Evolution: Dartrix evolves from Rowlet starting from level 17 and evolves to Decidueye starting from level 34.

Decidueye.Name: Decidueye
Decidueye.Description: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent’s weak point before they notice what’s happening.
Decidueye.Evolution: Decidueye evolves from Dartrix starting from level 34, which evolves from Rowlet starting from level 17.

Litten.Name: Litten
Litten.Description: Trying to pet Litten before it trusts you will result in a nasty scratch from its sharp claws. Be careful.
Litten.Evolution: Litten evolves to Torracat starting from level 17, which evolves to Incineroar starting from level 34.

Torracat.Name: Torracat
Torracat.Description: When facing a powerful enemy, Torracat’s fighting spirit gets pumped up, and its fire bell blazes hotter.
Torracat.Evolution: Torracat evolves from Litten starting from level 17 and evolves to Incineroar starting from level 34.

Incineroar.Name: Incineroar
Incineroar.Description: Incineroar’s rough and aggressive behavior is its most notable trait, but the way it helps out small Pokémon shows that it has a kind side as well.
Incineroar.Evolution: Incineroar evolves from Torracat starting from level 34, which evolves from Litten starting from level 17.

Popplio.Name: Popplio
Popplio.Description: If Popplio want to create big, powerful balloons, they must be persistent. It takes daily practice for these Pokémon to develop their skills.
Popplio.Evolution: Popplio evolves to Brionne starting from level 17, which evolves to Primarina starting from level 34.

Brionne.Name: Brionne
Brionne.Description: On nights when the sea is calm, Brionne dance with one another to the singing of the Primarina that’s leading them.
Brionne.Evolution: Brionne evolves from Popplio starting from level 17 and evolves to Primarina starting from level 34.

Primarina.Name: Primarina
Primarina.Description: For Primarina, every battle’s a stage. Its singing and the dancing of its balloons will mesmerize the audience.
Primarina.Evolution: Primarina evolves from Brionne starting from level 34, which evolves from Popplio starting from level 17.

Pikipek.Name: Pikipek
Pikipek.Description: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!
Pikipek.Evolution: Pikipek evolves to Trumbeak starting from level 14, which evolves to Toucannon starting from level 28.

Trumbeak.Name: Trumbeak
Trumbeak.Description: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.
Trumbeak.Evolution: Trumbeak evolves from Pikipek starting from level 14 and evolves to Toucannon starting from level 28.

Toucannon.Name: Toucannon
Toucannon.Description: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.
Toucannon.Evolution: Toucannon evolves from Trumbeak starting from level 28, which evolves from Pikipek starting from level 14.

Yungoos.Name: Yungoos
Yungoos.Description: It spends its waking hours searching endlessly for food. When Yungoos is hungry, its ferocity gains a certain edge.
Yungoos.Evolution: Yungoos evolves to Gumshoos starting from level 20 in the daytime.

Gumshoos.Name: Gumshoos
Gumshoos.Description: Gumshoos specializes in relentlessly tracking down prey. The simple-minded Skwovet doesn’t seem to provide Gumshoos enough challenge.
Gumshoos.Evolution: Gumshoos evolves from Yungoos starting from level 20 in the daytime.

Grubbin.Name: Grubbin
Grubbin.Description: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.
Grubbin.Evolution: Grubbin evolves to Charjabug starting from level 20, which evolves to Vikavolt when leveled up.

Charjabug.Name: Charjabug
Charjabug.Description: Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eats into electricity. An electric sac in its belly stores the electricity for later use.
Charjabug.Evolution: Charjabug evolves from Grubbin starting from level 20 and evolves to Vikavolt when leveled up.

Vikavolt.Name: Vikavolt
Vikavolt.Description: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.
Vikavolt.Evolution: Vikavolt evolves from Charjabug when leveled up, which evolves from Grubbin starting from level 20.

Crabrawler.Name: Crabrawler
Crabrawler.Description: If it loses its pincers, they’ll quickly regrow. The pincers are popular ingredients in paella since their shells produce a tasty soup stock.

Crabominable.Name: Crabominable
Crabominable.Description: Though its punches are powerful, this Pokémon’s movements are sluggish. It blows icy bubbles from its mouth to immobilize its opponents.

Oricorio.Name: Oricorio
Oricorio.Description: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

Sensu Oricorio.Name: Sensu Oricorio
Sensu Oricorio.Description: The elegant, attractive dance of these Oricorio is popular with adults, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.
Sensu Oricorio.Evolution: Sensu Oricorio transforms from Oricorio when given a Purple Nectar.

Pa'u Oricorio.Name: Pa'u Oricorio
Pa'u Oricorio.Description: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It gets so caught up in its dancing that it sometimes doesn’t hear its Trainer’s orders.
Pa'u Oricorio.Evolution: Pa'u Oricorio transforms from Oricorio when given a Pink Nectar.

Pom-pom Oricorio.Name: Pom-pom Oricorio
Pom-pom Oricorio.Description: The energetic, cheerful dance of these Oricorio is popular with children, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.
Pom-pom Oricorio.Evolution: Pom-pom Oricorio transforms from Oricorio when given a Yellow Nectar.

Cutiefly.Name: Cutiefly
Cutiefly.Description: An opponent’s aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent’s next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.
Cutiefly.Evolution: Cutiefly evolves to Ribombee starting from level 25.

Ribombee.Name: Ribombee
Ribombee.Description: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.
Ribombee.Evolution: Ribombee evolves from Cutiefly starting from level 25.

Rockruff.Name: Rockruff
Rockruff.Description: This Pokémon travels in a pack with others until it grows up. When its mood turns sour, it starts striking the ground with the rocks on its neck.
Rockruff.Evolution: Rockruff evolves to Lycanroc starting from level 25 in the nighttime.

Lycanroc.Name: Lycanroc
Lycanroc.Description: It has a calm and collected demeanor. It swiftly closes in on its prey, then slices them with the rocks in its mane.
Lycanroc.Evolution: Lycanroc evolves from Rockruff starting from level 25 in the nighttime.

Wishiwashi.Name: Wishiwashi
Wishiwashi.Description: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

Mareanie.Name: Mareanie
Mareanie.Description: It has excellent regenerative capabilities. Legs that a Mareanie has lost have a very bitter, astringent flavor—they’re not suitable as food.
Mareanie.Evolution: Mareanie evolves to Toxapex starting from level 38.

Toxapex.Name: Toxapex
Toxapex.Description: Toxapex gets into fierce battles with Bruxish over areas where warm ocean currents flow, but the odds are always against it.
Toxapex.Evolution: Toxapex evolves from Mareanie starting from level 38.

Mudbray.Name: Mudbray
Mudbray.Description: Though a slow walker, Mudbray is plenty strong. Its pace doesn’t change even when it’s loaded with 50 times its own body weight.
Mudbray.Evolution: Mudbray evolves to Mudsdale starting from level 30.

Mudsdale.Name: Mudsdale
Mudsdale.Description: Its legs are fortified with mud and harder than stone, and they can reduce a large truck to scrap with one kick.
Mudsdale.Evolution: Mudsdale evolves from Mudbray starting from level 30.

Dewpider.Name: Dewpider
Dewpider.Description: Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.
Dewpider.Evolution: Dewpider evolves to Araquanid starting from level 22.

Araquanid.Name: Araquanid
Araquanid.Description: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.
Araquanid.Evolution: Araquanid evolves from Dewpider starting from level 22.

Fomantis.Name: Fomantis
Fomantis.Description: Many Trainers give their Fomantis their own flowerpots so they can sunbathe in peace and quiet.
Fomantis.Evolution: Fomantis evolves to Lurantis starting from level 34 in the daytime.

Lurantis.Name: Lurantis
Lurantis.Description: A lot of time and effort is required to maintain the vivid colors of its petals. This Pokémon puts its Trainer’s attentiveness to the test.
Lurantis.Evolution: Lurantis evolves from Fomantis starting from level 34 in the daytime.

Morelull.Name: Morelull
Morelull.Description: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.
Morelull.Evolution: Morelull evolves to Shiinotic starting from level 24.

Shiinotic.Name: Shiinotic
Shiinotic.Description: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don’t go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.
Shiinotic.Evolution: Shiinotic evolves from Morelull starting from level 24.

Salandit.Name: Salandit
Salandit.Description: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.
Salandit.Evolution: Salandit evolves to Salazzle starting from level 33.

Salazzle.Name: Salazzle
Salazzle.Description: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.
Salazzle.Evolution: Salazzle evolves from Salandit starting from level 33.

Stufful.Name: Stufful
Stufful.Description: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.
Stufful.Evolution: Stufful evolves to Bewear starting from level 27.

Bewear.Name: Bewear
Bewear.Description: The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.
Bewear.Evolution: Bewear evolves from Stufful starting from level 27.

Bounsweet.Name: Bounsweet
Bounsweet.Description: A Greedent drawn in by the sweet scent of these Pokémon will tuck the Bounsweet in among the berries in its tail and carry them all away.
Bounsweet.Evolution: Bounsweet evolves to Steenee starting from level 18, which evolves to Tsareena when leveled up while knowing Stomp.

Steenee.Name: Steenee
Steenee.Description: Steenee bounces energetically through forests. If the rind that peels off its body is pulverized, it can be used to treat stomach pains.
Steenee.Evolution: Steenee evolves from Bounsweet starting from level 18 and evolves to Tsareena when leveled up while knowing Stomp.

Tsareena.Name: Tsareena
Tsareena.Description: This Pokémon launches fierce yet elegant kicks with its long, slender legs. It views Quaquaval as its rival.
Tsareena.Evolution: Tsareena evolves from Steenee when leveled up while knowing Stomp, which evolves from Bounsweet starting from level 18.

Comfey.Name: Comfey
Comfey.Description: These Pokémon smell very nice. All Comfey wear different flowers, so each of these Pokémon has its own individual scent.

Oranguru.Name: Oranguru
Oranguru.Description: This Pokémon lives quietly in the depths of the forest. The purple, cape-like fur gets longer and longer as Oranguru ages.

Passimian.Name: Passimian
Passimian.Description: The boss chooses 10 members of the group to go out hunting. The hunting party will evenly split the food they find with the rest of the group.

Wimpod.Name: Wimpod
Wimpod.Description: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy’s presence.
Wimpod.Evolution: Wimpod evolves to Golisopod starting from level 30.

Golisopod.Name: Golisopod
Golisopod.Description: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.
Golisopod.Evolution: Golisopod evolves from Wimpod starting from level 30.

Sandygast.Name: Sandygast
Sandygast.Description: It flings sand into the eyes of its prey and tries to close in on them while they’re blinded, but since Sandygast is so slow, the prey tends to escape.
Sandygast.Evolution: Sandygast evolves to Palossand starting from level 42.

Palossand.Name: Palossand
Palossand.Description: From the hollows in its arms, it fires the bones of its victims, which are all dried up after being drained of their vitality.
Palossand.Evolution: Palossand evolves from Sandygast starting from level 42.

Pyukumuku.Name: Pyukumuku
Pyukumuku.Description: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

Type: Null.Name: Type: Null
Type: Null.Description: It was modeled after a mighty Pokémon of myth. The mask placed upon it limits its power in order to keep it under control.
Type: Null.Evolution: Type: Null evolves to Silvally when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Silvally.Name: Silvally
Silvally.Description: The final factor needed to release this Pokémon’s true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.
Silvally.Evolution: Silvally evolves from Type: Null when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Minior.Name: Minior
Minior.Description: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

Komala.Name: Komala
Komala.Description: A potent anesthetic can be made by diluting Komala’s drool. This anesthetic was used for surgeries in the past.

Turtonator.Name: Turtonator
Turtonator.Description: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

Togedemaru.Name: Togedemaru
Togedemaru.Description: When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.

Mimikyu.Name: Mimikyu
Mimikyu.Description: Mimikyu was only recently identified as a Pokémon. Previously, people thought it was just a ghost wearing a cloth.

Bruxish.Name: Bruxish
Bruxish.Description: When sunlight reflects on the ripples created by a Bruxish grinding its teeth, the water all around sparkles brilliantly.

Drampa.Name: Drampa
Drampa.Description: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

Dhelmise.Name: Dhelmise
Dhelmise.Description: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.

Jangmo-o.Name: Jangmo-o
Jangmo-o.Description: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that’s become as hard as metal.
Jangmo-o.Evolution: Jangmo-o evolves to Hakamo-o starting from level 35, which evolves to Kommo-o starting from level 45.

Hakamo-o.Name: Hakamo-o
Hakamo-o.Description: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.
Hakamo-o.Evolution: Hakamo-o evolves from Jangmo-o starting from level 35 and evolves to Kommo-o starting from level 45.

Kommo-o.Name: Kommo-o
Kommo-o.Description: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.
Kommo-o.Evolution: Kommo-o evolves from Hakamo-o starting from level 45, which evolves from Jangmo-o starting from level 35.

Alolan Rattata.Name: Alolan Rattata
Alolan Rattata.Description: Its whiskers provide it with a keen sense of smell, enabling it to pick up the scent of hidden food and locate it instantly.
Alolan Rattata.Evolution: Alolan Rattata evolves to Alolan Raticate starting from level 20 in the nighttime.

Alolan Raticate.Name: Alolan Raticate
Alolan Raticate.Description: It makes its Rattata underlings gather food for it, dining solely on the most nutritious and delicious fare.
Alolan Raticate.Evolution: Alolan Raticate evolves from Alolan Rattata starting from level 20 in the nighttime.

Alolan Raichu.Name: Alolan Raichu
Alolan Raichu.Description: This Pokémon rides on its tail while it uses its psychic powers to levitate. It attacks with star-shaped thunderbolts.

Alolan Sandshrew.Name: Alolan Sandshrew
Alolan Sandshrew.Description: It lives in snowy mountains on southern islands. When a blizzard rolls in, this Pokémon hunkers down in the snow to avoid getting blown away.
Alolan Sandshrew.Evolution: Alolan Sandshrew evolves to Alolan Sandslash using a Ice Stone.

Alolan Sandslash.Name: Alolan Sandslash
Alolan Sandslash.Description: Many people climb snowy mountains, hoping to see the icy spikes of these Pokémon glistening in the light of dawn.
Alolan Sandslash.Evolution: Alolan Sandslash evolves from Alolan Sandshrew using a Ice Stone.

Alolan Vulpix.Name: Alolan Vulpix
Alolan Vulpix.Description: These Pokémon live in packs in the snowy mountains and defend themselves with icy breath. I suspect this species changed its form to adapt to the frigid climate.
Alolan Vulpix.Evolution: Alolan Vulpix evolves to Alolan Ninetales using a Ice Stone.

Alolan Ninetales.Name: Alolan Ninetales
Alolan Ninetales.Description: Dwells on sacred peaks perpetually covered in snow. Said to appear to virtuous people who have lost their way on mountain paths—it then guides them back down to the mountain’s base.
Alolan Ninetales.Evolution: Alolan Ninetales evolves from Alolan Vulpix using a Ice Stone.

Alolan Diglett.Name: Alolan Diglett
Alolan Diglett.Description: Its three hairs change shape depending on Diglett’s mood. They’re a useful communication tool among these Pokémon.
Alolan Diglett.Evolution: Alolan Diglett evolves to Alolan Dugtrio starting from level 26.

Alolan Dugtrio.Name: Alolan Dugtrio
Alolan Dugtrio.Description: The three of them get along very well. Through their formidable teamwork, they defeat powerful opponents.
Alolan Dugtrio.Evolution: Alolan Dugtrio evolves from Alolan Diglett starting from level 26.

Alolan Meowth.Name: Alolan Meowth
Alolan Meowth.Description: Deeply proud and keenly smart, this Pokémon moves with cunning during battle and relentlessly attacks enemies’ weak points.
Alolan Meowth.Evolution: Alolan Meowth evolves to Alolan Persian when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Alolan Persian.Name: Alolan Persian
Alolan Persian.Description: This Pokémon is one tough opponent. Not only does it have formidable physical abilities, but it’s also not above fighting dirty.
Alolan Persian.Evolution: Alolan Persian evolves from Alolan Meowth when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Alolan Geodude.Name: Alolan Geodude
Alolan Geodude.Description: Its stone head is imbued with electricity and magnetism. If you carelessly step on one, you’ll be in for a painful shock.
Alolan Geodude.Evolution: Alolan Geodude evolves to Alolan Graveler starting from level 25, which evolves to Alolan Golem when traded.

Alolan Graveler.Name: Alolan Graveler
Alolan Graveler.Description: When it comes rolling down a mountain path, anything in its way gets zapped by electricity and sent flying.
Alolan Graveler.Evolution: Alolan Graveler evolves from Alolan Geodude starting from level 25 and evolves to Alolan Golem when traded.

Alolan Golem.Name: Alolan Golem
Alolan Golem.Description: It uses magnetism to accelerate and fire off rocks tinged with electricity. Even if it doesn’t score a direct hit, the jolt of electricity will do the job.
Alolan Golem.Evolution: Alolan Golem evolves from Alolan Graveler when traded, which evolves from Alolan Geodude starting from level 25.

Alolan Grimer.Name: Alolan Grimer
Alolan Grimer.Description: It has a passion for trash above all else, speedily digesting it and creating brilliant crystals of sparkling poison.
Alolan Grimer.Evolution: Alolan Grimer evolves to Alolan Muk starting from level 38.

Alolan Muk.Name: Alolan Muk
Alolan Muk.Description: Muk’s coloration becomes increasingly vivid the more it feasts on its favorite dish—trash.
Alolan Muk.Evolution: Alolan Muk evolves from Alolan Grimer starting from level 38.

Alolan Exeggutor.Name: Alolan Exeggutor
Alolan Exeggutor.Description: This Pokémon’s psychic powers aren’t as strong as they once were. The head on this Exeggutor’s tail scans surrounding areas with weak telepathy.

Alolan Marowak.Name: Alolan Marowak
Alolan Marowak.Description: The cursed flames that light up the bone carried by this Pokémon are said to cause both mental and physical pain that will never fade.

Tapu Koko.Name: Tapu Koko
Tapu Koko.Description: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.

Tapu Lele.Name: Tapu Lele
Tapu Lele.Description: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

Tapu Bulu.Name: Tapu Bulu
Tapu Bulu.Description: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.

Tapu Fini.Name: Tapu Fini
Tapu Fini.Description: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

Cosmog.Name: Cosmog
Cosmog.Description: Cosmog is very curious but not very cautious, often placing itself in danger. If things start to look dicey, it teleports away.
Cosmog.Evolution: Cosmog evolves to Cosmoem starting from level 43, which evolves to Solgaleo starting from level 53 in the daytime and evolves to Lunala starting from level 53 in the nighttime.

Cosmoem.Name: Cosmoem
Cosmoem.Description: It sucks in dust from the air at an astounding rate, frantically building up energy within its core as preparation for evolution.
Cosmoem.Evolution: Cosmoem evolves from Cosmog starting from level 43 and evolves to Solgaleo starting from level 53 in the daytime and evolves to Lunala starting from level 53 in the nighttime.

Solgaleo.Name: Solgaleo
Solgaleo.Description: Solgaleo was once known as the Beast That Devours the Sun. Energy in the form of light radiates boundlessly from it.
Solgaleo.Evolution: Solgaleo evolves from Cosmoem starting from level 53 in the daytime, which evolves from Cosmog starting from level 43.

Lunala.Name: Lunala
Lunala.Description: It steals the light from its surroundings and then becomes the full moon, showering its own light across the night sky.
Lunala.Evolution: Lunala evolves from Cosmoem starting from level 53 in the nighttime, which evolves from Cosmog starting from level 43.

Nihilego.Name: Nihilego
Nihilego.Description: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokémon.

Buzzwole.Name: Buzzwole
Buzzwole.Description: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

Pheromosa.Name: Pheromosa
Pheromosa.Description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Xurkitree.Name: Xurkitree
Xurkitree.Description: They’ve been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

Celesteela.Name: Celesteela
Celesteela.Description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Kartana.Name: Kartana
Kartana.Description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Guzzlord.Name: Guzzlord
Guzzlord.Description: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.

Necrozma.Name: Necrozma
Necrozma.Description: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

Magearna.Name: Magearna
Magearna.Description: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

Marshadow.Name: Marshadow
Marshadow.Description: This Pokémon can conceal itself in any shadow, so it went undiscovered for a long time.

Poipole.Name: Poipole
Poipole.Description: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.
Poipole.Evolution: Poipole evolves to Naganadel when leveled up while knowing Dragon Pulse.

Naganadel.Name: Naganadel
Naganadel.Description: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.
Naganadel.Evolution: Naganadel evolves from Poipole when leveled up while knowing Dragon Pulse.

Stakataka.Name: Stakataka
Stakataka.Description: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute’s true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

Blacephalon.Name: Blacephalon
Blacephalon.Description: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.

Zeraora.Name: Zeraora
Zeraora.Description: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

Meltan.Name: Meltan
Meltan.Description: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

Melmetal.Name: Melmetal
Melmetal.Description: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

Grookey.Name: Grookey
Grookey.Description: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.
Grookey.Evolution: Grookey evolves to Thwackey starting from level 16, which evolves to Rillaboom starting from level 35.

Thwackey.Name: Thwackey
Thwackey.Description: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.
Thwackey.Evolution: Thwackey evolves from Grookey starting from level 16 and evolves to Rillaboom starting from level 35.

Rillaboom.Name: Rillaboom
Rillaboom.Description: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
Rillaboom.Evolution: Rillaboom evolves from Thwackey starting from level 35, which evolves from Grookey starting from level 16.

Scorbunny.Name: Scorbunny
Scorbunny.Description: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.
Scorbunny.Evolution: Scorbunny evolves to Raboot starting from level 16, which evolves to Cinderace starting from level 35.

Raboot.Name: Raboot
Raboot.Description: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
Raboot.Evolution: Raboot evolves from Scorbunny starting from level 16 and evolves to Cinderace starting from level 35.

Cinderace.Name: Cinderace
Cinderace.Description: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
Cinderace.Evolution: Cinderace evolves from Raboot starting from level 35, which evolves from Scorbunny starting from level 16.

Sobble.Name: Sobble
Sobble.Description: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.
Sobble.Evolution: Sobble evolves to Drizzile starting from level 16, which evolves to Inteleon starting from level 35.

Drizzile.Name: Drizzile
Drizzile.Description: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
Drizzile.Evolution: Drizzile evolves from Sobble starting from level 16 and evolves to Inteleon starting from level 35.

Inteleon.Name: Inteleon
Inteleon.Description: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
Inteleon.Evolution: Inteleon evolves from Drizzile starting from level 35, which evolves from Sobble starting from level 16.

Skwovet.Name: Skwovet
Skwovet.Description: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.
Skwovet.Evolution: Skwovet evolves to Greedent starting from level 24.

Greedent.Name: Greedent
Greedent.Description: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.
Greedent.Evolution: Greedent evolves from Skwovet starting from level 24.

Rookidee.Name: Rookidee
Rookidee.Description: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee’s wings, it’ll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.
Rookidee.Evolution: Rookidee evolves to Corvisquire starting from level 18, which evolves to Corviknight starting from level 38.

Corvisquire.Name: Corvisquire
Corvisquire.Description: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.
Corvisquire.Evolution: Corvisquire evolves from Rookidee starting from level 18 and evolves to Corviknight starting from level 38.

Corviknight.Name: Corviknight
Corviknight.Description: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.
Corviknight.Evolution: Corviknight evolves from Corvisquire starting from level 38, which evolves from Rookidee starting from level 18.

Blipbug.Name: Blipbug
Blipbug.Description: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.
Blipbug.Evolution: Blipbug evolves to Dottler starting from level 10, which evolves to Orbeetle starting from level 30.

Dottler.Name: Dottler
Dottler.Description: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
Dottler.Evolution: Dottler evolves from Blipbug starting from level 10 and evolves to Orbeetle starting from level 30.

Orbeetle.Name: Orbeetle
Orbeetle.Description: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.
Orbeetle.Evolution: Orbeetle evolves from Dottler starting from level 30, which evolves from Blipbug starting from level 10.

Nickit.Name: Nickit
Nickit.Description: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.
Nickit.Evolution: Nickit evolves to Thievul starting from level 18.

Thievul.Name: Thievul
Thievul.Description: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
Thievul.Evolution: Thievul evolves from Nickit starting from level 18.

Gossifleur.Name: Gossifleur
Gossifleur.Description: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.
Gossifleur.Evolution: Gossifleur evolves to Eldegoss starting from level 20.

Eldegoss.Name: Eldegoss
Eldegoss.Description: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.
Eldegoss.Evolution: Eldegoss evolves from Gossifleur starting from level 20.

Wooloo.Name: Wooloo
Wooloo.Description: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.
Wooloo.Evolution: Wooloo evolves to Dubwool starting from level 24.

Dubwool.Name: Dubwool
Dubwool.Description: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
Dubwool.Evolution: Dubwool evolves from Wooloo starting from level 24.

Chewtle.Name: Chewtle
Chewtle.Description: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.
Chewtle.Evolution: Chewtle evolves to Drednaw starting from level 22.

Drednaw.Name: Drednaw
Drednaw.Description: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.
Drednaw.Evolution: Drednaw evolves from Chewtle starting from level 22.

Yamper.Name: Yamper
Yamper.Description: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.
Yamper.Evolution: Yamper evolves to Boltund starting from level 25.

Boltund.Name: Boltund
Boltund.Description: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
Boltund.Evolution: Boltund evolves from Yamper starting from level 25.

Rolycoly.Name: Rolycoly
Rolycoly.Description: Chunks of the surface of this Pokémon’s body that have grown old and flaked off have long been used for fuel as an alternative to coal.
Rolycoly.Evolution: Rolycoly evolves to Carkol starting from level 18, which evolves to Coalossal starting from level 34.

Carkol.Name: Carkol
Carkol.Description: Due to the coal tar created inside it, the heap of coal on Carkol’s back never falls apart, even when the Pokémon rolls around at high speeds.
Carkol.Evolution: Carkol evolves from Rolycoly starting from level 18 and evolves to Coalossal starting from level 34.

Coalossal.Name: Coalossal
Coalossal.Description: It’s gentle usually but fearsome when angered. With a body that burns at over 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit, it crushes foes and turns them to ash.
Coalossal.Evolution: Coalossal evolves from Carkol starting from level 34, which evolves from Rolycoly starting from level 18.

Applin.Name: Applin
Applin.Description: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.
Applin.Evolution: Applin evolves to Flapple somehow and evolves to Appletun somehow.

Flapple.Name: Flapple
Flapple.Description: It uses its own body fluid to repair its apple. Strong Flapple that have won many battles have apples that are clay colored all over.

Appletun.Name: Appletun
Appletun.Description: When some Lechonk come along to lick the sweet nectar on Appletun’s back, Appletun will spew sticky nectar at them to drive them away.

Silicobra.Name: Silicobra
Silicobra.Description: Silicobra’s large nostrils are specialized for spraying sand, so this Pokémon is not very good at telling apart different smells.
Silicobra.Evolution: Silicobra evolves to Sandaconda starting from level 36.

Sandaconda.Name: Sandaconda
Sandaconda.Description: The sand it spews contains sharp, pointy gravel, which is actually just sand that Sandaconda’s saliva has hardened into irregular shapes.
Sandaconda.Evolution: Sandaconda evolves from Silicobra starting from level 36.

Cramorant.Name: Cramorant
Cramorant.Description: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

Arrokuda.Name: Arrokuda
Arrokuda.Description: It takes down prey by charging into them with its hard, pointed jaw. But Arrokuda’s eyesight is poor, so this tactic has a low success rate.
Arrokuda.Evolution: Arrokuda evolves to Barraskewda starting from level 26.

Barraskewda.Name: Barraskewda
Barraskewda.Description: It swims at speeds of over 100 knots and battles fiercely with pods of Finizen over prey.
Barraskewda.Evolution: Barraskewda evolves from Arrokuda starting from level 26.

Toxel.Name: Toxel
Toxel.Description: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.
Toxel.Evolution: Toxel evolves to Toxtricity starting from level 30.

Toxtricity.Name: Toxtricity
Toxtricity.Description: As it gulps down stagnant water and generates electricity in its body, a sound like a rhythm played by a bass guitar reverberates all around.
Toxtricity.Evolution: Toxtricity evolves from Toxel starting from level 30.

Sizzlipede.Name: Sizzlipede
Sizzlipede.Description: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.
Sizzlipede.Evolution: Sizzlipede evolves to Centiskorch starting from level 28.

Centiskorch.Name: Centiskorch
Centiskorch.Description: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.
Centiskorch.Evolution: Centiskorch evolves from Sizzlipede starting from level 28.

Clobbopus.Name: Clobbopus
Clobbopus.Description: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.
Clobbopus.Evolution: Clobbopus evolves to Grapploct when leveled up.

Grapploct.Name: Grapploct
Grapploct.Description: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
Grapploct.Evolution: Grapploct evolves from Clobbopus when leveled up.

Sinistea.Name: Sinistea
Sinistea.Description: Sinistea gets into your body when you drink it, and then it steals your vitality from within. It also tastes awful.

Polteageist.Name: Polteageist
Polteageist.Description: Though risky to drink, this Pokémon’s tea tastes delicious. Gourmets who have no fear of danger drink Polteageist tea day after day.

Hatenna.Name: Hatenna
Hatenna.Description: It senses the feelings of other living creatures. Be careful not to expose it to strong emotions for too long, or it will end up exhausted.
Hatenna.Evolution: Hatenna evolves to Hattrem starting from level 32, which evolves to Hatterene starting from level 42.

Hattrem.Name: Hattrem
Hattrem.Description: The moment this Pokémon finds someone who’s emitting strong emotions, it will pummel them senseless with its braids to silence them.
Hattrem.Evolution: Hattrem evolves from Hatenna starting from level 32 and evolves to Hatterene starting from level 42.

Hatterene.Name: Hatterene
Hatterene.Description: Beware of forests that show no signs of living creatures within. You may have wandered into Hatterene’s territory.
Hatterene.Evolution: Hatterene evolves from Hattrem starting from level 42, which evolves from Hatenna starting from level 32.

Impidimp.Name: Impidimp
Impidimp.Description: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.
Impidimp.Evolution: Impidimp evolves to Morgrem starting from level 32, which evolves to Grimmsnarl starting from level 42.

Morgrem.Name: Morgrem
Morgrem.Description: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It’s popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.
Morgrem.Evolution: Morgrem evolves from Impidimp starting from level 32 and evolves to Grimmsnarl starting from level 42.

Grimmsnarl.Name: Grimmsnarl
Grimmsnarl.Description: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.
Grimmsnarl.Evolution: Grimmsnarl evolves from Morgrem starting from level 42, which evolves from Impidimp starting from level 32.

Galarian Zigzagoon.Name: Galarian Zigzagoon
Galarian Zigzagoon.Description: Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.

Galarian Linoone.Name: Galarian Linoone
Galarian Linoone.Description: This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.
Galarian Linoone.Evolution: Galarian Linoone evolves to Obstagoon starting from level 35.

Obstagoon.Name: Obstagoon
Obstagoon.Description: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
Obstagoon.Evolution: Obstagoon evolves from Galarian Linoone starting from level 35.

Galarian Meowth.Name: Galarian Meowth
Galarian Meowth.Description: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.
Galarian Meowth.Evolution: Galarian Meowth evolves to Perrserker starting from level 28.

Perrserker.Name: Perrserker
Perrserker.Description: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.
Perrserker.Evolution: Perrserker evolves from Galarian Meowth starting from level 28.

Galarian Ponyta.Name: Galarian Ponyta
Galarian Ponyta.Description: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

Galarian Rapidash.Name: Galarian Rapidash
Galarian Rapidash.Description: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

Galarian Slowpoke.Name: Galarian Slowpoke
Galarian Slowpoke.Description: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

Galarian Slowbro.Name: Galarian Slowbro
Galarian Slowbro.Description: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

Galarian Slowking.Name: Galarian Slowking
Galarian Slowking.Description: While chanting strange spells, this Pokémon combines its internal toxins with what it’s eaten, creating strange potions.

Galarian Corsola.Name: Galarian Corsola
Galarian Corsola.Description: Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. This Pokémon absorbs others’ life-force through its branches.
Galarian Corsola.Evolution: Galarian Corsola evolves to Cursola starting from level 38.

Cursola.Name: Cursola
Cursola.Description: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.
Cursola.Evolution: Cursola evolves from Galarian Corsola starting from level 38.

Galarian Farfetch'd.Name: Galarian Farfetch'd
Galarian Farfetch'd.Description: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch’d that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.
Galarian Farfetch'd.Evolution: Galarian Farfetch'd evolves to Sirfetch'd somehow.

Sirfetch'd.Name: Sirfetch'd
Sirfetch'd.Description: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.
Sirfetch'd.Evolution: Sirfetch'd evolves from Galarian Farfetch'd somehow.

Galarian Weezing.Name: Galarian Weezing
Galarian Weezing.Description: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.

Galarian Mr. Mime.Name: Galarian Mr. Mime
Galarian Mr. Mime.Description: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It’ll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.
Galarian Mr. Mime.Evolution: Galarian Mr. Mime evolves to Mr. Rime starting from level 42.

Mr. Rime.Name: Mr. Rime
Mr. Rime.Description: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
Mr. Rime.Evolution: Mr. Rime evolves from Galarian Mr. Mime starting from level 42.

Galarian Darumaka.Name: Galarian Darumaka
Galarian Darumaka.Description: The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.

Galarian Darmanitan.Name: Galarian Darmanitan
Galarian Darmanitan.Description: Though it has a gentle disposition, it’s also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.

Galarian Yamask.Name: Galarian Yamask
Galarian Yamask.Description: It’s said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.
Galarian Yamask.Evolution: Galarian Yamask evolves to Runerigus somehow.

Runerigus.Name: Runerigus
Runerigus.Description: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
Runerigus.Evolution: Runerigus evolves from Galarian Yamask somehow.

Galarian Stunfisk.Name: Galarian Stunfisk
Galarian Stunfisk.Description: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

Milcery.Name: Milcery
Milcery.Description: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

Alcremie.Name: Alcremie
Alcremie.Description: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

Falinks.Name: Falinks
Falinks.Description: The leader, known as the brass, uses its extendible horn to issue orders to the others when it’s time to change formation.

Pincurchin.Name: Pincurchin
Pincurchin.Description: This Pokémon is so timid that even brushing against seaweed will make it discharge electricity in surprise. Its lips do not conduct electricity.

Snom.Name: Snom
Snom.Description: Within its internal organs, Snom amplifies the frigid air it gets from eating snow and then uses this amplified air to create icicle-like spikes.
Snom.Evolution: Snom evolves to Frosmoth when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Frosmoth.Name: Frosmoth
Frosmoth.Description: It causes blizzards as it flies around with its huge, chill-emanating wings. Clean meltwater is its favorite thing to drink.
Frosmoth.Evolution: Frosmoth evolves from Snom when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Stonjourner.Name: Stonjourner
Stonjourner.Description: This Pokémon spends its life gazing at the setting sun. It strides leisurely across grassy plains on legs of rock that weigh over 400 pounds each.

Eiscue.Name: Eiscue
Eiscue.Description: If you lick the ice covering its face, you’ll find it has a faintly salty taste. This species rode here on ocean currents from a cold, faraway land.

Indeedee.Name: Indeedee
Indeedee.Description: This Pokémon never leaves its Trainer’s side. It predicts their actions with its psychic power and takes care of their day-to-day needs.

Morpeko.Name: Morpeko
Morpeko.Description: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

Cufant.Name: Cufant
Cufant.Description: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.
Cufant.Evolution: Cufant evolves to Copperajah starting from level 34.

Copperajah.Name: Copperajah
Copperajah.Description: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.
Copperajah.Evolution: Copperajah evolves from Cufant starting from level 34.

Dracozolt.Name: Dracozolt
Dracozolt.Description: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

Arctozolt.Name: Arctozolt
Arctozolt.Description: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

Dracovish.Name: Dracovish
Dracovish.Description: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.

Arctovish.Name: Arctovish
Arctovish.Description: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

Duraludon.Name: Duraludon
Duraludon.Description: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

Dreepy.Name: Dreepy
Dreepy.Description: It has a habit of biting at Clauncher even though it doesn’t feed on them. This is said to be vestigial behavior from when Dreepy was alive.
Dreepy.Evolution: Dreepy evolves to Drakloak starting from level 50, which evolves to Dragapult starting from level 60.

Drakloak.Name: Drakloak
Drakloak.Description: This Pokémon stores up energy in its lungs, then shoots it out. It takes care of Dreepy and battles alongside them until they’re all grown up.
Drakloak.Evolution: Drakloak evolves from Dreepy starting from level 50 and evolves to Dragapult starting from level 60.

Dragapult.Name: Dragapult
Dragapult.Description: The fastest Dragapult of the group is always surrounded by Dreepy that want to fly at sonic speed.
Dragapult.Evolution: Dragapult evolves from Drakloak starting from level 60, which evolves from Dreepy starting from level 50.

Zacian.Name: Zacian
Zacian.Description: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

Zamazenta.Name: Zamazenta
Zamazenta.Description: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

Eternatus.Name: Eternatus
Eternatus.Description: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

Kubfu.Name: Kubfu
Kubfu.Description: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.

Urshifu.Name: Urshifu
Urshifu.Description: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

Zarude.Name: Zarude
Zarude.Description: Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

Regieleki.Name: Regieleki
Regieleki.Description: Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar’s electricity.

Regidrago.Name: Regidrago
Regidrago.Description: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokémon.

Glastrier.Name: Glastrier
Glastrier.Description: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

Spectrier.Name: Spectrier
Spectrier.Description: As it dashes through the night, Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.

Calyrex.Name: Calyrex
Calyrex.Description: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

Galarian Articuno.Name: Galarian Articuno
Galarian Articuno.Description: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.

Galarian Zapdos.Name: Galarian Zapdos
Galarian Zapdos.Description: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.

Galarian Moltres.Name: Galarian Moltres
Galarian Moltres.Description: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.

Wyrdeer.Name: Wyrdeer
Wyrdeer.Description: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

Kleavor.Name: Kleavor
Kleavor.Description: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one’s only recourse is to flee.
Kleavor.Evolution: Kleavor evolves from Scyther when leveled up.

Ursaluna.Name: Ursaluna
Ursaluna.Description: I believe it was Hisui’s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.
Ursaluna.Evolution: Ursaluna evolves from Ursaring somehow, which evolves from Teddiursa starting from level 30.

Basculegion.Name: Basculegion
Basculegion.Description: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.

Sneasler.Name: Sneasler
Sneasler.Description: Because of Sneasler’s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
Sneasler.Evolution: Sneasler evolves from Hisuian Sneasel somehow.

Overqwil.Name: Overqwil
Overqwil.Description: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.
Overqwil.Evolution: Overqwil evolves from Hisuian Qwilfish somehow.

Enamorus.Name: Enamorus
Enamorus.Description: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

Sprigatito.Name: Sprigatito
Sprigatito.Description: The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokémon is in the sun.
Sprigatito.Evolution: Sprigatito evolves to Floragato starting from level 16, which evolves to Meowscarada starting from level 36.

Floragato.Name: Floragato
Floragato.Description: The hardness of Floragato’s fur depends on the Pokémon’s mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.
Floragato.Evolution: Floragato evolves from Sprigatito starting from level 16 and evolves to Meowscarada starting from level 36.

Meowscarada.Name: Meowscarada
Meowscarada.Description: With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. Meowscarada sets off the bombs before its foes realize what’s going on.
Meowscarada.Evolution: Meowscarada evolves from Floragato starting from level 36, which evolves from Sprigatito starting from level 16.

Fuecoco.Name: Fuecoco
Fuecoco.Description: Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop Fuecoco’s head and flickers to and fro.
Fuecoco.Evolution: Fuecoco evolves to Crocalor starting from level 16, which evolves to Skeledirge starting from level 36.

Crocalor.Name: Crocalor
Crocalor.Description: The valve in Crocalor’s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokémon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.
Crocalor.Evolution: Crocalor evolves from Fuecoco starting from level 16 and evolves to Skeledirge starting from level 36.

Skeledirge.Name: Skeledirge
Skeledirge.Description: Skeledirge’s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.
Skeledirge.Evolution: Skeledirge evolves from Crocalor starting from level 36, which evolves from Fuecoco starting from level 16.

Quaxly.Name: Quaxly
Quaxly.Description: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.
Quaxly.Evolution: Quaxly evolves to Quaxwell starting from level 16, which evolves to Quaquaval starting from level 36.

Quaxwell.Name: Quaxwell
Quaxwell.Description: The hardworking Quaxwell observes people and Pokémon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.
Quaxwell.Evolution: Quaxwell evolves from Quaxly starting from level 16 and evolves to Quaquaval starting from level 36.

Quaquaval.Name: Quaquaval
Quaquaval.Description: Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokémon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.
Quaquaval.Evolution: Quaquaval evolves from Quaxwell starting from level 36, which evolves from Quaxly starting from level 16.

Lechonk.Name: Lechonk
Lechonk.Description: This Pokémon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokémon detest.
Lechonk.Evolution: Lechonk evolves to Oinkologne starting from level 18.

Oinkologne.Name: Oinkologne
Oinkologne.Description: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.
Oinkologne.Evolution: Oinkologne evolves from Lechonk starting from level 18.

Tarountula.Name: Tarountula
Tarountula.Description: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread’s strength is the topic of ongoing research.
Tarountula.Evolution: Tarountula evolves to Spidops starting from level 15.

Spidops.Name: Spidops
Spidops.Description: Spidops covers its territory in tough, sticky threads to set up traps for intruders.
Spidops.Evolution: Spidops evolves from Tarountula starting from level 15.

Nymble.Name: Nymble
Nymble.Description: It’s highly skilled at a fighting style in which it uses its jumping capabilities to dodge incoming attacks while also dealing damage to opponents.
Nymble.Evolution: Nymble evolves to Lokix starting from level 24.

Lokix.Name: Lokix
Lokix.Description: It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it can’t stay in this mode for long.
Lokix.Evolution: Lokix evolves from Nymble starting from level 24.

Pawmi.Name: Pawmi
Pawmi.Description: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.
Pawmi.Evolution: Pawmi evolves to Pawmo starting from level 18, which evolves to Pawmot somehow.

Pawmo.Name: Pawmo
Pawmo.Description: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.
Pawmo.Evolution: Pawmo evolves from Pawmi starting from level 18 and evolves to Pawmot somehow.

Pawmot.Name: Pawmot
Pawmot.Description: Pawmot’s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.
Pawmot.Evolution: Pawmot evolves from Pawmo somehow, which evolves from Pawmi starting from level 18.

Tandemaus.Name: Tandemaus
Tandemaus.Description: The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.

Maushold.Name: Maushold
Maushold.Description: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

Fidough.Name: Fidough
Fidough.Description: The yeast in Fidough’s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokémon has been protected by people since long ago.
Fidough.Evolution: Fidough evolves to Dachsbun starting from level 26.

Dachsbun.Name: Dachsbun
Dachsbun.Description: The surface of this Pokémon’s skin hardens when exposed to intense heat, and its body has an appetizing aroma.
Dachsbun.Evolution: Dachsbun evolves from Fidough starting from level 26.

Smoliv.Name: Smoliv
Smoliv.Description: This Pokémon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.
Smoliv.Evolution: Smoliv evolves to Dolliv starting from level 25, which evolves to Arboliva starting from level 35.

Dolliv.Name: Dolliv
Dolliv.Description: It basks in the sun to its heart’s content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, Dolliv departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.
Dolliv.Evolution: Dolliv evolves from Smoliv starting from level 25 and evolves to Arboliva starting from level 35.

Arboliva.Name: Arboliva
Arboliva.Description: This Pokémon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.
Arboliva.Evolution: Arboliva evolves from Dolliv starting from level 35, which evolves from Smoliv starting from level 25.

Squawkabilly.Name: Squawkabilly
Squawkabilly.Description: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

Nacli.Name: Nacli
Nacli.Description: The ground scrapes its body as it travels, causing it to leave salt behind. Salt is constantly being created and replenished inside Nacli’s body.
Nacli.Evolution: Nacli evolves to Naclstack starting from level 24, which evolves to Garganacl starting from level 38.

Naclstack.Name: Naclstack
Naclstack.Description: It compresses rock salt inside its body and shoots out hardened salt pellets with enough force to perforate an iron sheet.
Naclstack.Evolution: Naclstack evolves from Nacli starting from level 24 and evolves to Garganacl starting from level 38.

Garganacl.Name: Garganacl
Garganacl.Description: Many Pokémon gather around Garganacl, hoping to lick at its mineral-rich salt.
Garganacl.Evolution: Garganacl evolves from Naclstack starting from level 38, which evolves from Nacli starting from level 24.

Charcadet.Name: Charcadet
Charcadet.Description: Its firepower increases when it fights, reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. It likes berries that are rich in fat.
Charcadet.Evolution: Charcadet evolves to Armarouge using a Auspicious Armor and evolves to Ceruledge using a Malicious Armor.

Armarouge.Name: Armarouge
Armarouge.Description: This Pokémon clads itself in armor that has been fortified by psychic and fire energy, and it shoots blazing fireballs.
Armarouge.Evolution: Armarouge evolves from Charcadet using a Auspicious Armor.

Ceruledge.Name: Ceruledge
Ceruledge.Description: An old set of armor steeped in grudges caused this Pokémon’s evolution. Ceruledge cuts its enemies to pieces without mercy.
Ceruledge.Evolution: Ceruledge evolves from Charcadet using a Malicious Armor.
