Tadbulb.Name: Tadbulb
Tadbulb.Description: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.
Tadbulb.Evolution: Tadbulb evolves to Bellibolt using a Thunder Stone.

Bellibolt.Name: Bellibolt
Bellibolt.Description: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt’s belly-button dynamo.
Bellibolt.Evolution: Bellibolt evolves from Tadbulb using a Thunder Stone.

Wattrel.Name: Wattrel
Wattrel.Description: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.
Wattrel.Evolution: Wattrel evolves to Kilowattrel starting from level 25.

Kilowattrel.Name: Kilowattrel
Kilowattrel.Description: It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. There’s hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.
Kilowattrel.Evolution: Kilowattrel evolves from Wattrel starting from level 25.

Maschiff.Name: Maschiff
Maschiff.Description: Its well-developed jaw and fangs are strong enough to crunch through boulders, and its thick fat makes for an excellent defense.
Maschiff.Evolution: Maschiff evolves to Mabosstiff starting from level 30.

Mabosstiff.Name: Mabosstiff
Mabosstiff.Description: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.
Mabosstiff.Evolution: Mabosstiff evolves from Maschiff starting from level 30.

Shroodle.Name: Shroodle
Shroodle.Description: To keep enemies away from its territory, it paints markings around its nest using a poisonous liquid that has an acrid odor.
Shroodle.Evolution: Shroodle evolves to Grafaiai starting from level 28.

Grafaiai.Name: Grafaiai
Grafaiai.Description: Each Grafaiai paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.
Grafaiai.Evolution: Grafaiai evolves from Shroodle starting from level 28.

Bramblin.Name: Bramblin
Bramblin.Description: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

Brambleghast.Name: Brambleghast
Brambleghast.Description: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

Toedscool.Name: Toedscool
Toedscool.Description: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Toedscool.Evolution: Toedscool evolves to Toedscruel starting from level 30.

Toedscruel.Name: Toedscruel
Toedscruel.Description: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.
Toedscruel.Evolution: Toedscruel evolves from Toedscool starting from level 30.

Klawf.Name: Klawf
Klawf.Description: This Pokémon lives on sheer cliffs. It sidesteps opponents’ attacks, then lunges for their weak spots with its claws.

Capsakid.Name: Capsakid
Capsakid.Description: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.
Capsakid.Evolution: Capsakid evolves to Scovillain using a Fire Stone.

Scovillain.Name: Scovillain
Scovillain.Description: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.
Scovillain.Evolution: Scovillain evolves from Capsakid using a Fire Stone.

Rellor.Name: Rellor
Rellor.Description: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.

Rabsca.Name: Rabsca
Rabsca.Description: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.

Flittle.Name: Flittle
Flittle.Description: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.
Flittle.Evolution: Flittle evolves to Espathra starting from level 35.

Espathra.Name: Espathra
Espathra.Description: It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.
Espathra.Evolution: Espathra evolves from Flittle starting from level 35.

Tinkatink.Name: Tinkatink
Tinkatink.Description: This Pokémon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it’s satisfied with the result.
Tinkatink.Evolution: Tinkatink evolves to Tinkatuff starting from level 24, which evolves to Tinkaton starting from level 38.

Tinkatuff.Name: Tinkatuff
Tinkatuff.Description: These Pokémon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each other’s hammers by smashing them together.
Tinkatuff.Evolution: Tinkatuff evolves from Tinkatink starting from level 24 and evolves to Tinkaton starting from level 38.

Tinkaton.Name: Tinkaton
Tinkaton.Description: The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.
Tinkaton.Evolution: Tinkaton evolves from Tinkatuff starting from level 38, which evolves from Tinkatink starting from level 24.

Wiglett.Name: Wiglett
Wiglett.Description: Though it looks like Diglett, Wiglett is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.
Wiglett.Evolution: Wiglett evolves to Wugtrio starting from level 26.

Wugtrio.Name: Wugtrio
Wugtrio.Description: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.
Wugtrio.Evolution: Wugtrio evolves from Wiglett starting from level 26.

Bombirdier.Name: Bombirdier
Bombirdier.Description: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.

Finizen.Name: Finizen
Finizen.Description: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

Palafin.Name: Palafin
Palafin.Description: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

Varoom.Name: Varoom
Varoom.Description: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.
Varoom.Evolution: Varoom evolves to Revavroom starting from level 40.

Revavroom.Name: Revavroom
Revavroom.Description: Revavroom viciously threatens others with the sound of its exhaust. It sticks its tongue out from its cylindrical mouth and sprays toxic fluids.
Revavroom.Evolution: Revavroom evolves from Varoom starting from level 40.

Cyclizar.Name: Cyclizar
Cyclizar.Description: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider’s body heat warms Cyclizar’s back and lifts the Pokémon’s spirit.

Orthworm.Name: Orthworm
Orthworm.Description: This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It maintains its metal body by consuming iron from the soil.

Glimmet.Name: Glimmet
Glimmet.Description: Glimmet’s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.
Glimmet.Evolution: Glimmet evolves to Glimmora starting from level 35.

Glimmora.Name: Glimmora
Glimmora.Description: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.
Glimmora.Evolution: Glimmora evolves from Glimmet starting from level 35.

Greavard.Name: Greavard
Greavard.Description: This friendly Pokémon doesn’t like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.
Greavard.Evolution: Greavard evolves to Houndstone starting from level 30 in the nighttime.

Houndstone.Name: Houndstone
Houndstone.Description: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.
Houndstone.Evolution: Houndstone evolves from Greavard starting from level 30 in the nighttime.

Flamigo.Name: Flamigo
Flamigo.Description: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as “synchronizing,” an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

Cetoddle.Name: Cetoddle
Cetoddle.Description: It lives in frigid regions in pods of five or so individuals. It loves the minerals found in snow and ice.
Cetoddle.Evolution: Cetoddle evolves to Cetitan using a Ice Stone.

Cetitan.Name: Cetitan
Cetitan.Description: Ice energy builds up in the horn on its upper jaw, causing the horn to reach cryogenic temperatures that freeze its surroundings.
Cetitan.Evolution: Cetitan evolves from Cetoddle using a Ice Stone.

Veluza.Name: Veluza
Veluza.Description: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.

Dondozo.Name: Dondozo
Dondozo.Description: It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very smart.

Tatsugiri.Name: Tatsugiri
Tatsugiri.Description: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

Annihilape.Name: Annihilape
Annihilape.Description: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.
Annihilape.Evolution: Annihilape evolves from Primeape somehow, which evolves from Mankey starting from level 28.

Clodsire.Name: Clodsire
Clodsire.Description: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.
Clodsire.Evolution: Clodsire evolves from Wooper starting from level 20.

Farigiraf.Name: Farigiraf
Farigiraf.Description: The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as Farigiraf whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.

Dudunsparce.Name: Dudunsparce
Dudunsparce.Description: It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.

Kingambit.Name: Kingambit
Kingambit.Description: Though it commands a massive army in battle, it’s not skilled at devising complex strategies. It just uses brute strength to keep pushing.
Kingambit.Evolution: Kingambit evolves from Bisharp somehow, which evolves from Pawniard starting from level 52.

Great Tusk.Name: Great Tusk
Great Tusk.Description: This creature resembles a mysterious Pokémon that, according to a paranormal magazine, has lived since ancient times.

Scream Tail.Name: Scream Tail
Scream Tail.Description: It resembles a mysterious Pokémon described in a paranormal magazine as a Jigglypuff from one billion years ago.

Brute Bonnet.Name: Brute Bonnet
Brute Bonnet.Description: It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.

Flutter Mane.Name: Flutter Mane
Flutter Mane.Description: It has similar features to a ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a paranormal magazine, but the two have little else in common.

Slither Wing.Name: Slither Wing
Slither Wing.Description: This Pokémon somewhat resembles an ancient form of Volcarona that was introduced in a dubious magazine.

Sandy Shocks.Name: Sandy Shocks
Sandy Shocks.Description: It slightly resembles a Magneton that lived for 10,000 years and was featured in an article in a paranormal magazine.

Iron Treads.Name: Iron Treads
Iron Treads.Description: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.

Iron Bundle.Name: Iron Bundle
Iron Bundle.Description: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

Iron Hands.Name: Iron Hands
Iron Hands.Description: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.

Iron Jugulis.Name: Iron Jugulis
Iron Jugulis.Description: It’s possible that Iron Jugulis, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokémon.

Iron Moth.Name: Iron Moth
Iron Moth.Description: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

Iron Thorns.Name: Iron Thorns
Iron Thorns.Description: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.

Frigibax.Name: Frigibax
Frigibax.Description: This Pokémon lives in forests and craggy areas. Using the power of its dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its nest like a refrigerator.
Frigibax.Evolution: Frigibax evolves to Arctibax starting from level 35, which evolves to Baxcalibur starting from level 54.

Arctibax.Name: Arctibax
Arctibax.Description: It attacks with the blade of its frozen dorsal fin by doing a front flip in the air. Arctibax’s strong back and legs allow it to pull off this technique.
Arctibax.Evolution: Arctibax evolves from Frigibax starting from level 35 and evolves to Baxcalibur starting from level 54.

Baxcalibur.Name: Baxcalibur
Baxcalibur.Description: It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.
Baxcalibur.Evolution: Baxcalibur evolves from Arctibax starting from level 54, which evolves from Frigibax starting from level 35.

Gimmighoul.Name: Gimmighoul
Gimmighoul.Description: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

Gholdengo.Name: Gholdengo
Gholdengo.Description: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.

Wo-Chien.Name: Wo-Chien
Wo-Chien.Description: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.

Chien-Pao.Name: Chien-Pao
Chien-Pao.Description: The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokémon.

Ting-Lu.Name: Ting-Lu
Ting-Lu.Description: It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.

Chi-Yu.Name: Chi-Yu
Chi-Yu.Description: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.

Roaring Moon.Name: Roaring Moon
Roaring Moon.Description: According to an article in a dubious magazine, this Pokémon has some connection to a phenomenon that occurs in a certain region.

Iron Valiant.Name: Iron Valiant
Iron Valiant.Description: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

Koraidon.Name: Koraidon
Koraidon.Description: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

Miraidon.Name: Miraidon
Miraidon.Description: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

10% Zygarde.Name: 10% Zygarde
10% Zygarde.Description: Born when around 10% of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered from all over, this form is skilled in close-range combat.

Black Kyurem.Name: Black Kyurem
Black Kyurem.Description: The sameness of Zekrom’s and Kyurem’s genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Zekrom. Kyurem can now use the power of both electricity and ice.

Blade Aegislash.Name: Blade Aegislash
Blade Aegislash.Description: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.

Complete Zygarde.Name: Complete Zygarde
Complete Zygarde.Description: Born when all of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.

jp: パーフェクトフォルム
ディフェンスフォルム

Fan Rotom.Name: Fan Rotom
Fan Rotom.Description: There are several appliances that Rotom can inspirit, but the first one to be developed was the electric fan.

Frost Rotom.Name: Frost Rotom
Frost Rotom.Description: The special motor within the refrigerator is the key to bringing about Rotom’s change in form.

Heat Rotom.Name: Heat Rotom
Heat Rotom.Description: This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven. It will sear the surrounding area with its burning heat, then smile in delight.

Mega Absol.Name: Mega Absol
Mega Absol.Description: It converts the energy from Mega Evolution into an intimidating aura. Fainthearted people expire from shock at the sight of it.

Mega Aerodactyl.Name: Mega Aerodactyl
Mega Aerodactyl.Description: The power of Mega Evolution has completely restored its genes. The rocks on its body are harder than diamond.

Mega Alakazam.Name: Mega Alakazam
Mega Alakazam.Description: It’s adept at precognition. When attacks completely miss Alakazam, that’s because it’s seeing the future.

Mega Ampharos.Name: Mega Ampharos
Mega Ampharos.Description: Massive amounts of energy intensely stimulated Ampharos’s cells, apparently awakening its long-sleeping dragon’s blood.

Mega Banette.Name: Mega Banette
Mega Banette.Description: Mega Evolution increases its vindictiveness, and the cursing power that was held back by its zipper comes spilling out.

Mega Beedrill.Name: Mega Beedrill
Mega Beedrill.Description: Its legs have become poison stingers. It stabs its prey repeatedly with the stingers on its limbs, dealing the final blow with the stinger on its rear.

Mega Blastoise.Name: Mega Blastoise
Mega Blastoise.Description: The cannon on its back is as powerful as a tank gun. Its tough legs and back enable it to withstand the recoil from firing the cannon.

Mega Charizard X.Name: Mega Charizard X
Mega Charizard X.Description: The overwhelming power that fills its entire body causes it to turn black and create intense blue flames.

Mega Charizard Y.Name: Mega Charizard Y
Mega Charizard Y.Description: Its bond with its Trainer is the source of its power. It boasts speed and maneuverability greater than that of a jet fighter.

Mega Garchomp.Name: Mega Garchomp
Mega Garchomp.Description: Its disposition is more vicious than before its Mega Evolution. Garchomp carves its opponents up with the scythes on both arms.

Mega Gengar.Name: Mega Gengar
Mega Gengar.Description: It can pass through other dimensions and can appear anywhere. It caused a stir one time when it stuck just one leg out of a wall.

Mega Glalie.Name: Mega Glalie
Mega Glalie.Description: The power of Mega Evolution was so strong that it smashed Glalie’s jaw. Its inability to eat very well leaves Glalie irritated.

Mega Gyarados.Name: Mega Gyarados
Mega Gyarados.Description: Although it obeys its instinctive drive to destroy everything within its reach, it will respond to orders from a Trainer it truly trusts.

Mega Heracross.Name: Mega Heracross
Mega Heracross.Description: A tremendous influx of energy builds it up, but when Mega Evolution ends, Heracross is bothered by terrible soreness in its muscles.

Mega Houndoom.Name: Mega Houndoom
Mega Houndoom.Description: Houndoom’s entire body generates heat when it Mega Evolves. Its fearsome fiery breath turns its opponents to ash.

Mega Kangaskhan.Name: Mega Kangaskhan
Mega Kangaskhan.Description: Its child has grown rapidly, thanks to the energy of Mega Evolution. Mother and child show their harmonious teamwork in battle.

Mega Lopunny.Name: Mega Lopunny
Mega Lopunny.Description: Mega Evolution awakens its combative instincts. It has shed any fur that got in the way of its attacks.

Mega Lucario.Name: Mega Lucario
Mega Lucario.Description: Bathed in explosive energy, its combative instincts have awakened. For its enemies, it has no mercy whatsoever.

Mega Manectric.Name: Mega Manectric
Mega Manectric.Description: Too much electricity has built up in its body, irritating Manectric. Its explosive speed is equal to that of a lightning bolt.

Mega Mawile.Name: Mega Mawile
Mega Mawile.Description: Its two sets of jaws thrash about violently as if they each had a will of their own. One gnash from them can turn a boulder to dust.

Mega Metagross.Name: Mega Metagross
Mega Metagross.Description: When it knows it can’t win, it digs the claws on its legs into its opponent and starts the countdown to a big explosion.

Mega Mewtwo Y.Name: Mega Mewtwo Y
Mega Mewtwo Y.Description: Despite its diminished size, its mental power has grown phenomenally. With a mere thought, it can smash a skyscraper to smithereens.

Mega Pidgeot.Name: Mega Pidgeot
Mega Pidgeot.Description: With its muscular strength now greatly increased, it can fly continuously for two weeks without resting.

Mega Pinsir.Name: Mega Pinsir
Mega Pinsir.Description: With its vaunted horns, it can lift an opponent 10 times heavier than itself and fly about with ease.

Mega Sableye.Name: Mega Sableye
Mega Sableye.Description: It blocks any and all attacks with its giant-sized gemstone. However, the stone’s a heavy burden, and it limits Mega Sableye’s movements.

Mega Salamence.Name: Mega Salamence
Mega Salamence.Description: It puts its forelegs inside its shell to streamline itself for flight. Salamence flies at high speeds over all kinds of topographical features.

Mega Scizor.Name: Mega Scizor
Mega Scizor.Description: It’s better at beating things than grasping them. When it battles for a long time, the weight of its pincers becomes too much to bear.

Mega Sharpedo.Name: Mega Sharpedo
Mega Sharpedo.Description: The moment it charges into its opponent, sharp spikes pop out of Sharpedo’s head, leaving its opponent with deep wounds.

Mega Slowbro.Name: Mega Slowbro
Mega Slowbro.Description: Under the influence of Shellder’s digestive fluids, Slowpoke has awakened, gaining a great deal of power—and a little motivation to boot.

Mega Tyranitar.Name: Mega Tyranitar
Mega Tyranitar.Description: The effects of Mega Evolution make it more ferocious than ever. It’s unclear whether it can even hear its Trainer’s orders.

Mega Venusaur.Name: Mega Venusaur
Mega Venusaur.Description: In order to support its flower, which has grown larger due to Mega Evolution, its back and legs have become stronger.

Mow Rotom.Name: Mow Rotom
Mow Rotom.Description: This Rotom has possessed a lawn mower. It will mow down grass and flowers, then swagger around with pride at its accomplishments.

Origin Giratina.Name: Origin Giratina
Origin Giratina.Description: Giratina loses its legs upon changing into this form. I believe this Pokémon must hail from a world where the heavens and the earth are as one, though I have no way of proving it.
Origin Giratina.Evolution: Origin Giratina transforms from Giratina when given a Griseous Orb.

jp: ゲンシカイキのすがた
ゲンシカイキのすがた

Resolute Keldeo.Name: Resolute Keldeo
Resolute Keldeo.Description: The power that lay hidden in its body now covers its horn, turning it into a sword that can slice through anything.

Sandy Wormadam.Name: Sandy Wormadam
Sandy Wormadam.Description: Its earthen skin is reasonably hard—it has no problem repelling a Starly’s pecking, at least.

Sky Shaymin.Name: Sky Shaymin
Sky Shaymin.Description: Upon taking in the scent of a particular rare flower, Shaymin is enveloped in light, and its tiny body transforms. I took a whiff of the flower myself, but alas, my body remained unchanged.
Sky Shaymin.Evolution: Sky Shaymin transforms from Shaymin when given a Gracidea.

Therian Landorus.Name: Therian Landorus
Therian Landorus.Description: Landorus soars through the sky in this form, bestowing plentiful harvests upon the land and earning the people’s reverence. It can traverse the whole of Hisui in a mere couple of hours.
Therian Landorus.Evolution: Therian Landorus transforms from Landorus when given a Reveal Glass.

Therian Thundurus.Name: Therian Thundurus
Therian Thundurus.Description: Quick as a flash, it materializes out of nowhere. It pulverizes foes into nothingness with showers of devastatingly powerful lightning bolts launched from the string of orbs on its tail.
Therian Thundurus.Evolution: Therian Thundurus transforms from Thundurus when given a Reveal Glass.

Therian Tornadus.Name: Therian Tornadus
Therian Tornadus.Description: An example of what is known as a “form change,” though I suspect this strange avian guise to be Tornadus’s true form. Tornadus has been sighted crossing the ocean while in this form.
Therian Tornadus.Evolution: Therian Tornadus transforms from Tornadus when given a Reveal Glass.

Trash Wormadam.Name: Trash Wormadam
Trash Wormadam.Description: Its body, composed of refuse, blends in to the scenery so much as to be inconspicuous. This seems to be the perfect way for the Pokémon to evade the detection of predators.

Wash Rotom.Name: Wash Rotom
Wash Rotom.Description: The model of washing machine that Rotom can inspirit has been discontinued, so these appliances are now traded at high prices.

White Kyurem.Name: White Kyurem
White Kyurem.Description: It has foreseen that a world of truth will arrive for people and Pokémon. It strives to protect that future.

Zen Darmanitan.Name: Zen Darmanitan
Zen Darmanitan.Description: When wounded, it stops moving. It goes as still as stone to meditate, sharpening its mind and spirit.

Shiny Bulbasaur.Name: Shiny Bulbasaur
Shiny Bulbasaur.Description: For some time after its birth, it grows by taking nourishment from the seed on its back.
Shiny Bulbasaur.Evolution: Bulbasaur evolves to Ivysaur starting from level 16, which evolves to Venusaur starting from level 32.

Shiny Ivysaur.Name: Shiny Ivysaur
Shiny Ivysaur.Description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower’s coming bloom.
Shiny Ivysaur.Evolution: Ivysaur evolves from Bulbasaur starting from level 16 and evolves to Venusaur starting from level 32.

Shiny Venusaur.Name: Shiny Venusaur
Shiny Venusaur.Description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.
Shiny Venusaur.Evolution: Venusaur evolves from Ivysaur starting from level 32, which evolves from Bulbasaur starting from level 16.

Shiny Charmander.Name: Shiny Charmander
Shiny Charmander.Description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If the Pokémon is healthy, its tail burns intensely.
Shiny Charmander.Evolution: Charmander evolves to Charmeleon starting from level 16, which evolves to Charizard starting from level 36.

Shiny Charmeleon.Name: Shiny Charmeleon
Shiny Charmeleon.Description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
Shiny Charmeleon.Evolution: Charmeleon evolves from Charmander starting from level 16 and evolves to Charizard starting from level 36.

Shiny Charizard.Name: Shiny Charizard
Shiny Charizard.Description: It is said that Charizard’s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
Shiny Charizard.Evolution: Charizard evolves from Charmeleon starting from level 36, which evolves from Charmander starting from level 16.

Shiny Squirtle.Name: Shiny Squirtle
Shiny Squirtle.Description: It hides in its shell to protect itself, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
Shiny Squirtle.Evolution: Squirtle evolves to Wartortle starting from level 16, which evolves to Blastoise starting from level 36.

Shiny Wartortle.Name: Shiny Wartortle
Shiny Wartortle.Description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
Shiny Wartortle.Evolution: Wartortle evolves from Squirtle starting from level 16 and evolves to Blastoise starting from level 36.

Shiny Blastoise.Name: Shiny Blastoise
Shiny Blastoise.Description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
Shiny Blastoise.Evolution: Blastoise evolves from Wartortle starting from level 36, which evolves from Squirtle starting from level 16.

Shiny Caterpie.Name: Shiny Caterpie
Shiny Caterpie.Description: It releases a stench from its red antennae to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.
Shiny Caterpie.Evolution: Caterpie evolves to Metapod starting from level 7, which evolves to Butterfree starting from level 10.

Shiny Metapod.Name: Shiny Metapod
Shiny Metapod.Description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. The Pokémon quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

Shiny Butterfree.Name: Shiny Butterfree
Shiny Butterfree.Description: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
Shiny Butterfree.Evolution: Butterfree evolves from Metapod starting from level 10, which evolves from Caterpie starting from level 7.

Shiny Weedle.Name: Shiny Weedle
Shiny Weedle.Description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.
Shiny Weedle.Evolution: Weedle evolves to Kakuna starting from level 7, which evolves to Beedrill starting from level 10.

Shiny Kakuna.Name: Shiny Kakuna
Shiny Kakuna.Description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

Shiny Beedrill.Name: Shiny Beedrill
Shiny Beedrill.Description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.
Shiny Beedrill.Evolution: Beedrill evolves from Kakuna starting from level 10, which evolves from Weedle starting from level 7.

Shiny Pidgey.Name: Shiny Pidgey
Shiny Pidgey.Description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
Shiny Pidgey.Evolution: Pidgey evolves to Pidgeotto starting from level 18, which evolves to Pidgeot starting from level 36.

Shiny Pidgeotto.Name: Shiny Pidgeotto
Shiny Pidgeotto.Description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.
Shiny Pidgeotto.Evolution: Pidgeotto evolves from Pidgey starting from level 18 and evolves to Pidgeot starting from level 36.

Shiny Pidgeot.Name: Shiny Pidgeot
Shiny Pidgeot.Description: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
Shiny Pidgeot.Evolution: Pidgeot evolves from Pidgeotto starting from level 36, which evolves from Pidgey starting from level 18.

Shiny Rattata.Name: Shiny Rattata
Shiny Rattata.Description: It’s cautious in the extreme, and its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
Shiny Rattata.Evolution: Rattata evolves to Raticate starting from level 20.

Shiny Raticate.Name: Shiny Raticate
Shiny Raticate.Description: It whittles down its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder block walls.
Shiny Raticate.Evolution: Raticate evolves from Rattata starting from level 20.

Shiny Spearow.Name: Shiny Spearow
Shiny Spearow.Description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.
Shiny Spearow.Evolution: Spearow evolves to Fearow starting from level 20.

Shiny Fearow.Name: Shiny Fearow
Shiny Fearow.Description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.
Shiny Fearow.Evolution: Fearow evolves from Spearow starting from level 20.

Shiny Ekans.Name: Shiny Ekans
Shiny Ekans.Description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.
Shiny Ekans.Evolution: Ekans evolves to Arbok starting from level 22.

Shiny Arbok.Name: Shiny Arbok
Shiny Arbok.Description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.
Shiny Arbok.Evolution: Arbok evolves from Ekans starting from level 22.

Shiny Pikachu.Name: Shiny Pikachu
Shiny Pikachu.Description: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
Shiny Pikachu.Evolution: Pikachu evolves from Pichu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Raichu using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Raichu.Name: Shiny Raichu
Shiny Raichu.Description: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.
Shiny Raichu.Evolution: Raichu evolves from Pikachu using a Thunder Stone, which evolves from Pichu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Sandshrew.Name: Shiny Sandshrew
Shiny Sandshrew.Description: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
Shiny Sandshrew.Evolution: Sandshrew evolves to Sandslash starting from level 22.

Shiny Sandslash.Name: Shiny Sandslash
Shiny Sandslash.Description: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.
Shiny Sandslash.Evolution: Sandslash evolves from Sandshrew starting from level 22.

Shiny Nidoran\u2642.Name: Shiny Nidoran♂
Shiny Nidoran\u2642.Description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.
Shiny Nidoran\u2642.Evolution: Nidoran♂ evolves to Nidorino starting from level 16, which evolves to Nidoking using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Nidoran\u2640.Name: Shiny Nidoran♀
Shiny Nidoran\u2640.Description: While this Pokémon does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the venom it secretes from its barbs can be fatal.
Shiny Nidoran\u2640.Evolution: Nidoran♀ evolves to Nidorina starting from level 16, which evolves to Nidoqueen using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Nidorina.Name: Shiny Nidorina
Shiny Nidorina.Description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow more slowly than Nidorino’s.
Shiny Nidorina.Evolution: Nidorina evolves from Nidoran♀ starting from level 16 and evolves to Nidoqueen using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Nidoqueen.Name: Shiny Nidoqueen
Shiny Nidoqueen.Description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.
Shiny Nidoqueen.Evolution: Nidoqueen evolves from Nidorina using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Nidoran♀ starting from level 16.

Shiny Nidorino.Name: Shiny Nidorino
Shiny Nidorino.Description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes venom upon impact.
Shiny Nidorino.Evolution: Nidorino evolves from Nidoran♂ starting from level 16 and evolves to Nidoking using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Nidoking.Name: Shiny Nidoking
Shiny Nidoking.Description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.
Shiny Nidoking.Evolution: Nidoking evolves from Nidorino using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Nidoran♂ starting from level 16.

Shiny Clefairy.Name: Shiny Clefairy
Shiny Clefairy.Description: It can be found in quiet mountain areas on a full moon’s night. Its dancing and its tiny, faintly glowing wings confer upon it a lovely fairylike quality.
Shiny Clefairy.Evolution: Clefairy evolves from Cleffa when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Clefable using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Clefable.Name: Shiny Clefable
Shiny Clefable.Description: Legend says that on clear, quiet nights, it listens for the voices of its kin living on the moon. I, too, often think of my homeland, so far away.
Shiny Clefable.Evolution: Clefable evolves from Clefairy using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Cleffa when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Vulpix.Name: Shiny Vulpix
Shiny Vulpix.Description: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.
Shiny Vulpix.Evolution: Vulpix evolves to Ninetales using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Ninetales.Name: Shiny Ninetales
Shiny Ninetales.Description: The coat of gleaming golden fur is quite magnificent. This species is said to store sacred power in its nine long tails and to live for a millennium.
Shiny Ninetales.Evolution: Ninetales evolves from Vulpix using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Jigglypuff.Name: Shiny Jigglypuff
Shiny Jigglypuff.Description: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.
Shiny Jigglypuff.Evolution: Jigglypuff evolves from Igglybuff when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Wigglytuff using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Wigglytuff.Name: Shiny Wigglytuff
Shiny Wigglytuff.Description: The rich, fluffy fur that covers its body feels so good that anyone who feels it can’t stop touching it.
Shiny Wigglytuff.Evolution: Wigglytuff evolves from Jigglypuff using a Moon Stone, which evolves from Igglybuff when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Zubat.Name: Shiny Zubat
Shiny Zubat.Description: Makes its home in gloomy caves. Atrophied eyes have left this Pokémon blind, so it scans its surroundings via sound waves that it emits from its mouth as it flies.
Shiny Zubat.Evolution: Zubat evolves to Golbat starting from level 22, which evolves to Crobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Golbat.Name: Shiny Golbat
Shiny Golbat.Description: It sinks its sharp fangs into other creatures and slurps up their blood. A closer look at the fangs reveals that they are hollow and akin to straws.
Shiny Golbat.Evolution: Golbat evolves from Zubat starting from level 22 and evolves to Crobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Oddish.Name: Shiny Oddish
Shiny Oddish.Description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.
Shiny Oddish.Evolution: Oddish evolves to Gloom starting from level 21, which evolves to Vileplume using a Leaf Stone and evolves to Bellossom using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Gloom.Name: Shiny Gloom
Shiny Gloom.Description: The nectar it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious that it can make noses curl from more than a mile away.
Shiny Gloom.Evolution: Gloom evolves from Oddish starting from level 21 and evolves to Vileplume using a Leaf Stone and evolves to Bellossom using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Vileplume.Name: Shiny Vileplume
Shiny Vileplume.Description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
Shiny Vileplume.Evolution: Vileplume evolves from Gloom using a Leaf Stone, which evolves from Oddish starting from level 21.

Shiny Paras.Name: Shiny Paras
Shiny Paras.Description: Sometimes seen at the foot of trees in humid forests. The mushrooms on its back—called tochukaso—are not present on infant specimens and instead emerge as Paras matures.
Shiny Paras.Evolution: Paras evolves to Parasect starting from level 24.

Shiny Parasect.Name: Shiny Parasect
Shiny Parasect.Description: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect’s actions.
Shiny Parasect.Evolution: Parasect evolves from Paras starting from level 24.

Shiny Venonat.Name: Shiny Venonat
Shiny Venonat.Description: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.
Shiny Venonat.Evolution: Venonat evolves to Venomoth starting from level 31.

Shiny Venomoth.Name: Shiny Venomoth
Shiny Venomoth.Description: When it attacks, it flaps its large wings violently to scatter its poisonous powder all around.
Shiny Venomoth.Evolution: Venomoth evolves from Venonat starting from level 31.

Shiny Diglett.Name: Shiny Diglett
Shiny Diglett.Description: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.
Shiny Diglett.Evolution: Diglett evolves to Dugtrio starting from level 26.

Shiny Dugtrio.Name: Shiny Dugtrio
Shiny Dugtrio.Description: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.
Shiny Dugtrio.Evolution: Dugtrio evolves from Diglett starting from level 26.

Shiny Meowth.Name: Shiny Meowth
Shiny Meowth.Description: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.
Shiny Meowth.Evolution: Meowth evolves to Persian starting from level 28.

Shiny Persian.Name: Shiny Persian
Shiny Persian.Description: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.
Shiny Persian.Evolution: Persian evolves from Meowth starting from level 28.

Shiny Psyduck.Name: Shiny Psyduck
Shiny Psyduck.Description: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.
Shiny Psyduck.Evolution: Psyduck evolves to Golduck starting from level 33.

Shiny Golduck.Name: Shiny Golduck
Shiny Golduck.Description: It swims gracefully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.
Shiny Golduck.Evolution: Golduck evolves from Psyduck starting from level 33.

Shiny Mankey.Name: Shiny Mankey
Shiny Mankey.Description: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.
Shiny Mankey.Evolution: Mankey evolves to Primeape starting from level 28.

Shiny Primeape.Name: Shiny Primeape
Shiny Primeape.Description: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.
Shiny Primeape.Evolution: Primeape evolves from Mankey starting from level 28.

Shiny Growlithe.Name: Shiny Growlithe
Shiny Growlithe.Description: It’s very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
Shiny Growlithe.Evolution: Growlithe evolves to Arcanine using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Arcanine.Name: Shiny Arcanine
Shiny Arcanine.Description: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.
Shiny Arcanine.Evolution: Arcanine evolves from Growlithe using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Poliwag.Name: Shiny Poliwag
Shiny Poliwag.Description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.
Shiny Poliwag.Evolution: Poliwag evolves to Poliwhirl starting from level 25, which evolves to Poliwrath using a Water Stone and evolves to Politoed when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Shiny Poliwhirl.Name: Shiny Poliwhirl
Shiny Poliwhirl.Description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.
Shiny Poliwhirl.Evolution: Poliwhirl evolves from Poliwag starting from level 25 and evolves to Poliwrath using a Water Stone and evolves to Politoed when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Shiny Poliwrath.Name: Shiny Poliwrath
Shiny Poliwrath.Description: With its extremely tough muscles, it could keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.
Shiny Poliwrath.Evolution: Poliwrath evolves from Poliwhirl using a Water Stone, which evolves from Poliwag starting from level 25.

Shiny Abra.Name: Shiny Abra
Shiny Abra.Description: Spends 18 hours of the day sleeping. Even while asleep, Abra can control its psychic powers—should danger approach, the Pokémon will simply teleport away.
Shiny Abra.Evolution: Abra evolves to Kadabra starting from level 16, which evolves to Alakazam when traded.

Shiny Kadabra.Name: Shiny Kadabra
Shiny Kadabra.Description: There are rumors that a child with mystical powers became a Kadabra; however, this remains unverified. I suspect that the spoon Kadabra holds enhances its brain waves.
Shiny Kadabra.Evolution: Kadabra evolves from Abra starting from level 16 and evolves to Alakazam when traded.

Shiny Alakazam.Name: Shiny Alakazam
Shiny Alakazam.Description: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.
Shiny Alakazam.Evolution: Alakazam evolves from Kadabra when traded, which evolves from Abra starting from level 16.

Shiny Machop.Name: Shiny Machop
Shiny Machop.Description: Though as small as a child, it has strength enough to easily throw a well-built adult. Striving to become ever stronger, Machop trains by carrying a Graveler on its shoulders.
Shiny Machop.Evolution: Machop evolves to Machoke starting from level 28, which evolves to Machamp when traded.

Shiny Machoke.Name: Shiny Machoke
Shiny Machoke.Description: A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists with tasks such as construction and clearing land.
Shiny Machoke.Evolution: Machoke evolves from Machop starting from level 28 and evolves to Machamp when traded.

Shiny Machamp.Name: Shiny Machamp
Shiny Machamp.Description: In close combat, its four arms afford it offensive and defensive supremacy. In but a blink, this valiant Pokémon can overwhelm its foes with more than 1,000 blows from its fists.
Shiny Machamp.Evolution: Machamp evolves from Machoke when traded, which evolves from Machop starting from level 28.

Shiny Bellsprout.Name: Shiny Bellsprout
Shiny Bellsprout.Description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.
Shiny Bellsprout.Evolution: Bellsprout evolves to Weepinbell starting from level 21, which evolves to Victreebel using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Weepinbell.Name: Shiny Weepinbell
Shiny Weepinbell.Description: This Pokémon has the appearance of a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.
Shiny Weepinbell.Evolution: Weepinbell evolves from Bellsprout starting from level 21 and evolves to Victreebel using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Victreebel.Name: Shiny Victreebel
Shiny Victreebel.Description: In its mouth, it pools a fragrant nectar-like fluid. The fluid is really an acid that dissolves anything.
Shiny Victreebel.Evolution: Victreebel evolves from Weepinbell using a Leaf Stone, which evolves from Bellsprout starting from level 21.

Shiny Tentacool.Name: Shiny Tentacool
Shiny Tentacool.Description: They fire beams from the glassy, magenta orbs that resemble eyes atop their heads, and they drift in shallow seas. During low tide, they can sometimes be found on beaches, desiccated.
Shiny Tentacool.Evolution: Tentacool evolves to Tentacruel starting from level 30.

Shiny Tentacruel.Name: Shiny Tentacruel
Shiny Tentacruel.Description: It has 80 tentacles, each with a venomous tip. These tentacles are also extendible, lengthening when Tentacruel attempts to catch prey. Use caution.
Shiny Tentacruel.Evolution: Tentacruel evolves from Tentacool starting from level 30.

Shiny Geodude.Name: Shiny Geodude
Shiny Geodude.Description: Makes its home in mountainous regions, using its arms to climb along harsh mountain roads. Can be troublesome—carelessly kicking one will cause it to fly into a rage and chase after you.
Shiny Geodude.Evolution: Geodude evolves to Graveler starting from level 25, which evolves to Golem when traded.

Shiny Graveler.Name: Shiny Graveler
Shiny Graveler.Description: Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads.
Shiny Graveler.Evolution: Graveler evolves from Geodude starting from level 25 and evolves to Golem when traded.

Shiny Golem.Name: Shiny Golem
Shiny Golem.Description: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.
Shiny Golem.Evolution: Golem evolves from Graveler when traded, which evolves from Geodude starting from level 25.

Shiny Ponyta.Name: Shiny Ponyta
Shiny Ponyta.Description: These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.
Shiny Ponyta.Evolution: Ponyta evolves to Rapidash starting from level 40.

Shiny Rapidash.Name: Shiny Rapidash
Shiny Rapidash.Description: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.
Shiny Rapidash.Evolution: Rapidash evolves from Ponyta starting from level 40.

Shiny Slowpoke.Name: Shiny Slowpoke
Shiny Slowpoke.Description: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.
Shiny Slowpoke.Evolution: Slowpoke evolves to Slowbro starting from level 37 and evolves to Slowking when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Shiny Slowbro.Name: Shiny Slowbro
Shiny Slowbro.Description: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.
Shiny Slowbro.Evolution: Slowbro evolves from Slowpoke starting from level 37.

Shiny Magnemite.Name: Shiny Magnemite
Shiny Magnemite.Description: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges electromagnetic waves and so on from the units at its sides.
Shiny Magnemite.Evolution: Magnemite evolves to Magneton starting from level 30, which evolves to Magnezone using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Magneton.Name: Shiny Magneton
Shiny Magneton.Description: They’re formed by several Magnemite linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
Shiny Magneton.Evolution: Magneton evolves from Magnemite starting from level 30 and evolves to Magnezone using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Farfetch'd.Name: Shiny Farfetch'd
Shiny Farfetch'd.Description: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

Shiny Doduo.Name: Shiny Doduo
Shiny Doduo.Description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
Shiny Doduo.Evolution: Doduo evolves to Dodrio starting from level 31.

Shiny Dodrio.Name: Shiny Dodrio
Shiny Dodrio.Description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. This Pokémon runs at nearly 40 mph.
Shiny Dodrio.Evolution: Dodrio evolves from Doduo starting from level 31.

Shiny Seel.Name: Shiny Seel
Shiny Seel.Description: This Pokémon lives on icebergs. It uses the sharp point on its head to break up ice as it swims in the sea.
Shiny Seel.Evolution: Seel evolves to Dewgong starting from level 34.

Shiny Dewgong.Name: Shiny Dewgong
Shiny Dewgong.Description: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.
Shiny Dewgong.Evolution: Dewgong evolves from Seel starting from level 34.

Shiny Grimer.Name: Shiny Grimer
Shiny Grimer.Description: When two of these Pokémon’s bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.
Shiny Grimer.Evolution: Grimer evolves to Muk starting from level 38.

Shiny Muk.Name: Shiny Muk
Shiny Muk.Description: It’s so stinky! Muk’s body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.
Shiny Muk.Evolution: Muk evolves from Grimer starting from level 38.

Shiny Shellder.Name: Shiny Shellder
Shiny Shellder.Description: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.
Shiny Shellder.Evolution: Shellder evolves to Cloyster using a Water Stone.

Shiny Cloyster.Name: Shiny Cloyster
Shiny Cloyster.Description: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.
Shiny Cloyster.Evolution: Cloyster evolves from Shellder using a Water Stone.

Shiny Gastly.Name: Shiny Gastly
Shiny Gastly.Description: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.
Shiny Gastly.Evolution: Gastly evolves to Haunter starting from level 25, which evolves to Gengar when traded.

Shiny Haunter.Name: Shiny Haunter
Shiny Haunter.Description: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, Haunter lurks, silently stalking its next victim.
Shiny Haunter.Evolution: Haunter evolves from Gastly starting from level 25 and evolves to Gengar when traded.

Shiny Gengar.Name: Shiny Gengar
Shiny Gengar.Description: Hiding in people’s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.
Shiny Gengar.Evolution: Gengar evolves from Haunter when traded, which evolves from Gastly starting from level 25.

Shiny Onix.Name: Shiny Onix
Shiny Onix.Description: This chain of immense stones resembles a giant serpent. Tremors shake the earth above as it burrows deep beneath the ground, feeding on boulders as it goes.
Shiny Onix.Evolution: Onix evolves to Steelix when traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Shiny Drowzee.Name: Shiny Drowzee
Shiny Drowzee.Description: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.
Shiny Drowzee.Evolution: Drowzee evolves to Hypno starting from level 26.

Shiny Hypno.Name: Shiny Hypno
Shiny Hypno.Description: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.
Shiny Hypno.Evolution: Hypno evolves from Drowzee starting from level 26.

Shiny Krabby.Name: Shiny Krabby
Shiny Krabby.Description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are lost in battle.
Shiny Krabby.Evolution: Krabby evolves to Kingler starting from level 28.

Shiny Kingler.Name: Shiny Kingler
Shiny Kingler.Description: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.
Shiny Kingler.Evolution: Kingler evolves from Krabby starting from level 28.

Shiny Voltorb.Name: Shiny Voltorb
Shiny Voltorb.Description: It’s usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.
Shiny Voltorb.Evolution: Voltorb evolves to Electrode starting from level 30.

Shiny Electrode.Name: Shiny Electrode
Shiny Electrode.Description: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of the Bomb Ball.
Shiny Electrode.Evolution: Electrode evolves from Voltorb starting from level 30.

Shiny Exeggcute.Name: Shiny Exeggcute
Shiny Exeggcute.Description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.
Shiny Exeggcute.Evolution: Exeggcute evolves to Exeggutor using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Exeggutor.Name: Shiny Exeggutor
Shiny Exeggutor.Description: It is called the Walking Jungle. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
Shiny Exeggutor.Evolution: Exeggutor evolves from Exeggcute using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Cubone.Name: Shiny Cubone
Shiny Cubone.Description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.
Shiny Cubone.Evolution: Cubone evolves to Marowak starting from level 28 in the nighttime.

Shiny Marowak.Name: Shiny Marowak
Shiny Marowak.Description: The bones it uses have been in its possession since it was born. It has a ferocious nature.
Shiny Marowak.Evolution: Marowak evolves from Cubone starting from level 28 in the nighttime.

Shiny Hitmonlee.Name: Shiny Hitmonlee
Shiny Hitmonlee.Description: Its legs can stretch to double their length. First-time foes are startled by Hitmonlee’s extensible reach.
Shiny Hitmonlee.Evolution: Hitmonlee evolves from Tyrogue starting from level 20 when its Attack is higher than its Defense.

Shiny Hitmonchan.Name: Shiny Hitmonchan
Shiny Hitmonchan.Description: When Hitmonchan twists its arm while throwing a punch, the blow will pulverize even concrete. The Pokémon rests after three minutes of fighting.
Shiny Hitmonchan.Evolution: Hitmonchan evolves from Tyrogue starting from level 20 when its Defense is higher than its Attack.

Shiny Lickitung.Name: Shiny Lickitung
Shiny Lickitung.Description: Wields its long tongue deftly, as though it were an arm. The Pokémon’s viscous saliva, once it has been collected and boiled down, yields a strong and highly useful adhesive.
Shiny Lickitung.Evolution: Lickitung evolves to Lickilicky when leveled up while knowing Rollout.

Shiny Koffing.Name: Shiny Koffing
Shiny Koffing.Description: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell; they are also explosive.
Shiny Koffing.Evolution: Koffing evolves to Weezing starting from level 35.

Shiny Weezing.Name: Shiny Weezing
Shiny Weezing.Description: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.
Shiny Weezing.Evolution: Weezing evolves from Koffing starting from level 35.

Shiny Rhyhorn.Name: Shiny Rhyhorn
Shiny Rhyhorn.Description: Ludicrously strong—when it butts heads with a mountain, it is the mountain that shatters. But its short legs struggle with turns, and it is incapable of stopping unless it collides with something.
Shiny Rhyhorn.Evolution: Rhyhorn evolves to Rhydon starting from level 42, which evolves to Rhyperior when traded while holding a Protector.

Shiny Rhydon.Name: Shiny Rhydon
Shiny Rhydon.Description: Rapidly rotates its horn to bore through bedrock. It swaggers around volcanic regions, protected from the lava’s heat by its tough, armorlike hide.
Shiny Rhydon.Evolution: Rhydon evolves from Rhyhorn starting from level 42 and evolves to Rhyperior when traded while holding a Protector.

Shiny Chansey.Name: Shiny Chansey
Shiny Chansey.Description: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.
Shiny Chansey.Evolution: Chansey evolves from Happiny when leveled up while holding a Oval Stone in the daytime and evolves to Blissey when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Tangela.Name: Shiny Tangela
Shiny Tangela.Description: It is cloaked entirely in blue vines, preventing any glimpse of its true identity. The vines impart a refreshing sensation when chewed—they’re useful as a spice.
Shiny Tangela.Evolution: Tangela evolves to Tangrowth when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Shiny Kangaskhan.Name: Shiny Kangaskhan
Shiny Kangaskhan.Description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets its baby out to play only when it feels safe to do so.

Shiny Horsea.Name: Shiny Horsea
Shiny Horsea.Description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits black ink and flees.
Shiny Horsea.Evolution: Horsea evolves to Seadra starting from level 32, which evolves to Kingdra when traded while holding a Dragon Scale.

Shiny Seadra.Name: Shiny Seadra
Shiny Seadra.Description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.
Shiny Seadra.Evolution: Seadra evolves from Horsea starting from level 32 and evolves to Kingdra when traded while holding a Dragon Scale.

Shiny Goldeen.Name: Shiny Goldeen
Shiny Goldeen.Description: It swims at a steady five knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.
Shiny Goldeen.Evolution: Goldeen evolves to Seaking starting from level 33.

Shiny Seaking.Name: Shiny Seaking
Shiny Seaking.Description: To protect its family, it will fight with its drill-sharp horn. It lives in hollowed rocks in streams.
Shiny Seaking.Evolution: Seaking evolves from Goldeen starting from level 33.

Shiny Staryu.Name: Shiny Staryu
Shiny Staryu.Description: If Staryu’s body is damaged, it will regenerate as long as the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.
Shiny Staryu.Evolution: Staryu evolves to Starmie using a Water Stone.

Shiny Starmie.Name: Shiny Starmie
Shiny Starmie.Description: At the center of its body is a red core that sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.
Shiny Starmie.Evolution: Starmie evolves from Staryu using a Water Stone.

Shiny Mr. Mime.Name: Shiny Mr. Mime
Shiny Mr. Mime.Description: The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.
Shiny Mr. Mime.Evolution: Mr. Mime evolves from Mime Jr. when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Shiny Scyther.Name: Shiny Scyther
Shiny Scyther.Description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.
Shiny Scyther.Evolution: Scyther evolves to Scizor when traded while holding a Metal Coat and evolves to Kleavor when leveled up.

Shiny Jynx.Name: Shiny Jynx
Shiny Jynx.Description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.
Shiny Jynx.Evolution: Jynx evolves from Smoochum starting from level 30.

Shiny Electabuzz.Name: Shiny Electabuzz
Shiny Electabuzz.Description: Feeds on electrical energy. During sudden showers beneath looming thunderclouds, one can observe Electabuzz scaling tall trees, where the Pokémon will then wait for lightning to strike.
Shiny Electabuzz.Evolution: Electabuzz evolves from Elekid starting from level 30 and evolves to Electivire when traded while holding a Electirizer.

Shiny Magmar.Name: Shiny Magmar
Shiny Magmar.Description: Legend has it that this Pokémon was born from the crater of a volcano. When wounded, it bathes in lava to heal its body, much as one would soak in a hot spring.
Shiny Magmar.Evolution: Magmar evolves from Magby starting from level 30 and evolves to Magmortar when traded while holding a Magmarizer.

Shiny Pinsir.Name: Shiny Pinsir
Shiny Pinsir.Description: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn apart. What it can’t tear, it tosses far away.

Shiny Tauros.Name: Shiny Tauros
Shiny Tauros.Description: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd’s protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.

Shiny Magikarp.Name: Shiny Magikarp
Shiny Magikarp.Description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Shiny Magikarp.Evolution: Magikarp evolves to Gyarados starting from level 20.

Shiny Gyarados.Name: Shiny Gyarados
Shiny Gyarados.Description: It appears whenever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.
Shiny Gyarados.Evolution: Gyarados evolves from Magikarp starting from level 20.

Shiny Lapras.Name: Shiny Lapras
Shiny Lapras.Description: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.

Shiny Ditto.Name: Shiny Ditto
Shiny Ditto.Description: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

Shiny Eevee.Name: Shiny Eevee
Shiny Eevee.Description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.
Shiny Eevee.Evolution: Eevee evolves to Vaporeon using a Water Stone, evolves to Jolteon using a Thunder Stone, evolves to Flareon using a Fire Stone, evolves to Espeon when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime, evolves to Umbreon when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime, evolves to Leafeon using a Leaf Stone, evolves to Glaceon using a Ice Stone and evolves to Sylveon when leveled up while knowing a Fairy-type move.

Shiny Vaporeon.Name: Shiny Vaporeon
Shiny Vaporeon.Description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can’t be seen when it melts away into water.
Shiny Vaporeon.Evolution: Vaporeon evolves from Eevee using a Water Stone.

Shiny Jolteon.Name: Shiny Jolteon
Shiny Jolteon.Description: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.
Shiny Jolteon.Evolution: Jolteon evolves from Eevee using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Flareon.Name: Shiny Flareon
Shiny Flareon.Description: It fluffs out its fur collar to cool down its body temperature, which can reach 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.
Shiny Flareon.Evolution: Flareon evolves from Eevee using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Porygon.Name: Shiny Porygon
Shiny Porygon.Description: It has no discernible heartbeat and does not seem to draw breath, and yet it appears to function without issue. I cannot even begin to explain this utterly bizarre anomaly.
Shiny Porygon.Evolution: Porygon evolves to Porygon2 when traded while holding a Upgrade, which evolves to Porygon-Z when traded while holding a Dubious Disc.

Shiny Omanyte.Name: Shiny Omanyte
Shiny Omanyte.Description: It’s a Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.
Shiny Omanyte.Evolution: Omanyte evolves to Omastar starting from level 40.

Shiny Omastar.Name: Shiny Omastar
Shiny Omastar.Description: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.
Shiny Omastar.Evolution: Omastar evolves from Omanyte starting from level 40.

Shiny Kabuto.Name: Shiny Kabuto
Shiny Kabuto.Description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a sturdy shell.
Shiny Kabuto.Evolution: Kabuto evolves to Kabutops starting from level 40.

Shiny Kabutops.Name: Shiny Kabutops
Shiny Kabutops.Description: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.
Shiny Kabutops.Evolution: Kabutops evolves from Kabuto starting from level 40.

Shiny Aerodactyl.Name: Shiny Aerodactyl
Shiny Aerodactyl.Description: It’s a Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

Shiny Snorlax.Name: Shiny Snorlax
Shiny Snorlax.Description: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.
Shiny Snorlax.Evolution: Snorlax evolves from Munchlax when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Articuno.Name: Shiny Articuno
Shiny Articuno.Description: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

Shiny Zapdos.Name: Shiny Zapdos
Shiny Zapdos.Description: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

Shiny Moltres.Name: Shiny Moltres
Shiny Moltres.Description: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.

Shiny Dratini.Name: Shiny Dratini
Shiny Dratini.Description: It is born large to start with. It repeatedly sheds its skin as it steadily grows longer.
Shiny Dratini.Evolution: Dratini evolves to Dragonair starting from level 30, which evolves to Dragonite starting from level 55.

Shiny Dragonair.Name: Shiny Dragonair
Shiny Dragonair.Description: It is called the divine Pokémon. When its entire body brightens slightly, the weather changes.
Shiny Dragonair.Evolution: Dragonair evolves from Dratini starting from level 30 and evolves to Dragonite starting from level 55.

Shiny Dragonite.Name: Shiny Dragonite
Shiny Dragonite.Description: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.
Shiny Dragonite.Evolution: Dragonite evolves from Dragonair starting from level 55, which evolves from Dratini starting from level 30.

Shiny Mewtwo.Name: Shiny Mewtwo
Shiny Mewtwo.Description: Mewtwo was created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

Shiny Mew.Name: Shiny Mew
Shiny Mew.Description: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

Shiny Chikorita.Name: Shiny Chikorita
Shiny Chikorita.Description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the air’s temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.
Shiny Chikorita.Evolution: Chikorita evolves to Bayleef starting from level 16, which evolves to Meganium starting from level 32.

Shiny Bayleef.Name: Shiny Bayleef
Shiny Bayleef.Description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
Shiny Bayleef.Evolution: Bayleef evolves from Chikorita starting from level 16 and evolves to Meganium starting from level 32.

Shiny Meganium.Name: Shiny Meganium
Shiny Meganium.Description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.
Shiny Meganium.Evolution: Meganium evolves from Bayleef starting from level 32, which evolves from Chikorita starting from level 16.

Shiny Cyndaquil.Name: Shiny Cyndaquil
Shiny Cyndaquil.Description: Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.
Shiny Cyndaquil.Evolution: Cyndaquil evolves to Quilava starting from level 14, which evolves to Typhlosion starting from level 36.

Shiny Quilava.Name: Shiny Quilava
Shiny Quilava.Description: This creature’s fur is most mysterious—it is wholly impervious to the burning touch of flame. Should Quilava turn its back to you, take heed! Such a posture indicates a forthcoming attack.
Shiny Quilava.Evolution: Quilava evolves from Cyndaquil starting from level 14 and evolves to Typhlosion starting from level 36.

Shiny Typhlosion.Name: Shiny Typhlosion
Shiny Typhlosion.Description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.
Shiny Typhlosion.Evolution: Typhlosion evolves from Quilava starting from level 36, which evolves from Cyndaquil starting from level 14.

Shiny Totodile.Name: Shiny Totodile
Shiny Totodile.Description: It has a habit of biting everything with its well-developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.
Shiny Totodile.Evolution: Totodile evolves to Croconaw starting from level 18, which evolves to Feraligatr starting from level 30.

Shiny Croconaw.Name: Shiny Croconaw
Shiny Croconaw.Description: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.
Shiny Croconaw.Evolution: Croconaw evolves from Totodile starting from level 18 and evolves to Feraligatr starting from level 30.

Shiny Feraligatr.Name: Shiny Feraligatr
Shiny Feraligatr.Description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
Shiny Feraligatr.Evolution: Feraligatr evolves from Croconaw starting from level 30, which evolves from Totodile starting from level 18.

Shiny Sentret.Name: Shiny Sentret
Shiny Sentret.Description: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.
Shiny Sentret.Evolution: Sentret evolves to Furret starting from level 15.

Shiny Furret.Name: Shiny Furret
Shiny Furret.Description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
Shiny Furret.Evolution: Furret evolves from Sentret starting from level 15.

Shiny Hoothoot.Name: Shiny Hoothoot
Shiny Hoothoot.Description: It switches its standing foot so quickly that the switch can’t be seen. It cries at the same time every day.
Shiny Hoothoot.Evolution: Hoothoot evolves to Noctowl starting from level 20.

Shiny Noctowl.Name: Shiny Noctowl
Shiny Noctowl.Description: If it flips its head upside down, it’s a sign that it is engaged in very complex thinking.
Shiny Noctowl.Evolution: Noctowl evolves from Hoothoot starting from level 20.

Shiny Ledyba.Name: Shiny Ledyba
Shiny Ledyba.Description: It’s so timid that it can’t move unless it’s with a swarm. It conveys its feelings through scent.
Shiny Ledyba.Evolution: Ledyba evolves to Ledian starting from level 18.

Shiny Ledian.Name: Shiny Ledian
Shiny Ledian.Description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.
Shiny Ledian.Evolution: Ledian evolves from Ledyba starting from level 18.

Shiny Spinarak.Name: Shiny Spinarak
Shiny Spinarak.Description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong thread. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.
Shiny Spinarak.Evolution: Spinarak evolves to Ariados starting from level 22.

Shiny Ariados.Name: Shiny Ariados
Shiny Ariados.Description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
Shiny Ariados.Evolution: Ariados evolves from Spinarak starting from level 22.

Shiny Crobat.Name: Shiny Crobat
Shiny Crobat.Description: Its hind limbs have become another set of wings. Crobat expertly maneuvers its four wings to dart in exquisite fashion through even the most confined caves without losing any speed.
Shiny Crobat.Evolution: Crobat evolves from Golbat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves from Zubat starting from level 22.

Shiny Chinchou.Name: Shiny Chinchou
Shiny Chinchou.Description: It discharges positive and negative electricity from the tips of its antennae to shock its foes.
Shiny Chinchou.Evolution: Chinchou evolves to Lanturn starting from level 27.

Shiny Lanturn.Name: Shiny Lanturn
Shiny Lanturn.Description: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed the Deep-Sea Star.
Shiny Lanturn.Evolution: Lanturn evolves from Chinchou starting from level 27.

Shiny Pichu.Name: Shiny Pichu
Shiny Pichu.Description: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.
Shiny Pichu.Evolution: Pichu evolves to Pikachu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Raichu using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Cleffa.Name: Shiny Cleffa
Shiny Cleffa.Description: In silhouette, they resemble twinkling starlight. When shooting stars rain from the night sky, Cleffa gather in numbers and dance as though they are indeed incarnations of the stars.
Shiny Cleffa.Evolution: Cleffa evolves to Clefairy when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Clefable using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Igglybuff.Name: Shiny Igglybuff
Shiny Igglybuff.Description: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.
Shiny Igglybuff.Evolution: Igglybuff evolves to Jigglypuff when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Wigglytuff using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Togepi.Name: Shiny Togepi
Shiny Togepi.Description: This ovate creature is frequently mistaken for a moving egg when encountered out in the fields or in the mountains. Its guileless smile soothes the soul.
Shiny Togepi.Evolution: Togepi evolves to Togetic when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Togekiss using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Togetic.Name: Shiny Togetic
Shiny Togetic.Description: No records exist of Togetic being seen in the wilds. Rumors abound that it evolves under the loving care of a trusted human companion, upon whom the Pokémon then bestows great joy.
Shiny Togetic.Evolution: Togetic evolves from Togepi when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Togekiss using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Natu.Name: Shiny Natu
Shiny Natu.Description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
Shiny Natu.Evolution: Natu evolves to Xatu starting from level 25.

Shiny Xatu.Name: Shiny Xatu
Shiny Xatu.Description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.
Shiny Xatu.Evolution: Xatu evolves from Natu starting from level 25.

Shiny Mareep.Name: Shiny Mareep
Shiny Mareep.Description: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.
Shiny Mareep.Evolution: Mareep evolves to Flaaffy starting from level 15, which evolves to Ampharos starting from level 30.

Shiny Flaaffy.Name: Shiny Flaaffy
Shiny Flaaffy.Description: Because of its rubbery, electricity-resistant skin, it can store lots of electricity in its fur.
Shiny Flaaffy.Evolution: Flaaffy evolves from Mareep starting from level 15 and evolves to Ampharos starting from level 30.

Shiny Ampharos.Name: Shiny Ampharos
Shiny Ampharos.Description: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean’s surface.
Shiny Ampharos.Evolution: Ampharos evolves from Flaaffy starting from level 30, which evolves from Mareep starting from level 15.

Shiny Bellossom.Name: Shiny Bellossom
Shiny Bellossom.Description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
Shiny Bellossom.Evolution: Bellossom evolves from Gloom using a Sun Stone, which evolves from Oddish starting from level 21.

Shiny Marill.Name: Shiny Marill
Shiny Marill.Description: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.
Shiny Marill.Evolution: Marill evolves from Azurill when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet and evolves to Azumarill starting from level 18.

Shiny Azumarill.Name: Shiny Azumarill
Shiny Azumarill.Description: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.
Shiny Azumarill.Evolution: Azumarill evolves from Marill starting from level 18, which evolves from Azurill when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Sudowoodo.Name: Shiny Sudowoodo
Shiny Sudowoodo.Description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.
Shiny Sudowoodo.Evolution: Sudowoodo evolves from Bonsly when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Shiny Politoed.Name: Shiny Politoed
Shiny Politoed.Description: A group of Poliwag and Poliwhirl will form with a Politoed as the leader. Politoed’s cries make the Pokémon of the group obey.
Shiny Politoed.Evolution: Politoed evolves from Poliwhirl when traded while holding a King's Rock, which evolves from Poliwag starting from level 25.

Shiny Hoppip.Name: Shiny Hoppip
Shiny Hoppip.Description: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.
Shiny Hoppip.Evolution: Hoppip evolves to Skiploom starting from level 18, which evolves to Jumpluff starting from level 27.

Shiny Skiploom.Name: Shiny Skiploom
Shiny Skiploom.Description: When the weather grows cold, Skiploom’s flower closes and the Pokémon cannot photosynthesize, so it flies away to warmer regions.
Shiny Skiploom.Evolution: Skiploom evolves from Hoppip starting from level 18 and evolves to Jumpluff starting from level 27.

Shiny Jumpluff.Name: Shiny Jumpluff
Shiny Jumpluff.Description: Beware its cotton spores. If you accidentally breathe them in, you’ll be racked with coughs and itchiness.
Shiny Jumpluff.Evolution: Jumpluff evolves from Skiploom starting from level 27, which evolves from Hoppip starting from level 18.

Shiny Aipom.Name: Shiny Aipom
Shiny Aipom.Description: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.
Shiny Aipom.Evolution: Aipom evolves to Ambipom when leveled up while knowing Double Hit.

Shiny Sunkern.Name: Shiny Sunkern
Shiny Sunkern.Description: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.
Shiny Sunkern.Evolution: Sunkern evolves to Sunflora using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Sunflora.Name: Shiny Sunflora
Shiny Sunflora.Description: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.
Shiny Sunflora.Evolution: Sunflora evolves from Sunkern using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Yanma.Name: Shiny Yanma
Shiny Yanma.Description: Its frail wings are so thin that one can see clear through them. However, during flight these wings exhibit the power to churn air with force enough to launch a house skyward.
Shiny Yanma.Evolution: Yanma evolves to Yanmega when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Shiny Wooper.Name: Shiny Wooper
Shiny Wooper.Description: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
Shiny Wooper.Evolution: Wooper evolves to Quagsire starting from level 20.

Shiny Quagsire.Name: Shiny Quagsire
Shiny Quagsire.Description: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.
Shiny Quagsire.Evolution: Quagsire evolves from Wooper starting from level 20.

Shiny Espeon.Name: Shiny Espeon
Shiny Espeon.Description: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy’s actions.
Shiny Espeon.Evolution: Espeon evolves from Eevee when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Shiny Umbreon.Name: Shiny Umbreon
Shiny Umbreon.Description: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.
Shiny Umbreon.Evolution: Umbreon evolves from Eevee when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Shiny Murkrow.Name: Shiny Murkrow
