Shiny Murkrow.Description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.
Shiny Murkrow.Evolution: Murkrow evolves to Honchkrow using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Slowking.Name: Shiny Slowking
Shiny Slowking.Description: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
Shiny Slowking.Evolution: Slowking evolves from Slowpoke when traded while holding a King's Rock.

Shiny Misdreavus.Name: Shiny Misdreavus
Shiny Misdreavus.Description: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.
Shiny Misdreavus.Evolution: Misdreavus evolves to Mismagius using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Unown.Name: Shiny Unown
Shiny Unown.Description: It is hard to believe these strangely shaped Pokémon are truly living creatures. I’ve pointed out that the species’ many forms resemble writing from other lands; no one will take me seriously.

Shiny Wobbuffet.Name: Shiny Wobbuffet
Shiny Wobbuffet.Description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. This behavior is said to be proof that its tail hides a secret.
Shiny Wobbuffet.Evolution: Wobbuffet evolves from Wynaut starting from level 15.

Shiny Girafarig.Name: Shiny Girafarig
Shiny Girafarig.Description: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

Shiny Pineco.Name: Shiny Pineco
Shiny Pineco.Description: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.
Shiny Pineco.Evolution: Pineco evolves to Forretress starting from level 31.

Shiny Forretress.Name: Shiny Forretress
Shiny Forretress.Description: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.
Shiny Forretress.Evolution: Forretress evolves from Pineco starting from level 31.

Shiny Dunsparce.Name: Shiny Dunsparce
Shiny Dunsparce.Description: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

Shiny Gligar.Name: Shiny Gligar
Shiny Gligar.Description: Its tail is tipped by a thick, horrible stinger. To bring down prey, it will first obscure their vision by covering their faces with its body, and then it will use the stinger to inject them with venom.
Shiny Gligar.Evolution: Gligar evolves to Gliscor when leveled up while holding a Razor Fang in the nighttime.

Shiny Steelix.Name: Shiny Steelix
Shiny Steelix.Description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard—not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.
Shiny Steelix.Evolution: Steelix evolves from Onix when traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Shiny Snubbull.Name: Shiny Snubbull
Shiny Snubbull.Description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by many people to be cute.
Shiny Snubbull.Evolution: Snubbull evolves to Granbull starting from level 23.

Shiny Granbull.Name: Shiny Granbull
Shiny Granbull.Description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.
Shiny Granbull.Evolution: Granbull evolves from Snubbull starting from level 23.

Shiny Qwilfish.Name: Shiny Qwilfish
Shiny Qwilfish.Description: Experienced fishers say they try to catch Qwilfish in the brief moment that these Pokémon become defenseless just after launching poisonous spikes.

Shiny Scizor.Name: Shiny Scizor
Shiny Scizor.Description: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.
Shiny Scizor.Evolution: Scizor evolves from Scyther when traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Shiny Shuckle.Name: Shiny Shuckle
Shiny Shuckle.Description: It stores berries in its shell. The berries mix with its body fluids to become delicious juices.

Shiny Heracross.Name: Shiny Heracross
Shiny Heracross.Description: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

Shiny Sneasel.Name: Shiny Sneasel
Shiny Sneasel.Description: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.
Shiny Sneasel.Evolution: Sneasel evolves to Weavile when leveled up while holding a Razor Claw in the nighttime.

Shiny Teddiursa.Name: Shiny Teddiursa
Shiny Teddiursa.Description: Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon have a smile back on its face.
Shiny Teddiursa.Evolution: Teddiursa evolves to Ursaring starting from level 30.

Shiny Ursaring.Name: Shiny Ursaring
Shiny Ursaring.Description: It is quite skilled at climbing trees. If it comes across a Primeape while searching for berries in the treetops, trouble will surely ensue.
Shiny Ursaring.Evolution: Ursaring evolves from Teddiursa starting from level 30.

Shiny Slugma.Name: Shiny Slugma
Shiny Slugma.Description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
Shiny Slugma.Evolution: Slugma evolves to Magcargo starting from level 38.

Shiny Magcargo.Name: Shiny Magcargo
Shiny Magcargo.Description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Flames burst from gaps in its shell made of hardened magma.
Shiny Magcargo.Evolution: Magcargo evolves from Slugma starting from level 38.

Shiny Swinub.Name: Shiny Swinub
Shiny Swinub.Description: Swinub excels at sniffing out mushrooms buried beneath grass or snow. Since ancient times, the people of Hisui have often relied upon this skill.
Shiny Swinub.Evolution: Swinub evolves to Piloswine starting from level 33, which evolves to Mamoswine when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Shiny Piloswine.Name: Shiny Piloswine
Shiny Piloswine.Description: The long fur of this Pokémon covers its eyes, ears, and even limbs, allowing Piloswine to resist harshly frigid conditions. The Pokémon’s white tusks can be used to defeat its enemies.
Shiny Piloswine.Evolution: Piloswine evolves from Swinub starting from level 33 and evolves to Mamoswine when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Shiny Corsola.Name: Shiny Corsola
Shiny Corsola.Description: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

Shiny Remoraid.Name: Shiny Remoraid
Shiny Remoraid.Description: Spits water from its mouth with incredible accuracy. It captures Burmy by shooting them down off the branches from which they dangle.
Shiny Remoraid.Evolution: Remoraid evolves to Octillery starting from level 25.

Shiny Octillery.Name: Shiny Octillery
Shiny Octillery.Description: While Octillery still shoots water from its mouth, the drastic anatomical difference between it and Remoraid meant that for a long time, no one believed the former evolved from the latter.
Shiny Octillery.Evolution: Octillery evolves from Remoraid starting from level 25.

Shiny Delibird.Name: Shiny Delibird
Shiny Delibird.Description: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

Shiny Mantine.Name: Shiny Mantine
Shiny Mantine.Description: This calm and gentle Pokémon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokémon due to this behavior.
Shiny Mantine.Evolution: Mantine evolves from Mantyke when leveled up.

Shiny Skarmory.Name: Shiny Skarmory
Shiny Skarmory.Description: Skarmory is clad entirely in ironhard armor. It flies at speeds over 180 mph.

Shiny Houndour.Name: Shiny Houndour
Shiny Houndour.Description: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.
Shiny Houndour.Evolution: Houndour evolves to Houndoom starting from level 24.

Shiny Houndoom.Name: Shiny Houndoom
Shiny Houndoom.Description: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.
Shiny Houndoom.Evolution: Houndoom evolves from Houndour starting from level 24.

Shiny Kingdra.Name: Shiny Kingdra
Shiny Kingdra.Description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.
Shiny Kingdra.Evolution: Kingdra evolves from Seadra when traded while holding a Dragon Scale, which evolves from Horsea starting from level 32.

Shiny Phanpy.Name: Shiny Phanpy
Shiny Phanpy.Description: It is far stronger than it appears. If a Phanpy is swinging its trunk around and your arm gets hit by it, your arm bone will shatter.
Shiny Phanpy.Evolution: Phanpy evolves to Donphan starting from level 25.

Shiny Donphan.Name: Shiny Donphan
Shiny Donphan.Description: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.
Shiny Donphan.Evolution: Donphan evolves from Phanpy starting from level 25.

Shiny Porygon2.Name: Shiny Porygon2
Shiny Porygon2.Description: A bizarre item caused this Pokémon to evolve. While it now exhibits many new gestures and expressions, its biology remains inscrutable.
Shiny Porygon2.Evolution: Porygon2 evolves from Porygon when traded while holding a Upgrade and evolves to Porygon-Z when traded while holding a Dubious Disc.

Shiny Stantler.Name: Shiny Stantler
Shiny Stantler.Description: It’s said that this Pokémon used to be stronger long ago when it had many enemies, and that it was even able to evolve under its own power.

Shiny Smeargle.Name: Shiny Smeargle
Shiny Smeargle.Description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

Shiny Tyrogue.Name: Shiny Tyrogue
Shiny Tyrogue.Description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.
Shiny Tyrogue.Evolution: Tyrogue evolves to Hitmonlee starting from level 20 when its Attack is higher than its Defense, evolves to Hitmonchan starting from level 20 when its Defense is higher than its Attack and evolves to Hitmontop starting from level 20 when its Attack is equal to its Defense.

Shiny Hitmontop.Name: Shiny Hitmontop
Shiny Hitmontop.Description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by a factor of 10.
Shiny Hitmontop.Evolution: Hitmontop evolves from Tyrogue starting from level 20 when its Attack is equal to its Defense.

Shiny Smoochum.Name: Shiny Smoochum
Shiny Smoochum.Description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.
Shiny Smoochum.Evolution: Smoochum evolves to Jynx starting from level 30.

Shiny Elekid.Name: Shiny Elekid
Shiny Elekid.Description: They generate electricity by spinning their arms. During a thunderstorm, if one hears the lively voices of children out in the wilderness, what one is actually hearing are the voices of Elekid.
Shiny Elekid.Evolution: Elekid evolves to Electabuzz starting from level 30, which evolves to Electivire when traded while holding a Electirizer.

Shiny Magby.Name: Shiny Magby
Shiny Magby.Description: This Pokémon lives in volcanic areas. With each breath, sparks spurt from its mouth and nose. When Magby is in good health, its flames gain a yellow tint.
Shiny Magby.Evolution: Magby evolves to Magmar starting from level 30, which evolves to Magmortar when traded while holding a Magmarizer.

Shiny Miltank.Name: Shiny Miltank
Shiny Miltank.Description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

Shiny Blissey.Name: Shiny Blissey
Shiny Blissey.Description: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
Shiny Blissey.Evolution: Blissey evolves from Chansey when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves from Happiny when leveled up while holding a Oval Stone in the daytime.

Shiny Raikou.Name: Shiny Raikou
Shiny Raikou.Description: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

Shiny Entei.Name: Shiny Entei
Shiny Entei.Description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

Shiny Suicune.Name: Shiny Suicune
Shiny Suicune.Description: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

Shiny Larvitar.Name: Shiny Larvitar
Shiny Larvitar.Description: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.
Shiny Larvitar.Evolution: Larvitar evolves to Pupitar starting from level 30, which evolves to Tyranitar starting from level 55.

Shiny Pupitar.Name: Shiny Pupitar
Shiny Pupitar.Description: Its shell is as hard as bedrock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.
Shiny Pupitar.Evolution: Pupitar evolves from Larvitar starting from level 30 and evolves to Tyranitar starting from level 55.

Shiny Tyranitar.Name: Shiny Tyranitar
Shiny Tyranitar.Description: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.
Shiny Tyranitar.Evolution: Tyranitar evolves from Pupitar starting from level 55, which evolves from Larvitar starting from level 30.

Shiny Lugia.Name: Shiny Lugia
Shiny Lugia.Description: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

Shiny Celebi.Name: Shiny Celebi
Shiny Celebi.Description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

Shiny Treecko.Name: Shiny Treecko
Shiny Treecko.Description: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny hooks, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.
Shiny Treecko.Evolution: Treecko evolves to Grovyle starting from level 16, which evolves to Sceptile starting from level 36.

Shiny Grovyle.Name: Shiny Grovyle
Shiny Grovyle.Description: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.
Shiny Grovyle.Evolution: Grovyle evolves from Treecko starting from level 16 and evolves to Sceptile starting from level 36.

Shiny Sceptile.Name: Shiny Sceptile
Shiny Sceptile.Description: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.
Shiny Sceptile.Evolution: Sceptile evolves from Grovyle starting from level 36, which evolves from Treecko starting from level 16.

Shiny Torchic.Name: Shiny Torchic
Shiny Torchic.Description: A fire burns inside it, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
Shiny Torchic.Evolution: Torchic evolves to Combusken starting from level 16, which evolves to Blaziken starting from level 36.

Shiny Combusken.Name: Shiny Combusken
Shiny Combusken.Description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.
Shiny Combusken.Evolution: Combusken evolves from Torchic starting from level 16 and evolves to Blaziken starting from level 36.

Shiny Blaziken.Name: Shiny Blaziken
Shiny Blaziken.Description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.
Shiny Blaziken.Evolution: Blaziken evolves from Combusken starting from level 36, which evolves from Torchic starting from level 16.

Shiny Mudkip.Name: Shiny Mudkip
Shiny Mudkip.Description: Using the fin on its head, Mudkip senses the flow of water to keep track of what’s going on around it. Mudkip has the strength to heft boulders.
Shiny Mudkip.Evolution: Mudkip evolves to Marshtomp starting from level 16, which evolves to Swampert starting from level 36.

Shiny Marshtomp.Name: Shiny Marshtomp
Shiny Marshtomp.Description: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.
Shiny Marshtomp.Evolution: Marshtomp evolves from Mudkip starting from level 16 and evolves to Swampert starting from level 36.

Shiny Swampert.Name: Shiny Swampert
Shiny Swampert.Description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.
Shiny Swampert.Evolution: Swampert evolves from Marshtomp starting from level 36, which evolves from Mudkip starting from level 16.

Shiny Poochyena.Name: Shiny Poochyena
Shiny Poochyena.Description: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
Shiny Poochyena.Evolution: Poochyena evolves to Mightyena starting from level 18.

Shiny Mightyena.Name: Shiny Mightyena
Shiny Mightyena.Description: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.
Shiny Mightyena.Evolution: Mightyena evolves from Poochyena starting from level 18.

Shiny Zigzagoon.Name: Shiny Zigzagoon
Shiny Zigzagoon.Description: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
Shiny Zigzagoon.Evolution: Zigzagoon evolves to Linoone starting from level 20.

Shiny Linoone.Name: Shiny Linoone
Shiny Linoone.Description: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
Shiny Linoone.Evolution: Linoone evolves from Zigzagoon starting from level 20.

Shiny Wurmple.Name: Shiny Wurmple
Shiny Wurmple.Description: Likes sap and is abundant in the wild. Why it evolves into various different forms is unknown. One cannot tell from a Wurmple’s appearance which form it will take when it evolves.
Shiny Wurmple.Evolution: Wurmple evolves to Silcoon starting from level 7, which evolves to Beautifly starting from level 10 and evolves to Cascoon starting from level 7, which evolves to Dustox starting from level 10.

Shiny Silcoon.Name: Shiny Silcoon
Shiny Silcoon.Description: Wraps itself in thin strings of silk while it stores energy for evolution. It can’t extend its limbs and its movement is slow, but its eyes keep a sharp lookout—Silcoon is always on guard.

Shiny Beautifly.Name: Shiny Beautifly
Shiny Beautifly.Description: A colorful and incredibly beautiful but also greedy Pokémon. In an effort to keep its favorite food all to itself, it will chase away Combee as they try to gather nectar.
Shiny Beautifly.Evolution: Beautifly evolves from Silcoon starting from level 10, which evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7.

Shiny Cascoon.Name: Shiny Cascoon
Shiny Cascoon.Description: The silk coating its body is thin but sufficiently strong. Cascoon’s silk has a luster and texture superior to that of Silcoon’s, and clothes made using Cascoon silk are regarded as top-notch.
Shiny Cascoon.Evolution: Cascoon evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7 and evolves to Dustox starting from level 10.

Shiny Dustox.Name: Shiny Dustox
Shiny Dustox.Description: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.
Shiny Dustox.Evolution: Dustox evolves from Cascoon starting from level 10, which evolves from Wurmple starting from level 7.

Shiny Lotad.Name: Shiny Lotad
Shiny Lotad.Description: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry for Pokémon that can’t swim.
Shiny Lotad.Evolution: Lotad evolves to Lombre starting from level 14, which evolves to Ludicolo using a Water Stone.

Shiny Lombre.Name: Shiny Lombre
Shiny Lombre.Description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
Shiny Lombre.Evolution: Lombre evolves from Lotad starting from level 14 and evolves to Ludicolo using a Water Stone.

Shiny Ludicolo.Name: Shiny Ludicolo
Shiny Ludicolo.Description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.
Shiny Ludicolo.Evolution: Ludicolo evolves from Lombre using a Water Stone, which evolves from Lotad starting from level 14.

Shiny Seedot.Name: Shiny Seedot
Shiny Seedot.Description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon that try to peck at it.
Shiny Seedot.Evolution: Seedot evolves to Nuzleaf starting from level 14, which evolves to Shiftry using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Nuzleaf.Name: Shiny Nuzleaf
Shiny Nuzleaf.Description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in the forest.
Shiny Nuzleaf.Evolution: Nuzleaf evolves from Seedot starting from level 14 and evolves to Shiftry using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Shiftry.Name: Shiny Shiftry
Shiny Shiftry.Description: By flapping its leafy fans, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.
Shiny Shiftry.Evolution: Shiftry evolves from Nuzleaf using a Leaf Stone, which evolves from Seedot starting from level 14.

Shiny Taillow.Name: Shiny Taillow
Shiny Taillow.Description: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.
Shiny Taillow.Evolution: Taillow evolves to Swellow starting from level 22.

Shiny Swellow.Name: Shiny Swellow
Shiny Swellow.Description: It circles the sky in search of prey and dives sharply to catch its target.
Shiny Swellow.Evolution: Swellow evolves from Taillow starting from level 22.

Shiny Wingull.Name: Shiny Wingull
Shiny Wingull.Description: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.
Shiny Wingull.Evolution: Wingull evolves to Pelipper starting from level 25.

Shiny Pelipper.Name: Shiny Pelipper
Shiny Pelipper.Description: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.
Shiny Pelipper.Evolution: Pelipper evolves from Wingull starting from level 25.

Shiny Ralts.Name: Shiny Ralts
Shiny Ralts.Description: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.
Shiny Ralts.Evolution: Ralts evolves to Kirlia starting from level 20, which evolves to Gardevoir starting from level 30 and evolves to Gallade using a Dawn Stone.

Shiny Kirlia.Name: Shiny Kirlia
Shiny Kirlia.Description: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.
Shiny Kirlia.Evolution: Kirlia evolves from Ralts starting from level 20 and evolves to Gardevoir starting from level 30 and evolves to Gallade using a Dawn Stone.

Shiny Gardevoir.Name: Shiny Gardevoir
Shiny Gardevoir.Description: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.
Shiny Gardevoir.Evolution: Gardevoir evolves from Kirlia starting from level 30, which evolves from Ralts starting from level 20.

Shiny Surskit.Name: Shiny Surskit
Shiny Surskit.Description: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.
Shiny Surskit.Evolution: Surskit evolves to Masquerain starting from level 22.

Shiny Masquerain.Name: Shiny Masquerain
Shiny Masquerain.Description: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.
Shiny Masquerain.Evolution: Masquerain evolves from Surskit starting from level 22.

Shiny Shroomish.Name: Shiny Shroomish
Shiny Shroomish.Description: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.
Shiny Shroomish.Evolution: Shroomish evolves to Breloom starting from level 23.

Shiny Breloom.Name: Shiny Breloom
Shiny Breloom.Description: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.
Shiny Breloom.Evolution: Breloom evolves from Shroomish starting from level 23.

Shiny Slakoth.Name: Shiny Slakoth
Shiny Slakoth.Description: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.
Shiny Slakoth.Evolution: Slakoth evolves to Vigoroth starting from level 18, which evolves to Slaking starting from level 36.

Shiny Vigoroth.Name: Shiny Vigoroth
Shiny Vigoroth.Description: It is always hungry because it won’t stop rampaging. Even while it is eating, it can’t keep still.
Shiny Vigoroth.Evolution: Vigoroth evolves from Slakoth starting from level 18 and evolves to Slaking starting from level 36.

Shiny Slaking.Name: Shiny Slaking
Shiny Slaking.Description: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.
Shiny Slaking.Evolution: Slaking evolves from Vigoroth starting from level 36, which evolves from Slakoth starting from level 18.

Shiny Nincada.Name: Shiny Nincada
Shiny Nincada.Description: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.
Shiny Nincada.Evolution: Nincada evolves to Ninjask starting from level 20 and evolves to Shedinja somehow.

Shiny Ninjask.Name: Shiny Ninjask
Shiny Ninjask.Description: Because they move so quickly, they sometimes become unseeable. They congregate around tree sap.
Shiny Ninjask.Evolution: Ninjask evolves from Nincada starting from level 20.

Shiny Shedinja.Name: Shiny Shedinja
Shiny Shedinja.Description: It is a discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

Shiny Whismur.Name: Shiny Whismur
Shiny Whismur.Description: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.
Shiny Whismur.Evolution: Whismur evolves to Loudred starting from level 20, which evolves to Exploud starting from level 40.

Shiny Loudred.Name: Shiny Loudred
Shiny Loudred.Description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Shiny Loudred.Evolution: Loudred evolves from Whismur starting from level 20 and evolves to Exploud starting from level 40.

Shiny Exploud.Name: Shiny Exploud
Shiny Exploud.Description: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.
Shiny Exploud.Evolution: Exploud evolves from Loudred starting from level 40, which evolves from Whismur starting from level 20.

Shiny Makuhita.Name: Shiny Makuhita
Shiny Makuhita.Description: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.
Shiny Makuhita.Evolution: Makuhita evolves to Hariyama starting from level 24.

Shiny Hariyama.Name: Shiny Hariyama
Shiny Hariyama.Description: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.
Shiny Hariyama.Evolution: Hariyama evolves from Makuhita starting from level 24.

Shiny Azurill.Name: Shiny Azurill
Shiny Azurill.Description: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.
Shiny Azurill.Evolution: Azurill evolves to Marill when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves to Azumarill starting from level 18.

Shiny Nosepass.Name: Shiny Nosepass
Shiny Nosepass.Description: Once the people of Hisui discovered that its red nose always points north, they grew to rely on it greatly when traveling afar. The nose seems to work in a similar way to ancient compasses.
Shiny Nosepass.Evolution: Nosepass evolves to Probopass using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Skitty.Name: Shiny Skitty
Shiny Skitty.Description: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in circles, chasing its own tail.
Shiny Skitty.Evolution: Skitty evolves to Delcatty using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Delcatty.Name: Shiny Delcatty
Shiny Delcatty.Description: It is highly popular among Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
Shiny Delcatty.Evolution: Delcatty evolves from Skitty using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Sableye.Name: Shiny Sableye
Shiny Sableye.Description: Materials from gems it has eaten float to the surface of its body and can form an infinite number of patterns among individuals.

Shiny Mawile.Name: Shiny Mawile
Shiny Mawile.Description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

Shiny Aron.Name: Shiny Aron
Shiny Aron.Description: It usually lives deep in mountains. But when it’s hungry, it shows up at the foot of the mountains and eats railroad tracks and cars.
Shiny Aron.Evolution: Aron evolves to Lairon starting from level 32, which evolves to Aggron starting from level 42.

Shiny Lairon.Name: Shiny Lairon
Shiny Lairon.Description: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.
Shiny Lairon.Evolution: Lairon evolves from Aron starting from level 32 and evolves to Aggron starting from level 42.

Shiny Aggron.Name: Shiny Aggron
Shiny Aggron.Description: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
Shiny Aggron.Evolution: Aggron evolves from Lairon starting from level 42, which evolves from Aron starting from level 32.

Shiny Meditite.Name: Shiny Meditite
Shiny Meditite.Description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.
Shiny Meditite.Evolution: Meditite evolves to Medicham starting from level 37.

Shiny Medicham.Name: Shiny Medicham
Shiny Medicham.Description: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.
Shiny Medicham.Evolution: Medicham evolves from Meditite starting from level 37.

Shiny Electrike.Name: Shiny Electrike
Shiny Electrike.Description: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
Shiny Electrike.Evolution: Electrike evolves to Manectric starting from level 26.

Shiny Manectric.Name: Shiny Manectric
Shiny Manectric.Description: It discharges electricity from its mane. The Pokémon creates a thundercloud overhead from which to drop lightning bolts.
Shiny Manectric.Evolution: Manectric evolves from Electrike starting from level 26.

Shiny Plusle.Name: Shiny Plusle
Shiny Plusle.Description: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

Shiny Minun.Name: Shiny Minun
Shiny Minun.Description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

Shiny Volbeat.Name: Shiny Volbeat
Shiny Volbeat.Description: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise’s sweet aroma.

Shiny Illumise.Name: Shiny Illumise
Shiny Illumise.Description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

Shiny Roselia.Name: Shiny Roselia
Shiny Roselia.Description: Though beautiful, it has highly poisonous thorns. There is an old tradition in my homeland wherein one would send these thorns to an opponent to challenge them to a duel.
Shiny Roselia.Evolution: Roselia evolves from Budew when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime and evolves to Roserade using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Gulpin.Name: Shiny Gulpin
Shiny Gulpin.Description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
Shiny Gulpin.Evolution: Gulpin evolves to Swalot starting from level 26.

Shiny Swalot.Name: Shiny Swalot
Shiny Swalot.Description: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.
Shiny Swalot.Evolution: Swalot evolves from Gulpin starting from level 26.

Shiny Carvanha.Name: Shiny Carvanha
Shiny Carvanha.Description: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.
Shiny Carvanha.Evolution: Carvanha evolves to Sharpedo starting from level 30.

Shiny Sharpedo.Name: Shiny Sharpedo
Shiny Sharpedo.Description: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as the Bully of the Sea.
Shiny Sharpedo.Evolution: Sharpedo evolves from Carvanha starting from level 30.

Shiny Wailmer.Name: Shiny Wailmer
Shiny Wailmer.Description: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nostrils.
Shiny Wailmer.Evolution: Wailmer evolves to Wailord starting from level 40.

Shiny Wailord.Name: Shiny Wailord
Shiny Wailord.Description: It’s the biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.
Shiny Wailord.Evolution: Wailord evolves from Wailmer starting from level 40.

Shiny Numel.Name: Shiny Numel
Shiny Numel.Description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.
Shiny Numel.Evolution: Numel evolves to Camerupt starting from level 33.

Shiny Camerupt.Name: Shiny Camerupt
Shiny Camerupt.Description: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
Shiny Camerupt.Evolution: Camerupt evolves from Numel starting from level 33.

Shiny Torkoal.Name: Shiny Torkoal
Shiny Torkoal.Description: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

Shiny Spoink.Name: Shiny Spoink
Shiny Spoink.Description: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.
Shiny Spoink.Evolution: Spoink evolves to Grumpig starting from level 32.

Shiny Grumpig.Name: Shiny Grumpig
Shiny Grumpig.Description: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.
Shiny Grumpig.Evolution: Grumpig evolves from Spoink starting from level 32.

Shiny Spinda.Name: Shiny Spinda
Shiny Spinda.Description: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Their tottering steps hinder the aim of foes.

Shiny Trapinch.Name: Shiny Trapinch
Shiny Trapinch.Description: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
Shiny Trapinch.Evolution: Trapinch evolves to Vibrava starting from level 35, which evolves to Flygon starting from level 45.

Shiny Vibrava.Name: Shiny Vibrava
Shiny Vibrava.Description: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.
Shiny Vibrava.Evolution: Vibrava evolves from Trapinch starting from level 35 and evolves to Flygon starting from level 45.

Shiny Flygon.Name: Shiny Flygon
Shiny Flygon.Description: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as the Desert Spirit.
Shiny Flygon.Evolution: Flygon evolves from Vibrava starting from level 45, which evolves from Trapinch starting from level 35.

Shiny Cacnea.Name: Shiny Cacnea
Shiny Cacnea.Description: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.
Shiny Cacnea.Evolution: Cacnea evolves to Cacturne starting from level 32.

Shiny Cacturne.Name: Shiny Cacturne
Shiny Cacturne.Description: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.
Shiny Cacturne.Evolution: Cacturne evolves from Cacnea starting from level 32.

Shiny Swablu.Name: Shiny Swablu
Shiny Swablu.Description: It can’t relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.
Shiny Swablu.Evolution: Swablu evolves to Altaria starting from level 35.

Shiny Altaria.Name: Shiny Altaria
Shiny Altaria.Description: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Shiny Altaria.Evolution: Altaria evolves from Swablu starting from level 35.

Shiny Zangoose.Name: Shiny Zangoose
Shiny Zangoose.Description: If it comes across a Seviper, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.

Shiny Seviper.Name: Shiny Seviper
Shiny Seviper.Description: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It’s Zangoose’s archrival.

Shiny Lunatone.Name: Shiny Lunatone
Shiny Lunatone.Description: It becomes active on nights with a full moon, so it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

Shiny Solrock.Name: Shiny Solrock
Shiny Solrock.Description: This new Pokémon species is rumored to be an avatar of the sun. The Pokémon gives off light while spinning.

Shiny Barboach.Name: Shiny Barboach
Shiny Barboach.Description: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.
Shiny Barboach.Evolution: Barboach evolves to Whiscash starting from level 30.

Shiny Whiscash.Name: Shiny Whiscash
Shiny Whiscash.Description: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.
Shiny Whiscash.Evolution: Whiscash evolves from Barboach starting from level 30.

Shiny Corphish.Name: Shiny Corphish
Shiny Corphish.Description: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
Shiny Corphish.Evolution: Corphish evolves to Crawdaunt starting from level 30.

Shiny Crawdaunt.Name: Shiny Crawdaunt
Shiny Crawdaunt.Description: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.
Shiny Crawdaunt.Evolution: Crawdaunt evolves from Corphish starting from level 30.

Shiny Baltoy.Name: Shiny Baltoy
Shiny Baltoy.Description: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.
Shiny Baltoy.Evolution: Baltoy evolves to Claydol starting from level 36.

Shiny Claydol.Name: Shiny Claydol
Shiny Claydol.Description: An ancient clay figurine was exposed to a mysterious ray of light, and it came to life as a Pokémon.
Shiny Claydol.Evolution: Claydol evolves from Baltoy starting from level 36.

Shiny Lileep.Name: Shiny Lileep
Shiny Lileep.Description: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
Shiny Lileep.Evolution: Lileep evolves to Cradily starting from level 40.

Shiny Cradily.Name: Shiny Cradily
Shiny Cradily.Description: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.
Shiny Cradily.Evolution: Cradily evolves from Lileep starting from level 40.

Shiny Anorith.Name: Shiny Anorith
Shiny Anorith.Description: This Pokémon ancestor was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with its claws.
Shiny Anorith.Evolution: Anorith evolves to Armaldo starting from level 40.

Shiny Armaldo.Name: Shiny Armaldo
Shiny Armaldo.Description: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.
Shiny Armaldo.Evolution: Armaldo evolves from Anorith starting from level 40.

Shiny Feebas.Name: Shiny Feebas
Shiny Feebas.Description: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.
Shiny Feebas.Evolution: Feebas evolves to Milotic when leveled up.

Shiny Milotic.Name: Shiny Milotic
Shiny Milotic.Description: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.
Shiny Milotic.Evolution: Milotic evolves from Feebas when leveled up.

Shiny Castform.Name: Shiny Castform
Shiny Castform.Description: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

Shiny Snowy Castform.Name: Shiny Snowy Castform
Shiny Snowy Castform.Description: This is Castform’s form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!

Shiny Sunny Castform.Name: Shiny Sunny Castform
Shiny Sunny Castform.Description: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!

Shiny Rainy Castform.Name: Shiny Rainy Castform
Shiny Rainy Castform.Description: This is Castform’s form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn’t change to this form.

Shiny Kecleon.Name: Shiny Kecleon
Shiny Kecleon.Description: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.

Shiny Shuppet.Name: Shiny Shuppet
Shiny Shuppet.Description: It feeds on the dark emotions of sadness and hatred, which make it grow steadily stronger.
Shiny Shuppet.Evolution: Shuppet evolves to Banette starting from level 37.

Shiny Banette.Name: Shiny Banette
Shiny Banette.Description: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
Shiny Banette.Evolution: Banette evolves from Shuppet starting from level 37.

Shiny Duskull.Name: Shiny Duskull
Shiny Duskull.Description: I’ve heard that the children of Hisui all begin to behave once they’ve been told the story of how this Pokémon roams about before the witching hour to spirit away misbehaving children.
Shiny Duskull.Evolution: Duskull evolves to Dusclops starting from level 37, which evolves to Dusknoir when traded while holding a Reaper Cloth.

Shiny Dusclops.Name: Shiny Dusclops
Shiny Dusclops.Description: There are rumors that peeking inside its bandage-wrapped body will cause one to get pulled in through the gaps between the bandages, never to return. I’ve been too scared to verify.
Shiny Dusclops.Evolution: Dusclops evolves from Duskull starting from level 37 and evolves to Dusknoir when traded while holding a Reaper Cloth.

Shiny Tropius.Name: Shiny Tropius
Shiny Tropius.Description: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

Shiny Chimecho.Name: Shiny Chimecho
Shiny Chimecho.Description: Can emit waves of air powerful enough to knock out prey taller than itself. I hypothesize that it amplifies the faint sound of wind within its body.
Shiny Chimecho.Evolution: Chimecho evolves from Chingling when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Shiny Absol.Name: Shiny Absol
Shiny Absol.Description: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.

Shiny Wynaut.Name: Shiny Wynaut
Shiny Wynaut.Description: They grow strong by pushing up against one another en masse. They love eating sweet fruit.
Shiny Wynaut.Evolution: Wynaut evolves to Wobbuffet starting from level 15.

Shiny Snorunt.Name: Shiny Snorunt
Shiny Snorunt.Description: It is said that a home visited by a Snorunt will prosper. It can withstand cold of −150 degrees Fahrenheit.
Shiny Snorunt.Evolution: Snorunt evolves to Glalie starting from level 42 and evolves to Froslass using a Dawn Stone.

Shiny Glalie.Name: Shiny Glalie
Shiny Glalie.Description: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.
Shiny Glalie.Evolution: Glalie evolves from Snorunt starting from level 42.

Shiny Spheal.Name: Shiny Spheal
Shiny Spheal.Description: During the season when drift ice approaches the shore, Spheal prefers living on the ice—where fewer predators lurk—rather than the land. Its fur retains heat superbly and resists harsh cold.
Shiny Spheal.Evolution: Spheal evolves to Sealeo starting from level 32, which evolves to Walrein starting from level 44.

Shiny Sealeo.Name: Shiny Sealeo
Shiny Sealeo.Description: Its white whiskers are very sensitive. Sealeo will balance Spheal on the tip of its nose, checking its scent and its feel to be sure the Spheal is healthy.
Shiny Sealeo.Evolution: Sealeo evolves from Spheal starting from level 32 and evolves to Walrein starting from level 44.

Shiny Walrein.Name: Shiny Walrein
Shiny Walrein.Description: Its thick tusks are strong enough to shatter drift ice. They have been known to break, but they will grow back by the next year. The Hisui region is well known for these broken tusks.
Shiny Walrein.Evolution: Walrein evolves from Sealeo starting from level 44, which evolves from Spheal starting from level 32.

Shiny Clamperl.Name: Shiny Clamperl
Shiny Clamperl.Description: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.
Shiny Clamperl.Evolution: Clamperl evolves to Huntail when traded while holding a Deep Sea Tooth and evolves to Gorebyss when traded while holding a Deep Sea Scale.

Shiny Huntail.Name: Shiny Huntail
Shiny Huntail.Description: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.
Shiny Huntail.Evolution: Huntail evolves from Clamperl when traded while holding a Deep Sea Tooth.

Shiny Gorebyss.Name: Shiny Gorebyss
Shiny Gorebyss.Description: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.
Shiny Gorebyss.Evolution: Gorebyss evolves from Clamperl when traded while holding a Deep Sea Scale.

Shiny Relicanth.Name: Shiny Relicanth
Shiny Relicanth.Description: This rare Pokémon was discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Shiny Luvdisc.Name: Shiny Luvdisc
Shiny Luvdisc.Description: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

Shiny Bagon.Name: Shiny Bagon
Shiny Bagon.Description: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.
Shiny Bagon.Evolution: Bagon evolves to Shelgon starting from level 30, which evolves to Salamence starting from level 50.

Shiny Shelgon.Name: Shiny Shelgon
Shiny Shelgon.Description: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.
Shiny Shelgon.Evolution: Shelgon evolves from Bagon starting from level 30 and evolves to Salamence starting from level 50.

Shiny Salamence.Name: Shiny Salamence
Shiny Salamence.Description: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.
Shiny Salamence.Evolution: Salamence evolves from Shelgon starting from level 50, which evolves from Bagon starting from level 30.

Shiny Beldum.Name: Shiny Beldum
Shiny Beldum.Description: They converse with one another by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
Shiny Beldum.Evolution: Beldum evolves to Metang starting from level 20, which evolves to Metagross starting from level 45.

Shiny Metang.Name: Shiny Metang
Shiny Metang.Description: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won’t be scratched if it collides with a jet.
Shiny Metang.Evolution: Metang evolves from Beldum starting from level 20 and evolves to Metagross starting from level 45.

Shiny Metagross.Name: Shiny Metagross
Shiny Metagross.Description: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
Shiny Metagross.Evolution: Metagross evolves from Metang starting from level 45, which evolves from Beldum starting from level 20.

Shiny Regirock.Name: Shiny Regirock
Shiny Regirock.Description: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, Regirock attaches rocks to repair itself.

Shiny Regice.Name: Shiny Regice
Shiny Regice.Description: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of −328 degrees Fahrenheit.

Shiny Registeel.Name: Shiny Registeel
Shiny Registeel.Description: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

Shiny Latias.Name: Shiny Latias
Shiny Latias.Description: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

Shiny Latios.Name: Shiny Latios
Shiny Latios.Description: It is a highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its forelegs in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

Shiny Kyogre.Name: Shiny Kyogre
Shiny Kyogre.Description: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

Shiny Groudon.Name: Shiny Groudon
Shiny Groudon.Description: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.

Shiny Rayquaza.Name: Shiny Rayquaza
Shiny Rayquaza.Description: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

Shiny Jirachi.Name: Shiny Jirachi
Shiny Jirachi.Description: It is said to wake up for just seven days every 1,000 years and use its power to grant any wish.

Shiny Deoxys.Name: Shiny Deoxys
Shiny Deoxys.Description: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteorite underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

Shiny Turtwig.Name: Shiny Turtwig
Shiny Turtwig.Description: This Pokémon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.
Shiny Turtwig.Evolution: Turtwig evolves to Grotle starting from level 18, which evolves to Torterra starting from level 32.

Shiny Grotle.Name: Shiny Grotle
Shiny Grotle.Description: Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.
Shiny Grotle.Evolution: Grotle evolves from Turtwig starting from level 18 and evolves to Torterra starting from level 32.

Shiny Torterra.Name: Shiny Torterra
Shiny Torterra.Description: This remarkable, large-bodied Pokémon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.
Shiny Torterra.Evolution: Torterra evolves from Grotle starting from level 32, which evolves from Turtwig starting from level 18.

Shiny Chimchar.Name: Shiny Chimchar
Shiny Chimchar.Description: Full of vigor and always in high spirits. It was once known by the name “Lantern-Tail” and feared as some kind of apparition.
Shiny Chimchar.Evolution: Chimchar evolves to Monferno starting from level 14, which evolves to Infernape starting from level 36.

Shiny Monferno.Name: Shiny Monferno
Shiny Monferno.Description: The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.
Shiny Monferno.Evolution: Monferno evolves from Chimchar starting from level 14 and evolves to Infernape starting from level 36.

Shiny Infernape.Name: Shiny Infernape
Shiny Infernape.Description: A tall, hardy Pokémon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance—truly a sight to behold.
Shiny Infernape.Evolution: Infernape evolves from Monferno starting from level 36, which evolves from Chimchar starting from level 14.

Shiny Piplup.Name: Shiny Piplup
Shiny Piplup.Description: Prefers cold climes and appears along coasts. It’s an adorable little thing—as cute as any child—but it’s also prideful, unwilling to accept handouts from people.
Shiny Piplup.Evolution: Piplup evolves to Prinplup starting from level 16, which evolves to Empoleon starting from level 36.

Shiny Prinplup.Name: Shiny Prinplup
Shiny Prinplup.Description: It swims gracefully through the frigid sea and sings with a voice like the roaring tide. It has powerful, sturdy wings and dignity to match.
Shiny Prinplup.Evolution: Prinplup evolves from Piplup starting from level 16 and evolves to Empoleon starting from level 36.

Shiny Empoleon.Name: Shiny Empoleon
Shiny Empoleon.Description: Since ancient times, it has been revered by the people of Hisui, who call it the Master of the Waves. Its wings are a match for even master-crafted blades.
Shiny Empoleon.Evolution: Empoleon evolves from Prinplup starting from level 36, which evolves from Piplup starting from level 16.

Shiny Starly.Name: Shiny Starly
Shiny Starly.Description: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.
Shiny Starly.Evolution: Starly evolves to Staravia starting from level 14, which evolves to Staraptor starting from level 34.

Shiny Staravia.Name: Shiny Staravia
Shiny Staravia.Description: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
Shiny Staravia.Evolution: Staravia evolves from Starly starting from level 14 and evolves to Staraptor starting from level 34.

Shiny Staraptor.Name: Shiny Staraptor
Shiny Staraptor.Description: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.
Shiny Staraptor.Evolution: Staraptor evolves from Staravia starting from level 34, which evolves from Starly starting from level 14.

Shiny Bidoof.Name: Shiny Bidoof
Shiny Bidoof.Description: Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.
Shiny Bidoof.Evolution: Bidoof evolves to Bibarel starting from level 15.

Shiny Bibarel.Name: Shiny Bibarel
Shiny Bibarel.Description: Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokémon create dams on rivers to live in.
Shiny Bibarel.Evolution: Bibarel evolves from Bidoof starting from level 15.

Shiny Kricketot.Name: Shiny Kricketot
Shiny Kricketot.Description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
Shiny Kricketot.Evolution: Kricketot evolves to Kricketune starting from level 10.

Shiny Kricketune.Name: Shiny Kricketune
Shiny Kricketune.Description: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.
Shiny Kricketune.Evolution: Kricketune evolves from Kricketot starting from level 10.

Shiny Shinx.Name: Shiny Shinx
Shiny Shinx.Description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.
Shiny Shinx.Evolution: Shinx evolves to Luxio starting from level 15, which evolves to Luxray starting from level 30.

Shiny Luxio.Name: Shiny Luxio
Shiny Luxio.Description: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.
Shiny Luxio.Evolution: Luxio evolves from Shinx starting from level 15 and evolves to Luxray starting from level 30.

Shiny Luxray.Name: Shiny Luxray
Shiny Luxray.Description: Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.
Shiny Luxray.Evolution: Luxray evolves from Luxio starting from level 30, which evolves from Shinx starting from level 15.

Shiny Budew.Name: Shiny Budew
Shiny Budew.Description: When the sun’s light strengthens, the bud atop this Pokémon’s head opens. This is a sign to the people that the harsh winter is over, and the season of budding has begun.
Shiny Budew.Evolution: Budew evolves to Roselia when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime, which evolves to Roserade using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Roserade.Name: Shiny Roserade
Shiny Roserade.Description: Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.
Shiny Roserade.Evolution: Roserade evolves from Roselia using a Shiny Stone, which evolves from Budew when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Shiny Cranidos.Name: Shiny Cranidos
Shiny Cranidos.Description: An incredibly rare sight. They duel each other by ramming their heads together, and the resulting sound echoes throughout the area like the pealing of a bell.
Shiny Cranidos.Evolution: Cranidos evolves to Rampardos starting from level 30.

Shiny Rampardos.Name: Shiny Rampardos
Shiny Rampardos.Description: Very little is known about its biology. Can knock down massive trees by smashing its beautiful, pearl-like crown against them.
Shiny Rampardos.Evolution: Rampardos evolves from Cranidos starting from level 30.

Shiny Shieldon.Name: Shiny Shieldon
Shiny Shieldon.Description: Much remains unknown about this Pokémon, as few have ever seen it. However, we know that it is calm and dislikes conflict, and it enjoys polishing its face against trees and rocks.
Shiny Shieldon.Evolution: Shieldon evolves to Bastiodon starting from level 30.

Shiny Bastiodon.Name: Shiny Bastiodon
Shiny Bastiodon.Description: Its face is sturdy—as strong as diamond—and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat.
Shiny Bastiodon.Evolution: Bastiodon evolves from Shieldon starting from level 30.

Shiny Burmy.Name: Shiny Burmy
Shiny Burmy.Description: If its cloak is even slightly damaged, Burmy will immediately repair it with whatever is close at hand. The Pokémon within the cloak is scrawny and vulnerable to the cold.
Shiny Burmy.Evolution: Burmy evolves to Wormadam starting from level 20 and evolves to Mothim starting from level 20.

Shiny Wormadam.Name: Shiny Wormadam
Shiny Wormadam.Description: The cloak—fashioned from plant matter—has merged with the Pokémon and is now part of the body, like fur or skin. I suspect this fusion is an effect of the energy involved in evolution.

Shiny Mothim.Name: Shiny Mothim
Shiny Mothim.Description: Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers, Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.
Shiny Mothim.Evolution: Mothim evolves from Burmy starting from level 20.

Shiny Combee.Name: Shiny Combee
Shiny Combee.Description: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.
Shiny Combee.Evolution: Combee evolves to Vespiquen starting from level 21.

Shiny Vespiquen.Name: Shiny Vespiquen
Shiny Vespiquen.Description: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control Combee.
Shiny Vespiquen.Evolution: Vespiquen evolves from Combee starting from level 21.

Shiny Pachirisu.Name: Shiny Pachirisu
Shiny Pachirisu.Description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

Shiny Buizel.Name: Shiny Buizel
Shiny Buizel.Description: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.
Shiny Buizel.Evolution: Buizel evolves to Floatzel starting from level 26.

Shiny Floatzel.Name: Shiny Floatzel
Shiny Floatzel.Description: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and help fishers carry what they caught.
Shiny Floatzel.Evolution: Floatzel evolves from Buizel starting from level 26.

Shiny Cherubi.Name: Shiny Cherubi
Shiny Cherubi.Description: Once the fruit growing alongside the main body is large and plump, Cherubi will use the nutrients within to evolve. The fruit then detaches, becoming nourishment for other creatures.
Shiny Cherubi.Evolution: Cherubi evolves to Cherrim starting from level 25.

Shiny Cherrim.Name: Shiny Cherrim
Shiny Cherrim.Description: Motionless, save for the occasional quiver. A rich array of Pokémon can be found gathered around it, drawn by the scent exuded from Cherrim’s folded petals.
Shiny Cherrim.Evolution: Cherrim evolves from Cherubi starting from level 25.

Shiny Shellos.Name: Shiny Shellos
Shiny Shellos.Description: Found in abundance on seashores bordering warm waters. Shellos are unexpectedly friendly and will crawl toward any person they see. Take care not to get coated in mucus!
Shiny Shellos.Evolution: Shellos evolves to Gastrodon starting from level 30.

Shiny Gastrodon.Name: Shiny Gastrodon
Shiny Gastrodon.Description: Eats beach sand for nourishment. Should one Gastrodon encounter another of a different color, a fierce battle will inevitably ensue.
Shiny Gastrodon.Evolution: Gastrodon evolves from Shellos starting from level 30.

Shiny Ambipom.Name: Shiny Ambipom
Shiny Ambipom.Description: To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.
Shiny Ambipom.Evolution: Ambipom evolves from Aipom when leveled up while knowing Double Hit.

Shiny Drifloon.Name: Shiny Drifloon
Shiny Drifloon.Description: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”
Shiny Drifloon.Evolution: Drifloon evolves to Drifblim starting from level 28.

Shiny Drifblim.Name: Shiny Drifblim
Shiny Drifblim.Description: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.
Shiny Drifblim.Evolution: Drifblim evolves from Drifloon starting from level 28.

Shiny Buneary.Name: Shiny Buneary
Shiny Buneary.Description: My hypothesis as to why Buneary rolls up its ears is that its hearing is far too keen. I surmise that the Pokémon protects its hearing by limiting the sound that may enter its ears.
Shiny Buneary.Evolution: Buneary evolves to Lopunny when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Lopunny.Name: Shiny Lopunny
Shiny Lopunny.Description: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokémon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.
Shiny Lopunny.Evolution: Lopunny evolves from Buneary when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Mismagius.Name: Shiny Mismagius
Shiny Mismagius.Description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.
Shiny Mismagius.Evolution: Mismagius evolves from Misdreavus using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Honchkrow.Name: Shiny Honchkrow
Shiny Honchkrow.Description: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than 100 of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.
Shiny Honchkrow.Evolution: Honchkrow evolves from Murkrow using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Glameow.Name: Shiny Glameow
Shiny Glameow.Description: Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokémon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.
Shiny Glameow.Evolution: Glameow evolves to Purugly starting from level 38.

Shiny Purugly.Name: Shiny Purugly
Shiny Purugly.Description: Though impudent and difficult to tame, Purugly enjoys great popularity due to its fur, the beauty of which surpasses even velveteen.
Shiny Purugly.Evolution: Purugly evolves from Glameow starting from level 38.

Shiny Chingling.Name: Shiny Chingling
Shiny Chingling.Description: This Pokémon gave me an excruciating headache when it seemingly cried out without making a sound. Perhaps there are some sounds that the human ear is simply incapable of hearing.
Shiny Chingling.Evolution: Chingling evolves to Chimecho when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Shiny Stunky.Name: Shiny Stunky
Shiny Stunky.Description: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.
Shiny Stunky.Evolution: Stunky evolves to Skuntank starting from level 34.

Shiny Skuntank.Name: Shiny Skuntank
Shiny Skuntank.Description: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.
Shiny Skuntank.Evolution: Skuntank evolves from Stunky starting from level 34.

Shiny Bronzor.Name: Shiny Bronzor
Shiny Bronzor.Description: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.
Shiny Bronzor.Evolution: Bronzor evolves to Bronzong starting from level 33.

Shiny Bronzong.Name: Shiny Bronzong
Shiny Bronzong.Description: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.
Shiny Bronzong.Evolution: Bronzong evolves from Bronzor starting from level 33.

Shiny Bonsly.Name: Shiny Bonsly
Shiny Bonsly.Description: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.
Shiny Bonsly.Evolution: Bonsly evolves to Sudowoodo when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Shiny Mime Jr..Name: Shiny Mime Jr.
Shiny Mime Jr..Description: Known to turn up in bustling marketplaces now and again. It mimics people much as a child would, then watches how they react, eyes sparkling.
Shiny Mime Jr..Evolution: Mime Jr. evolves to Mr. Mime when leveled up while knowing Mimic.

Shiny Happiny.Name: Shiny Happiny
Shiny Happiny.Description: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It’s bothered by how curly its hair looks.
Shiny Happiny.Evolution: Happiny evolves to Chansey when leveled up while holding a Oval Stone in the daytime, which evolves to Blissey when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Chatot.Name: Shiny Chatot
Shiny Chatot.Description: A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.

Shiny Spiritomb.Name: Shiny Spiritomb
Shiny Spiritomb.Description: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.

Shiny Gible.Name: Shiny Gible
Shiny Gible.Description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
Shiny Gible.Evolution: Gible evolves to Gabite starting from level 24, which evolves to Garchomp starting from level 48.

Shiny Gabite.Name: Shiny Gabite
Shiny Gabite.Description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
Shiny Gabite.Evolution: Gabite evolves from Gible starting from level 24 and evolves to Garchomp starting from level 48.

Shiny Garchomp.Name: Shiny Garchomp
Shiny Garchomp.Description: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.
Shiny Garchomp.Evolution: Garchomp evolves from Gabite starting from level 48, which evolves from Gible starting from level 24.

Shiny Munchlax.Name: Shiny Munchlax
Shiny Munchlax.Description: Its robust stomach allows it to nonchalantly devour even rotted matter. It pays frequent visits to villages, seeking out food scraps intended for compost.
Shiny Munchlax.Evolution: Munchlax evolves to Snorlax when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Riolu.Name: Shiny Riolu
Shiny Riolu.Description: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions, such as joy and rage, in the form of waves.
Shiny Riolu.Evolution: Riolu evolves to Lucario when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Shiny Lucario.Name: Shiny Lucario
Shiny Lucario.Description: A well-trained one can use its aura to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.
Shiny Lucario.Evolution: Lucario evolves from Riolu when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the daytime.

Shiny Hippopotas.Name: Shiny Hippopotas
Shiny Hippopotas.Description: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.
Shiny Hippopotas.Evolution: Hippopotas evolves to Hippowdon starting from level 34.

Shiny Hippowdon.Name: Shiny Hippowdon
Shiny Hippowdon.Description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.
Shiny Hippowdon.Evolution: Hippowdon evolves from Hippopotas starting from level 34.

Shiny Skorupi.Name: Shiny Skorupi
Shiny Skorupi.Description: Its claws are not only razor-sharp but poisonous, making Skorupi a highly dangerous Pokémon. It seems to be weakened by cold temperatures, however.
Shiny Skorupi.Evolution: Skorupi evolves to Drapion starting from level 40.

Shiny Drapion.Name: Shiny Drapion
Shiny Drapion.Description: Has a brutish, ferocious temperament. With immense strength and a sturdy shell off which swords will bounce, it rampages about and wreaks havoc.
Shiny Drapion.Evolution: Drapion evolves from Skorupi starting from level 40.

Shiny Croagunk.Name: Shiny Croagunk
Shiny Croagunk.Description: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
Shiny Croagunk.Evolution: Croagunk evolves to Toxicroak starting from level 37.

Shiny Toxicroak.Name: Shiny Toxicroak
Shiny Toxicroak.Description: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
Shiny Toxicroak.Evolution: Toxicroak evolves from Croagunk starting from level 37.

Shiny Carnivine.Name: Shiny Carnivine
Shiny Carnivine.Description: Though this is a plant Pokémon, it has a gluttonous and unruly temperament. Carnivine attacks its prey with its cavernous maw wide open.

Shiny Finneon.Name: Shiny Finneon
Shiny Finneon.Description: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.
Shiny Finneon.Evolution: Finneon evolves to Lumineon starting from level 31.

Shiny Lumineon.Name: Shiny Lumineon
Shiny Lumineon.Description: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.
Shiny Lumineon.Evolution: Lumineon evolves from Finneon starting from level 31.

Shiny Mantyke.Name: Shiny Mantyke
Shiny Mantyke.Description: Though ball-like in shape, this Pokémon is a proficient swimmer. I have discovered that if a Mantyke spends much time with schools of Remoraid, it will eventually achieve evolution.

Shiny Snover.Name: Shiny Snover
Shiny Snover.Description: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.
Shiny Snover.Evolution: Snover evolves to Abomasnow starting from level 40.

Shiny Abomasnow.Name: Shiny Abomasnow
Shiny Abomasnow.Description: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
Shiny Abomasnow.Evolution: Abomasnow evolves from Snover starting from level 40.

Shiny Weavile.Name: Shiny Weavile
Shiny Weavile.Description: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
Shiny Weavile.Evolution: Weavile evolves from Sneasel when leveled up while holding a Razor Claw in the nighttime.

Shiny Magnezone.Name: Shiny Magnezone
Shiny Magnezone.Description: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed Magneton’s molecular structure, turning it into Magnezone.
Shiny Magnezone.Evolution: Magnezone evolves from Magneton using a Thunder Stone, which evolves from Magnemite starting from level 30.

Shiny Lickilicky.Name: Shiny Lickilicky
Shiny Lickilicky.Description: Its tongue can extend and contract freely, and it is capable of reaching lengths over 10 times Lickilicky’s height. Beware of the saliva, as it contains corrosive elements.
Shiny Lickilicky.Evolution: Lickilicky evolves from Lickitung when leveled up while knowing Rollout.

Shiny Rhyperior.Name: Shiny Rhyperior
Shiny Rhyperior.Description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a curious item. Its rocklike hide is composed of a mysterious substance and can withstand a blow from a masterwork sword with nary a scratch.
Shiny Rhyperior.Evolution: Rhyperior evolves from Rhydon when traded while holding a Protector, which evolves from Rhyhorn starting from level 42.

Shiny Tangrowth.Name: Shiny Tangrowth
Shiny Tangrowth.Description: Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.
Shiny Tangrowth.Evolution: Tangrowth evolves from Tangela when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Shiny Electivire.Name: Shiny Electivire
Shiny Electivire.Description: Its evolution was induced by an unusual item, and its electrical output rises along with its heart rate. From its tails, it can unleash an electric current measuring 20,000 volts.

Shiny Magmortar.Name: Shiny Magmortar
Shiny Magmortar.Description: Use of a strange item caused this Pokémon to evolve. Fireballs launched from the ends of its tubelike arms are hot enough to melt an iron pot in an instant.
Shiny Magmortar.Evolution: Magmortar evolves from Magmar when traded while holding a Magmarizer, which evolves from Magby starting from level 30.

Shiny Togekiss.Name: Shiny Togekiss
Shiny Togekiss.Description: Scant few have ever sighted this Pokémon. After studying what literature remains, I am certain Togekiss will reveal itself when peace reigns in the land.
Shiny Togekiss.Evolution: Togekiss evolves from Togetic using a Shiny Stone, which evolves from Togepi when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Yanmega.Name: Shiny Yanmega
Shiny Yanmega.Description: Extremely violent. When hunting, it wastes none of its energy, aiming only for prey’s most vulnerable spots. Any who manage to tame this Pokémon must be of incredible bravery.
Shiny Yanmega.Evolution: Yanmega evolves from Yanma when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power.

Shiny Leafeon.Name: Shiny Leafeon
Shiny Leafeon.Description: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.
Shiny Leafeon.Evolution: Leafeon evolves from Eevee using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Glaceon.Name: Shiny Glaceon
Shiny Glaceon.Description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.
Shiny Glaceon.Evolution: Glaceon evolves from Eevee using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Gliscor.Name: Shiny Gliscor
Shiny Gliscor.Description: It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.
Shiny Gliscor.Evolution: Gliscor evolves from Gligar when leveled up while holding a Razor Fang in the nighttime.

Shiny Mamoswine.Name: Shiny Mamoswine
Shiny Mamoswine.Description: This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui’s frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine’s constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.
Shiny Mamoswine.Evolution: Mamoswine evolves from Piloswine when leveled up while knowing Ancient Power, which evolves from Swinub starting from level 33.

Shiny Porygon-Z.Name: Shiny Porygon-Z
Shiny Porygon-Z.Description: A curious item induced this evolution. The Pokémon’s offensive capabilities have greatly increased, but the strangeness of its behavior has magnified in equal measure. This worries me.

Shiny Gallade.Name: Shiny Gallade
Shiny Gallade.Description: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
Shiny Gallade.Evolution: Gallade evolves from Kirlia using a Dawn Stone, which evolves from Ralts starting from level 20.

Shiny Probopass.Name: Shiny Probopass
Shiny Probopass.Description: It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.
Shiny Probopass.Evolution: Probopass evolves from Nosepass using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Dusknoir.Name: Shiny Dusknoir
Shiny Dusknoir.Description: Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.
Shiny Dusknoir.Evolution: Dusknoir evolves from Dusclops when traded while holding a Reaper Cloth, which evolves from Duskull starting from level 37.

Shiny Froslass.Name: Shiny Froslass
Shiny Froslass.Description: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.
Shiny Froslass.Evolution: Froslass evolves from Snorunt using a Dawn Stone.

Shiny Rotom.Name: Shiny Rotom
Shiny Rotom.Description: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

Shiny Uxie.Name: Shiny Uxie
Shiny Uxie.Description: A Pokémon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.

Shiny Mesprit.Name: Shiny Mesprit
Shiny Mesprit.Description: Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokémon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.

Shiny Azelf.Name: Shiny Azelf
Shiny Azelf.Description: The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokémon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.

Shiny Dialga.Name: Shiny Dialga
Shiny Dialga.Description: This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.

Shiny Palkia.Name: Shiny Palkia
Shiny Palkia.Description: This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.

Shiny Heatran.Name: Shiny Heatran
Shiny Heatran.Description: Stories tell of this Pokémon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.

Shiny Regigigas.Name: Shiny Regigigas
Shiny Regigigas.Description: According to legend, Regigigas pulled landmasses together and bound them with rope to create the continent of Hisui. Though I have my doubts, the story could well contain a shred of truth.

Shiny Giratina.Name: Shiny Giratina
Shiny Giratina.Description: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.

Shiny Cresselia.Name: Shiny Cresselia
Shiny Cresselia.Description: Cresselia is reminiscent of the crescent moon. It leaves a brilliant line of light in its wake as it flies across the night sky. I daresay it resembles the heavenly maiden who created the Milky Way.

Shiny Phione.Name: Shiny Phione
Shiny Phione.Description: Can be seen floating offshore during seasons when the seas are warm. Its azure body blends in with the ocean waters—logic suggests this is a defense mechanism against natural predators.

Shiny Manaphy.Name: Shiny Manaphy
Shiny Manaphy.Description: Rumored to migrate across the oceans and visit Hisui’s coastal waters only rarely. Although Manaphy resembles Phione, it is also quite different. The relation between the two is unclear.

Shiny Darkrai.Name: Shiny Darkrai
Shiny Darkrai.Description: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village’s inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.

Shiny Shaymin.Name: Shiny Shaymin
Shiny Shaymin.Description: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.

Shiny Arceus.Name: Shiny Arceus
Shiny Arceus.Description: It is the heavenly fount from which pours the light that shines across Hisui. Its luminance guides and protects all Pokémon. Hisuian mythology states that Arceus is the creator of all things.

Shiny Victini.Name: Shiny Victini
Shiny Victini.Description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.

Shiny Snivy.Name: Shiny Snivy
Shiny Snivy.Description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
Shiny Snivy.Evolution: Snivy evolves to Servine starting from level 17, which evolves to Serperior starting from level 36.

Shiny Servine.Name: Shiny Servine
Shiny Servine.Description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
Shiny Servine.Evolution: Servine evolves from Snivy starting from level 17 and evolves to Serperior starting from level 36.

Shiny Serperior.Name: Shiny Serperior
Shiny Serperior.Description: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
Shiny Serperior.Evolution: Serperior evolves from Servine starting from level 36, which evolves from Snivy starting from level 17.

Shiny Tepig.Name: Shiny Tepig
Shiny Tepig.Description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.
Shiny Tepig.Evolution: Tepig evolves to Pignite starting from level 17, which evolves to Emboar starting from level 36.

Shiny Pignite.Name: Shiny Pignite
Shiny Pignite.Description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.
Shiny Pignite.Evolution: Pignite evolves from Tepig starting from level 17 and evolves to Emboar starting from level 36.

Shiny Emboar.Name: Shiny Emboar
Shiny Emboar.Description: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
Shiny Emboar.Evolution: Emboar evolves from Pignite starting from level 36, which evolves from Tepig starting from level 17.

Shiny Oshawott.Name: Shiny Oshawott
Shiny Oshawott.Description: This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I’ve conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”
Shiny Oshawott.Evolution: Oshawott evolves to Dewott starting from level 17, which evolves to Samurott starting from level 36.

Shiny Dewott.Name: Shiny Dewott
