Shiny Dewott.Description: Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.
Shiny Dewott.Evolution: Dewott evolves from Oshawott starting from level 17 and evolves to Samurott starting from level 36.

Shiny Samurott.Name: Shiny Samurott
Shiny Samurott.Description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
Shiny Samurott.Evolution: Samurott evolves from Dewott starting from level 36, which evolves from Oshawott starting from level 17.

Shiny Patrat.Name: Shiny Patrat
Shiny Patrat.Description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.
Shiny Patrat.Evolution: Patrat evolves to Watchog starting from level 20.

Shiny Watchog.Name: Shiny Watchog
Shiny Watchog.Description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.
Shiny Watchog.Evolution: Watchog evolves from Patrat starting from level 20.

Shiny Lillipup.Name: Shiny Lillipup
Shiny Lillipup.Description: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.
Shiny Lillipup.Evolution: Lillipup evolves to Herdier starting from level 16, which evolves to Stoutland starting from level 32.

Shiny Herdier.Name: Shiny Herdier
Shiny Herdier.Description: The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.
Shiny Herdier.Evolution: Herdier evolves from Lillipup starting from level 16 and evolves to Stoutland starting from level 32.

Shiny Stoutland.Name: Shiny Stoutland
Shiny Stoutland.Description: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.
Shiny Stoutland.Evolution: Stoutland evolves from Herdier starting from level 32, which evolves from Lillipup starting from level 16.

Shiny Purrloin.Name: Shiny Purrloin
Shiny Purrloin.Description: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.
Shiny Purrloin.Evolution: Purrloin evolves to Liepard starting from level 20.

Shiny Liepard.Name: Shiny Liepard
Shiny Liepard.Description: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.
Shiny Liepard.Evolution: Liepard evolves from Purrloin starting from level 20.

Shiny Pansage.Name: Shiny Pansage
Shiny Pansage.Description: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.
Shiny Pansage.Evolution: Pansage evolves to Simisage using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Simisage.Name: Shiny Simisage
Shiny Simisage.Description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Shiny Simisage.Evolution: Simisage evolves from Pansage using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Pansear.Name: Shiny Pansear
Shiny Pansear.Description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Shiny Pansear.Evolution: Pansear evolves to Simisear using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Simisear.Name: Shiny Simisear
Shiny Simisear.Description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
Shiny Simisear.Evolution: Simisear evolves from Pansear using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Panpour.Name: Shiny Panpour
Shiny Panpour.Description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
Shiny Panpour.Evolution: Panpour evolves to Simipour using a Water Stone.

Shiny Simipour.Name: Shiny Simipour
Shiny Simipour.Description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.
Shiny Simipour.Evolution: Simipour evolves from Panpour using a Water Stone.

Shiny Munna.Name: Shiny Munna
Shiny Munna.Description: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.
Shiny Munna.Evolution: Munna evolves to Musharna using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Musharna.Name: Shiny Musharna
Shiny Musharna.Description: It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.
Shiny Musharna.Evolution: Musharna evolves from Munna using a Moon Stone.

Shiny Pidove.Name: Shiny Pidove
Shiny Pidove.Description: It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.
Shiny Pidove.Evolution: Pidove evolves to Tranquill starting from level 21, which evolves to Unfezant starting from level 32.

Shiny Tranquill.Name: Shiny Tranquill
Shiny Tranquill.Description: These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.
Shiny Tranquill.Evolution: Tranquill evolves from Pidove starting from level 21 and evolves to Unfezant starting from level 32.

Shiny Unfezant.Name: Shiny Unfezant
Shiny Unfezant.Description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
Shiny Unfezant.Evolution: Unfezant evolves from Tranquill starting from level 32, which evolves from Pidove starting from level 21.

Shiny Blitzle.Name: Shiny Blitzle
Shiny Blitzle.Description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
Shiny Blitzle.Evolution: Blitzle evolves to Zebstrika starting from level 27.

Shiny Zebstrika.Name: Shiny Zebstrika
Shiny Zebstrika.Description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Shiny Zebstrika.Evolution: Zebstrika evolves from Blitzle starting from level 27.

Shiny Roggenrola.Name: Shiny Roggenrola
Shiny Roggenrola.Description: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.
Shiny Roggenrola.Evolution: Roggenrola evolves to Boldore starting from level 25, which evolves to Gigalith when traded.

Shiny Boldore.Name: Shiny Boldore
Shiny Boldore.Description: It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.
Shiny Boldore.Evolution: Boldore evolves from Roggenrola starting from level 25 and evolves to Gigalith when traded.

Shiny Gigalith.Name: Shiny Gigalith
Shiny Gigalith.Description: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.
Shiny Gigalith.Evolution: Gigalith evolves from Boldore when traded, which evolves from Roggenrola starting from level 25.

Shiny Woobat.Name: Shiny Woobat
Shiny Woobat.Description: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.
Shiny Woobat.Evolution: Woobat evolves to Swoobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Swoobat.Name: Shiny Swoobat
Shiny Swoobat.Description: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.
Shiny Swoobat.Evolution: Swoobat evolves from Woobat when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Drilbur.Name: Shiny Drilbur
Shiny Drilbur.Description: It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.
Shiny Drilbur.Evolution: Drilbur evolves to Excadrill starting from level 31.

Shiny Excadrill.Name: Shiny Excadrill
Shiny Excadrill.Description: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.
Shiny Excadrill.Evolution: Excadrill evolves from Drilbur starting from level 31.

Shiny Audino.Name: Shiny Audino
Shiny Audino.Description: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

Shiny Timburr.Name: Shiny Timburr
Shiny Timburr.Description: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.
Shiny Timburr.Evolution: Timburr evolves to Gurdurr starting from level 25, which evolves to Conkeldurr when traded.

Shiny Gurdurr.Name: Shiny Gurdurr
Shiny Gurdurr.Description: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there’s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.
Shiny Gurdurr.Evolution: Gurdurr evolves from Timburr starting from level 25 and evolves to Conkeldurr when traded.

Shiny Conkeldurr.Name: Shiny Conkeldurr
Shiny Conkeldurr.Description: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.
Shiny Conkeldurr.Evolution: Conkeldurr evolves from Gurdurr when traded, which evolves from Timburr starting from level 25.

Shiny Tympole.Name: Shiny Tympole
Shiny Tympole.Description: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.
Shiny Tympole.Evolution: Tympole evolves to Palpitoad starting from level 25, which evolves to Seismitoad starting from level 36.

Shiny Palpitoad.Name: Shiny Palpitoad
Shiny Palpitoad.Description: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.
Shiny Palpitoad.Evolution: Palpitoad evolves from Tympole starting from level 25 and evolves to Seismitoad starting from level 36.

Shiny Seismitoad.Name: Shiny Seismitoad
Shiny Seismitoad.Description: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.
Shiny Seismitoad.Evolution: Seismitoad evolves from Palpitoad starting from level 36, which evolves from Tympole starting from level 25.

Shiny Throh.Name: Shiny Throh
Shiny Throh.Description: They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.

Shiny Sawk.Name: Shiny Sawk
Shiny Sawk.Description: The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.

Shiny Sewaddle.Name: Shiny Sewaddle
Shiny Sewaddle.Description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.
Shiny Sewaddle.Evolution: Sewaddle evolves to Swadloon starting from level 20, which evolves to Leavanny when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Swadloon.Name: Shiny Swadloon
Shiny Swadloon.Description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
Shiny Swadloon.Evolution: Swadloon evolves from Sewaddle starting from level 20 and evolves to Leavanny when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Leavanny.Name: Shiny Leavanny
Shiny Leavanny.Description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.
Shiny Leavanny.Evolution: Leavanny evolves from Swadloon when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet, which evolves from Sewaddle starting from level 20.

Shiny Venipede.Name: Shiny Venipede
Shiny Venipede.Description: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.
Shiny Venipede.Evolution: Venipede evolves to Whirlipede starting from level 22, which evolves to Scolipede starting from level 30.

Shiny Whirlipede.Name: Shiny Whirlipede
Shiny Whirlipede.Description: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.

Shiny Scolipede.Name: Shiny Scolipede
Shiny Scolipede.Description: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.
Shiny Scolipede.Evolution: Scolipede evolves from Whirlipede starting from level 30, which evolves from Venipede starting from level 22.

Shiny Cottonee.Name: Shiny Cottonee
Shiny Cottonee.Description: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.
Shiny Cottonee.Evolution: Cottonee evolves to Whimsicott using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Whimsicott.Name: Shiny Whimsicott
Shiny Whimsicott.Description: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.
Shiny Whimsicott.Evolution: Whimsicott evolves from Cottonee using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Petilil.Name: Shiny Petilil
Shiny Petilil.Description: If the leaves on its head are pruned with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.
Shiny Petilil.Evolution: Petilil evolves to Lilligant using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Lilligant.Name: Shiny Lilligant
Shiny Lilligant.Description: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.
Shiny Lilligant.Evolution: Lilligant evolves from Petilil using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Basculin.Name: Shiny Basculin
Shiny Basculin.Description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.

Shiny Sandile.Name: Shiny Sandile
Shiny Sandile.Description: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.
Shiny Sandile.Evolution: Sandile evolves to Krokorok starting from level 29, which evolves to Krookodile starting from level 40.

Shiny Krokorok.Name: Shiny Krokorok
Shiny Krokorok.Description: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.
Shiny Krokorok.Evolution: Krokorok evolves from Sandile starting from level 29 and evolves to Krookodile starting from level 40.

Shiny Krookodile.Name: Shiny Krookodile
Shiny Krookodile.Description: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
Shiny Krookodile.Evolution: Krookodile evolves from Krokorok starting from level 40, which evolves from Sandile starting from level 29.

Shiny Darumaka.Name: Shiny Darumaka
Shiny Darumaka.Description: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it’s pushed or pulled.
Shiny Darumaka.Evolution: Darumaka evolves to Darmanitan starting from level 35.

Shiny Darmanitan.Name: Shiny Darmanitan
Shiny Darmanitan.Description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
Shiny Darmanitan.Evolution: Darmanitan evolves from Darumaka starting from level 35.

Shiny Maractus.Name: Shiny Maractus
Shiny Maractus.Description: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

Shiny Dwebble.Name: Shiny Dwebble
Shiny Dwebble.Description: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.
Shiny Dwebble.Evolution: Dwebble evolves to Crustle starting from level 34.

Shiny Crustle.Name: Shiny Crustle
Shiny Crustle.Description: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.
Shiny Crustle.Evolution: Crustle evolves from Dwebble starting from level 34.

Shiny Scraggy.Name: Shiny Scraggy
Shiny Scraggy.Description: It protects itself with its durable skin. It’s thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.
Shiny Scraggy.Evolution: Scraggy evolves to Scrafty starting from level 39.

Shiny Scrafty.Name: Shiny Scrafty
Shiny Scrafty.Description: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.
Shiny Scrafty.Evolution: Scrafty evolves from Scraggy starting from level 39.

Shiny Sigilyph.Name: Shiny Sigilyph
Shiny Sigilyph.Description: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

Shiny Yamask.Name: Shiny Yamask
Shiny Yamask.Description: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.
Shiny Yamask.Evolution: Yamask evolves to Cofagrigus starting from level 34.

Shiny Cofagrigus.Name: Shiny Cofagrigus
Shiny Cofagrigus.Description: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They’re symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.
Shiny Cofagrigus.Evolution: Cofagrigus evolves from Yamask starting from level 34.

Shiny Tirtouga.Name: Shiny Tirtouga
Shiny Tirtouga.Description: Tirtouga is considered to be the ancestor of many turtle Pokémon. It was restored to life from a fossil.
Shiny Tirtouga.Evolution: Tirtouga evolves to Carracosta starting from level 37.

Shiny Carracosta.Name: Shiny Carracosta
Shiny Carracosta.Description: This Pokémon emerges from the water in search of prey despite the fact that it moves more slowly on land.
Shiny Carracosta.Evolution: Carracosta evolves from Tirtouga starting from level 37.

Shiny Archen.Name: Shiny Archen
Shiny Archen.Description: Archen is said to be the ancestor of bird Pokémon. It lived in treetops, eating berries and bug Pokémon.
Shiny Archen.Evolution: Archen evolves to Archeops starting from level 37.

Shiny Archeops.Name: Shiny Archeops
Shiny Archeops.Description: Though capable of flight, Archeops was apparently better at hunting on the ground.
Shiny Archeops.Evolution: Archeops evolves from Archen starting from level 37.

Shiny Trubbish.Name: Shiny Trubbish
Shiny Trubbish.Description: This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.
Shiny Trubbish.Evolution: Trubbish evolves to Garbodor starting from level 36.

Shiny Garbodor.Name: Shiny Garbodor
Shiny Garbodor.Description: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
Shiny Garbodor.Evolution: Garbodor evolves from Trubbish starting from level 36.

Shiny Zorua.Name: Shiny Zorua
Shiny Zorua.Description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
Shiny Zorua.Evolution: Zorua evolves to Zoroark starting from level 30.

Shiny Zoroark.Name: Shiny Zoroark
Shiny Zoroark.Description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
Shiny Zoroark.Evolution: Zoroark evolves from Zorua starting from level 30.

Shiny Minccino.Name: Shiny Minccino
Shiny Minccino.Description: They pet each other with their tails as a form of greeting. Of the two, the one whose tail is fluffier is a bit more boastful.
Shiny Minccino.Evolution: Minccino evolves to Cinccino using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Cinccino.Name: Shiny Cinccino
Shiny Cinccino.Description: A special oil that seeps through their fur helps them avoid attacks. The oil fetches a high price at market.
Shiny Cinccino.Evolution: Cinccino evolves from Minccino using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Gothita.Name: Shiny Gothita
Shiny Gothita.Description: Beware of touching the ribbon-shaped feelers that control its psychic power. Gothita will begin bawling if you do.
Shiny Gothita.Evolution: Gothita evolves to Gothorita starting from level 32, which evolves to Gothitelle starting from level 41.

Shiny Gothorita.Name: Shiny Gothorita
Shiny Gothorita.Description: Using its psychic power, it arranges pebbles to form the shapes of constellations. Some people believe this Pokémon came from outer space.
Shiny Gothorita.Evolution: Gothorita evolves from Gothita starting from level 32 and evolves to Gothitelle starting from level 41.

Shiny Gothitelle.Name: Shiny Gothitelle
Shiny Gothitelle.Description: It gazes at the stars to predict the future. It acts somewhat detached because it has seen the end of all existence.
Shiny Gothitelle.Evolution: Gothitelle evolves from Gothorita starting from level 41, which evolves from Gothita starting from level 32.

Shiny Solosis.Name: Shiny Solosis
Shiny Solosis.Description: Many say that the special liquid covering this Pokémon’s body would allow it to survive in the vacuum of space.
Shiny Solosis.Evolution: Solosis evolves to Duosion starting from level 32, which evolves to Reuniclus starting from level 41.

Shiny Duosion.Name: Shiny Duosion
Shiny Duosion.Description: Its brain has split into two, and the two halves rarely think alike. Its actions are utterly unpredictable.
Shiny Duosion.Evolution: Duosion evolves from Solosis starting from level 32 and evolves to Reuniclus starting from level 41.

Shiny Reuniclus.Name: Shiny Reuniclus
Shiny Reuniclus.Description: It’s said that drinking the liquid surrounding Reuniclus grants wisdom. Problem is, the liquid is highly toxic to anything besides Reuniclus itself.
Shiny Reuniclus.Evolution: Reuniclus evolves from Duosion starting from level 41, which evolves from Solosis starting from level 32.

Shiny Ducklett.Name: Shiny Ducklett
Shiny Ducklett.Description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.
Shiny Ducklett.Evolution: Ducklett evolves to Swanna starting from level 35.

Shiny Swanna.Name: Shiny Swanna
Shiny Swanna.Description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
Shiny Swanna.Evolution: Swanna evolves from Ducklett starting from level 35.

Shiny Vanillite.Name: Shiny Vanillite
Shiny Vanillite.Description: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.
Shiny Vanillite.Evolution: Vanillite evolves to Vanillish starting from level 35, which evolves to Vanilluxe starting from level 47.

Shiny Vanillish.Name: Shiny Vanillish
Shiny Vanillish.Description: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it’s a kind Pokémon.
Shiny Vanillish.Evolution: Vanillish evolves from Vanillite starting from level 35 and evolves to Vanilluxe starting from level 47.

Shiny Vanilluxe.Name: Shiny Vanilluxe
Shiny Vanilluxe.Description: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.
Shiny Vanilluxe.Evolution: Vanilluxe evolves from Vanillish starting from level 47, which evolves from Vanillite starting from level 35.

Shiny Deerling.Name: Shiny Deerling
Shiny Deerling.Description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon’s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.
Shiny Deerling.Evolution: Deerling evolves to Sawsbuck starting from level 34.

Shiny Sawsbuck.Name: Shiny Sawsbuck
Shiny Sawsbuck.Description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.
Shiny Sawsbuck.Evolution: Sawsbuck evolves from Deerling starting from level 34.

Shiny Emolga.Name: Shiny Emolga
Shiny Emolga.Description: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can’t fly properly.

Shiny Karrablast.Name: Shiny Karrablast
Shiny Karrablast.Description: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet’s shell. Karrablast doesn’t eat the shell— it eats only the contents.
Shiny Karrablast.Evolution: Karrablast evolves to Escavalier when traded.

Shiny Escavalier.Name: Shiny Escavalier
Shiny Escavalier.Description: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch’d.
Shiny Escavalier.Evolution: Escavalier evolves from Karrablast when traded.

Shiny Foongus.Name: Shiny Foongus
Shiny Foongus.Description: This Pokémon prefers damp places. It spurts out poison spores to repel approaching enemies.
Shiny Foongus.Evolution: Foongus evolves to Amoonguss starting from level 39.

Shiny Amoonguss.Name: Shiny Amoonguss
Shiny Amoonguss.Description: Amoonguss mimics Poké Balls. It is not yet clear whether this mimicry is effective against other Pokémon.
Shiny Amoonguss.Evolution: Amoonguss evolves from Foongus starting from level 39.

Shiny Frillish.Name: Shiny Frillish
Shiny Frillish.Description: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.
Shiny Frillish.Evolution: Frillish evolves to Jellicent starting from level 40.

Shiny Jellicent.Name: Shiny Jellicent
Shiny Jellicent.Description: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It’s rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.
Shiny Jellicent.Evolution: Jellicent evolves from Frillish starting from level 40.

Shiny Alomomola.Name: Shiny Alomomola
Shiny Alomomola.Description: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

Shiny Joltik.Name: Shiny Joltik
Shiny Joltik.Description: Joltik latch on to other Pokémon and suck out static electricity. They’re often found sticking to Yamper’s hindquarters.
Shiny Joltik.Evolution: Joltik evolves to Galvantula starting from level 36.

Shiny Galvantula.Name: Shiny Galvantula
Shiny Galvantula.Description: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokémon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.
Shiny Galvantula.Evolution: Galvantula evolves from Joltik starting from level 36.

Shiny Ferroseed.Name: Shiny Ferroseed
Shiny Ferroseed.Description: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed’s spikes grow big and strong.
Shiny Ferroseed.Evolution: Ferroseed evolves to Ferrothorn starting from level 40.

Shiny Ferrothorn.Name: Shiny Ferrothorn
Shiny Ferrothorn.Description: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.
Shiny Ferrothorn.Evolution: Ferrothorn evolves from Ferroseed starting from level 40.

Shiny Klink.Name: Shiny Klink
Shiny Klink.Description: It’s suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people’s invention of the first gears.
Shiny Klink.Evolution: Klink evolves to Klang starting from level 38, which evolves to Klinklang starting from level 49.

Shiny Klang.Name: Shiny Klang
Shiny Klang.Description: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokémon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.
Shiny Klang.Evolution: Klang evolves from Klink starting from level 38 and evolves to Klinklang starting from level 49.

Shiny Klinklang.Name: Shiny Klinklang
Shiny Klinklang.Description: The three gears that compose this Pokémon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn’t a living creature.
Shiny Klinklang.Evolution: Klinklang evolves from Klang starting from level 49, which evolves from Klink starting from level 38.

Shiny Tynamo.Name: Shiny Tynamo
Shiny Tynamo.Description: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.
Shiny Tynamo.Evolution: Tynamo evolves to Eelektrik starting from level 39, which evolves to Eelektross using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Eelektrik.Name: Shiny Eelektrik
Shiny Eelektrik.Description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
Shiny Eelektrik.Evolution: Eelektrik evolves from Tynamo starting from level 39 and evolves to Eelektross using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Eelektross.Name: Shiny Eelektross
Shiny Eelektross.Description: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.
Shiny Eelektross.Evolution: Eelektross evolves from Eelektrik using a Thunder Stone, which evolves from Tynamo starting from level 39.

Shiny Elgyem.Name: Shiny Elgyem
Shiny Elgyem.Description: This Pokémon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.
Shiny Elgyem.Evolution: Elgyem evolves to Beheeyem starting from level 42.

Shiny Beheeyem.Name: Shiny Beheeyem
Shiny Beheeyem.Description: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.
Shiny Beheeyem.Evolution: Beheeyem evolves from Elgyem starting from level 42.

Shiny Litwick.Name: Shiny Litwick
Shiny Litwick.Description: The younger the life this Pokémon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.
Shiny Litwick.Evolution: Litwick evolves to Lampent starting from level 41, which evolves to Chandelure using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Lampent.Name: Shiny Lampent
Shiny Lampent.Description: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.
Shiny Lampent.Evolution: Lampent evolves from Litwick starting from level 41 and evolves to Chandelure using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Chandelure.Name: Shiny Chandelure
Shiny Chandelure.Description: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence— or so it’s said.
Shiny Chandelure.Evolution: Chandelure evolves from Lampent using a Dusk Stone, which evolves from Litwick starting from level 41.

Shiny Axew.Name: Shiny Axew
Shiny Axew.Description: If you see peculiar teeth marks on boulders or trees, it means an Axew is likely living nearby.
Shiny Axew.Evolution: Axew evolves to Fraxure starting from level 38, which evolves to Haxorus starting from level 48.

Shiny Fraxure.Name: Shiny Fraxure
Shiny Fraxure.Description: Fraxure uses its thick tusks to neatly cut prey into two portions—one to eat now and one to save for later.
Shiny Fraxure.Evolution: Fraxure evolves from Axew starting from level 38 and evolves to Haxorus starting from level 48.

Shiny Haxorus.Name: Shiny Haxorus
Shiny Haxorus.Description: It overwhelms enemies with its prized tusks, which are sharp enough to cut through a metal transmission tower in one strike.
Shiny Haxorus.Evolution: Haxorus evolves from Fraxure starting from level 48, which evolves from Axew starting from level 38.

Shiny Cubchoo.Name: Shiny Cubchoo
Shiny Cubchoo.Description: When Cubchoo starts sneezing, watch out! If it spatters you with its frosty snot, you’ll get frostbite.
Shiny Cubchoo.Evolution: Cubchoo evolves to Beartic starting from level 37.

Shiny Beartic.Name: Shiny Beartic
Shiny Beartic.Description: Feared as the Snow-White Demon in northern lands, Beartic uses its frosty claws and fangs to attack prey.
Shiny Beartic.Evolution: Beartic evolves from Cubchoo starting from level 37.

Shiny Cryogonal.Name: Shiny Cryogonal
Shiny Cryogonal.Description: Cryogonal uses its chains of ice to constrict its opponents and then flash-freezes them where they stand.

Shiny Shelmet.Name: Shiny Shelmet
Shiny Shelmet.Description: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.
Shiny Shelmet.Evolution: Shelmet evolves to Accelgor when traded.

Shiny Accelgor.Name: Shiny Accelgor
Shiny Accelgor.Description: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.
Shiny Accelgor.Evolution: Accelgor evolves from Shelmet when traded.

Shiny Stunfisk.Name: Shiny Stunfisk
Shiny Stunfisk.Description: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

Shiny Mienfoo.Name: Shiny Mienfoo
Shiny Mienfoo.Description: Though small, Mienfoo’s temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.
Shiny Mienfoo.Evolution: Mienfoo evolves to Mienshao starting from level 50.

Shiny Mienshao.Name: Shiny Mienshao
Shiny Mienshao.Description: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokémon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.
Shiny Mienshao.Evolution: Mienshao evolves from Mienfoo starting from level 50.

Shiny Druddigon.Name: Shiny Druddigon
Shiny Druddigon.Description: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

Shiny Golett.Name: Shiny Golett
Shiny Golett.Description: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.
Shiny Golett.Evolution: Golett evolves to Golurk starting from level 43.

Shiny Golurk.Name: Shiny Golurk
Shiny Golurk.Description: There’s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn’t been proven.
Shiny Golurk.Evolution: Golurk evolves from Golett starting from level 43.

Shiny Pawniard.Name: Shiny Pawniard
Shiny Pawniard.Description: Any chips in its blades would prove fatal for it. After each battle, it diligently maintains its blades using its favorite sharpening stone.
Shiny Pawniard.Evolution: Pawniard evolves to Bisharp starting from level 52.

Shiny Bisharp.Name: Shiny Bisharp
Shiny Bisharp.Description: Bisharp mercilessly cuts its opponents to pieces with the sharp blades covering its body. It will do anything to win.
Shiny Bisharp.Evolution: Bisharp evolves from Pawniard starting from level 52.

Shiny Bouffalant.Name: Shiny Bouffalant
Shiny Bouffalant.Description: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

Shiny Rufflet.Name: Shiny Rufflet
Shiny Rufflet.Description: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.
Shiny Rufflet.Evolution: Rufflet evolves to Braviary starting from level 54.

Shiny Braviary.Name: Shiny Braviary
Shiny Braviary.Description: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
Shiny Braviary.Evolution: Braviary evolves from Rufflet starting from level 54.

Shiny Vullaby.Name: Shiny Vullaby
Shiny Vullaby.Description: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.
Shiny Vullaby.Evolution: Vullaby evolves to Mandibuzz starting from level 54.

Shiny Mandibuzz.Name: Shiny Mandibuzz
Shiny Mandibuzz.Description: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.
Shiny Mandibuzz.Evolution: Mandibuzz evolves from Vullaby starting from level 54.

Shiny Heatmor.Name: Shiny Heatmor
Shiny Heatmor.Description: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

Shiny Durant.Name: Shiny Durant
Shiny Durant.Description: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

Shiny Deino.Name: Shiny Deino
Shiny Deino.Description: It nests deep inside a cave. Food there is scarce, so Deino will sink its teeth into anything that moves and attempt to eat it.
Shiny Deino.Evolution: Deino evolves to Zweilous starting from level 50, which evolves to Hydreigon starting from level 64.

Shiny Zweilous.Name: Shiny Zweilous
Shiny Zweilous.Description: The two heads have different likes and dislikes. Because the heads fight with each other, Zweilous gets stronger without needing to rely on others.
Shiny Zweilous.Evolution: Zweilous evolves from Deino starting from level 50 and evolves to Hydreigon starting from level 64.

Shiny Hydreigon.Name: Shiny Hydreigon
Shiny Hydreigon.Description: It’s said that Hydreigon grew ferocious because people in times long past loathed it, considering it to be evil incarnate and attacking it relentlessly.
Shiny Hydreigon.Evolution: Hydreigon evolves from Zweilous starting from level 64, which evolves from Deino starting from level 50.

Shiny Larvesta.Name: Shiny Larvesta
Shiny Larvesta.Description: In ancient times, Larvesta was worshiped as the emissary of the sun. However, it was also viewed as a burden since it often caused forest fires.
Shiny Larvesta.Evolution: Larvesta evolves to Volcarona starting from level 59.

Shiny Volcarona.Name: Shiny Volcarona
Shiny Volcarona.Description: This Pokémon scatters burning scales. Most of the danger of these scales is not in their heat—it’s in the way they rob the surrounding air of oxygen.
Shiny Volcarona.Evolution: Volcarona evolves from Larvesta starting from level 59.

Shiny Cobalion.Name: Shiny Cobalion
Shiny Cobalion.Description: From the moment it’s born, this Pokémon radiates the air of a leader. Its presence will calm even vicious foes.

Shiny Terrakion.Name: Shiny Terrakion
Shiny Terrakion.Description: In Unovan legend, Terrakion battled against humans in an effort to protect other Pokémon.

Shiny Virizion.Name: Shiny Virizion
Shiny Virizion.Description: It darts around opponents with a flurry of quick movements, slicing them up with its horns.

Shiny Tornadus.Name: Shiny Tornadus
Shiny Tornadus.Description: This storm-stirring Pokémon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.

Shiny Thundurus.Name: Shiny Thundurus
Shiny Thundurus.Description: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.

Shiny Reshiram.Name: Shiny Reshiram
Shiny Reshiram.Description: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

Shiny Zekrom.Name: Shiny Zekrom
Shiny Zekrom.Description: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom’s lightning.

Shiny Landorus.Name: Shiny Landorus
Shiny Landorus.Description: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

Shiny Kyurem.Name: Shiny Kyurem
Shiny Kyurem.Description: It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.

Shiny Keldeo.Name: Shiny Keldeo
Shiny Keldeo.Description: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

Shiny Meloetta.Name: Shiny Meloetta
Shiny Meloetta.Description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Shiny Genesect.Name: Shiny Genesect
Shiny Genesect.Description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

Shiny Chespin.Name: Shiny Chespin
Shiny Chespin.Description: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn’t faze it.
Shiny Chespin.Evolution: Chespin evolves to Quilladin starting from level 16, which evolves to Chesnaught starting from level 36.

Shiny Quilladin.Name: Shiny Quilladin
Shiny Quilladin.Description: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won’t start fights.
Shiny Quilladin.Evolution: Quilladin evolves from Chespin starting from level 16 and evolves to Chesnaught starting from level 36.

Shiny Chesnaught.Name: Shiny Chesnaught
Shiny Chesnaught.Description: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.
Shiny Chesnaught.Evolution: Chesnaught evolves from Quilladin starting from level 36, which evolves from Chespin starting from level 16.

Shiny Fennekin.Name: Shiny Fennekin
Shiny Fennekin.Description: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
Shiny Fennekin.Evolution: Fennekin evolves to Braixen starting from level 16, which evolves to Delphox starting from level 36.

Shiny Braixen.Name: Shiny Braixen
Shiny Braixen.Description: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
Shiny Braixen.Evolution: Braixen evolves from Fennekin starting from level 16 and evolves to Delphox starting from level 36.

Shiny Delphox.Name: Shiny Delphox
Shiny Delphox.Description: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
Shiny Delphox.Evolution: Delphox evolves from Braixen starting from level 36, which evolves from Fennekin starting from level 16.

Shiny Froakie.Name: Shiny Froakie
Shiny Froakie.Description: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
Shiny Froakie.Evolution: Froakie evolves to Frogadier starting from level 16, which evolves to Greninja starting from level 36.

Shiny Frogadier.Name: Shiny Frogadier
Shiny Frogadier.Description: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.
Shiny Frogadier.Evolution: Frogadier evolves from Froakie starting from level 16 and evolves to Greninja starting from level 36.

Shiny Greninja.Name: Shiny Greninja
Shiny Greninja.Description: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
Shiny Greninja.Evolution: Greninja evolves from Frogadier starting from level 36, which evolves from Froakie starting from level 16.

Shiny Bunnelby.Name: Shiny Bunnelby
Shiny Bunnelby.Description: It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.
Shiny Bunnelby.Evolution: Bunnelby evolves to Diggersby starting from level 20.

Shiny Diggersby.Name: Shiny Diggersby
Shiny Diggersby.Description: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.
Shiny Diggersby.Evolution: Diggersby evolves from Bunnelby starting from level 20.

Shiny Fletchling.Name: Shiny Fletchling
Shiny Fletchling.Description: Fletchling can be found in both rural and urban areas. They once had a huge territorial dispute with Squawkabilly. Fights broke out all over town.
Shiny Fletchling.Evolution: Fletchling evolves to Fletchinder starting from level 17, which evolves to Talonflame starting from level 35.

Shiny Fletchinder.Name: Shiny Fletchinder
Shiny Fletchinder.Description: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.
Shiny Fletchinder.Evolution: Fletchinder evolves from Fletchling starting from level 17 and evolves to Talonflame starting from level 35.

Shiny Talonflame.Name: Shiny Talonflame
Shiny Talonflame.Description: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.
Shiny Talonflame.Evolution: Talonflame evolves from Fletchinder starting from level 35, which evolves from Fletchling starting from level 17.

Shiny Scatterbug.Name: Shiny Scatterbug
Shiny Scatterbug.Description: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.
Shiny Scatterbug.Evolution: Scatterbug evolves to Spewpa starting from level 9, which evolves to Vivillon starting from level 12.

Shiny Spewpa.Name: Shiny Spewpa
Shiny Spewpa.Description: Spewpa doesn’t live in a fixed location. It roams where it pleases across the fields and mountains, building up the energy it needs to evolve.
Shiny Spewpa.Evolution: Spewpa evolves from Scatterbug starting from level 9 and evolves to Vivillon starting from level 12.

Shiny Vivillon.Name: Shiny Vivillon
Shiny Vivillon.Description: The patterns on this Pokémon’s wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.
Shiny Vivillon.Evolution: Vivillon evolves from Spewpa starting from level 12, which evolves from Scatterbug starting from level 9.

Shiny Litleo.Name: Shiny Litleo
Shiny Litleo.Description: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.
Shiny Litleo.Evolution: Litleo evolves to Pyroar starting from level 35.

Shiny Pyroar.Name: Shiny Pyroar
Shiny Pyroar.Description: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.
Shiny Pyroar.Evolution: Pyroar evolves from Litleo starting from level 35.

Shiny Flab\u00e9b\u00e9.Name: Shiny Flabébé
Shiny Flab\u00e9b\u00e9.Description: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’s collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.
Shiny Flab\u00e9b\u00e9.Evolution: Flabébé evolves to Floette starting from level 19, which evolves to Florges using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Floette.Name: Shiny Floette
Shiny Floette.Description: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.
Shiny Floette.Evolution: Floette evolves from Flabébé starting from level 19 and evolves to Florges using a Shiny Stone.

Shiny Florges.Name: Shiny Florges
Shiny Florges.Description: Its life can span several hundred years. It’s said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.
Shiny Florges.Evolution: Florges evolves from Floette using a Shiny Stone, which evolves from Flabébé starting from level 19.

Shiny Skiddo.Name: Shiny Skiddo
Shiny Skiddo.Description: As long as it has sunlight and water, Skiddo can make energy with the leaves on its body, allowing it to live on rocky mountains barren of food.
Shiny Skiddo.Evolution: Skiddo evolves to Gogoat starting from level 32.

Shiny Gogoat.Name: Shiny Gogoat
Shiny Gogoat.Description: These Pokémon live in herds in mountainous places. The victor in their contests of clashing horns will become the leader of the herd.
Shiny Gogoat.Evolution: Gogoat evolves from Skiddo starting from level 32.

Shiny Pancham.Name: Shiny Pancham
Shiny Pancham.Description: Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.
Shiny Pancham.Evolution: Pancham evolves to Pangoro starting from level 32.

Shiny Pangoro.Name: Shiny Pangoro
Shiny Pangoro.Description: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.
Shiny Pangoro.Evolution: Pangoro evolves from Pancham starting from level 32.

Shiny Furfrou.Name: Shiny Furfrou
Shiny Furfrou.Description: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

Shiny Espurr.Name: Shiny Espurr
Shiny Espurr.Description: There’s enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can’t be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.
Shiny Espurr.Evolution: Espurr evolves to Meowstic starting from level 25.

Shiny Meowstic.Name: Shiny Meowstic
Shiny Meowstic.Description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
Shiny Meowstic.Evolution: Meowstic evolves from Espurr starting from level 25.

Shiny Honedge.Name: Shiny Honedge
Shiny Honedge.Description: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.
Shiny Honedge.Evolution: Honedge evolves to Doublade starting from level 35, which evolves to Aegislash using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Doublade.Name: Shiny Doublade
Shiny Doublade.Description: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.
Shiny Doublade.Evolution: Doublade evolves from Honedge starting from level 35 and evolves to Aegislash using a Dusk Stone.

Shiny Aegislash.Name: Shiny Aegislash
Shiny Aegislash.Description: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
Shiny Aegislash.Evolution: Aegislash evolves from Doublade using a Dusk Stone, which evolves from Honedge starting from level 35.

Shiny Spritzee.Name: Shiny Spritzee
Shiny Spritzee.Description: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.
Shiny Spritzee.Evolution: Spritzee evolves to Aromatisse when traded while holding a Sachet.

Shiny Aromatisse.Name: Shiny Aromatisse
Shiny Aromatisse.Description: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent’s will to fight.
Shiny Aromatisse.Evolution: Aromatisse evolves from Spritzee when traded while holding a Sachet.

Shiny Swirlix.Name: Shiny Swirlix
Shiny Swirlix.Description: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix’s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.
Shiny Swirlix.Evolution: Swirlix evolves to Slurpuff when traded while holding a Whipped Dream.

Shiny Slurpuff.Name: Shiny Slurpuff
Shiny Slurpuff.Description: Slurpuff’s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.
Shiny Slurpuff.Evolution: Slurpuff evolves from Swirlix when traded while holding a Whipped Dream.

Shiny Inkay.Name: Shiny Inkay
Shiny Inkay.Description: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.
Shiny Inkay.Evolution: Inkay evolves to Malamar starting from level 30.

Shiny Malamar.Name: Shiny Malamar
Shiny Malamar.Description: It’s said that Malamar’s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.
Shiny Malamar.Evolution: Malamar evolves from Inkay starting from level 30.

Shiny Binacle.Name: Shiny Binacle
Shiny Binacle.Description: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.
Shiny Binacle.Evolution: Binacle evolves to Barbaracle starting from level 39.

Shiny Barbaracle.Name: Shiny Barbaracle
Shiny Barbaracle.Description: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.
Shiny Barbaracle.Evolution: Barbaracle evolves from Binacle starting from level 39.

Shiny Skrelp.Name: Shiny Skrelp
Shiny Skrelp.Description: This Pokémon is a poor swimmer. If it’s caught in a fierce storm, it will sometimes get washed far away and become unable to return to its home.
Shiny Skrelp.Evolution: Skrelp evolves to Dragalge starting from level 48.

Shiny Dragalge.Name: Shiny Dragalge
Shiny Dragalge.Description: Since Finizen is the better swimmer, Dragalge will approach it under the cover of seaweed, then immobilize it with a poisonous attack.
Shiny Dragalge.Evolution: Dragalge evolves from Skrelp starting from level 48.

Shiny Clauncher.Name: Shiny Clauncher
Shiny Clauncher.Description: Clauncher’s claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn’t appeal to all tastes.
Shiny Clauncher.Evolution: Clauncher evolves to Clawitzer starting from level 37.

Shiny Clawitzer.Name: Shiny Clawitzer
Shiny Clawitzer.Description: The cannonballs of seawater that Clawitzer launches from its claw are powerful enough to punch through tanker hulls.
Shiny Clawitzer.Evolution: Clawitzer evolves from Clauncher starting from level 37.

Shiny Helioptile.Name: Shiny Helioptile
Shiny Helioptile.Description: The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.
Shiny Helioptile.Evolution: Helioptile evolves to Heliolisk using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Heliolisk.Name: Shiny Heliolisk
Shiny Heliolisk.Description: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.
Shiny Heliolisk.Evolution: Heliolisk evolves from Helioptile using a Sun Stone.

Shiny Amaura.Name: Shiny Amaura
Shiny Amaura.Description: Amaura is an ancient Pokémon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.
Shiny Amaura.Evolution: Amaura evolves to Aurorus starting from level 39 in the nighttime.

Shiny Aurorus.Name: Shiny Aurorus
Shiny Aurorus.Description: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.
Shiny Aurorus.Evolution: Aurorus evolves from Amaura starting from level 39 in the nighttime.

Shiny Sylveon.Name: Shiny Sylveon
Shiny Sylveon.Description: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.
Shiny Sylveon.Evolution: Sylveon evolves from Eevee when leveled up while knowing a Fairy-type move.

Shiny Hawlucha.Name: Shiny Hawlucha
Shiny Hawlucha.Description: Hawlucha live quietly without flocking together. They fight constantly with their natural enemies: noisy groups of Primeape.

Shiny Dedenne.Name: Shiny Dedenne
Shiny Dedenne.Description: Dedenne emit electrical waves from the whiskers on their cheeks to communicate with each other. When low on electricity, they curl up and sleep.

Shiny Carbink.Name: Shiny Carbink
Shiny Carbink.Description: It’s said that somewhere in the world, there’s a mineral vein housing a large pack of slumbering Carbink. It’s also said that this pack has a queen.

Shiny Goomy.Name: Shiny Goomy
Shiny Goomy.Description: Goomy’s horns are excellent sensory organs that cover all five of Goomy’s senses. Goomy picks up on danger from the movement of the air.
Shiny Goomy.Evolution: Goomy evolves to Sliggoo starting from level 40, which evolves to Goodra starting from level 50.

Shiny Sliggoo.Name: Shiny Sliggoo
Shiny Sliggoo.Description: When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated—it’ll dissolve anything.
Shiny Sliggoo.Evolution: Sliggoo evolves from Goomy starting from level 40 and evolves to Goodra starting from level 50.

Shiny Goodra.Name: Shiny Goodra
Shiny Goodra.Description: This Pokémon is uncontrollable when enraged. It rampages on and on, lashing its tail with enough power to send a dump truck flying.
Shiny Goodra.Evolution: Goodra evolves from Sliggoo starting from level 50, which evolves from Goomy starting from level 40.

Shiny Klefki.Name: Shiny Klefki
Shiny Klefki.Description: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.

Shiny Phantump.Name: Shiny Phantump
Shiny Phantump.Description: With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.
Shiny Phantump.Evolution: Phantump evolves to Trevenant when traded.

Shiny Trevenant.Name: Shiny Trevenant
Shiny Trevenant.Description: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.
Shiny Trevenant.Evolution: Trevenant evolves from Phantump when traded.

Shiny Pumpkaboo.Name: Shiny Pumpkaboo
Shiny Pumpkaboo.Description: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.
Shiny Pumpkaboo.Evolution: Pumpkaboo evolves to Gourgeist when traded.

Shiny Gourgeist.Name: Shiny Gourgeist
Shiny Gourgeist.Description: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.
Shiny Gourgeist.Evolution: Gourgeist evolves from Pumpkaboo when traded.

Shiny Bergmite.Name: Shiny Bergmite
Shiny Bergmite.Description: Bergmite protects itself by coating its body in ice formed by frigid air of −148 degrees Fahrenheit. It fights with Frigibax whenever they meet.
Shiny Bergmite.Evolution: Bergmite evolves to Avalugg starting from level 37.

Shiny Avalugg.Name: Shiny Avalugg
Shiny Avalugg.Description: This Pokémon uses its massive icy body to flatten anything that gets in its way. When it’s floating out on the ocean, it looks exactly like drift ice.
Shiny Avalugg.Evolution: Avalugg evolves from Bergmite starting from level 37.

Shiny Noibat.Name: Shiny Noibat
Shiny Noibat.Description: Noibat can change the frequency of its sound waves at will, and it generates ultrasonic waves of up to 200,000 hertz.
Shiny Noibat.Evolution: Noibat evolves to Noivern starting from level 48.

Shiny Noivern.Name: Shiny Noivern
Shiny Noivern.Description: In the dark, even Hydreigon are terrified of this Pokémon. But in the light, Noivern is the one that avoids battle.
Shiny Noivern.Evolution: Noivern evolves from Noibat starting from level 48.

Shiny Xerneas.Name: Shiny Xerneas
Shiny Xerneas.Description: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

Shiny Yveltal.Name: Shiny Yveltal
Shiny Yveltal.Description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

Shiny Zygarde.Name: Shiny Zygarde
Shiny Zygarde.Description: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

Shiny Diancie.Name: Shiny Diancie
Shiny Diancie.Description: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

Shiny Hoopa.Name: Shiny Hoopa
Shiny Hoopa.Description: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

Shiny Volcanion.Name: Shiny Volcanion
Shiny Volcanion.Description: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

Shiny Rowlet.Name: Shiny Rowlet
Shiny Rowlet.Description: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.
Shiny Rowlet.Evolution: Rowlet evolves to Dartrix starting from level 17, which evolves to Decidueye starting from level 34.

Shiny Dartrix.Name: Shiny Dartrix
Shiny Dartrix.Description: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power—presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.
Shiny Dartrix.Evolution: Dartrix evolves from Rowlet starting from level 17 and evolves to Decidueye starting from level 34.

Shiny Decidueye.Name: Shiny Decidueye
Shiny Decidueye.Description: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent’s weak point before they notice what’s happening.
Shiny Decidueye.Evolution: Decidueye evolves from Dartrix starting from level 34, which evolves from Rowlet starting from level 17.

Shiny Litten.Name: Shiny Litten
Shiny Litten.Description: Trying to pet Litten before it trusts you will result in a nasty scratch from its sharp claws. Be careful.
Shiny Litten.Evolution: Litten evolves to Torracat starting from level 17, which evolves to Incineroar starting from level 34.

Shiny Torracat.Name: Shiny Torracat
Shiny Torracat.Description: When facing a powerful enemy, Torracat’s fighting spirit gets pumped up, and its fire bell blazes hotter.
Shiny Torracat.Evolution: Torracat evolves from Litten starting from level 17 and evolves to Incineroar starting from level 34.

Shiny Incineroar.Name: Shiny Incineroar
Shiny Incineroar.Description: Incineroar’s rough and aggressive behavior is its most notable trait, but the way it helps out small Pokémon shows that it has a kind side as well.
Shiny Incineroar.Evolution: Incineroar evolves from Torracat starting from level 34, which evolves from Litten starting from level 17.

Shiny Popplio.Name: Shiny Popplio
Shiny Popplio.Description: If Popplio want to create big, powerful balloons, they must be persistent. It takes daily practice for these Pokémon to develop their skills.
Shiny Popplio.Evolution: Popplio evolves to Brionne starting from level 17, which evolves to Primarina starting from level 34.

Shiny Brionne.Name: Shiny Brionne
Shiny Brionne.Description: On nights when the sea is calm, Brionne dance with one another to the singing of the Primarina that’s leading them.
Shiny Brionne.Evolution: Brionne evolves from Popplio starting from level 17 and evolves to Primarina starting from level 34.

Shiny Primarina.Name: Shiny Primarina
Shiny Primarina.Description: For Primarina, every battle’s a stage. Its singing and the dancing of its balloons will mesmerize the audience.
Shiny Primarina.Evolution: Primarina evolves from Brionne starting from level 34, which evolves from Popplio starting from level 17.

Shiny Pikipek.Name: Shiny Pikipek
Shiny Pikipek.Description: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!
Shiny Pikipek.Evolution: Pikipek evolves to Trumbeak starting from level 14, which evolves to Toucannon starting from level 28.

Shiny Trumbeak.Name: Shiny Trumbeak
Shiny Trumbeak.Description: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.
Shiny Trumbeak.Evolution: Trumbeak evolves from Pikipek starting from level 14 and evolves to Toucannon starting from level 28.

Shiny Toucannon.Name: Shiny Toucannon
Shiny Toucannon.Description: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.
Shiny Toucannon.Evolution: Toucannon evolves from Trumbeak starting from level 28, which evolves from Pikipek starting from level 14.

Shiny Yungoos.Name: Shiny Yungoos
Shiny Yungoos.Description: It spends its waking hours searching endlessly for food. When Yungoos is hungry, its ferocity gains a certain edge.
Shiny Yungoos.Evolution: Yungoos evolves to Gumshoos starting from level 20 in the daytime.

Shiny Gumshoos.Name: Shiny Gumshoos
Shiny Gumshoos.Description: Gumshoos specializes in relentlessly tracking down prey. The simple-minded Skwovet doesn’t seem to provide Gumshoos enough challenge.
Shiny Gumshoos.Evolution: Gumshoos evolves from Yungoos starting from level 20 in the daytime.

Shiny Grubbin.Name: Shiny Grubbin
Shiny Grubbin.Description: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.
Shiny Grubbin.Evolution: Grubbin evolves to Charjabug starting from level 20, which evolves to Vikavolt when leveled up.

Shiny Charjabug.Name: Shiny Charjabug
Shiny Charjabug.Description: Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eats into electricity. An electric sac in its belly stores the electricity for later use.
Shiny Charjabug.Evolution: Charjabug evolves from Grubbin starting from level 20 and evolves to Vikavolt when leveled up.

Shiny Vikavolt.Name: Shiny Vikavolt
Shiny Vikavolt.Description: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.
Shiny Vikavolt.Evolution: Vikavolt evolves from Charjabug when leveled up, which evolves from Grubbin starting from level 20.

Shiny Crabrawler.Name: Shiny Crabrawler
Shiny Crabrawler.Description: If it loses its pincers, they’ll quickly regrow. The pincers are popular ingredients in paella since their shells produce a tasty soup stock.

Shiny Crabominable.Name: Shiny Crabominable
Shiny Crabominable.Description: Though its punches are powerful, this Pokémon’s movements are sluggish. It blows icy bubbles from its mouth to immobilize its opponents.

Shiny Oricorio.Name: Shiny Oricorio
Shiny Oricorio.Description: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

Shiny Sensu Oricorio.Name: Shiny Sensu Oricorio
Shiny Sensu Oricorio.Description: The elegant, attractive dance of these Oricorio is popular with adults, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.
Shiny Sensu Oricorio.Evolution: Sensu Oricorio transforms from Oricorio when given a Purple Nectar.

Shiny Pa'u Oricorio.Name: Shiny Pa'u Oricorio
Shiny Pa'u Oricorio.Description: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It gets so caught up in its dancing that it sometimes doesn’t hear its Trainer’s orders.
Shiny Pa'u Oricorio.Evolution: Pa'u Oricorio transforms from Oricorio when given a Pink Nectar.

Shiny Pom-pom Oricorio.Name: Shiny Pom-pom Oricorio
Shiny Pom-pom Oricorio.Description: The energetic, cheerful dance of these Oricorio is popular with children, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.
Shiny Pom-pom Oricorio.Evolution: Pom-pom Oricorio transforms from Oricorio when given a Yellow Nectar.

Shiny Cutiefly.Name: Shiny Cutiefly
Shiny Cutiefly.Description: An opponent’s aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent’s next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.
Shiny Cutiefly.Evolution: Cutiefly evolves to Ribombee starting from level 25.

Shiny Ribombee.Name: Shiny Ribombee
Shiny Ribombee.Description: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.
Shiny Ribombee.Evolution: Ribombee evolves from Cutiefly starting from level 25.

Shiny Rockruff.Name: Shiny Rockruff
Shiny Rockruff.Description: This Pokémon travels in a pack with others until it grows up. When its mood turns sour, it starts striking the ground with the rocks on its neck.
Shiny Rockruff.Evolution: Rockruff evolves to Lycanroc starting from level 25 in the nighttime.

Shiny Lycanroc.Name: Shiny Lycanroc
Shiny Lycanroc.Description: It has a calm and collected demeanor. It swiftly closes in on its prey, then slices them with the rocks in its mane.
Shiny Lycanroc.Evolution: Lycanroc evolves from Rockruff starting from level 25 in the nighttime.

Shiny Wishiwashi.Name: Shiny Wishiwashi
Shiny Wishiwashi.Description: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

Shiny Mareanie.Name: Shiny Mareanie
Shiny Mareanie.Description: It has excellent regenerative capabilities. Legs that a Mareanie has lost have a very bitter, astringent flavor—they’re not suitable as food.
Shiny Mareanie.Evolution: Mareanie evolves to Toxapex starting from level 38.

Shiny Toxapex.Name: Shiny Toxapex
Shiny Toxapex.Description: Toxapex gets into fierce battles with Bruxish over areas where warm ocean currents flow, but the odds are always against it.
Shiny Toxapex.Evolution: Toxapex evolves from Mareanie starting from level 38.

Shiny Mudbray.Name: Shiny Mudbray
Shiny Mudbray.Description: Though a slow walker, Mudbray is plenty strong. Its pace doesn’t change even when it’s loaded with 50 times its own body weight.
Shiny Mudbray.Evolution: Mudbray evolves to Mudsdale starting from level 30.

Shiny Mudsdale.Name: Shiny Mudsdale
Shiny Mudsdale.Description: Its legs are fortified with mud and harder than stone, and they can reduce a large truck to scrap with one kick.
Shiny Mudsdale.Evolution: Mudsdale evolves from Mudbray starting from level 30.

Shiny Dewpider.Name: Shiny Dewpider
Shiny Dewpider.Description: Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.
Shiny Dewpider.Evolution: Dewpider evolves to Araquanid starting from level 22.

Shiny Araquanid.Name: Shiny Araquanid
Shiny Araquanid.Description: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.
Shiny Araquanid.Evolution: Araquanid evolves from Dewpider starting from level 22.

Shiny Fomantis.Name: Shiny Fomantis
Shiny Fomantis.Description: Many Trainers give their Fomantis their own flowerpots so they can sunbathe in peace and quiet.
Shiny Fomantis.Evolution: Fomantis evolves to Lurantis starting from level 34 in the daytime.

Shiny Lurantis.Name: Shiny Lurantis
Shiny Lurantis.Description: A lot of time and effort is required to maintain the vivid colors of its petals. This Pokémon puts its Trainer’s attentiveness to the test.
Shiny Lurantis.Evolution: Lurantis evolves from Fomantis starting from level 34 in the daytime.

Shiny Morelull.Name: Shiny Morelull
Shiny Morelull.Description: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.
Shiny Morelull.Evolution: Morelull evolves to Shiinotic starting from level 24.

Shiny Shiinotic.Name: Shiny Shiinotic
Shiny Shiinotic.Description: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don’t go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.
Shiny Shiinotic.Evolution: Shiinotic evolves from Morelull starting from level 24.

Shiny Salandit.Name: Shiny Salandit
Shiny Salandit.Description: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.
Shiny Salandit.Evolution: Salandit evolves to Salazzle starting from level 33.

Shiny Salazzle.Name: Shiny Salazzle
Shiny Salazzle.Description: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.
Shiny Salazzle.Evolution: Salazzle evolves from Salandit starting from level 33.

Shiny Stufful.Name: Shiny Stufful
Shiny Stufful.Description: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.
Shiny Stufful.Evolution: Stufful evolves to Bewear starting from level 27.

Shiny Bewear.Name: Shiny Bewear
Shiny Bewear.Description: The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.
Shiny Bewear.Evolution: Bewear evolves from Stufful starting from level 27.

Shiny Bounsweet.Name: Shiny Bounsweet
Shiny Bounsweet.Description: A Greedent drawn in by the sweet scent of these Pokémon will tuck the Bounsweet in among the berries in its tail and carry them all away.
Shiny Bounsweet.Evolution: Bounsweet evolves to Steenee starting from level 18, which evolves to Tsareena when leveled up while knowing Stomp.

Shiny Steenee.Name: Shiny Steenee
Shiny Steenee.Description: Steenee bounces energetically through forests. If the rind that peels off its body is pulverized, it can be used to treat stomach pains.
Shiny Steenee.Evolution: Steenee evolves from Bounsweet starting from level 18 and evolves to Tsareena when leveled up while knowing Stomp.

Shiny Tsareena.Name: Shiny Tsareena
Shiny Tsareena.Description: This Pokémon launches fierce yet elegant kicks with its long, slender legs. It views Quaquaval as its rival.
Shiny Tsareena.Evolution: Tsareena evolves from Steenee when leveled up while knowing Stomp, which evolves from Bounsweet starting from level 18.

Shiny Comfey.Name: Shiny Comfey
Shiny Comfey.Description: These Pokémon smell very nice. All Comfey wear different flowers, so each of these Pokémon has its own individual scent.

Shiny Oranguru.Name: Shiny Oranguru
Shiny Oranguru.Description: This Pokémon lives quietly in the depths of the forest. The purple, cape-like fur gets longer and longer as Oranguru ages.

Shiny Passimian.Name: Shiny Passimian
Shiny Passimian.Description: The boss chooses 10 members of the group to go out hunting. The hunting party will evenly split the food they find with the rest of the group.

Shiny Wimpod.Name: Shiny Wimpod
Shiny Wimpod.Description: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy’s presence.
Shiny Wimpod.Evolution: Wimpod evolves to Golisopod starting from level 30.

Shiny Golisopod.Name: Shiny Golisopod
Shiny Golisopod.Description: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.
Shiny Golisopod.Evolution: Golisopod evolves from Wimpod starting from level 30.

Shiny Sandygast.Name: Shiny Sandygast
Shiny Sandygast.Description: It flings sand into the eyes of its prey and tries to close in on them while they’re blinded, but since Sandygast is so slow, the prey tends to escape.
Shiny Sandygast.Evolution: Sandygast evolves to Palossand starting from level 42.

Shiny Palossand.Name: Shiny Palossand
Shiny Palossand.Description: From the hollows in its arms, it fires the bones of its victims, which are all dried up after being drained of their vitality.
Shiny Palossand.Evolution: Palossand evolves from Sandygast starting from level 42.

Shiny Pyukumuku.Name: Shiny Pyukumuku
Shiny Pyukumuku.Description: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

Shiny Type: Null.Name: Shiny Type: Null
Shiny Type: Null.Description: It was modeled after a mighty Pokémon of myth. The mask placed upon it limits its power in order to keep it under control.
Shiny Type: Null.Evolution: Type: Null evolves to Silvally when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Silvally.Name: Shiny Silvally
Shiny Silvally.Description: The final factor needed to release this Pokémon’s true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.
Shiny Silvally.Evolution: Silvally evolves from Type: Null when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Minior.Name: Shiny Minior
Shiny Minior.Description: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

Shiny Komala.Name: Shiny Komala
Shiny Komala.Description: A potent anesthetic can be made by diluting Komala’s drool. This anesthetic was used for surgeries in the past.

Shiny Turtonator.Name: Shiny Turtonator
Shiny Turtonator.Description: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

Shiny Togedemaru.Name: Shiny Togedemaru
Shiny Togedemaru.Description: When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.

Shiny Mimikyu.Name: Shiny Mimikyu
Shiny Mimikyu.Description: Mimikyu was only recently identified as a Pokémon. Previously, people thought it was just a ghost wearing a cloth.

Shiny Bruxish.Name: Shiny Bruxish
Shiny Bruxish.Description: When sunlight reflects on the ripples created by a Bruxish grinding its teeth, the water all around sparkles brilliantly.

Shiny Drampa.Name: Shiny Drampa
Shiny Drampa.Description: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

Shiny Dhelmise.Name: Shiny Dhelmise
Shiny Dhelmise.Description: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.

Shiny Jangmo-o.Name: Shiny Jangmo-o
Shiny Jangmo-o.Description: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that’s become as hard as metal.
Shiny Jangmo-o.Evolution: Jangmo-o evolves to Hakamo-o starting from level 35, which evolves to Kommo-o starting from level 45.

Shiny Hakamo-o.Name: Shiny Hakamo-o
Shiny Hakamo-o.Description: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.
Shiny Hakamo-o.Evolution: Hakamo-o evolves from Jangmo-o starting from level 35 and evolves to Kommo-o starting from level 45.

Shiny Kommo-o.Name: Shiny Kommo-o
Shiny Kommo-o.Description: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.
Shiny Kommo-o.Evolution: Kommo-o evolves from Hakamo-o starting from level 45, which evolves from Jangmo-o starting from level 35.

Shiny Alolan Rattata.Name: Shiny Alolan Rattata
Shiny Alolan Rattata.Description: Its whiskers provide it with a keen sense of smell, enabling it to pick up the scent of hidden food and locate it instantly.
Shiny Alolan Rattata.Evolution: Alolan Rattata evolves to Alolan Raticate starting from level 20 in the nighttime.

Shiny Alolan Raticate.Name: Shiny Alolan Raticate
Shiny Alolan Raticate.Description: It makes its Rattata underlings gather food for it, dining solely on the most nutritious and delicious fare.
Shiny Alolan Raticate.Evolution: Alolan Raticate evolves from Alolan Rattata starting from level 20 in the nighttime.

Shiny Alolan Raichu.Name: Shiny Alolan Raichu
Shiny Alolan Raichu.Description: This Pokémon rides on its tail while it uses its psychic powers to levitate. It attacks with star-shaped thunderbolts.

Shiny Alolan Sandshrew.Name: Shiny Alolan Sandshrew
Shiny Alolan Sandshrew.Description: It lives in snowy mountains on southern islands. When a blizzard rolls in, this Pokémon hunkers down in the snow to avoid getting blown away.
Shiny Alolan Sandshrew.Evolution: Alolan Sandshrew evolves to Alolan Sandslash using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Alolan Sandslash.Name: Shiny Alolan Sandslash
Shiny Alolan Sandslash.Description: Many people climb snowy mountains, hoping to see the icy spikes of these Pokémon glistening in the light of dawn.
Shiny Alolan Sandslash.Evolution: Alolan Sandslash evolves from Alolan Sandshrew using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Alolan Vulpix.Name: Shiny Alolan Vulpix
Shiny Alolan Vulpix.Description: These Pokémon live in packs in the snowy mountains and defend themselves with icy breath. I suspect this species changed its form to adapt to the frigid climate.
Shiny Alolan Vulpix.Evolution: Alolan Vulpix evolves to Alolan Ninetales using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Alolan Ninetales.Name: Shiny Alolan Ninetales
Shiny Alolan Ninetales.Description: Dwells on sacred peaks perpetually covered in snow. Said to appear to virtuous people who have lost their way on mountain paths—it then guides them back down to the mountain’s base.
Shiny Alolan Ninetales.Evolution: Alolan Ninetales evolves from Alolan Vulpix using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Alolan Diglett.Name: Shiny Alolan Diglett
Shiny Alolan Diglett.Description: Its three hairs change shape depending on Diglett’s mood. They’re a useful communication tool among these Pokémon.
Shiny Alolan Diglett.Evolution: Alolan Diglett evolves to Alolan Dugtrio starting from level 26.

Shiny Alolan Dugtrio.Name: Shiny Alolan Dugtrio
Shiny Alolan Dugtrio.Description: The three of them get along very well. Through their formidable teamwork, they defeat powerful opponents.
Shiny Alolan Dugtrio.Evolution: Alolan Dugtrio evolves from Alolan Diglett starting from level 26.

Shiny Alolan Meowth.Name: Shiny Alolan Meowth
Shiny Alolan Meowth.Description: Deeply proud and keenly smart, this Pokémon moves with cunning during battle and relentlessly attacks enemies’ weak points.
Shiny Alolan Meowth.Evolution: Alolan Meowth evolves to Alolan Persian when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Alolan Persian.Name: Shiny Alolan Persian
Shiny Alolan Persian.Description: This Pokémon is one tough opponent. Not only does it have formidable physical abilities, but it’s also not above fighting dirty.
Shiny Alolan Persian.Evolution: Alolan Persian evolves from Alolan Meowth when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet.

Shiny Alolan Geodude.Name: Shiny Alolan Geodude
Shiny Alolan Geodude.Description: Its stone head is imbued with electricity and magnetism. If you carelessly step on one, you’ll be in for a painful shock.
Shiny Alolan Geodude.Evolution: Alolan Geodude evolves to Alolan Graveler starting from level 25, which evolves to Alolan Golem when traded.

Shiny Alolan Graveler.Name: Shiny Alolan Graveler
Shiny Alolan Graveler.Description: When it comes rolling down a mountain path, anything in its way gets zapped by electricity and sent flying.
