Shiny Alolan Graveler.Evolution: Alolan Graveler evolves from Alolan Geodude starting from level 25 and evolves to Alolan Golem when traded.

Shiny Alolan Golem.Name: Shiny Alolan Golem
Shiny Alolan Golem.Description: It uses magnetism to accelerate and fire off rocks tinged with electricity. Even if it doesn’t score a direct hit, the jolt of electricity will do the job.
Shiny Alolan Golem.Evolution: Alolan Golem evolves from Alolan Graveler when traded, which evolves from Alolan Geodude starting from level 25.

Shiny Alolan Grimer.Name: Shiny Alolan Grimer
Shiny Alolan Grimer.Description: It has a passion for trash above all else, speedily digesting it and creating brilliant crystals of sparkling poison.
Shiny Alolan Grimer.Evolution: Alolan Grimer evolves to Alolan Muk starting from level 38.

Shiny Alolan Muk.Name: Shiny Alolan Muk
Shiny Alolan Muk.Description: Muk’s coloration becomes increasingly vivid the more it feasts on its favorite dish—trash.
Shiny Alolan Muk.Evolution: Alolan Muk evolves from Alolan Grimer starting from level 38.

Shiny Alolan Exeggutor.Name: Shiny Alolan Exeggutor
Shiny Alolan Exeggutor.Description: This Pokémon’s psychic powers aren’t as strong as they once were. The head on this Exeggutor’s tail scans surrounding areas with weak telepathy.

Shiny Alolan Marowak.Name: Shiny Alolan Marowak
Shiny Alolan Marowak.Description: The cursed flames that light up the bone carried by this Pokémon are said to cause both mental and physical pain that will never fade.

Shiny Tapu Koko.Name: Shiny Tapu Koko
Shiny Tapu Koko.Description: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.

Shiny Tapu Lele.Name: Shiny Tapu Lele
Shiny Tapu Lele.Description: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

Shiny Tapu Bulu.Name: Shiny Tapu Bulu
Shiny Tapu Bulu.Description: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.

Shiny Tapu Fini.Name: Shiny Tapu Fini
Shiny Tapu Fini.Description: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

Shiny Cosmog.Name: Shiny Cosmog
Shiny Cosmog.Description: Cosmog is very curious but not very cautious, often placing itself in danger. If things start to look dicey, it teleports away.
Shiny Cosmog.Evolution: Cosmog evolves to Cosmoem starting from level 43, which evolves to Solgaleo starting from level 53 in the daytime and evolves to Lunala starting from level 53 in the nighttime.

Shiny Cosmoem.Name: Shiny Cosmoem
Shiny Cosmoem.Description: It sucks in dust from the air at an astounding rate, frantically building up energy within its core as preparation for evolution.

Shiny Solgaleo.Name: Shiny Solgaleo
Shiny Solgaleo.Description: Solgaleo was once known as the Beast That Devours the Sun. Energy in the form of light radiates boundlessly from it.
Shiny Solgaleo.Evolution: Solgaleo evolves from Cosmoem starting from level 53 in the daytime, which evolves from Cosmog starting from level 43.

Shiny Lunala.Name: Shiny Lunala
Shiny Lunala.Description: It steals the light from its surroundings and then becomes the full moon, showering its own light across the night sky.
Shiny Lunala.Evolution: Lunala evolves from Cosmoem starting from level 53 in the nighttime, which evolves from Cosmog starting from level 43.

Shiny Nihilego.Name: Shiny Nihilego
Shiny Nihilego.Description: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokémon.

Shiny Buzzwole.Name: Shiny Buzzwole
Shiny Buzzwole.Description: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

Shiny Pheromosa.Name: Shiny Pheromosa
Shiny Pheromosa.Description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Shiny Xurkitree.Name: Shiny Xurkitree
Shiny Xurkitree.Description: They’ve been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

Shiny Celesteela.Name: Shiny Celesteela
Shiny Celesteela.Description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Shiny Kartana.Name: Shiny Kartana
Shiny Kartana.Description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Shiny Guzzlord.Name: Shiny Guzzlord
Shiny Guzzlord.Description: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.

Shiny Necrozma.Name: Shiny Necrozma
Shiny Necrozma.Description: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

Shiny Magearna.Name: Shiny Magearna
Shiny Magearna.Description: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

Shiny Marshadow.Name: Shiny Marshadow
Shiny Marshadow.Description: This Pokémon can conceal itself in any shadow, so it went undiscovered for a long time.

Shiny Poipole.Name: Shiny Poipole
Shiny Poipole.Description: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.
Shiny Poipole.Evolution: Poipole evolves to Naganadel when leveled up while knowing Dragon Pulse.

Shiny Naganadel.Name: Shiny Naganadel
Shiny Naganadel.Description: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.
Shiny Naganadel.Evolution: Naganadel evolves from Poipole when leveled up while knowing Dragon Pulse.

Shiny Stakataka.Name: Shiny Stakataka
Shiny Stakataka.Description: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute’s true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

Shiny Blacephalon.Name: Shiny Blacephalon
Shiny Blacephalon.Description: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.

Shiny Zeraora.Name: Shiny Zeraora
Shiny Zeraora.Description: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

Shiny Meltan.Name: Shiny Meltan
Shiny Meltan.Description: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

Shiny Melmetal.Name: Shiny Melmetal
Shiny Melmetal.Description: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

Shiny Grookey.Name: Shiny Grookey
Shiny Grookey.Description: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.
Shiny Grookey.Evolution: Grookey evolves to Thwackey starting from level 16, which evolves to Rillaboom starting from level 35.

Shiny Thwackey.Name: Shiny Thwackey
Shiny Thwackey.Description: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.
Shiny Thwackey.Evolution: Thwackey evolves from Grookey starting from level 16 and evolves to Rillaboom starting from level 35.

Shiny Rillaboom.Name: Shiny Rillaboom
Shiny Rillaboom.Description: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
Shiny Rillaboom.Evolution: Rillaboom evolves from Thwackey starting from level 35, which evolves from Grookey starting from level 16.

Shiny Scorbunny.Name: Shiny Scorbunny
Shiny Scorbunny.Description: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.
Shiny Scorbunny.Evolution: Scorbunny evolves to Raboot starting from level 16, which evolves to Cinderace starting from level 35.

Shiny Raboot.Name: Shiny Raboot
Shiny Raboot.Description: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
Shiny Raboot.Evolution: Raboot evolves from Scorbunny starting from level 16 and evolves to Cinderace starting from level 35.

Shiny Cinderace.Name: Shiny Cinderace
Shiny Cinderace.Description: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
Shiny Cinderace.Evolution: Cinderace evolves from Raboot starting from level 35, which evolves from Scorbunny starting from level 16.

Shiny Sobble.Name: Shiny Sobble
Shiny Sobble.Description: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.
Shiny Sobble.Evolution: Sobble evolves to Drizzile starting from level 16, which evolves to Inteleon starting from level 35.

Shiny Drizzile.Name: Shiny Drizzile
Shiny Drizzile.Description: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
Shiny Drizzile.Evolution: Drizzile evolves from Sobble starting from level 16 and evolves to Inteleon starting from level 35.

Shiny Inteleon.Name: Shiny Inteleon
Shiny Inteleon.Description: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
Shiny Inteleon.Evolution: Inteleon evolves from Drizzile starting from level 35, which evolves from Sobble starting from level 16.

Shiny Skwovet.Name: Shiny Skwovet
Shiny Skwovet.Description: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.
Shiny Skwovet.Evolution: Skwovet evolves to Greedent starting from level 24.

Shiny Greedent.Name: Shiny Greedent
Shiny Greedent.Description: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.
Shiny Greedent.Evolution: Greedent evolves from Skwovet starting from level 24.

Shiny Rookidee.Name: Shiny Rookidee
Shiny Rookidee.Description: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee’s wings, it’ll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.
Shiny Rookidee.Evolution: Rookidee evolves to Corvisquire starting from level 18, which evolves to Corviknight starting from level 38.

Shiny Corvisquire.Name: Shiny Corvisquire
Shiny Corvisquire.Description: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.
Shiny Corvisquire.Evolution: Corvisquire evolves from Rookidee starting from level 18 and evolves to Corviknight starting from level 38.

Shiny Corviknight.Name: Shiny Corviknight
Shiny Corviknight.Description: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.
Shiny Corviknight.Evolution: Corviknight evolves from Corvisquire starting from level 38, which evolves from Rookidee starting from level 18.

Shiny Blipbug.Name: Shiny Blipbug
Shiny Blipbug.Description: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.
Shiny Blipbug.Evolution: Blipbug evolves to Dottler starting from level 10, which evolves to Orbeetle starting from level 30.

Shiny Dottler.Name: Shiny Dottler
Shiny Dottler.Description: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

Shiny Orbeetle.Name: Shiny Orbeetle
Shiny Orbeetle.Description: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.
Shiny Orbeetle.Evolution: Orbeetle evolves from Dottler starting from level 30, which evolves from Blipbug starting from level 10.

Shiny Nickit.Name: Shiny Nickit
Shiny Nickit.Description: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.
Shiny Nickit.Evolution: Nickit evolves to Thievul starting from level 18.

Shiny Thievul.Name: Shiny Thievul
Shiny Thievul.Description: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
Shiny Thievul.Evolution: Thievul evolves from Nickit starting from level 18.

Shiny Gossifleur.Name: Shiny Gossifleur
Shiny Gossifleur.Description: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.
Shiny Gossifleur.Evolution: Gossifleur evolves to Eldegoss starting from level 20.

Shiny Eldegoss.Name: Shiny Eldegoss
Shiny Eldegoss.Description: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.
Shiny Eldegoss.Evolution: Eldegoss evolves from Gossifleur starting from level 20.

Shiny Wooloo.Name: Shiny Wooloo
Shiny Wooloo.Description: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.
Shiny Wooloo.Evolution: Wooloo evolves to Dubwool starting from level 24.

Shiny Dubwool.Name: Shiny Dubwool
Shiny Dubwool.Description: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
Shiny Dubwool.Evolution: Dubwool evolves from Wooloo starting from level 24.

Shiny Chewtle.Name: Shiny Chewtle
Shiny Chewtle.Description: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.
Shiny Chewtle.Evolution: Chewtle evolves to Drednaw starting from level 22.

Shiny Drednaw.Name: Shiny Drednaw
Shiny Drednaw.Description: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.
Shiny Drednaw.Evolution: Drednaw evolves from Chewtle starting from level 22.

Shiny Yamper.Name: Shiny Yamper
Shiny Yamper.Description: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.
Shiny Yamper.Evolution: Yamper evolves to Boltund starting from level 25.

Shiny Boltund.Name: Shiny Boltund
Shiny Boltund.Description: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
Shiny Boltund.Evolution: Boltund evolves from Yamper starting from level 25.

Shiny Rolycoly.Name: Shiny Rolycoly
Shiny Rolycoly.Description: Chunks of the surface of this Pokémon’s body that have grown old and flaked off have long been used for fuel as an alternative to coal.
Shiny Rolycoly.Evolution: Rolycoly evolves to Carkol starting from level 18, which evolves to Coalossal starting from level 34.

Shiny Carkol.Name: Shiny Carkol
Shiny Carkol.Description: Due to the coal tar created inside it, the heap of coal on Carkol’s back never falls apart, even when the Pokémon rolls around at high speeds.
Shiny Carkol.Evolution: Carkol evolves from Rolycoly starting from level 18 and evolves to Coalossal starting from level 34.

Shiny Coalossal.Name: Shiny Coalossal
Shiny Coalossal.Description: It’s gentle usually but fearsome when angered. With a body that burns at over 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit, it crushes foes and turns them to ash.
Shiny Coalossal.Evolution: Coalossal evolves from Carkol starting from level 34, which evolves from Rolycoly starting from level 18.

Shiny Applin.Name: Shiny Applin
Shiny Applin.Description: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.
Shiny Applin.Evolution: Applin evolves to Flapple somehow and evolves to Appletun somehow.

Shiny Flapple.Name: Shiny Flapple
Shiny Flapple.Description: It uses its own body fluid to repair its apple. Strong Flapple that have won many battles have apples that are clay colored all over.

Shiny Appletun.Name: Shiny Appletun
Shiny Appletun.Description: When some Lechonk come along to lick the sweet nectar on Appletun’s back, Appletun will spew sticky nectar at them to drive them away.

Shiny Silicobra.Name: Shiny Silicobra
Shiny Silicobra.Description: Silicobra’s large nostrils are specialized for spraying sand, so this Pokémon is not very good at telling apart different smells.
Shiny Silicobra.Evolution: Silicobra evolves to Sandaconda starting from level 36.

Shiny Sandaconda.Name: Shiny Sandaconda
Shiny Sandaconda.Description: The sand it spews contains sharp, pointy gravel, which is actually just sand that Sandaconda’s saliva has hardened into irregular shapes.
Shiny Sandaconda.Evolution: Sandaconda evolves from Silicobra starting from level 36.

Shiny Cramorant.Name: Shiny Cramorant
Shiny Cramorant.Description: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

Shiny Arrokuda.Name: Shiny Arrokuda
Shiny Arrokuda.Description: It takes down prey by charging into them with its hard, pointed jaw. But Arrokuda’s eyesight is poor, so this tactic has a low success rate.
Shiny Arrokuda.Evolution: Arrokuda evolves to Barraskewda starting from level 26.

Shiny Barraskewda.Name: Shiny Barraskewda
Shiny Barraskewda.Description: It swims at speeds of over 100 knots and battles fiercely with pods of Finizen over prey.
Shiny Barraskewda.Evolution: Barraskewda evolves from Arrokuda starting from level 26.

Shiny Toxel.Name: Shiny Toxel
Shiny Toxel.Description: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.
Shiny Toxel.Evolution: Toxel evolves to Toxtricity starting from level 30.

Shiny Toxtricity.Name: Shiny Toxtricity
Shiny Toxtricity.Description: As it gulps down stagnant water and generates electricity in its body, a sound like a rhythm played by a bass guitar reverberates all around.
Shiny Toxtricity.Evolution: Toxtricity evolves from Toxel starting from level 30.

Shiny Sizzlipede.Name: Shiny Sizzlipede
Shiny Sizzlipede.Description: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.
Shiny Sizzlipede.Evolution: Sizzlipede evolves to Centiskorch starting from level 28.

Shiny Centiskorch.Name: Shiny Centiskorch
Shiny Centiskorch.Description: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.
Shiny Centiskorch.Evolution: Centiskorch evolves from Sizzlipede starting from level 28.

Shiny Clobbopus.Name: Shiny Clobbopus
Shiny Clobbopus.Description: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.
Shiny Clobbopus.Evolution: Clobbopus evolves to Grapploct when leveled up.

Shiny Grapploct.Name: Shiny Grapploct
Shiny Grapploct.Description: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
Shiny Grapploct.Evolution: Grapploct evolves from Clobbopus when leveled up.

Shiny Sinistea.Name: Shiny Sinistea
Shiny Sinistea.Description: Sinistea gets into your body when you drink it, and then it steals your vitality from within. It also tastes awful.

Shiny Polteageist.Name: Shiny Polteageist
Shiny Polteageist.Description: Though risky to drink, this Pokémon’s tea tastes delicious. Gourmets who have no fear of danger drink Polteageist tea day after day.

Shiny Hatenna.Name: Shiny Hatenna
Shiny Hatenna.Description: It senses the feelings of other living creatures. Be careful not to expose it to strong emotions for too long, or it will end up exhausted.
Shiny Hatenna.Evolution: Hatenna evolves to Hattrem starting from level 32, which evolves to Hatterene starting from level 42.

Shiny Hattrem.Name: Shiny Hattrem
Shiny Hattrem.Description: The moment this Pokémon finds someone who’s emitting strong emotions, it will pummel them senseless with its braids to silence them.
Shiny Hattrem.Evolution: Hattrem evolves from Hatenna starting from level 32 and evolves to Hatterene starting from level 42.

Shiny Hatterene.Name: Shiny Hatterene
Shiny Hatterene.Description: Beware of forests that show no signs of living creatures within. You may have wandered into Hatterene’s territory.
Shiny Hatterene.Evolution: Hatterene evolves from Hattrem starting from level 42, which evolves from Hatenna starting from level 32.

Shiny Impidimp.Name: Shiny Impidimp
Shiny Impidimp.Description: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.
Shiny Impidimp.Evolution: Impidimp evolves to Morgrem starting from level 32, which evolves to Grimmsnarl starting from level 42.

Shiny Morgrem.Name: Shiny Morgrem
Shiny Morgrem.Description: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It’s popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.
Shiny Morgrem.Evolution: Morgrem evolves from Impidimp starting from level 32 and evolves to Grimmsnarl starting from level 42.

Shiny Grimmsnarl.Name: Shiny Grimmsnarl
Shiny Grimmsnarl.Description: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.
Shiny Grimmsnarl.Evolution: Grimmsnarl evolves from Morgrem starting from level 42, which evolves from Impidimp starting from level 32.

Shiny Galarian Zigzagoon.Name: Shiny Galarian Zigzagoon
Shiny Galarian Zigzagoon.Description: Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.

Shiny Galarian Linoone.Name: Shiny Galarian Linoone
Shiny Galarian Linoone.Description: This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.
Shiny Galarian Linoone.Evolution: Galarian Linoone evolves to Obstagoon starting from level 35.

Shiny Obstagoon.Name: Shiny Obstagoon
Shiny Obstagoon.Description: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
Shiny Obstagoon.Evolution: Obstagoon evolves from Galarian Linoone starting from level 35.

Shiny Galarian Meowth.Name: Shiny Galarian Meowth
Shiny Galarian Meowth.Description: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.
Shiny Galarian Meowth.Evolution: Galarian Meowth evolves to Perrserker starting from level 28.

Shiny Perrserker.Name: Shiny Perrserker
Shiny Perrserker.Description: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.
Shiny Perrserker.Evolution: Perrserker evolves from Galarian Meowth starting from level 28.

Shiny Galarian Ponyta.Name: Shiny Galarian Ponyta
Shiny Galarian Ponyta.Description: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

Shiny Galarian Rapidash.Name: Shiny Galarian Rapidash
Shiny Galarian Rapidash.Description: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

Shiny Galarian Slowpoke.Name: Shiny Galarian Slowpoke
Shiny Galarian Slowpoke.Description: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

Shiny Galarian Slowbro.Name: Shiny Galarian Slowbro
Shiny Galarian Slowbro.Description: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

Shiny Galarian Slowking.Name: Shiny Galarian Slowking
Shiny Galarian Slowking.Description: While chanting strange spells, this Pokémon combines its internal toxins with what it’s eaten, creating strange potions.

Shiny Galarian Corsola.Name: Shiny Galarian Corsola
Shiny Galarian Corsola.Description: Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. This Pokémon absorbs others’ life-force through its branches.
Shiny Galarian Corsola.Evolution: Galarian Corsola evolves to Cursola starting from level 38.

Shiny Cursola.Name: Shiny Cursola
Shiny Cursola.Description: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.
Shiny Cursola.Evolution: Cursola evolves from Galarian Corsola starting from level 38.

Shiny Galarian Farfetch'd.Name: Shiny Galarian Farfetch'd
Shiny Galarian Farfetch'd.Description: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch’d that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.
Shiny Galarian Farfetch'd.Evolution: Galarian Farfetch'd evolves to Sirfetch'd somehow.

Shiny Sirfetch'd.Name: Shiny Sirfetch'd
Shiny Sirfetch'd.Description: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.
Shiny Sirfetch'd.Evolution: Sirfetch'd evolves from Galarian Farfetch'd somehow.

Shiny Galarian Weezing.Name: Shiny Galarian Weezing
Shiny Galarian Weezing.Description: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.

Shiny Galarian Mr. Mime.Name: Shiny Galarian Mr. Mime
Shiny Galarian Mr. Mime.Description: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It’ll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.
Shiny Galarian Mr. Mime.Evolution: Galarian Mr. Mime evolves to Mr. Rime starting from level 42.

Shiny Mr. Rime.Name: Shiny Mr. Rime
Shiny Mr. Rime.Description: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
Shiny Mr. Rime.Evolution: Mr. Rime evolves from Galarian Mr. Mime starting from level 42.

Shiny Galarian Darumaka.Name: Shiny Galarian Darumaka
Shiny Galarian Darumaka.Description: The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.

Shiny Galarian Darmanitan.Name: Shiny Galarian Darmanitan
Shiny Galarian Darmanitan.Description: Though it has a gentle disposition, it’s also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.

Shiny Galarian Yamask.Name: Shiny Galarian Yamask
Shiny Galarian Yamask.Description: It’s said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.
Shiny Galarian Yamask.Evolution: Galarian Yamask evolves to Runerigus somehow.

Shiny Runerigus.Name: Shiny Runerigus
Shiny Runerigus.Description: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
Shiny Runerigus.Evolution: Runerigus evolves from Galarian Yamask somehow.

Shiny Galarian Stunfisk.Name: Shiny Galarian Stunfisk
Shiny Galarian Stunfisk.Description: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

Shiny Milcery.Name: Shiny Milcery
Shiny Milcery.Description: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

Shiny Alcremie.Name: Shiny Alcremie
Shiny Alcremie.Description: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

Shiny Falinks.Name: Shiny Falinks
Shiny Falinks.Description: The leader, known as the brass, uses its extendible horn to issue orders to the others when it’s time to change formation.

Shiny Pincurchin.Name: Shiny Pincurchin
Shiny Pincurchin.Description: This Pokémon is so timid that even brushing against seaweed will make it discharge electricity in surprise. Its lips do not conduct electricity.

Shiny Snom.Name: Shiny Snom
Shiny Snom.Description: Within its internal organs, Snom amplifies the frigid air it gets from eating snow and then uses this amplified air to create icicle-like spikes.
Shiny Snom.Evolution: Snom evolves to Frosmoth when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Shiny Frosmoth.Name: Shiny Frosmoth
Shiny Frosmoth.Description: It causes blizzards as it flies around with its huge, chill-emanating wings. Clean meltwater is its favorite thing to drink.
Shiny Frosmoth.Evolution: Frosmoth evolves from Snom when leveled up while holding a Friendship Bracelet in the nighttime.

Shiny Stonjourner.Name: Shiny Stonjourner
Shiny Stonjourner.Description: This Pokémon spends its life gazing at the setting sun. It strides leisurely across grassy plains on legs of rock that weigh over 400 pounds each.

Shiny Eiscue.Name: Shiny Eiscue
Shiny Eiscue.Description: If you lick the ice covering its face, you’ll find it has a faintly salty taste. This species rode here on ocean currents from a cold, faraway land.

Shiny Indeedee.Name: Shiny Indeedee
Shiny Indeedee.Description: This Pokémon never leaves its Trainer’s side. It predicts their actions with its psychic power and takes care of their day-to-day needs.

Shiny Morpeko.Name: Shiny Morpeko
Shiny Morpeko.Description: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

Shiny Cufant.Name: Shiny Cufant
Shiny Cufant.Description: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.
Shiny Cufant.Evolution: Cufant evolves to Copperajah starting from level 34.

Shiny Copperajah.Name: Shiny Copperajah
Shiny Copperajah.Description: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.
Shiny Copperajah.Evolution: Copperajah evolves from Cufant starting from level 34.

Shiny Dracozolt.Name: Shiny Dracozolt
Shiny Dracozolt.Description: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

Shiny Arctozolt.Name: Shiny Arctozolt
Shiny Arctozolt.Description: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

Shiny Dracovish.Name: Shiny Dracovish
Shiny Dracovish.Description: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.

Shiny Arctovish.Name: Shiny Arctovish
Shiny Arctovish.Description: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

Shiny Duraludon.Name: Shiny Duraludon
Shiny Duraludon.Description: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

Shiny Dreepy.Name: Shiny Dreepy
Shiny Dreepy.Description: It has a habit of biting at Clauncher even though it doesn’t feed on them. This is said to be vestigial behavior from when Dreepy was alive.
Shiny Dreepy.Evolution: Dreepy evolves to Drakloak starting from level 50, which evolves to Dragapult starting from level 60.

Shiny Drakloak.Name: Shiny Drakloak
Shiny Drakloak.Description: This Pokémon stores up energy in its lungs, then shoots it out. It takes care of Dreepy and battles alongside them until they’re all grown up.
Shiny Drakloak.Evolution: Drakloak evolves from Dreepy starting from level 50 and evolves to Dragapult starting from level 60.

Shiny Dragapult.Name: Shiny Dragapult
Shiny Dragapult.Description: The fastest Dragapult of the group is always surrounded by Dreepy that want to fly at sonic speed.
Shiny Dragapult.Evolution: Dragapult evolves from Drakloak starting from level 60, which evolves from Dreepy starting from level 50.

Shiny Zacian.Name: Shiny Zacian
Shiny Zacian.Description: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

Shiny Zamazenta.Name: Shiny Zamazenta
Shiny Zamazenta.Description: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

Shiny Eternatus.Name: Shiny Eternatus
Shiny Eternatus.Description: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

Shiny Kubfu.Name: Shiny Kubfu
Shiny Kubfu.Description: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.

Shiny Urshifu.Name: Shiny Urshifu
Shiny Urshifu.Description: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

Shiny Zarude.Name: Shiny Zarude
Shiny Zarude.Description: Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

Shiny Regieleki.Name: Shiny Regieleki
Shiny Regieleki.Description: Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar’s electricity.

Shiny Regidrago.Name: Shiny Regidrago
Shiny Regidrago.Description: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokémon.

Shiny Glastrier.Name: Shiny Glastrier
Shiny Glastrier.Description: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

Shiny Spectrier.Name: Shiny Spectrier
Shiny Spectrier.Description: As it dashes through the night, Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.

Shiny Calyrex.Name: Shiny Calyrex
Shiny Calyrex.Description: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

Shiny Galarian Articuno.Name: Shiny Galarian Articuno
Shiny Galarian Articuno.Description: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.

Shiny Galarian Zapdos.Name: Shiny Galarian Zapdos
Shiny Galarian Zapdos.Description: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.

Shiny Galarian Moltres.Name: Shiny Galarian Moltres
Shiny Galarian Moltres.Description: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.

Shiny Wyrdeer.Name: Shiny Wyrdeer
Shiny Wyrdeer.Description: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

Shiny Kleavor.Name: Shiny Kleavor
Shiny Kleavor.Description: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one’s only recourse is to flee.
Shiny Kleavor.Evolution: Kleavor evolves from Scyther when leveled up.

Shiny Ursaluna.Name: Shiny Ursaluna
Shiny Ursaluna.Description: I believe it was Hisui’s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.
Shiny Ursaluna.Evolution: Ursaluna evolves from Ursaring somehow, which evolves from Teddiursa starting from level 30.

Shiny Basculegion.Name: Shiny Basculegion
Shiny Basculegion.Description: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.

Shiny Sneasler.Name: Shiny Sneasler
Shiny Sneasler.Description: Because of Sneasler’s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
Shiny Sneasler.Evolution: Sneasler evolves from Hisuian Sneasel somehow.

Shiny Overqwil.Name: Shiny Overqwil
Shiny Overqwil.Description: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.
Shiny Overqwil.Evolution: Overqwil evolves from Hisuian Qwilfish somehow.

Shiny Enamorus.Name: Shiny Enamorus
Shiny Enamorus.Description: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

Shiny Sprigatito.Name: Shiny Sprigatito
Shiny Sprigatito.Description: The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokémon is in the sun.
Shiny Sprigatito.Evolution: Sprigatito evolves to Floragato starting from level 16, which evolves to Meowscarada starting from level 36.

Shiny Floragato.Name: Shiny Floragato
Shiny Floragato.Description: The hardness of Floragato’s fur depends on the Pokémon’s mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.
Shiny Floragato.Evolution: Floragato evolves from Sprigatito starting from level 16 and evolves to Meowscarada starting from level 36.

Shiny Meowscarada.Name: Shiny Meowscarada
Shiny Meowscarada.Description: With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. Meowscarada sets off the bombs before its foes realize what’s going on.
Shiny Meowscarada.Evolution: Meowscarada evolves from Floragato starting from level 36, which evolves from Sprigatito starting from level 16.

Shiny Fuecoco.Name: Shiny Fuecoco
Shiny Fuecoco.Description: Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop Fuecoco’s head and flickers to and fro.
Shiny Fuecoco.Evolution: Fuecoco evolves to Crocalor starting from level 16, which evolves to Skeledirge starting from level 36.

Shiny Crocalor.Name: Shiny Crocalor
Shiny Crocalor.Description: The valve in Crocalor’s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokémon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.
Shiny Crocalor.Evolution: Crocalor evolves from Fuecoco starting from level 16 and evolves to Skeledirge starting from level 36.

Shiny Skeledirge.Name: Shiny Skeledirge
Shiny Skeledirge.Description: Skeledirge’s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.
Shiny Skeledirge.Evolution: Skeledirge evolves from Crocalor starting from level 36, which evolves from Fuecoco starting from level 16.

Shiny Quaxly.Name: Shiny Quaxly
Shiny Quaxly.Description: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.
Shiny Quaxly.Evolution: Quaxly evolves to Quaxwell starting from level 16, which evolves to Quaquaval starting from level 36.

Shiny Quaxwell.Name: Shiny Quaxwell
Shiny Quaxwell.Description: The hardworking Quaxwell observes people and Pokémon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.
Shiny Quaxwell.Evolution: Quaxwell evolves from Quaxly starting from level 16 and evolves to Quaquaval starting from level 36.

Shiny Quaquaval.Name: Shiny Quaquaval
Shiny Quaquaval.Description: Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokémon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.
Shiny Quaquaval.Evolution: Quaquaval evolves from Quaxwell starting from level 36, which evolves from Quaxly starting from level 16.

Shiny Lechonk.Name: Shiny Lechonk
Shiny Lechonk.Description: This Pokémon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokémon detest.
Shiny Lechonk.Evolution: Lechonk evolves to Oinkologne starting from level 18.

Shiny Oinkologne.Name: Shiny Oinkologne
Shiny Oinkologne.Description: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.
Shiny Oinkologne.Evolution: Oinkologne evolves from Lechonk starting from level 18.

Shiny Tarountula.Name: Shiny Tarountula
Shiny Tarountula.Description: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread’s strength is the topic of ongoing research.
Shiny Tarountula.Evolution: Tarountula evolves to Spidops starting from level 15.

Shiny Spidops.Name: Shiny Spidops
Shiny Spidops.Description: Spidops covers its territory in tough, sticky threads to set up traps for intruders.
Shiny Spidops.Evolution: Spidops evolves from Tarountula starting from level 15.

Shiny Nymble.Name: Shiny Nymble
Shiny Nymble.Description: It’s highly skilled at a fighting style in which it uses its jumping capabilities to dodge incoming attacks while also dealing damage to opponents.
Shiny Nymble.Evolution: Nymble evolves to Lokix starting from level 24.

Shiny Lokix.Name: Shiny Lokix
Shiny Lokix.Description: It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it can’t stay in this mode for long.
Shiny Lokix.Evolution: Lokix evolves from Nymble starting from level 24.

Shiny Pawmi.Name: Shiny Pawmi
Shiny Pawmi.Description: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.
Shiny Pawmi.Evolution: Pawmi evolves to Pawmo starting from level 18, which evolves to Pawmot somehow.

Shiny Pawmo.Name: Shiny Pawmo
Shiny Pawmo.Description: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.
Shiny Pawmo.Evolution: Pawmo evolves from Pawmi starting from level 18 and evolves to Pawmot somehow.

Shiny Pawmot.Name: Shiny Pawmot
Shiny Pawmot.Description: Pawmot’s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.
Shiny Pawmot.Evolution: Pawmot evolves from Pawmo somehow, which evolves from Pawmi starting from level 18.

Shiny Tandemaus.Name: Shiny Tandemaus
Shiny Tandemaus.Description: The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.

Shiny Maushold.Name: Shiny Maushold
Shiny Maushold.Description: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

Shiny Fidough.Name: Shiny Fidough
Shiny Fidough.Description: The yeast in Fidough’s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokémon has been protected by people since long ago.
Shiny Fidough.Evolution: Fidough evolves to Dachsbun starting from level 26.

Shiny Dachsbun.Name: Shiny Dachsbun
Shiny Dachsbun.Description: The surface of this Pokémon’s skin hardens when exposed to intense heat, and its body has an appetizing aroma.
Shiny Dachsbun.Evolution: Dachsbun evolves from Fidough starting from level 26.

Shiny Smoliv.Name: Shiny Smoliv
Shiny Smoliv.Description: This Pokémon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.
Shiny Smoliv.Evolution: Smoliv evolves to Dolliv starting from level 25, which evolves to Arboliva starting from level 35.

Shiny Dolliv.Name: Shiny Dolliv
Shiny Dolliv.Description: It basks in the sun to its heart’s content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, Dolliv departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.
Shiny Dolliv.Evolution: Dolliv evolves from Smoliv starting from level 25 and evolves to Arboliva starting from level 35.

Shiny Arboliva.Name: Shiny Arboliva
Shiny Arboliva.Description: This Pokémon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.
Shiny Arboliva.Evolution: Arboliva evolves from Dolliv starting from level 35, which evolves from Smoliv starting from level 25.

Shiny Squawkabilly.Name: Shiny Squawkabilly
Shiny Squawkabilly.Description: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

Shiny Nacli.Name: Shiny Nacli
Shiny Nacli.Description: The ground scrapes its body as it travels, causing it to leave salt behind. Salt is constantly being created and replenished inside Nacli’s body.
Shiny Nacli.Evolution: Nacli evolves to Naclstack starting from level 24, which evolves to Garganacl starting from level 38.

Shiny Naclstack.Name: Shiny Naclstack
Shiny Naclstack.Description: It compresses rock salt inside its body and shoots out hardened salt pellets with enough force to perforate an iron sheet.
Shiny Naclstack.Evolution: Naclstack evolves from Nacli starting from level 24 and evolves to Garganacl starting from level 38.

Shiny Garganacl.Name: Shiny Garganacl
Shiny Garganacl.Description: Many Pokémon gather around Garganacl, hoping to lick at its mineral-rich salt.
Shiny Garganacl.Evolution: Garganacl evolves from Naclstack starting from level 38, which evolves from Nacli starting from level 24.

Shiny Charcadet.Name: Shiny Charcadet
Shiny Charcadet.Description: Its firepower increases when it fights, reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. It likes berries that are rich in fat.
Shiny Charcadet.Evolution: Charcadet evolves to Armarouge using a Auspicious Armor and evolves to Ceruledge using a Malicious Armor.

Shiny Armarouge.Name: Shiny Armarouge
Shiny Armarouge.Description: This Pokémon clads itself in armor that has been fortified by psychic and fire energy, and it shoots blazing fireballs.
Shiny Armarouge.Evolution: Armarouge evolves from Charcadet using a Auspicious Armor.

Mega Mewtwo X.Name: Mega Mewtwo X
Mega Mewtwo X.Description: Psychic power has augmented its muscles. It has a grip strength of one ton and can sprint a hundred meters in two seconds flat!

Shiny Ho-Oh.Name: Shiny Ho-Oh
Shiny Ho-Oh.Description: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

Shiny Ceruledge.Name: Shiny Ceruledge
Shiny Ceruledge.Description: An old set of armor steeped in grudges caused this Pokémon’s evolution. Ceruledge cuts its enemies to pieces without mercy.
Shiny Ceruledge.Evolution: Ceruledge evolves from Charcadet using a Malicious Armor.

Shiny Tadbulb.Name: Shiny Tadbulb
Shiny Tadbulb.Description: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.
Shiny Tadbulb.Evolution: Tadbulb evolves to Bellibolt using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Bellibolt.Name: Shiny Bellibolt
Shiny Bellibolt.Description: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt’s belly-button dynamo.
Shiny Bellibolt.Evolution: Bellibolt evolves from Tadbulb using a Thunder Stone.

Shiny Wattrel.Name: Shiny Wattrel
Shiny Wattrel.Description: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.
Shiny Wattrel.Evolution: Wattrel evolves to Kilowattrel starting from level 25.

Shiny Kilowattrel.Name: Shiny Kilowattrel
Shiny Kilowattrel.Description: It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. There’s hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.
Shiny Kilowattrel.Evolution: Kilowattrel evolves from Wattrel starting from level 25.

Shiny Maschiff.Name: Shiny Maschiff
Shiny Maschiff.Description: Its well-developed jaw and fangs are strong enough to crunch through boulders, and its thick fat makes for an excellent defense.
Shiny Maschiff.Evolution: Maschiff evolves to Mabosstiff starting from level 30.

Shiny Mabosstiff.Name: Shiny Mabosstiff
Shiny Mabosstiff.Description: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.
Shiny Mabosstiff.Evolution: Mabosstiff evolves from Maschiff starting from level 30.

Shiny Shroodle.Name: Shiny Shroodle
Shiny Shroodle.Description: To keep enemies away from its territory, it paints markings around its nest using a poisonous liquid that has an acrid odor.
Shiny Shroodle.Evolution: Shroodle evolves to Grafaiai starting from level 28.

Shiny Grafaiai.Name: Shiny Grafaiai
Shiny Grafaiai.Description: Each Grafaiai paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.
Shiny Grafaiai.Evolution: Grafaiai evolves from Shroodle starting from level 28.

Shiny Bramblin.Name: Shiny Bramblin
Shiny Bramblin.Description: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

Shiny Brambleghast.Name: Shiny Brambleghast
Shiny Brambleghast.Description: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

Shiny Toedscool.Name: Shiny Toedscool
Shiny Toedscool.Description: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Shiny Toedscool.Evolution: Toedscool evolves to Toedscruel starting from level 30.

Shiny Toedscruel.Name: Shiny Toedscruel
Shiny Toedscruel.Description: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.
Shiny Toedscruel.Evolution: Toedscruel evolves from Toedscool starting from level 30.

Shiny Klawf.Name: Shiny Klawf
Shiny Klawf.Description: This Pokémon lives on sheer cliffs. It sidesteps opponents’ attacks, then lunges for their weak spots with its claws.

Shiny Capsakid.Name: Shiny Capsakid
Shiny Capsakid.Description: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.
Shiny Capsakid.Evolution: Capsakid evolves to Scovillain using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Scovillain.Name: Shiny Scovillain
Shiny Scovillain.Description: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.
Shiny Scovillain.Evolution: Scovillain evolves from Capsakid using a Fire Stone.

Shiny Rellor.Name: Shiny Rellor
Shiny Rellor.Description: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.

Shiny Rabsca.Name: Shiny Rabsca
Shiny Rabsca.Description: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.

Shiny Flittle.Name: Shiny Flittle
Shiny Flittle.Description: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.
Shiny Flittle.Evolution: Flittle evolves to Espathra starting from level 35.

Shiny Espathra.Name: Shiny Espathra
Shiny Espathra.Description: It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.
Shiny Espathra.Evolution: Espathra evolves from Flittle starting from level 35.

Shiny Tinkatink.Name: Shiny Tinkatink
Shiny Tinkatink.Description: This Pokémon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it’s satisfied with the result.
Shiny Tinkatink.Evolution: Tinkatink evolves to Tinkatuff starting from level 24, which evolves to Tinkaton starting from level 38.

Shiny Tinkatuff.Name: Shiny Tinkatuff
Shiny Tinkatuff.Description: These Pokémon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each other’s hammers by smashing them together.
Shiny Tinkatuff.Evolution: Tinkatuff evolves from Tinkatink starting from level 24 and evolves to Tinkaton starting from level 38.

Shiny Tinkaton.Name: Shiny Tinkaton
Shiny Tinkaton.Description: The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.
Shiny Tinkaton.Evolution: Tinkaton evolves from Tinkatuff starting from level 38, which evolves from Tinkatink starting from level 24.

Shiny Wiglett.Name: Shiny Wiglett
Shiny Wiglett.Description: Though it looks like Diglett, Wiglett is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.
Shiny Wiglett.Evolution: Wiglett evolves to Wugtrio starting from level 26.

Shiny Wugtrio.Name: Shiny Wugtrio
Shiny Wugtrio.Description: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.
Shiny Wugtrio.Evolution: Wugtrio evolves from Wiglett starting from level 26.

Shiny Bombirdier.Name: Shiny Bombirdier
Shiny Bombirdier.Description: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.

Shiny Finizen.Name: Shiny Finizen
Shiny Finizen.Description: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

Shiny Palafin.Name: Shiny Palafin
Shiny Palafin.Description: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

Shiny Varoom.Name: Shiny Varoom
Shiny Varoom.Description: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.
Shiny Varoom.Evolution: Varoom evolves to Revavroom starting from level 40.

Shiny Revavroom.Name: Shiny Revavroom
Shiny Revavroom.Description: Revavroom viciously threatens others with the sound of its exhaust. It sticks its tongue out from its cylindrical mouth and sprays toxic fluids.
Shiny Revavroom.Evolution: Revavroom evolves from Varoom starting from level 40.

Shiny Cyclizar.Name: Shiny Cyclizar
Shiny Cyclizar.Description: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider’s body heat warms Cyclizar’s back and lifts the Pokémon’s spirit.

Shiny Orthworm.Name: Shiny Orthworm
Shiny Orthworm.Description: This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It maintains its metal body by consuming iron from the soil.

Shiny Glimmet.Name: Shiny Glimmet
Shiny Glimmet.Description: Glimmet’s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.
Shiny Glimmet.Evolution: Glimmet evolves to Glimmora starting from level 35.

Shiny Glimmora.Name: Shiny Glimmora
Shiny Glimmora.Description: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.
Shiny Glimmora.Evolution: Glimmora evolves from Glimmet starting from level 35.

Shiny Greavard.Name: Shiny Greavard
Shiny Greavard.Description: This friendly Pokémon doesn’t like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.
Shiny Greavard.Evolution: Greavard evolves to Houndstone starting from level 30 in the nighttime.

Shiny Houndstone.Name: Shiny Houndstone
Shiny Houndstone.Description: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.
Shiny Houndstone.Evolution: Houndstone evolves from Greavard starting from level 30 in the nighttime.

Shiny Flamigo.Name: Shiny Flamigo
Shiny Flamigo.Description: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as “synchronizing,” an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

Shiny Cetoddle.Name: Shiny Cetoddle
Shiny Cetoddle.Description: It lives in frigid regions in pods of five or so individuals. It loves the minerals found in snow and ice.
Shiny Cetoddle.Evolution: Cetoddle evolves to Cetitan using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Cetitan.Name: Shiny Cetitan
Shiny Cetitan.Description: Ice energy builds up in the horn on its upper jaw, causing the horn to reach cryogenic temperatures that freeze its surroundings.
Shiny Cetitan.Evolution: Cetitan evolves from Cetoddle using a Ice Stone.

Shiny Veluza.Name: Shiny Veluza
Shiny Veluza.Description: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.

Shiny Dondozo.Name: Shiny Dondozo
Shiny Dondozo.Description: It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very smart.

Shiny Tatsugiri.Name: Shiny Tatsugiri
Shiny Tatsugiri.Description: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

Shiny Annihilape.Name: Shiny Annihilape
Shiny Annihilape.Description: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.
Shiny Annihilape.Evolution: Annihilape evolves from Primeape somehow, which evolves from Mankey starting from level 28.

Shiny Clodsire.Name: Shiny Clodsire
Shiny Clodsire.Description: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.
Shiny Clodsire.Evolution: Clodsire evolves from Wooper starting from level 20.

Shiny Farigiraf.Name: Shiny Farigiraf
Shiny Farigiraf.Description: The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as Farigiraf whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.

Shiny Dudunsparce.Name: Shiny Dudunsparce
Shiny Dudunsparce.Description: It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.

Shiny Kingambit.Name: Shiny Kingambit
Shiny Kingambit.Description: Though it commands a massive army in battle, it’s not skilled at devising complex strategies. It just uses brute strength to keep pushing.
Shiny Kingambit.Evolution: Kingambit evolves from Bisharp somehow, which evolves from Pawniard starting from level 52.

Shiny Great Tusk.Name: Shiny Great Tusk
Shiny Great Tusk.Description: This creature resembles a mysterious Pokémon that, according to a paranormal magazine, has lived since ancient times.

Shiny Scream Tail.Name: Shiny Scream Tail
Shiny Scream Tail.Description: It resembles a mysterious Pokémon described in a paranormal magazine as a Jigglypuff from one billion years ago.

Shiny Brute Bonnet.Name: Shiny Brute Bonnet
Shiny Brute Bonnet.Description: It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.

Shiny Flutter Mane.Name: Shiny Flutter Mane
Shiny Flutter Mane.Description: It has similar features to a ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a paranormal magazine, but the two have little else in common.

Shiny Slither Wing.Name: Shiny Slither Wing
Shiny Slither Wing.Description: This Pokémon somewhat resembles an ancient form of Volcarona that was introduced in a dubious magazine.

Shiny Sandy Shocks.Name: Shiny Sandy Shocks
Shiny Sandy Shocks.Description: It slightly resembles a Magneton that lived for 10,000 years and was featured in an article in a paranormal magazine.

Shiny Iron Treads.Name: Shiny Iron Treads
Shiny Iron Treads.Description: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.

Shiny Iron Bundle.Name: Shiny Iron Bundle
Shiny Iron Bundle.Description: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

Shiny Iron Hands.Name: Shiny Iron Hands
Shiny Iron Hands.Description: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.

Shiny Iron Jugulis.Name: Shiny Iron Jugulis
Shiny Iron Jugulis.Description: It’s possible that Iron Jugulis, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokémon.

Shiny Iron Moth.Name: Shiny Iron Moth
Shiny Iron Moth.Description: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

Shiny Iron Thorns.Name: Shiny Iron Thorns
Shiny Iron Thorns.Description: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.

Shiny Frigibax.Name: Shiny Frigibax
Shiny Frigibax.Description: This Pokémon lives in forests and craggy areas. Using the power of its dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its nest like a refrigerator.
Shiny Frigibax.Evolution: Frigibax evolves to Arctibax starting from level 35, which evolves to Baxcalibur starting from level 54.

Shiny Arctibax.Name: Shiny Arctibax
Shiny Arctibax.Description: It attacks with the blade of its frozen dorsal fin by doing a front flip in the air. Arctibax’s strong back and legs allow it to pull off this technique.
Shiny Arctibax.Evolution: Arctibax evolves from Frigibax starting from level 35 and evolves to Baxcalibur starting from level 54.

Shiny Baxcalibur.Name: Shiny Baxcalibur
Shiny Baxcalibur.Description: It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.
Shiny Baxcalibur.Evolution: Baxcalibur evolves from Arctibax starting from level 54, which evolves from Frigibax starting from level 35.

Shiny Gimmighoul.Name: Shiny Gimmighoul
Shiny Gimmighoul.Description: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

Shiny Gholdengo.Name: Shiny Gholdengo
Shiny Gholdengo.Description: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.

Shiny Wo-Chien.Name: Shiny Wo-Chien
Shiny Wo-Chien.Description: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.

Shiny Chien-Pao.Name: Shiny Chien-Pao
Shiny Chien-Pao.Description: The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokémon.

Shiny Ting-Lu.Name: Shiny Ting-Lu
Shiny Ting-Lu.Description: It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.

Shiny Chi-Yu.Name: Shiny Chi-Yu
Shiny Chi-Yu.Description: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.

Shiny Roaring Moon.Name: Shiny Roaring Moon
Shiny Roaring Moon.Description: According to an article in a dubious magazine, this Pokémon has some connection to a phenomenon that occurs in a certain region.

Shiny Iron Valiant.Name: Shiny Iron Valiant
Shiny Iron Valiant.Description: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

Shiny Koraidon.Name: Shiny Koraidon
Shiny Koraidon.Description: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

Shiny Miraidon.Name: Shiny Miraidon
Shiny Miraidon.Description: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

Shiny 10% Zygarde.Name: Shiny 10% Zygarde
Shiny 10% Zygarde.Description: Born when around 10% of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered from all over, this form is skilled in close-range combat.

Shiny Black Kyurem.Name: Shiny Black Kyurem
Shiny Black Kyurem.Description: The sameness of Zekrom’s and Kyurem’s genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Zekrom. Kyurem can now use the power of both electricity and ice.

Shiny Blade Aegislash.Name: Shiny Blade Aegislash
Shiny Blade Aegislash.Description: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.

Shiny Complete Zygarde.Name: Shiny Complete Zygarde
Shiny Complete Zygarde.Description: Born when all of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.

jp: パーフェクトフォルム
ディフェンスフォルム

Shiny Fan Rotom.Name: Shiny Fan Rotom
Shiny Fan Rotom.Description: There are several appliances that Rotom can inspirit, but the first one to be developed was the electric fan.

Shiny Frost Rotom.Name: Shiny Frost Rotom
Shiny Frost Rotom.Description: The special motor within the refrigerator is the key to bringing about Rotom’s change in form.

Shiny Heat Rotom.Name: Shiny Heat Rotom
Shiny Heat Rotom.Description: This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven. It will sear the surrounding area with its burning heat, then smile in delight.

Shiny Mega Absol.Name: Shiny Mega Absol
Shiny Mega Absol.Description: It converts the energy from Mega Evolution into an intimidating aura. Fainthearted people expire from shock at the sight of it.

Shiny Mega Aerodactyl.Name: Shiny Mega Aerodactyl
Shiny Mega Aerodactyl.Description: The power of Mega Evolution has completely restored its genes. The rocks on its body are harder than diamond.

Shiny Mega Alakazam.Name: Shiny Mega Alakazam
Shiny Mega Alakazam.Description: It’s adept at precognition. When attacks completely miss Alakazam, that’s because it’s seeing the future.

Shiny Mega Ampharos.Name: Shiny Mega Ampharos
Shiny Mega Ampharos.Description: Massive amounts of energy intensely stimulated Ampharos’s cells, apparently awakening its long-sleeping dragon’s blood.

Shiny Mega Banette.Name: Shiny Mega Banette
Shiny Mega Banette.Description: Mega Evolution increases its vindictiveness, and the cursing power that was held back by its zipper comes spilling out.

Shiny Mega Beedrill.Name: Shiny Mega Beedrill
Shiny Mega Beedrill.Description: Its legs have become poison stingers. It stabs its prey repeatedly with the stingers on its limbs, dealing the final blow with the stinger on its rear.

Shiny Mega Blastoise.Name: Shiny Mega Blastoise
Shiny Mega Blastoise.Description: The cannon on its back is as powerful as a tank gun. Its tough legs and back enable it to withstand the recoil from firing the cannon.

Shiny Mega Charizard X.Name: Shiny Mega Charizard X
Shiny Mega Charizard X.Description: The overwhelming power that fills its entire body causes it to turn black and create intense blue flames.

Shiny Mega Charizard Y.Name: Shiny Mega Charizard Y
Shiny Mega Charizard Y.Description: Its bond with its Trainer is the source of its power. It boasts speed and maneuverability greater than that of a jet fighter.

Shiny Mega Garchomp.Name: Shiny Mega Garchomp
Shiny Mega Garchomp.Description: Its disposition is more vicious than before its Mega Evolution. Garchomp carves its opponents up with the scythes on both arms.

Shiny Mega Gengar.Name: Shiny Mega Gengar
Shiny Mega Gengar.Description: It can pass through other dimensions and can appear anywhere. It caused a stir one time when it stuck just one leg out of a wall.

Shiny Mega Glalie.Name: Shiny Mega Glalie
Shiny Mega Glalie.Description: The power of Mega Evolution was so strong that it smashed Glalie’s jaw. Its inability to eat very well leaves Glalie irritated.

Shiny Mega Gyarados.Name: Shiny Mega Gyarados
Shiny Mega Gyarados.Description: Although it obeys its instinctive drive to destroy everything within its reach, it will respond to orders from a Trainer it truly trusts.

Shiny Mega Heracross.Name: Shiny Mega Heracross
Shiny Mega Heracross.Description: A tremendous influx of energy builds it up, but when Mega Evolution ends, Heracross is bothered by terrible soreness in its muscles.

Shiny Mega Houndoom.Name: Shiny Mega Houndoom
Shiny Mega Houndoom.Description: Houndoom’s entire body generates heat when it Mega Evolves. Its fearsome fiery breath turns its opponents to ash.

Shiny Mega Kangaskhan.Name: Shiny Mega Kangaskhan
Shiny Mega Kangaskhan.Description: Its child has grown rapidly, thanks to the energy of Mega Evolution. Mother and child show their harmonious teamwork in battle.

Shiny Mega Lopunny.Name: Shiny Mega Lopunny
Shiny Mega Lopunny.Description: Mega Evolution awakens its combative instincts. It has shed any fur that got in the way of its attacks.

Shiny Mega Lucario.Name: Shiny Mega Lucario
Shiny Mega Lucario.Description: Bathed in explosive energy, its combative instincts have awakened. For its enemies, it has no mercy whatsoever.

Shiny Mega Manectric.Name: Shiny Mega Manectric
Shiny Mega Manectric.Description: Too much electricity has built up in its body, irritating Manectric. Its explosive speed is equal to that of a lightning bolt.

Shiny Mega Mawile.Name: Shiny Mega Mawile
Shiny Mega Mawile.Description: Its two sets of jaws thrash about violently as if they each had a will of their own. One gnash from them can turn a boulder to dust.

Shiny Mega Metagross.Name: Shiny Mega Metagross
Shiny Mega Metagross.Description: When it knows it can’t win, it digs the claws on its legs into its opponent and starts the countdown to a big explosion.

Shiny Mega Mewtwo X.Name: Shiny Mega Mewtwo X
Shiny Mega Mewtwo X.Description: Psychic power has augmented its muscles. It has a grip strength of one ton and can sprint a hundred meters in two seconds flat!

Shiny Mega Mewtwo Y.Name: Shiny Mega Mewtwo Y
Shiny Mega Mewtwo Y.Description: Despite its diminished size, its mental power has grown phenomenally. With a mere thought, it can smash a skyscraper to smithereens.

Shiny Mega Pidgeot.Name: Shiny Mega Pidgeot
Shiny Mega Pidgeot.Description: With its muscular strength now greatly increased, it can fly continuously for two weeks without resting.

Shiny Mega Pinsir.Name: Shiny Mega Pinsir
Shiny Mega Pinsir.Description: With its vaunted horns, it can lift an opponent 10 times heavier than itself and fly about with ease.

Shiny Mega Sableye.Name: Shiny Mega Sableye
Shiny Mega Sableye.Description: It blocks any and all attacks with its giant-sized gemstone. However, the stone’s a heavy burden, and it limits Mega Sableye’s movements.

Shiny Mega Salamence.Name: Shiny Mega Salamence
Shiny Mega Salamence.Description: It puts its forelegs inside its shell to streamline itself for flight. Salamence flies at high speeds over all kinds of topographical features.

Shiny Mega Scizor.Name: Shiny Mega Scizor
Shiny Mega Scizor.Description: It’s better at beating things than grasping them. When it battles for a long time, the weight of its pincers becomes too much to bear.

Shiny Mega Sharpedo.Name: Shiny Mega Sharpedo
Shiny Mega Sharpedo.Description: The moment it charges into its opponent, sharp spikes pop out of Sharpedo’s head, leaving its opponent with deep wounds.

Shiny Mega Slowbro.Name: Shiny Mega Slowbro
Shiny Mega Slowbro.Description: Under the influence of Shellder’s digestive fluids, Slowpoke has awakened, gaining a great deal of power—and a little motivation to boot.

Shiny Mega Tyranitar.Name: Shiny Mega Tyranitar
Shiny Mega Tyranitar.Description: The effects of Mega Evolution make it more ferocious than ever. It’s unclear whether it can even hear its Trainer’s orders.

Shiny Mega Venusaur.Name: Shiny Mega Venusaur
Shiny Mega Venusaur.Description: In order to support its flower, which has grown larger due to Mega Evolution, its back and legs have become stronger.

Shiny Mow Rotom.Name: Shiny Mow Rotom
Shiny Mow Rotom.Description: This Rotom has possessed a lawn mower. It will mow down grass and flowers, then swagger around with pride at its accomplishments.

Shiny Origin Giratina.Name: Shiny Origin Giratina
Shiny Origin Giratina.Description: Giratina loses its legs upon changing into this form. I believe this Pokémon must hail from a world where the heavens and the earth are as one, though I have no way of proving it.
Shiny Origin Giratina.Evolution: Origin Giratina transforms from Giratina when given a Griseous Orb.

jp: ゲンシカイキのすがた
ゲンシカイキのすがた

Shiny Resolute Keldeo.Name: Shiny Resolute Keldeo
Shiny Resolute Keldeo.Description: The power that lay hidden in its body now covers its horn, turning it into a sword that can slice through anything.

Shiny Sandy Wormadam.Name: Shiny Sandy Wormadam
Shiny Sandy Wormadam.Description: Its earthen skin is reasonably hard—it has no problem repelling a Starly’s pecking, at least.

Shiny Sky Shaymin.Name: Shiny Sky Shaymin
Shiny Sky Shaymin.Description: Upon taking in the scent of a particular rare flower, Shaymin is enveloped in light, and its tiny body transforms. I took a whiff of the flower myself, but alas, my body remained unchanged.
Shiny Sky Shaymin.Evolution: Sky Shaymin transforms from Shaymin when given a Gracidea.

Shiny Therian Landorus.Name: Shiny Therian Landorus
Shiny Therian Landorus.Description: Landorus soars through the sky in this form, bestowing plentiful harvests upon the land and earning the people’s reverence. It can traverse the whole of Hisui in a mere couple of hours.
Shiny Therian Landorus.Evolution: Therian Landorus transforms from Landorus when given a Reveal Glass.

Shiny Therian Thundurus.Name: Shiny Therian Thundurus
Shiny Therian Thundurus.Description: Quick as a flash, it materializes out of nowhere. It pulverizes foes into nothingness with showers of devastatingly powerful lightning bolts launched from the string of orbs on its tail.
Shiny Therian Thundurus.Evolution: Therian Thundurus transforms from Thundurus when given a Reveal Glass.

Shiny Therian Tornadus.Name: Shiny Therian Tornadus
Shiny Therian Tornadus.Description: An example of what is known as a “form change,” though I suspect this strange avian guise to be Tornadus’s true form. Tornadus has been sighted crossing the ocean while in this form.
Shiny Therian Tornadus.Evolution: Therian Tornadus transforms from Tornadus when given a Reveal Glass.

Shiny Trash Wormadam.Name: Shiny Trash Wormadam
Shiny Trash Wormadam.Description: Its body, composed of refuse, blends in to the scenery so much as to be inconspicuous. This seems to be the perfect way for the Pokémon to evade the detection of predators.

Shiny Wash Rotom.Name: Shiny Wash Rotom
Shiny Wash Rotom.Description: The model of washing machine that Rotom can inspirit has been discontinued, so these appliances are now traded at high prices.

Shiny White Kyurem.Name: Shiny White Kyurem
Shiny White Kyurem.Description: It has foreseen that a world of truth will arrive for people and Pokémon. It strives to protect that future.

Shiny Zen Darmanitan.Name: Shiny Zen Darmanitan
Shiny Zen Darmanitan.Description: When wounded, it stops moving. It goes as still as stone to meditate, sharpening its mind and spirit.

Spring Blooming Diancie.Name: Spring Blooming Diancie
Spring Blooming Diancie.Description: It can instantly create many flowers by shaking its head to throw out seeds from the big flower on its head.

Flower Pheromosa.Name: Flower Pheromosa
Flower Pheromosa.Description: Although it's alien to this world, It's enjoying the sunny fashion for this Spring.

Shiny Spring Blooming Diancie.Name: Shiny Spring Blooming Diancie
Shiny Spring Blooming Diancie.Description: It can instantly create many flowers by shaking its head to throw out seeds from the big flower on its head.

Shiny Flower Pheromosa.Name: Shiny Flower Pheromosa
Shiny Flower Pheromosa.Description: Although it's alien to this world, It's enjoying the sunny fashion for this Spring.

Autumn Leafeon.Name: Autumn Leafeon
Autumn Leafeon.Evolution: Autumn Leafeon evolves from Autumn Eevee using a Leaf Stone.

Autumn Eevee.Name: Autumn Eevee
Autumn Eevee.Evolution: Autumn Eevee evolves to Autumn Leafeon using a Leaf Stone.

Autumn Torterra.Name: Autumn Torterra
Autumn Torterra.Evolution: Autumn Torterra evolves from Autumn Grotle starting from level 32, which evolves from Autumn Turtwig starting from level 18.

Autumn Grotle.Name: Autumn Grotle
Autumn Grotle.Evolution: Autumn Grotle evolves from Autumn Turtwig starting from level 18 and evolves to Autumn Torterra starting from level 32.

Autumn Turtwig.Name: Autumn Turtwig
Autumn Turtwig.Evolution: Autumn Turtwig evolves to Autumn Grotle starting from level 18, which evolves to Autumn Torterra starting from level 32.

Shiny Autumn Leafeon.Name: Shiny Autumn Leafeon
Shiny Autumn Leafeon.Evolution: Autumn Leafeon evolves from Autumn Eevee using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Autumn Eevee.Name: Shiny Autumn Eevee
Shiny Autumn Eevee.Evolution: Autumn Eevee evolves to Autumn Leafeon using a Leaf Stone.

Shiny Autumn Torterra.Name: Shiny Autumn Torterra
Shiny Autumn Torterra.Evolution: Autumn Torterra evolves from Autumn Grotle starting from level 32, which evolves from Autumn Turtwig starting from level 18.

Shiny Autumn Grotle.Name: Shiny Autumn Grotle
Shiny Autumn Grotle.Evolution: Autumn Grotle evolves from Autumn Turtwig starting from level 18 and evolves to Autumn Torterra starting from level 32.

Shiny Autumn Turtwig.Name: Shiny Autumn Turtwig
Shiny Autumn Turtwig.Evolution: Autumn Turtwig evolves to Autumn Grotle starting from level 18, which evolves to Autumn Torterra starting from level 32.

Anniversary Lapras.Name: Anniversary Lapras
Anniversary Lapras.Description: This gentle Pokémon loves to give people rides on its back. During the celebration, it covers itself with cake cream for everyone to enjoy.

Skater Wooper.Name: Skater Wooper
Skater Wooper.Description: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. There it discovered a skate shoe which made it more mobile on land!

Cupcake Alcremie.Name: Cupcake Alcremie
Cupcake Alcremie.Description: When Alcremie is content, it magically makes cupcakes for all to share.

Bug Catcher Weedle.Name: Bug Catcher Weedle
Bug Catcher Weedle.Description: Beware of its net. It hides in grass and bushes where it hunts small bugs for its collection.

Flower Paras.Name: Flower Paras
Flower Paras.Description: Burrows close to trees to cover itself. The flowers on its back gives it all the energy it needs.

Hatching Beautifly.Name: Hatching Beautifly
Hatching Beautifly.Description: Beautifly has a long mouth like a coiled needle, which is very convenient searching for hidden chocolate eggs in gardens. It rides the spring winds as it flits around gathering eggs.

Bird Nest Nuzleaf.Name: Bird Nest Nuzleaf
Bird Nest Nuzleaf.Description: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of Nuzleaf's grass flute lets birds whistle in joy.

Eggneton.Name: Eggneton
Eggneton.Description: This Pokémon is constantly putting out a powerful magnetic force. Most chocolate eggs are found when Eggneton approaches.

Egg Hunter Kangaskhan.Name: Egg Hunter Kangaskhan
Egg Hunter Kangaskhan.Description: There are records of Kangaskhan hiding chocolate eggs for their children to find on Easter.

Egg Basket Buneary.Name: Egg Basket Buneary
Egg Basket Buneary.Description: Buneary can crack eggs by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack is useful for hard boiled eggs.

Egg Searching Steenee.Name: Egg Searching Steenee
Egg Searching Steenee.Description: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from the bag its wearing.

Eternal Flower Floette.Name: Eternal Flower Floette
Eternal Flower Floette.Description: Terrifying energy is concealed within its ominous flower, but Floette still swings it about innocently.

Winter Sawsbuck.Name: Winter Sawsbuck
Winter Sawsbuck.Description: Though there are many enthusiasts for Sawsbuck as a species, this seasonal form in particular is not very popular.

Rudolph Vulpix.Name: Rudolph Vulpix
Rudolph Vulpix.Description: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.

Angel Diglett.Name: Angel Diglett
Angel Diglett.Description: It flies through the sky at midnight. It searches for a Christmas tree without a tree topper so it can sit on top.

Candy Cane Marowak.Name: Candy Cane Marowak
Candy Cane Marowak.Description: At Christmas eve, it replaces the bone with a candy cane to snack on a candy cane. This is the only time it lays down the bone.

Mrs. Claus Jynx.Name: Mrs. Claus Jynx
Mrs. Claus Jynx.Description: Appears to move to a rhythm of Christmas, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks to the jingle bells.

Christmas Mareep.Name: Christmas Mareep
Christmas Mareep.Description: If you hang lights in its fleece, it will generate enough electricity to turn them on. Don’t pet it, you’ll get a painful shock.

Santa Delibird.Name: Santa Delibird
Santa Delibird.Description: It has a generous habit of giving out presents to people and Pokémon, so it’s always shopping around for more presents.

Ornaments Spoink.Name: Ornaments Spoink
Ornaments Spoink.Description: Spoink keeps an ornament on top of its head. The ornament functions to amplify this Pokémon's Christmas powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger one.

Poinsettia Lilligant.Name: Poinsettia Lilligant
Poinsettia Lilligant.Description: Essential oils made from Lilligant poinsettia flowers have a sublime scent. These are in a lot of homes during Christmas.

Christmas Rowlet.Name: Christmas Rowlet
Christmas Rowlet.Description: During the day, it builds up energy via photosynthesis. At night, it flies silenty through the sky, scouting for the santa to bring his presents.

Wreath Comfey.Name: Wreath Comfey
Wreath Comfey.Description: This Pokémon smells very nice. All comfey wear different kinds of wreaths, so each one has its own individual Christmas scent.

Lights Pyukumuku.Name: Lights Pyukumuku
Lights Pyukumuku.Description: They will get on land during Christmas eve to shine its lights on the back. They go back to the sea after New Year’s eve.

Presents Komala.Name: Presents Komala
Presents Komala.Description: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative music of Christmas that it hears all year long.

Ornament Eldegoss.Name: Ornament Eldegoss
Ornament Eldegoss.Description: The ornament on the head of this Pokémon can be hung in the Christmas tree, shining bright.

Cake Appletun.Name: Cake Appletun
Cake Appletun.Description: Its body is covered with icing, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack at Christmas.

Elf Impidimp.Name: Elf Impidimp
Elf Impidimp.Description: It sneaks into people’s homes, puts presents underneath the Christmas tree and leaves via the chimney again.

クリスマスミルタンク
クリスマスサーナイト
クリスマスエルレイド

Small Pumpkaboo.Name: Small Pumpkaboo
Small Pumpkaboo.Description: Small Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where few lost souls lingered.

Super Pumpkaboo.Name: Super Pumpkaboo
Super Pumpkaboo.Description: Massive Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where a great number of lost souls lingered.

Large Pumpkaboo.Name: Large Pumpkaboo
Large Pumpkaboo.Description: Large Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where many lost souls lingered.

Small Gourgeist.Name: Small Gourgeist
Small Gourgeist.Description: A small-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a small-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Super Gourgeist.Name: Super Gourgeist
Super Gourgeist.Description: A supersized Pumpkaboo evolves into a supersized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Large Gourgeist.Name: Large Gourgeist
Large Gourgeist.Description: A large-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a large-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Busted Mimikyu.Name: Busted Mimikyu
Busted Mimikyu.Description: It has taken damage and can no longer hold the head of its cloth disguise upright. For as long as it lives, Mimikyu will never forget its attacker.

Partner Cap Pikachu.Name: Partner Cap Pikachu
Partner Cap Pikachu.Description: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed as the two overcame many hardships together.
